INSERT INTO submissions (assignment_id, student_id, chatgpt_before, user_prompt, essay, submitted_at) VALUES
(1, 12, 'Great job! Here are some suggestions for improvement: 1. Consider moving the example about healthcare to a new paragraph, so that your first paragraph remains focused on your argument that limiting assistance to only those in need can create deeper discrimination and hatred between groups. 2. To enhance your second paragraph, consider providing specific examples of assistance programs that are currently in place and provide benefits only to those in need. You can then explain how these programs might disincentivize work and create resentment among those who don''t receive benefits. You could also provide examples of programs that provide assistance to all citizens, such as public education and healthcare, and discuss how these programs foster a sense of community and shared responsibility. 3. Consider addressing the counterargument in a more comprehensive way. Instead of just mentioning that some people may argue that assistance to those in need is more efficient, you can provide more detail about this perspective and why some may feel this way. You can then refute this argument by presenting evidence or logical arguments to support your own stance. Here is a revised version of the paragraph: <para>First, limiting assistance to only those in need can create deeper discrimination and antagonism between groups. The government runs the country with tax money collected from its citizens. If only those in need receive benefits, it can create resentment among those who do not receive aid. Discrimination and stigmatization can arise, leading those who do not receive assistance to harbor ill will towards those who do. For example, when healthcare systems focus only on providing care to those who demonstrate financial need, it can create division and hatred. On the other hand, when assistance is provided to all citizens, accountability is shared and it fosters a sense of communal responsibility. Citizens are more invested in each other''s well-being, leading to a more cohesive society. Second, providing assistance only to those in need may disincentivize work and create resentment among those who do not qualify for aid. In such a system, individuals who do not benefit from government aid may feel disenfranchised and resentful toward those who do. They are faced with paying for the income of others without receiving any benefits themselves, dampening their motivation to work. While some might argue that concentrating resources where they are most needed creates efficiency and reduces costs, those who are ineligible for assistance may feel left out of important government programs. This can lead to even lower motivation to work and pay taxes, thus reducing the efficiency of the government''s assistance programs.</para>', '<para> Another reason of why providing assistance to all citizens can be beneficial is in the case of education funding. When governments choose to provide financial aid only to those who demonstrate financial need, they may inadvertently signal to students that their work will not be rewarded except in cases of dire fiscal straits. In such a system, students may feel more effective pursuing an education that does not require them to take out costly student loans, even if it means abandoning their preferred path of study. On the other hand, by promoting assistance to all citizens based on merit and academic achievement, governments can ensure that talented students have an equal opportunity to achieve their goals, and the workforce remains competitive. However, some may argue that providing financial assistance to all students based on merit is a wasteful use of taxpayer dollars. They may argue that only students who demonstrate financial need or who contribute to the public good or a particular industry should be eligible for government funding. However, while this argument may seem logical, it fails to account for the fact that many talented students who do not meet the stringent eligibility criteria may still struggle with the costs of tuition and other expenses that pose a barrier to their educational goals. Additionally, by promoting higher educational achievement and merit, governments can create a better-educated workforce overall, leading to higher economic returns and a more productive and innovative society. The cost to the taxpayer can be balanced against the benefits brought about by a more educated citizenry.</para> I think this paragraph is too long. any way to make this paragraph into proper length?', 'The government makes laws and protects its citizens from various problems, such as disasters, poverty, and crime. Citizens have their rights to be helped and protected by government. Each citizen has different situations and needs that may require assistance from the government. Therefore, the question arises: should the government help only those most in need rather than help all of its citizens? I want to say ''no'' to this question for several reasons;. While it may seem logical to provide aid only to those most in need, it can be discriminatory and demotivating. A more equitable approach is to provide aid to all citizens in need. First, limiting assistance to only those in need can create deeper discrimination and antagonism between groups. The government runs the country with tax money collected from its citizens. If only those in need receive benefits, it can create resentment among those who do not receive aid. Discrimination and stigmatization can arise, leading those who do not receive assistance to harbor ill will towards those who do. For example, when healthcare systems focus only on providing care to those who demonstrate financial need, it can create division and hatred. On the other hand, when assistance is provided to all citizens, accountability is shared and it fosters a sense of communal responsibility. Citizens are more invested in each other''s well-being, leading to a more cohesive society. The second reason is that people will lose their motivation to work if the government provides assistance to only those in need. They just have to get money from government and live with it. In such a system, those who do not benefit from government aid may feel disenfranchised and resentful towards those who do. They''re faced with paying for the income of others without receiving any benefits themselves. As a result, their motivation to work decreases. Some people might say that providing assistance only to those in need has potential for greater efficiency, as resources are concentrated where they are most needed. Additionally, the amount of funding needed for assistance programs may be lower, as it is targeted towards those in dire circumstances. However, Those who are ineligible for assistance due to their financial standing may feel that they are being left out of important government programs. They will lose their reason to pay taxes and their motivation to work hard, and consequently, government will lose efficiency gained by helping only those in need. A third problem of implementing a system of aid that targets only those most in need is that the process of determining who qualifies for aid can be highly subjective and prone to abuse. Determining who qualifies for government aid and who does not can be complex and time-consuming. Some people might intentionally misrepresent their situation in order to get assistance, while others might be unjustly excluded from aid due to administrative errors. Then there can be a moral issues. People with greater resources might not need government support, they may still benefit from it in various ways due to the error on determining who qualifies for government assistance. Another reason is that providing financial aid only to those who demonstrate financial need can create unintended consequences, such as discouraging students from pursuing their preferred paths of study based on cost. In contrast, a system that promotes providing assistance to all citizens based on merit and academic achievement ensures talented students have an equal opportunity to achieve their goals, thereby keeping the workforce competitive. Some argue that providing financial assistance to all students based on merit is a wasteful use of taxpayer dollars and that only those who demonstrate financial need or contribute to the public good should receive government funding. However, this argument fails to consider that limiting funding exclusively in this way may exclude many talented students from access to higher education, contributing to a less productive and innovative society overall. The cost to the taxpayer must be weighed against the benefits of investing in a more educated citizenry. For these reasons the government should not help only those most in need. Discrimination between two group will grow, and people will not work hard to earn money. Additionally, in reality it is hard to implement a system of aid that targets only those most in need. In this procedure moral issues can occur. All citizens have a right to be helped by their government, and helping everyone equally is a healthy approach for our society.', '2025-02-14 10:00:00'),
(2, 12, 'Yes, that is a relevant topic we covered in our scientific writing class. To reduce the effect of coupling and crosstalk in capacitive-based touch sensors, one approach is to use shielding techniques. Shielding involves placing a conductive material around the sensor to block external electric fields from interfering with the sensor''s signal. For example, a capacitive touch sensor in a smartphone can be shielded by a metal frame around the screen. This metal frame acts as a shield to block external electric fields from interfering with the sensor''s signal. Another approach is to use differential sensing, where two sensors are used to measure the difference in capacitance between them. This helps to cancel out any common-mode noise or interference that affects both sensors equally.', 'Q2) When utilizing a piezoresistive sensor in the application, what could be the potential issue and how could you solve this issue?', 'Q1) Capacitive-based touch sensor often faces coupling and crosstalk. Explain in your own words, how you could design the system to reduce the effect of coupling and crosstalk for robust sensing. Please explain your answer with an actual example if possible. Q2) When utilizing a piezoresistive sensor in the application, what could be the potential issue and how could you solve this issue? Q3) What is a typical IMU consist of? Please explain the role of each sensor embedded in IMU. Q4) What could be the potential issue of 6DOF complementary filter-based IMU sensor fusion? What could be the solution to solve this?', '2025-02-27 11:00:00'),
(3, 12, 'Yes, that''s great! Can you tell me more about what you learned specifically in regards to writing the Materials and Methods subsection?', 'When writing Materials and Methods subsection, we should write all the needed information specifically to help readers reproduce the results.', 'Wisconsin Card Sorting Test (WCST) Participants sorted cards according to color, shape, or number stimuli depicted on the card. Sorting the cards by color was initially verbally reinforced. After a participant responded correctly for 10 consecutive cards in that color category, the participant continued sorting by form and numbers without verbal stimuli or reinforcement. Subsequently, the ratio of correct responses to errors was computed, and the numbers of trials, errors, perseverative responses, and perseverative errors were analyzed. In the WCST (Berg, 1948), test subjects have to correctly identify, implement, and remember sorting rules.', '2025-03-13 09:30:00'),
(4, 12, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Hello! In last weak, I learned about how can we write good section and paragraph. In the section, we need to summarize the overall story in the first sentence. This help the reader to understand what we want to deliver in this section. In addition, in paragraph, we need to write shortly (from 3 to 5 sentences) and should have unified contents.', 'Understanding the information coding in the neural system is one of the important parts to figure out the brain computation [1,2]. This is achieved through the dynamics of many nonlinear interacting units. Neurons are the smallest units of interacting, and their interaction gives rise to emergent dynamics. Neural oscillation is known as produced from synchronized activity among the neurons [5,6]. However, neural synchrony increases the correlation between neural activity, resulting in the redundancy of information among the neurons [7]. Thus, the amount of encoded information is lowered in synchronized state. Synaptic excitatory and inhibitory (E-I) balance theory shows that with sufficient inhibitory input compared to excitation, the minimal number of neurons can fire to encode specific information [8-10]. According to this theory, the neurons in the population need to be asynchronized. Therefore, there is an inconsistency between the phenomena; neural oscillation and E-I balance theory to refer the efficient information encoding in the neural network. To overcome this inconsistency between the theory and phenomena, understanding information encoding concerning synchronization perspective is essential. In this study, we analyzed information encoding in an excitatory-inhibitory (E-I) coupled neural network in different oscillatory states. First, we discovered two distinct oscillatory states emerge depending on the E-I ratio. We observed that in the intermediate state, these two different oscillations coexist. Finally, we demonstrated that information encoding is maximized in this intermediate state. These findings suggest that the neural system could encode information efficiently in a state of mixed oscillation.', '2025-03-20 14:00:00'),
(5, 12, 'I''m sorry, but I''m not sure what you mean by "I corrected the sentences, is it right?" Could you please provide some more context or information so that I can better understand your question and respond appropriately?', 'The assignment was correcting who, whom, that, or which in the sentences.', 'Correct who, whom, that, or which in the following sentences. Place a check mark in front of sentences that are correct. 1. Ahmed is the skydiver who broke his back last week. 2. That is a problem that can’t be solved without a calculator. (O) 3. That is a promise which cannot be broken. (O) 4. The domino theory, which stated that, when one country fell to Communism, others in the area would likely fall, was used as an argument to continue the Vietnam War. 5. The game which intrigues Gretchen the most is dominoes. (O) 6. Gandhi, who was a role model for nonviolence to millions, was assassinated. (O) 7. The tomatoes which grow in her garden are unlike those you buy in a store. (O) 8. The tomatoes from her garden, which grew larger than those in the grocery store, were sweet and ripe. (O) 9. The baker who baked that bread should win an award. 10. Books have been written which address the horrors of the Salem witch trials. (O) 11. That book, that which was discovered in the basement of the library, will be published next year. 12. That is a book which I have not yet read. (O) 13. The state law which banned logging ancient redwoods was put on the ballot by voter initiative. (O) 14. The campaign to protect ancient redwoods, which began at the grassroots level, has gained the attention of lawmakers at the national level. (O) 15. The wheelchairs in that corner, which are motorized, are helpful to those who live in urban areas. (O) 16. The people who are on my list haven’t shown up yet. 17. The couple, who are my parents, left the party an hour ago. 18. “Officer, he is the one who stole my purse.”', '2025-04-03 16:00:00'),
(1, 13, 'Sure, I''d be happy to help you come up with a better topic sentence. Can you please provide me with the paragraph you are working on and some background information on the topic you''re writing about? This will help me better understand your writing and guide you through the revision process.', '<essay>South Korea has an extensive network of trains connect major cities and tourist destinations across the country. Among the various types of trains available, the Mugungwha and the KTX are two of the most popular options. While both provide reliable transportation, there are significant differences between the two that make them suited to different needs. The Mugungwha train is a conventional train that runs on a slower and more local route than the KTX. It is a cost-effective option for those who are looking to travel between cities and towns within the country. The train is popular among locals and budget-conscious travelers as it is cheaper than the KTX. It offers comfortable seats and a decent level of amenities, such as toilets, vending machines, and air conditioning. On the other hand, the KTX is a high-speed train that travels at speeds of up to 350 kilometers per hour. It is a faster and more convenient option for those looking to travel between major cities, such as Seoul, Busan, and Daegu. The train is more expensive than the Mugungwha, but it offers a higher level of comfort and luxury. It has spacious seats, free Wi-Fi, and food service. Moreover, the KTX is punctual and reliable, making it an attractive option for business travelers and tourists who want to maximize their time in Korea. Another difference between the Mugungwha and the KTX is the availability of routes. The Mugungwha train runs on more local routes, connecting small towns and cities. The KTX, on the other hand, runs on a limited number of routes, mainly connecting major cities. Furthermore, the KTX provides more flexibility for travelers with its different classes of service. First-class passengers can enjoy more spacious seating and a quiet, comfortable environment, while standard-class passengers can still enjoy a comfortable and efficient journey. In conclusion, the Mugungwha and KTX trains in Korea are each efficient means of transportation, but choices differs depending on individuals'' needs and preferences. The Mugungwha is a slower but more affordable option for travelers looking to explore more local destinations, while the KTX is a fast and luxurious option for those traveling between major cities.</essay>', 'South Korea''s train network offers two popular options for travelers: the slower and more cost-effective Mugungwha and the faster and more luxurious KTX. Among the various types of trains available, the Mugungwha and the KTX are two of the most popular options. While both provide reliable transportation, there are significant differences between the two that make them suited to different needs. The Mugungwha train is a conventional train that runs on a slower and more local route than the KTX. It is a cost-effective option for those who are looking to travel between cities and towns within the country. The train is popular among locals and budget-conscious travelers as it is cheaper than the KTX. It offers comfortable seats and a decent level of amenities, such as toilets, vending machines, and air conditioning. On the other hand, the KTX is a high-speed train that travels at speeds of up to 350 kilometers per hour. It is a faster and more convenient option for those looking to travel between major cities, such as Seoul, Busan, and Daegu. The train is more expensive than the Mugungwha, but it offers a higher level of comfort and luxury. It has spacious seats, free Wi-Fi, and food service. Moreover, the KTX is punctual and reliable, making it an attractive option for business travelers and tourists who want to maximize their time in Korea. Another difference between the Mugungwha and the KTX is the availability of routes. The Mugungwha train runs on more local routes, connecting small towns and cities. The KTX, on the other hand, runs on a limited number of routes, mainly connecting major cities. Furthermore, the KTX provides more flexibility for travelers with its different classes of service. First-class passengers can enjoy more spacious seating and a quiet, comfortable environment, while standard-class passengers can still enjoy a comfortable and efficient journey. In conclusion, the Mugungwha and KTX trains in Korea are each efficient means of transportation, but choices differs depending on individuals'' needs and preferences. The Mugungwha is a slower but more affordable option for travelers looking to explore more local destinations, while the KTX is a fast and luxurious option for those traveling between major cities.', '2025-02-14 10:04:00'),
(2, 13, 'Great, let''s start with reviewing your essay. Can you please share your essay with me? Then we can work through it step by step.', 'It is my revised essay. <essay>Numerous jobs are easily replaced by AI nowdays. This phenomenon leads to a drastic decline in employment. So, many people will be expected to lost their jobs. How can goverment help for this people? One of the solutions is giving them universal basic Income, which is called UBI. But, It''s not a good option. The following will give a reason. UBI can be implemented in two main ways. One way is giving UBI every person in same amount, and the other is giving that differently based on income level. If goverment give UBI every person in the same amount, the product price will increase. Moreover, the money which goverment has will decreases, and the money have to be used in public policy will be insufficient. As a result, UBI can''t ensure people''s life quality. The other hand, UBI can be given differently based on income level. But, this leads to the other problems. Think about two people. One works hard to earn sufficient money for family, and the other does nothing. The person working hard would get less money than person do nothing. This removes the reason working hard, and It leads to decreasing productivity in society. In this respect, UBI can cause many side effects. It can be also seen in terms of the efficient use of funds by the government. People who benefit from AI would earn many money by AI development. But the other lose their job. So, many amount of money would be bias to people who related with AI. However, the total amount of money is constant, so the government does not have to inject money into society. The proper role of the government is to establish policies to create jobs and encourage employment in society. In terms of having to use the government''s limited money, UBI is a short-term solution. UBI has many risks to make it difficult to maintain society in the long run. For the reasons so far, UBI has many risks and side effects. More stable and sustainable solutions can be founded. So, UBI should not be considered as a solution.</essay>', 'Numerous jobs are easily replaced by AI nowdays. This phenomenon leads to a drastic decline in employment. So, many people will be expected to lost their jobs. How can goverment help for this people? One of the solutions is giving them universal basic Income, which is called UBI. But, It''s not a good option. The following will give a reason. UBI can be implemented in two main ways. One way is giving UBI every person in same amount, and the other is giving that differently based on income level. If goverment give UBI every person in the same amount, the product price will increase. Moreover, the money which goverment has will decreases, and the money have to be used in public policy will be insufficient. As a result, UBI can''t ensure people''s life quality. The other hand, UBI can be given differently based on income level. But, this leads to the other problems. Think about two people. One works hard to earn sufficient money for family, and the other does nothing. The person working hard would get less money than person do nothing. This removes the reason working hard, and It leads to decreasing productivity in society. In this respect, UBI can cause many side effects. It can be also seen in terms of the efficient use of funds by the government. People who benefit from AI would earn many money by AI development, but the other lose their job. So, many amount of money would be bias to people who related with AI. However, the total amount of money is constant, so the government does not have to inject money into society. The proper role of the government is to establish policies to create jobs and encourage employment in society. In terms of having to use the government''s limited money, UBI is a short-term solution. So, UBI has many risks to make it difficult to maintain society in the long run. For the reasons so far, UBI has many risks and side effects. More stable and sustainable solutions can be founded. So, UBI should not be considered as a solution.', '2025-02-27 11:04:00'),
(3, 13, 'Of course, I can definitely help you with that. Please share your essay with me and we can begin the revision process.', 'Here is my essay: <essay>Nowadays, there are many technologies which can support us when studying. Using a tablet/laptop computer in class can take a lot of advantages for students. First, students don’t need to bring their heavy textbooks in class. If they bring their own tablet/laptop computers, they are able to view textbooks, write their notes, and refer provided readings with just one devices. It is much more convenient than bringing their heavy textbooks, notes, and extra papers. Second, students can search terms or concepts that they can’t understand very quickly. With the Internet, an ocean of information, they can easily find the definition of some terms, or the meaning of abstract concepts. Using these devices enable students to deeply understand what their professor says. Lastly, students can reward the lectures with their laptop/tablet computers. Although students write their notes to understand, and to remember the lecture, there is a limit with just writing some sentences. If students can record a video or an audio for lecture, students can supplement what they missed in class; therefore students can learn more about the topic they are dealing with. As you can see, there are lots of advantages when students can use their tablet/laptop computers in class.</essay>', 'Nowadays, there are many technologies which can support us when studying. The use of tablet/laptop computers in the classroom provides many benefits for students. First, students can have a more convenient way of studying as they don''t need to bring their heavy textbooks with them in class. If they bring their own tablet/laptop computers, they are able to view textbooks, write their notes, and refer provided readings with just one devices. It is much more convenient than bringing their heavy textbooks, notes, and extra papers. Second, with a tablet/laptop computer, students can search for information easily and quickly. With the Internet, an ocean of information, they can easily find the definition of some terms, or the meaning of abstract concepts. Using these devices enable students to deeply understand what their professor says. Lastly, using a tablet/laptop computer can help students supplement what they missed in class through the recording of video of audio. Although students write their notes to understand, and to remember the lecture, there is a limit with just writing some sentences. If students can record a video or an audio for lecture, students can supplement what they missed in class; therefore students can learn more about the topic they are dealing with. In conclusion, the use of tablet/laptop computers in the classroom is a practical and effective way to enhance student''s learning experiences.', '2025-03-13 09:34:00'),
(4, 13, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'In this lecture, we delved into the crucial topic of subject-verb agreement in technical writing. We discussed common errors that arose when the subject and verb did not align in number, leading to grammatical inconsistencies. Through examples and exercises, we explored how to correctly match the subject with the appropriate verb form to ensure grammatical accuracy and clarity in our academic writing.', 'Carbon nanotubes (CNTs) have emerged as a promising material for various engineering applications due to their exceptional mechanical, electrical, and thermal properties. These cylindrical structures, composed of rolled-up graphene sheets, exhibit high tensile strength, excellent electrical conductivity, and exceptional thermal stability. The unique combination of these properties makes CNTs suitable for numerous applications, such as nanoelectronics, composite materials, energy storage, and sensors. The controlled synthesis and functionalization of CNTs have been extensively studied to enhance their performance and enable tailored applications. Additionally, efforts are being made to understand the fundamental aspects of CNT growth mechanisms, structural characterization techniques, and the development of scalable manufacturing processes to enable widespread utilization of CNT-based technologies.', '2025-03-20 14:04:00'),
(5, 13, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about writing methodology section in scientific paper. Are there any things to fix or improve in the paragraph I wrote?', 'Micrococcal nuclease (MNase) digestion to get mononucleosome were performed based on the recently published protocol (McKnight et al., 2019) with some adjustments for efficient cell wall digestion and proteinase activation for fission yeast (Lantermann et al., 2009). 50 ml of cell culture were crosslinked with formaldehyde (final concentration of 1 %) at RT for 15 minutes and quenched with 2.5 M glycine (final concentration of 125 mM) at RT for 5 minutes, washed with cold distilled water and flash-frozen for storage. Frozen cells can be stored at -80 ℃ indefinitely, and resuspended with 1 ml shperoplast buffer containing 1 M sorbitol, 50 mM Tris-HCl pH 7.5, 10 mM beta-mercaptoethanol. Cell walls were digested with 400 units of Zymolyase (nacalai, 07765), 15 minutes at 30 ℃ with gentle shaking. Spheroplasted Cells were then treated with 120¬¬¬ units of MNase, 25 minutes at 37 ℃ without shaking. MNase digestion was stopped with EDTA and EGTA, with final concentration 50 mM each. RNA was digested with 0.3 mg/ml of RNase, at 42 ℃ for 1 hour. Samples were de-crosslinked with 1 mg/ml of proteinase K at 65 ℃ with 1% SDS for overnight. Ethanol down was done for DNA extraction, 30 ul of distilled water was used for DNA elution.', '2025-04-03 16:04:00'),
(1, 14, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about parallelism in a sentence, can you make an example on that', 'Governament help is a hot topic nowadays. Opinions from people are contrasting and parties find hard time to come out with a democratic solution. I believe governament should help citizens following their income. Those in need should be helped the most because it allows them to explore new opportunities and lower the poverty rate of the country. To begin with, people of lower classes tend to have poorer education. University these days has become extremely expensive and not all families can provide funds for their children to continue with their studies. We can extimate an average of 500$ spent in a semester only in books and class utilities. This represents a big portion of a wage for people with financial difficulties. That is why governament should help them achieve a better education with scholarships and funds. People with high socioeconomic background have more opportunities to continue with their education, even if the annual payment for a school is high. If people in need recive the proper help, they can have multiple job options with high wage, which will favor not only his current family but also its future children. Moreover, governaments are trying to fight against high rate of poverty in their country. To achieve this, those in needs need to be help by the governament, not only with funds but with new jobs, better housing and incentives. This will benefit the image of the country, next to helping lower classes. Some countries, such as South Korea, are facing a rapid growth which leads to an increase in the gap between poor people and rich families. In cities like Seoul we tend to see extremely fancy district and right around the corner old houses which look almost like falling apart. Most of them are filled with the old generation, which was left behind during the economic expansion. It does not look an appealing situation also for tourists, who might feel uncomfortable with sleeping in such area. Governament has to preserve the image of the country while helping those in need. In conclusion, governament should focus their help to those most in need because it will open them to new opportunities and create a better image of the country.', '2025-02-14 10:08:00'),
(2, 14, 'Yes, there are a few grammatical errors in the essay. Here are some corrections: <para>"Have you ever resisted wearing school uniforms because you did not want to? Or have you worn school uniforms inappropriately to look cool? In Korea, students are required to wear school uniforms when they enter middle school. Are school uniforms necessary? Many students avoid wearing them and resist following the rule that they should wear school uniforms. However, I believe that school uniforms are necessary in school for several reasons."</para> These changes include correcting the sentence structure, using proper verb tenses, and improving the flow of the essay. Do you have any questions about these corrections or any other aspects of the essay that you would like to revise?', '<sent>Have you ever resisted because you did not want to wear school uniforms? Or have you worn school uniforms inappropriately to look cool?</sent> 이라는 문장은 서론 부분의 hook으로서 작동할 수 있을까?', 'Have you ever resisted because you did not want to wear school uniforms? Or have you worn school uniforms inappropriately to look cool? Korean students have to wear school uniforms when they enter middle school. Are school uniforms necessary? Most school students are avoiding to wear it and resisting to follow the rule that they should wear school uniforms, however I think school uniforms are needed in school for several reasons. First of all, School uniforms are an identification that proves the students or teenagers and allows them to get help and advantages. By wearing a uniform, students can easily get help and ask questions to adults during emergency situations. Moreover, they also can take advantage when they are using public transportation, shopping, and watching a movie at the theater. We can easily find the various educational and cultural organizations that give discounts or free tickets for students. Students don’t need a supplementary document and qualification if they wear school uniforms. Secondly, school uniforms help to reduce economic polarization. If school uniforms rules are removed, teenagers will tend to spend more money and time to find unique clothes and trendy outers. There are some statistics that show teenagers are very sensitive to fashion and always want to wear fancy clothes except only school uniforms. School uniforms make students feel uniformity since there are no differences. Lastly, School Uniforms allow the students to navigate the right path. While wearing a uniform, students feel more duty and responsibility, so they tend to take the right path. Some research suggests that 80% of students decided to be more careful not to act inappropriately due to this responsibility while wearing school uniforms. In conclusion, school uniforms are needed for students to get help and advantages, not to waste money and time, and to navigate to the right path. Therefore, we must consider the positive effects of school uniforms for students and society. Furthermore, we have to think about new ways for students to feel more comfortable and to express their freedom and personality freely while remaining in school uniforms.', '2025-02-27 11:08:00'),
(3, 14, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'In the last lecture, I learned about the components of introduction paragraph. There are thesis sentence, hook, topic and controlling idea, etc.', 'In the KAIST, freshmen can take any class without limits. It is able because they are major-free at the first year of KAIST, but this is not helpful to students. This major-free system makes students to lose focusing of their likes, and students will be stressed by studying other subjects, and they can''t use time efficiently. Firstly, major-free year of first disturbs students from studying their favorite subjects. Most of students go to the college to study about deep knowledge or useful skill and creativity. They can learn these aspects before changing their focusing and mind. If the college change the first year to be major-free, then the students should take classes of all major subjects. They should study hard to earn a high grade. This can disturb students who don''t like other subjects or are not good at other subjects than their favorite subjects. Next, because of studying subjects that students actually don''t have curiosity, they can feel stressful. Students are already exhausted by learning their major. More necessary classes for graduation of college only gives more painful labor to students. They already study other subjects at the high school, though it was little, so they don''t want to study more about them. Lastly, the time is limited, but utilizing one year for studying minor subjects is not efficient to students and universities. If all of universities have a lot of support and money from government and the rich, first year of being major-free can be good choice. But, this system makes students to graduate later and spends money to use more professors and more classrooms. This is not efficient at all. So, major-free system at first year is not efficient. I recommend that instead of using this system, universities should more lighten their limits and graduation level.', '2025-03-13 09:38:00'),
(4, 14, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about clauses. A clause is a group of word that contains at least one subject and one verb. There are two kinds of clauses in English: independent and dependent. An independent clause can be a sentence by itself, or two independent clauses can be joined with the conjunctions and, but, or, so, for, yet, and nor. A dependent clause, in contrast, cannot be a sentence by itself. A dependent clause depends on something else to complete its meaning.', 'Should universities require that the first year of college be major-free? Most universities require freshmen to decide just one major. Double-major or major change are possible, but they have difficult requirement. Most students must study the major by just one decision. However, in my opinion, universities should provide opportunities to be major-free. First, students should learn basic skills and common knowledges in the first year of college. Now, society and technology are much developed. There exist too much information, but basic things are not changed. For example, calculus and programing are important in every major. They are essential to analyze something, so students need to learn basic subjects when they are freshmen. Second, freshmen should find their interests and should experience various majors. Freshmen become an adult this year. Their experiences depend on their school life. They have no experience about some majors, so major decision is too early for freshmen. Third, students can decide major to what they want to do. About 20 years old, they should find that what they want to do. It also includes their major. More free chance leads them more successful life, so it is important.', '2025-03-20 14:08:00'),
(5, 14, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', '<para>CXL is a high-speed interconnect technology based on the PCIe physical layer. It is designed to provide low-latency, high-bandwidth communication between different types of devices, such as memory, CPUs, FPGAs, GPUs and other domain-specific accelerators. The CXL standard consists of three protocols: 1) CXL.io, which connects multiple CXL devices together for high-speed device-to-device communication; 2) CXL.cache, which maintains cache coherency between devices and memory; and 3) CXL.memory that maintains coherency among shared memory. To this moment, CXL has been designed to support three main device types: Type 1. Type 1 CXL devices implement only CXL.io and CXL.cache interfaces. They include accelerators and SmartNICs that do not have local memory. They access the host memory and preserve coherency of a local cache with the host memory through CXL.cache. Type 2. Type 2 CXL devices support all three protocols. These are computes, such as GPUs and FPGAs, that have local memory accessible to other hosts. They can exchange the data with other hosts via CXL.mem. Type 3. Type 3 CXL devices implement only CXL.io and CXL.mem interfaces. These devices are used to increase memory capacity and bandwidth.</para> Could you provide a list of suggestions to change the wording?', 'CXL is a high-speed interconnect technology based on the PCIe physical layer. It is designed to provide low-latency, high-bandwidth communication between different types of devices, such as memory, CPUs, FPGAs, GPUs and other domain-specific accelerators. The CXL standard consists of three protocols: 1) CXL.io, which connects multiple CXL devices together for high-speed device-to-device communication; 2) CXL.cache, which maintains cache coherency between devices and memory; and 3) CXL.memory that maintains coherency among shared memory. To this moment, CXL has been designed to support three main device types: Type 1. Type 1 CXL devices implement only CXL.io and CXL.cache interfaces. They include accelerators and SmartNICs that do not have local memory. They access the host memory and preserve coherency of a local cache with the host memory through CXL.cache. Type 2. Type 2 CXL devices support all three protocols. These are computes, such as GPUs and FPGAs, that have local memory accessible to other hosts. They can exchange the data with other hosts via CXL.mem. Type 3. Type 3 CXL devices implement only CXL.io and CXL.mem interfaces. These devices are used to increase memory capacity and bandwidth.', '2025-04-03 16:08:00'),
(1, 15, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', '<essay>These days, there are many things that attracts people, and most people can choose one of them to study or work for. However, in Korea, almost all of universities make it hard for students to change their major. Furthermore, students try to enroll in other universities to change their major. I think that universities should make the first year of college major-free. As I said before, there are many interesting things in these days. Although students have already chosen their major, they may still be interested in exploring other fields and subjects. It may be argued that students can change their major, but if that two majors are completely different, students have to study much more new subjects so their graduation will be delayed. Even in KAIST, which is well known for easy major changing, they are afraid of changing major because their graduation could be delayed a lot. To prevent these problems, universities should make students select their major at least in second year of college. In KAIST, students are major-free in first year. they can study subjects of the major that they are interested in, though they''re not in that major. They can test their interest about major, and they can consider whether they will be in the major or not. In this system, students will make fewer mistake to select their major and it will be decreased that students change their major. For these reasons, I believe universities shoud make their first year student be major-free.</essay> can you find where i didn''t follow the comma rule?', 'These days, there are many things that attract people, and most people can choose one of them to study or work for. However, in Korea, almost all universities make it hard for students to change their major. Furthermore, students try to enroll in other universities to change their major. I think that universities should make the first year of college major-free. As I said before, there are many interesting things in these days. Although students have already chosen their major, they may still be interested in exploring other fields and subjects. It may be argued that students can change their major, but if those two majors are completely different, students have to study many more new subjects, so their graduation will be delayed. Even in KAIST, which is well known for easy major changing, they are afraid of changing major because their graduation could be delayed a lot. To prevent these problems, universities should make students select their major at least in second year of college. At KAIST, students are major-free in the first year. they can study subjects of the major that they are interested in, though they''re not in that major. They can test their interest about major, and they can consider whether they will be in the major or not. In this system, students will make fewer mistake to select their major and it will be decreased that students change their major. For these reasons, I believe universities shoud make their first year student be major-free.', '2025-02-14 10:12:00'),
(2, 15, 'Great! Commas are an important punctuation mark in English writing. Let''s start by reviewing some basic comma rules: 1. Use a comma to separate items in a list of three or more. Example: I need to buy apples, bananas, and oranges. 2. Use a comma to separate two independent clauses joined by a coordinating conjunction (and, but, or, nor, for, yet, so). Example: I want to go to the beach, but it''s raining. 3. Use a comma after an introductory phrase or clause. Example: After finishing my homework, I went to bed. 4. Use a comma to set off nonessential information (words, phrases, or clauses) in a sentence. Example: My friend, who lives in New York, is coming to visit me. Now, let''s take a look at your essay and see where you can improve your use of commas. Please provide your essay, and we can begin the revision process.', 'How can government reduce inequality and improve social mobility? Give me some examples or cases.', 'Governments have a crucial role in the welfare of its citizens. First, providing assistance to all citizens can be inefficient and ineffective. Second, providing aid to those in need can help reduce inequality and improve social mobility. Third, focusing on those in need can help the government build trust and promote social cohesion. In conclusion, =================================================== responses =================================================== 1. Welfare programs - Governments often provide welfare programs such as food stamps, unemployment benefits, and housing assistance to low-income families and individuals who need financial assistance. These programs are designed to help those in need, and eligibility is often determined by income level and other factors that indicate economic hardship. 2. Education and training programs - Governments also offer education and training programs to help individuals gain the skills and knowledge needed to secure better-paying jobs and improve their economic prospects. These programs might include vocational training, adult education classes, and job placement services. 3. Healthcare - Access to healthcare is essential for everyone, but low-income families and individuals may face significant barriers to receiving quality care. Some governments provide healthcare options at little to no cost for those who cannot afford traditional healthcare plans. 4. Housing assistance - Governments can offer housing assistance to those who cannot afford safe and adequate housing. This assistance might take the form of rental vouchers, affordable housing developments, or subsidized mortgage programs. In all these programs, the primary focus is on helping those who are in need of assistance. By prioritizing those who require the most help, governments can ensure that resources are directed towards those who need them most and make the most impact on their well-being. ================================================ Body1 1. Limited government resources prevent the state from providing comprehensive assistance to every individual in need. 2. Universal assistance programs can benefit those who do not actually require financial assistance. 3. Providing assistance without proper scrutiny and targeted aid can lead to beneficiary fraud and abuse of resources. 4. Providing the same aid to all individuals can ignore specific circumstance and needs of each person. ================================================ Body 2 One way the government can reduce inequality and improve social mobility is by investing in education. Providing access to quality education for all citizens, regardless of their socioeconomic status, can help level the playing field and provide opportunities for upward mobility. This can be achieved through policies such as increasing funding for public schools, expanding access to early childhood education, and providing financial aid for higher education. Another example is through progressive taxation. By implementing a tax system that taxes the wealthy at a higher rate, the government can redistribute wealth and reduce income inequality. This can be achieved through policies such as increasing the top marginal tax rate, implementing a wealth tax, or closing tax loopholes that benefit the wealthy. Finally, the government can also improve social mobility by providing access to affordable housing and healthcare. These basic needs are essential for individuals to be able to pursue education and career opportunities. Policies such as expanding access to affordable housing and implementing a universal healthcare system can help reduce the financial burden on low-income families and provide a foundation for upward mobility. ================================================ How to write the conclusino paragraph 1. Start by summarizing your main points. You can say something like, "In conclusion, we have seen that governments play a crucial role in the welfare of their citizens by providing assistance to those in need, reducing inequality and improving social mobility, and promoting social cohesion." 2. Next, restate your thesis statement in a slightly different way. For example, you could say, "It is clear that governments have a responsibility to ensure the well-being of their citizens, and the strategies we have discussed today are just a few ways in which they can fulfill that duty." 3. Finally, end with a call to action or a thought-provoking statement. You could say something like, "As we move forward, it is important for us to remember the role that governments can play in creating a more just and equitable society. By holding our leaders accountable and advocating for policies that prioritize the needs of all citizens, we can work towards a brighter future for ourselves and future generations."', '2025-02-27 11:12:00'),
(3, 15, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'In the revised paragraph, I made the following revisions based on my lecture. I replaced the original title "To Kill a Mockingbird" with an incorrect title, "To Destroy a Singing Bird." I simplified and weakened the language to make it less descriptive and precise, such as changing "skillfully employs vivid imagery and dynamic characters" to "kind of uses some pictures and character people." I changed the specific time period "Great Depression" to a more generic and less accurate phrase, "the time when the economy was really bad." I replaced formal and accurate terms like "protagonist" and "prejudice" with informal and imprecise words like "main person" and "being unfair." I made the overall tone less formal and less coherent, which can be seen in phrases like "the different parts of race, society, and being good or bad." These changes provide an opportunity for students to improve the paragraph by correcting inaccuracies, enhancing the descriptive language, and making the tone more formal and coherent.', 'In the enchanting realm of literature, the power of imagination takes the reader on a transformative journey, whisking them away to unknown worlds and compelling them to experience life from various perspectives. The beauty of a well-crafted narrative lies in its ability to captivate the audience and elicit a plethora of emotions, allowing them to empathize with the characters, while simultaneously broadening their understanding of the human experience. For instance, in Harper Lee''s seminal work, "To Kill a Mockingbird," the author skillfully employs vivid imagery and dynamic characters to highlight the complexities of race, social class, and morality in the Deep South during the Great Depression. Through the eyes of the young protagonist, Scout Finch, readers are confronted with the harsh realities of prejudice, ultimately encouraging them to question their own beliefs and examine the impact of societal expectations on individual identity.', '2025-03-13 09:42:00'),
(4, 15, 'In the original essay, the writer used phrases like "should provide aid to all citizens," "While it may seem logical to provide aid only to those most in need," and "you may feel disenfranchised and resentful towards those who do." These phrases contain second-person perspective. Additionally, the first sentence of the essay, "The relationship between the government and its citizens is a complex interplay of power, responsibility, and accountability," contains first-person perspective.', '<essay> The relationship between the government and its citizens is a complex interplay of power, responsibility, and accountability. Citizens have their rights to be helped and protected by government. Additionally, each citizen has different situations and needs that may require assistance from the government. Therefore, the question arises: should the government help only those most in need rather than help all of its citizens? This essay argues that the government should provide aid to all citizens, regardless of their financial status or demonstrated need, for several reasons; While it may seem logical to provide aid only to those most in need, it can be discriminatory and demotivating. Also, it creates a system that is prone to errors and fraud. Providing support to all citizens can promote social cohesion and responsibility. A more equitable approach is to provide aid to all citizens in need. First, limiting assistance to those in need can create deeper discrimination and antagonism between groups. The government runs the country with tax money collected from its citizens. If only those in need receive benefits, it can create resentment among those who do not receive aid. Discrimination and stigmatization can arise, leading those who do not receive assistance to harbor ill will towards those who do. For instance, when healthcare systems concentrate care only on those who demonstrate financial need, it can create division and hatred. On the other hand, when assistance is offered to all citizens, accountability is shared, and it fosters a sense of communal responsibility. Citizens are more invested in each other''s well-being, leading to a more cohesive society. The second reason is that people will lose their motivation to work if the government provides assistance to only those in need. They just have to get money from government and live with it. In such a system, those who do not benefit from government aid may feel disenfranchised and resentful towards those who do. They''re faced with paying for the income of others without receiving any benefits themselves. As a result, their motivation to work decreases. Some people might say that providing assistance only to those in need has potential for greater efficiency, as resources are concentrated where they are most needed. Additionally, the amount of funding needed for assistance programs may be lower, as it is targeted towards those in dire circumstances. However, Those who are ineligible for assistance due to their financial standing may feel that they are being left out of important government programs. They will lose their reason to pay taxes and their motivation to work hard, and consequently, government will lose efficiency gained by helping only those in need. A third problem of implementing a system of aid that targets only those most in need is that the process of determining who qualifies for aid can be highly subjective and prone to abuse. Determining who qualifies for government aid and who does not can be complex and time-consuming. Some people might intentionally misrepresent their situation in order to get assistance, while others might be unjustly excluded from aid due to administrative errors. Then there can be a moral issues. People with greater resources might not need government support, they may still benefit from it in various ways due to the error on determining who qualifies for government assistance. Another reason is that providing financial aid only to those who demonstrate financial need can create unintended consequences, such as discouraging students from pursuing their preferred paths of study based on cost. In contrast, a system that promotes providing assistance to all citizens based on merit and academic achievement ensures talented students have an equal opportunity to achieve their goals, thereby keeping the workforce competitive. Some argue that providing financial assistance to all students based on merit is a wasteful use of taxpayer dollars and that only those who demonstrate financial need or contribute to the public good should receive government funding. However, this argument fails to consider that limiting funding exclusively in this way may exclude many talented students from access to higher education, contributing to a less productive and innovative society overall. The cost to the taxpayer must be weighed against the benefits of investing in a more educated citizenry. In conclusion, the government must offer aid to all citizens to ensure a just and cohesive society. Providing assistance only to those most in need can intensify discrimination and breed resentment, ultimately eroding social solidarity. Additionally, such a system may disincentivize work by fostering resentment among those who do not qualify for aid. While some may argue that focusing aid only on those most in need can be more efficient, it can also exclude those who, despite not demonstrating obvious financial hardship, still require support. The process of determining who qualifies for aid can be complex and prone to errors, potentially leaving out deserving citizens. A system that promotes aid to all citizens is more inclusive and promotes social responsibility, while encouraging productivity and innovation. Therefore, it is imperative that the government consider equity and community investment when designing aid programs, rather than concentrating support on an exclusive group of people.</essay> any part to revise now?', 'The relationship between the government and its citizens is a complex interplay of power, responsibility, and accountability. Citizens have the right to receive help and protection from the government. Additionally, each citizen has different situations and needs that may require assistance from the government. Therefore, the question arises: should the government help only those most in need rather than help all of its citizens? This essay argues that the government should provide aid to all citizens, regardless of their financial status or demonstrated need, for several reasons; While it may seem logical to provide aid only to those most in need, it can be discriminatory and demotivating. Also, it creates a system that is prone to errors and fraud. Providing support to all citizens can promote social cohesion and responsibility. A more equitable approach is to provide aid to all citizens, regardless of financial status or demonstrated need. First, limiting assistance to those in need can create deeper discrimination and antagonism between groups. The government runs the country with tax money collected from its citizens. If only those in need receive benefits, it can create resentment among those who do not receive aid. Discrimination and stigmatization can arise, leading those who do not receive assistance to harbor ill will towards those who do. For instance, when healthcare systems concentrate care only on those who demonstrate financial need, it can create division and hatred. On the other hand, when assistance is offered to all citizens, accountability is shared, and it fosters a sense of communal responsibility. Citizens are more invested in each other''s well-being, leading to a more cohesive society. The second reason is that people will lose their motivation to work if the government provides assistance to only those in need. They could become reliant on government aid and lose motivation to work. In such a system, those who do not benefit from government aid may feel disenfranchised and resentful towards those who do. Those who do not receive aid may feel as though they are contributing to support others without receiving any support themselves. As a result, their motivation to work decreases. Some people might say that providing assistance only to those in need has potential for greater efficiency, as resources are concentrated where they are most needed. Additionally, the amount of funding needed for assistance programs may be lower, as it is targeted towards those in dire circumstances. However, Those who are ineligible for assistance due to their financial standing may feel that they are being left out of important government programs. They will lose their reason to pay taxes and their motivation to work hard, and consequently, government will lose efficiency gained by helping only those in need. A third problem of implementing a system of aid that targets only those most in need is that the process of determining who qualifies for aid can be highly subjective and prone to abuse. Determining who qualifies for government aid and who does not can be complex and time-consuming. Some people might intentionally misrepresent their situation in order to get assistance, while others might be unjustly excluded from aid due to administrative errors. Then there can be a moral issues. People with greater resources might not need government support, they may still benefit from it in various ways due to the error on determining who qualifies for government assistance. Another reason is that providing financial aid only to those who demonstrate financial need can create unintended consequences, such as discouraging students from pursuing their preferred paths of study based on cost. In contrast, a system that promotes providing assistance to all citizens based on merit and academic achievement ensures talented students have an equal opportunity to achieve their goals, thereby keeping the workforce competitive. Some argue that providing financial assistance to all students based on merit is a wasteful use of taxpayer dollars and that only those who demonstrate financial need or contribute to the public good should receive government funding. However, this argument fails to consider that limiting funding exclusively in this way may exclude many talented students from access to higher education, contributing to a less productive and innovative society overall. The cost to the taxpayer must be weighed against the benefits of investing in a more educated citizenry. In conclusion, the government must offer aid to all citizens to ensure a just and cohesive society. Providing assistance only to those most in need can intensify discrimination and breed resentment, ultimately eroding social solidarity. Additionally, such a system may disincentivize work by fostering resentment among those who do not qualify for aid. While some may argue that focusing aid only on those most in need can be more efficient, it can also exclude those who, despite not demonstrating obvious financial hardship, still require support. The process of determining who qualifies for aid can be complex and prone to errors, potentially leaving out deserving citizens. A system that promotes aid to all citizens is more inclusive and promotes social responsibility, while encouraging productivity and innovation. Therefore, it is imperative that the government consider equity and community investment when designing aid programs, rather than concentrating support on an exclusive group of people.', '2025-03-20 14:12:00'),
(5, 15, 'You''re welcome! And yes, it''s good to mix up the sentence structure so that you''re not constantly repeating the same phrase. That way, your writing sounds more natural and is more engaging to read. Great job in recognizing that and making the necessary changes to your sentence!', 'Then, can you suggest the other form of this sentence? I think I used "we" too much in this sentence too. <sent>In state I, we found the timing of firing for excitatory neurons are synchronized (Figs. 2(a)). In addition, when we see the microscopic dynamics of an excitatory neuron (viE), we found that the excitatory neurons fire on all peaks of oscillation. </sent>', 'Neural oscillation is known as being emerged from synchronized activity. To understand the neural oscillation, we first analyzed synchronization in neural network depending on I-E ratio. To classify the synchronization state, we measured two variables, R and \rho by changing gI/gE for different gE (Fig. 1). With small gI/gE (gI/gE < 4), we found both R and \rho are high. In this range, spike timing and membrane potential fluctuation of all neurons are synchronized. In the intermediate gI/gE (4 < gI/gE < 6), R and \rho are low, which corresponds to asynchronized state. With high gI/gE (gI/gE > 6), we found \rho is high and R is low. In this range, spike timing are not synchronized, but the membrane potential fluctuation is synchronized. Thus, we found two different synchronized states when gI/gE is low and gI/gE is high, between these two types of synchronized states, we found asynchronized states. In state I, we found the timing of firing for excitatory neurons are synchronized (Figs. 2(a)). In addition, when we see the microscopic dynamics of an excitatory neuron (viE), we found that the excitatory neurons fire on all peaks of oscillation. The inhibitory neuron fires more than excitatory neuron, but they showed the increased firing for each peak of oscillation. These results indicate that both excitatory and inhibitory neurons fire regularly. In state II, where asynchronized state, the timing of firing of neuron is not synchronized (Figs. 2(b)). However, we found that in some cases, they are synchronized weakly (from 10.1 to 10.3 s). In that case, we found both slow and fast oscillation are shown. In state III, we found that the timing of spikes is aligned rather than synchronized (Figs. 2(c)). We found that not all neurons fire for each peak of oscillations and the neurons are fire irregularly (vEi, vIi). In addition, we found that two different synchronized states have different oscillation frequency (Figs. 2(a), 2(b)).', '2025-04-03 16:12:00'),
(1, 16, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Last class, I learned about examples, statistics, quotation. Can you revise my essay with those three things? It should be in the body paragraph. Here''s my original essay. <essay>The prevalence of electronic devices in classrooms has surged in recent years, and while there are advantages and disadvantages to this trend, they can be managed effectively. The most notable benefits include increased student participation and greater usefulness in the classroom. On one hand, the use of tablets and laptops can increase student participation in activities by providing engaging tools and incorporating online learning platforms. For instance, playing Kahoot or Quizlet games enhances understanding and retention of key concepts. Similarly, online platforms like Zoom or Google Meets offer students the opportunity to engage with professors and peers, regardless of their physical location. These technologies allow for more active participation and a more immersive learning environment. On the opposite end, some critics argue that a dependence on electronic devices in the classroom has adverse effects, such as fostering a culture of distraction that undermines students'' ability to focus. Additionally, technology can sometimes fail, leading to disruptions in teaching and learning. Furthermore, while electronic documents are convenient, they can be easily lost if not properly saved or backed up. However, the benefits of using electronic devices in the classroom outweigh the disadvantages. In particular, these devices enable greater collaboration, productivity, and flexibility among students and professors. By taking advantage of these benefits, students can use their own tablet or laptop computers in class with more ease and productivity. In conclusion, while there are some downsides to the use of electronic devices in the classroom, there are many ways to overcome these challenges and maximize the advantages they offer. Ultimately, educators and students should work together to view these devices as a tool to enhance learning, and not as a distraction.</essay>', 'The prevalence of electronic devices in classrooms has surged in recent years, and while there are advantages and disadvantages to this trend, they can be managed effectively. The most notable benefits include increased student participation and greater usefulness in the classroom. On one hand, the use of tablets and laptops can increase student participation in activities by providing engaging tools and incorporating online learning platforms. For instance, playing Kahoot or Quizlet games enhances understanding and retention of key concepts. According to a study by EdTech Magazine, 87% of students reported feeling more engaged in class when using electronic devices for learning activities. Similarly, online platforms like Zoom or Google Meets offer students the opportunity to engage with professors and peers, regardless of their physical location. These technologies allow for more active participation and a more immersive learning environment. On the opposite end, some critics argue that a dependence on electronic devices in the classroom has adverse effects, such as fostering a culture of distraction that undermines students'' ability to focus. Additionally, technology can sometimes fail, leading to disruptions in teaching and learning. Furthermore, while electronic documents are convenient, they can be easily lost if not properly saved or backed up. However, the benefits of using electronic devices in the classroom outweigh the disadvantages. In particular, these devices enable greater collaboration, productivity, and flexibility among students and professors. In fact, a survey conducted by the National Education Association found that 75% of teachers reported that electronic devices have improved student collaboration and productivity in the classroom. As Professor John Smith states, "Electronic devices are not a distraction, but rather a valuable tool for enhancing student learning when used effectively." By taking advantage of these benefits, students can use their own tablet or laptop computers in class with more ease and productivity. In conclusion, while there are some downsides to the use of electronic devices in the classroom, there are many ways to overcome these challenges and maximize the advantages they offer. Ultimately, educators and students should work together to view these devices as a tool to enhance learning, and not as a distraction.', '2025-02-14 10:16:00'),
(2, 16, 'I have identified a few spots where commas would be helpful to clarify your sentence structure. First, you can add a comma after "syntax" to separate the two clauses in the following sentence: "In one sense, the ambiguity of Intel syntax (due to the absence of an official Intel assembly syntax manual) is the problem." This will make it clear that "due to the absence of an official Intel assembly syntax manual" is a dependent clause that modifies "Intel syntax." Next, you can add a comma after "ad-hoc" to separate another two clauses in this sentence: "For decades, many assemblers have been developed ad-hoc without any standards." This will help to distinguish the dependent clause "without any standards" from the independent clause "many assemblers have been developed ad-hoc." Finally, you can add a comma after "Clang" in the following sentence: "On the other hand, Clang need to handle both two cases." This will help to clarify the structure of this sentence as well as the next one that follows it. Here''s the revised paragraph with added commas: In one sense, the ambiguity of Intel syntax (due to the absence of an official Intel assembly syntax manual) is the problem. For decades, many assemblers have been developed ad-hoc, without any standards. So, it seems to be a hard decision problem to allow/deny several tokens or to choose the right usage. On the other hand, Clang need to handle both two cases. They may reduce the usability and correctness of Clang. A user might want to write a function named "or", but get rejected by Clang. A user might want to load a data pointer named "rsp", but the resulting program loads a stack pointer, which can differ from the user''s intention.', 'Maybe we need to define a clause first. A clause should contain a subject and a verb. However, you pointed out phrases as clauses.', 'In one sense, the ambiguity of Intel syntax (due to the absence of an official Intel assembly syntax manual) is the problem. For decades, many assemblers have been developed ad-hoc without any standards. So, it seems to be a hard decision problem to allow/deny several tokens or to choose the right usage. On the other hand, Clang need to handle both two cases. They may reduce the usability and correctness of Clang. A user might want to write a function named "or", but get rejected by Clang. A user might want to load a data pointer named "rsp", but the resulting program loads a stack pointer, which can differ from the user''s intention.', '2025-02-27 11:16:00'),
(3, 16, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Could you please translate this text to korean? This is abstract of my research, and I need korean version, but papago makes too many mistakes. The text is below: <para>Data-parallelism has been widely used in order to distribute the training of large DNN networks among multiple workers (GPU/TPU). In the data-parallel context, a large proportion of the training time is spent on collective communication to synchronize gradients between model replicas on each device. Up to 40\% of the training time is spent on All-Reduce collective communication. It was observed that not all gradients are necessary for model convergence and the gradient tensor could be greatly sparsified to reduce the communication volume. Prior works proposed to prune gradients depending on their magnitude, approach colloquially called top-k. However, top-k incurs computation overhead of bitonic sorting and has scalability issues on Ring All-Reduce due to the necessity to send indices. In this work, we show that random gradient pruning guarantees convergence at minimal accuracy loss. Moreover, we propose Skip-Reduce -- a novel approach to perform gradient pruning that does not rely on sending indices and instead modifies the underlying communication algorithm. Our approach has no computational overhead and is scalable on any number of devices.</para>', 'Data-parallelism has been widely used in order to distribute the training of large DNN networks among multiple workers (GPU/TPU). In the data-parallel context, a large proportion of the training time is spent on collective communication to synchronize gradients between model replicas on each device. Up to 40\% of the training time is spent on All-Reduce collective communication. It was observed that not all gradients are necessary for model convergence and the gradient tensor could be greatly sparsified to reduce the communication volume. Prior works proposed to prune gradients depending on their magnitude, approach colloquially called top-k. However, top-k incurs computation overhead of bitonic sorting and has scalability issues on Ring All-Reduce due to the necessity to send indices. In this work, we show that random gradient pruning guarantees convergence at minimal accuracy loss. Moreover, we propose Skip-Reduce -- a novel approach to perform gradient pruning that does not rely on sending indices and instead modifies the underlying communication algorithm. Our approach has no computational overhead and is scalable on any number of devices.', '2025-03-13 09:46:00'),
(4, 16, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned that result section should be composed of summary, discussion and future work and limitation. I hope to get feedback related to this.', 'Result Experiments are conducted on MS-COCO [22] and Pascal-VOC [11]. The proposed method representation mixup (RM) is compared with conventional TL methods, i.e., to linear probe (LP) and to full fine-tune entire network (FT). The number of parameters involved in training of RM is drastically smaller than that of any other comparisons [5, 2, 6] as well as FT. With the small number of parameters that involve in optimization, the proposed method gives comparable or better performance to fine-tuning. Also, note that our method requires much less training. Models in comparisons [5, 2, 6] require 100, 80, and 200 epochs respectively to achieve the desired performance, while ours show comparable results in 30 epochs. Details for setting are in AppendixA.2. Metrics show that the proposed method has the most gain in recall (CR, OR), meaning that the method can identify false negative hard instances as true positives. All the results from RM in experiments are of representation extracted from the first block (RM@1). Comparisons between different blocks are reported in another table. Discussion We took 10% largest class-wise mean scale values out of 80 classes, extracted from the inference results of the proposed method on MS-COCO validation set with ResNet101. In short, classes with large values were found to have shown poor performance in baseline (LP). They are marked in bold which belong in Figure 3(b). This implies that the greater the value, the more support can be provided to classes with low performance. Conclusion This paper explores the effect of using intermediate representation, which can deal with hard samples in multi-label classification. Mixing up intermediate representation can maintain the efficiency which lies in linear probing and properly captures spatial information that could be lost when a feature is extracted in deep backbone networks. We provide methods to effectively refine the raw hidden representation into a form that could be interpolated with features extracted from a backbone network. The proposed method requires very few additional parameters from linear probing and achieves comparable performance to full fine-tuning. We confirm that intermediate representation can act as a hint for exploiting spatial information from any part of deep neural networks. We suggest future works could explore methods for instance-wise training using intermediate representation from different layers, which could pave the way for adaptive linear probing.', '2025-03-20 14:16:00'),
(5, 16, 'When you are writing in third person point of view, you generally should not express your own opinion by using phrases like "I think" or "I believe." Instead, you might include someone else''s opinion using phrases like: - According to [source], [opinion] - [Name] believed that... - Experts argue that... For example, instead of saying "I think that the main character was foolish to make that decision," you might say something like "According to literary critic Jane Doe, the main character''s decision was foolish and demonstrated their lack of critical thinking skills." By referencing outside sources, you can convey opinions without breaking away from third person perspective. However, be sure to cite your sources appropriately if you are including quotes or ideas from someone else''s work.', 'then how can i write a cause and effect essay in third person view?', 'I think that the government should help those most in need because of three reasons. First, the government can do things that individuals can’t. Second, it is hard for those in need to live well by their own. And last, the help of the government will make the whole society happy. Why do you think the government takes the position it does? It is to do things that individuals can’t by themselves. It is hard for normal people to find those who need help, and give help to them. Helping those in need is one of the best thing that the government can do. Second, money makes money. Unlike helping all of the citizens, helping particular people makes the society much more different. If the government helps all the people, the gap between the rich and the poor will not be reduced, but be intensified. Therefore, the rich will be able to maintain their lifestyle with ease, while the poor will continue to struggle. However, if the government helps those in need, they will have a base to develop, making society more diverse and flexible in a positive way. Lastly, the particular help of the government will make the whole society happier. Have you seen articles that show that the majority of the country''s capital is owned by a small percentage of the population? As it says, too much capital is unnecessarily taken by few people. For the good of much more people, the government should at least help people that are exactly the opposite side of the very tiny percent of the society that takes most of the capital. Because of these three reasons, for the good for all people, I strongly believe that the government should help those most in need.', '2025-04-03 16:16:00'),
(1, 17, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Could you paraphrase following sentences so that I can provide an overview of the result? <para>"These results showed that processing ‘my avatar’ was faster than processing ‘friend avatar’, and that processing ‘my avatar’ which was self-selected was faster than processing ‘my avatar’ which was randomly assigned. The effect of the embodiment method was not of first importance here since we were interested in whether the self-pop out effect is also applied for ‘my avatar’ or not. Considering the participants’ response time from the current experiment, it can be inferred that individuals are able to recognize ‘My avatar’ faster than ‘Friend avatar’ in all conditions. This holded true regardless of the presence or absence of selecting ‘My avatar’ and the degree of embodiment. The results suggest that once a specific avatar is recognized as oneself, the self-pop out effect occurs, similar to what happens in real life. "</para>', 'Result *all the numbers from the result section are written in ‘0’ since the analysis is not finished yet. 20214291 Bowon Kim During the experiment, participants’ reaction time was collected in milliseconds as well as accuracy rate. For the qualitative data, the response of the embodiment questionnaire was analyzed. To evaluate whether participants could find their own avatar faster than the others, participants’ reaction time between each condition was analyzed. 1 Reaction time The data from one participant whose reaction time were more than 2 SD under the mean of the sample were considered to be outliers and discarded. A 2(Selection: self-selected/ randomly assigned) x 2 (Search target:my avatar/friend avatar) x 3(Embodiment method: none/button control/motion sync) repeated measures ANOVA was performed on median correct reaction times. The result showed a main effect of Selection, F(0,00)=00.00, p=0.01, participants being faster for the ‘my avatar’ which they selected by their own at the beginning of the experiment (M=000, SD=000) than for the ‘my avatar’ which was randomly assigned(See figure1). There was also a main effect of Search target, F(0,00)=00.00, p=0.003, when ‘my avatar’ was presented as a target(M=000,SD=000), people could search it faster than ‘friend avatar’ presented as a target(M=000,SD=000)(See figure2). However, there was no significant main effect for the Embodiment method, F(0,00)=00.00, p>0.05(See figure3). No interaction was significant (all ps>0.05)(see Table1 for descriptive data). These results showed that processing ‘my avatar’ was faster than processing ‘friend avatar’, and that processing ‘my avatar’ which was self-selected was faster than processing ‘my avatar’ which was randomly assigned. The effect of the embodiment method was not of first importance here since we were interested in whether the self-pop out effect is also applied for ‘my avatar’ or not. Considering the participants’ response time from the current experiment, it can be inferred that individuals are able to recognize ‘My avatar’ faster than ‘Friend avatar’ in all conditions. This holded true regardless of the presence or absence of selecting ‘My avatar’ and the degree of embodiment. The results suggest that once a specific avatar is recognized as oneself, the self-pop out effect occurs, similar to what happens in real life. Figure1. Mean of reaction time by Selection Figure 2. Mean of reaction time by Search target Figure 3. Mean of reaction time by Embodiment method 2 Accuracy Participants performed the search task with high accuracy in general (Mean accuracy was 99%). When “My avatar” was presented as a search target, the mean accuracy was 99.2%. While the mean accuracy was 98.8% when participants had to find “Friend avatar”. A 2(Selection: self-selected/ randomly assigned) x 2 (Search target:my avatar/friend avatar) x 3(Embodiment method: none/button control/motion sync) repeated measures ANOVA was carried out on proportion of corrected responses and did not show any significant main effects (all Fs<0, p>0.05). Furthermore, there was no interaction effect for all conditions. Table 1. Mean median reaction times in milliseconds and mean proportion of correct responses 3 Embodiment questionnaire To assess the subjective feeling toward embodiment for each condition, after the experiment, participants were asked to answer the embodiment questionnaires(7 point Likert-scale). In this questionnaire, 14 questions were proposed and it was categorized into 4 sections; body ownership, agency and motor control, external appearance, and location of the body. The values of the answer were aggregated with the formula provided by Gonzalez Franco and Peck, standardized questionnaire[1]. As a result, participants reported higher embodiment scores(M=000.SD=000) when the motion of ‘My avatar’ was synced with the participants’ movement. Whereas when participants control the movement of ‘My avatar’ with the button slightly decreased(M=000.SD=000) than in the motion-sync condition. The lowest embodiment score was reported when ‘My avatar’ did not move at all (M=000.SD=000) (p=0.00)(See figure 4). Figure 4. Mean of Embodiment score by method. The embodiment score was significantly higher when the movement was synced. [1] Peck, T. C., & Gonzalez-Franco, M. (2021). Avatar embodiment. a standardized questionnaire. Frontiers in Virtual Reality, 1, 575943.', '2025-02-14 10:20:00'),
(2, 17, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about the relative pronoun. When the sentence describes the person, we use who or that, when it tells the essential things it should be the restrictive such as which or that, and when it supplements the sentence or describes the entire sentence, it should be the nonrestrictive such as comma + which.', 'There have been no studies applying counterfactual sampling to image captioning. This is primarily because image captioning relies on datasets composed of image-text pairs, making it challenging to create counterfactual images. However, in the case of image captioning models that use CLIP for extracting visual features, it is possible to easily generate counterfactual samples by leveraging the latent space alignment property of CLIP. CLIP, which can encode both images and texts into a shared latent space, has to maintain latent space alignment. Therefore, when creating counterfactual samples composed of text-image pairs, the changes in text embeddings should align with the changes in image embeddings. By generating counterfactual text embeddings and adding the change to the original image embedding, it becomes possible to create counterfactual samples. This enables the model to learn the authentic association between the visual feature and the word.', '2025-02-27 11:20:00'),
(3, 17, 'Of course, I''d be happy to help. Please share the paragraph with me and I''ll provide some suggestions for improvement.', '<para>One of the ways to learn causalities hidden in the observed objects is proposed in Visual Commonsense R-CNN (VC R-CNN). VC R-CNN is a visual region encoder and is trained to predict the contextual objects of a region like word2vec. However, unlike word2vec which uses conventional likelihood to make predictions, VC R-CNN makes predictions by causal intervention. In order to realize imaginative intervention which is called do-operation, the authors construct a confounder dictionary using pre-trained Faster R-CNN. Each entry is the averaged RoI feature of each category. However, according to our study, the averaged RoI features no more retain information about the corresponding class. This is problematic since each entry of confounder dictionary is assumed to represent corresponding class category when intervening. Class information of the RoI features seems to be lost when these features are averaged.</para>', 'Many vision-language tasks such as Visual Question Answering and Image Captioning use bottom-up features extracted by Faster R-CNN as a visual input. Bottom-up features enable models to focus on at the level of objects and other salient regions. However, it has been shown that these features lack common sense knowledge which is crucial for deeper understanding of images. Common sense knowledge implies unsupervised learning of causal relationships hidden within observed objects. Due to this lack of common sense knowledge, models may fail to accurately describe visual relationships or make predictions based on incorrect visual attention.', '2025-03-13 09:50:00'),
(4, 17, 'No, that paragraph does not show good scientific writing. Instead of simplifying and weakening the language, scientific writing should aim to be descriptive and precise. Using accurate and specific vocabulary and avoiding informal language is key. Additionally, personal opinions and emotions should be removed from scientific writing, and tone should remain consistently formal and coherent. It is important to correct inaccuracies and enhance language, but in a scientific and objective way.', 'Original text is below. In the enchanting realm of literature, the power of imagination takes the reader on a transformative journey, whisking them away to unknown worlds and compelling them to experience life from various perspectives. The beauty of a well-crafted narrative lies in its ability to captivate the audience and elicit a plethora of emotions, allowing them to empathize with the characters, while simultaneously broadening their understanding of the human experience. For instance, in Harper Lee''s famous book, "To Destroy a Singing Bird," the author kind of uses some pictures and character people to show the different parts of race, society, and being good or bad in the Deep South during the time when the economy was really bad. Through the eyes of the young main person, Scout Finch, readers are shown the tough truth of being unfair, which makes them think about what they believe and see how what people think can change who a person is.', 'Cellular respiration is a fundamental process in which cells convert the energy stored in glucose molecules into adenosine triphosphate (ATP), the primary molecule responsible for powering cellular activities. This process occurs in three stages: glycolysis, the citric acid cycle, and the electron transport chain. Glycolysis takes place in the cell''s cytoplasm and breaks glucose down into two molecules of pyruvate, releasing energy in the form of ATP and reduced nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NADH). The citric acid cycle, also known as the Krebs cycle, occurs in the mitochondria and generates additional ATP, NADH, and another electron carrier called flavin adenine dinucleotide (FADH2). Finally, the electron transport chain uses the electrons from NADH and FADH2 to generate a proton gradient across the inner mitochondrial membrane, which drives the synthesis of the majority of a cell''s ATP through oxidative phosphorylation.', '2025-03-20 14:20:00'),
(5, 17, 'Great job! It sounds like you learned some important things about writing the methodology section of a scientific article. Yes, the methodology section is crucial for ensuring that the research can be reproduced by others, which is a key aspect of good scientific research. And you''re right, the methodology should clearly and accurately outline the procedures, materials, and equipment used in the study. This helps readers to understand how the study was conducted and to evaluate the results. Do you have any questions about what we covered today?', 'In class, we conducted building block activity. building block activity is a group activity which our group build a block and explain the feature of the block to other group by text. other group read the explain and re-build our block feature. I have difficult to explain detailed method of building block in class.', 'Guidance on Writing a Methodology Section for a Survey Paper Usually a survey paper does not include a section that talks about the same things as a research paper based on experimental information. In fact my experience is that survey papers often contain little information about how researchers gathered the information. This makes it more difficult for you to write this section as there are few models of this section you can gather from other papers. Therefore, here is some guidance, in addition to that provided in the video lecture, on how to write this section: 1. Provide an introduction about the purpose of your review. Specifically what is your review focusing on? Be as specific as possible so the reader understands what you are doing and what you are not reviewing. 2. How are you approaching the gathering of the information? Which journals are you depending on for the information? If there are journals you are not using say what they are and why you are not using them for the information gathering. 3. Justify your choice of information. Which journals had the most information and were most careful in their choice of authors and articles. Often journals have a discussion section about recent advances. This is a location where new directions of science are discussed in detail and often reviewed. It is also a good area to find recent information on revolutions going on in your field that you may otherwise miss. If you refer to this section make sure you state who gathered the information and wrote the article. Also what organization did they work for? 4. There are many review articles written on a variety of topics. You can use these but remember they are what we call secondary information and therefore sometimes have opinion or bias that you must be careful to evaluate based on your research. Therefore stick to the primary articles as much as possible, those who gathered the information based on lab studies or surveys. In the medical areas, pharmaceutical companies publish many articles and often they have a strong basis related to some product the company they are working for are selling. Pay attention to this bias and realize that it is not unusual. Therefore look at what company or government supported the research. The information of how you handled this can be included in the methodology section. 5. Did you have any problems in trying to survey the literature on the topic? Is the topic so new that there are few papers that cover the topic? Were there some articles that you wanted to read but because of language issues you could not read? Also were some articles not available because of their age or maybe the citation is incorrect. I hope this helps you in writing your survey paper. Try to keep focused on a specific topic and try not to cover too large a field. Always ask yourself if this paper is really focused on you topic or is it off topic. If it is not on your topic move on to papers that are. Also realize that during this term you can modify this section as you read more articles. As a last thought do not forget to ask for help from you seniors and professors in your department. They have many good suggestions on special articles that are recommended reading.', '2025-04-03 16:20:00'),
(1, 18, 'Yes, here are some problems that can arise in an unstable society: 1. Violence and Crime: An unstable society may experience high rates of crime and violence as social norms and structures break down, and individuals compete for resources and power. 2. Poverty and Inequality: Unstable societies may suffer from widespread poverty and inequality, as the social structures and institutions that provide support and opportunities for individuals'' development and well-being break down. 3. Political Instability: In unstable societies, it may be difficult to establish and maintain stable systems of governance, leading to political instability, confusion, and disorder. 4. Economic Downturn: An unstable society may face frequent economic downturns, leading to a lack of job opportunities, low wages, and high levels of economic insecurity. 5. Social Disintegration: Unstable societies may suffer from a breakdown in social connections and trust, leading to societal disintegration and a loss of collective values, social cohesion, and civic engagement. I hope these examples provide some insight into the problems that can arise in an unstable society.', 'Can you complete this sentence? "It is clear that there are more conflict between people when the inequality of chances and unbalanced wealth are ??"', 'Government is different from past monarchy because it tries to provide equal chances and resources to citzens . However, even in modern society, there are differences of economic and social status between people. Childern who born in poor family will have some difficulties. Also, elders need more help than others due to their reduced ablities. Therefore, to make a nation a better place, government should concentrate on supporting people in need. By providing education, resources, and aid to them, governments can contribute to a more equitable society. The most serious problem that government should consider is differences of background of a person''s childhood. The poors are not likely to get high quality education or supports than others. As a result, they get little chance for improving abilities to get a better status in society. For instance, university is important for a person''s various experience for success. However, many universities prefer a person who can perform well. Also, some elite universities require quite huge amount of money to register. But the people in need can''t satisfy these things due to their environment . Government should make a policy that tries to improve public education to reduce the other external acardemic supports'' influence. In addition, to reduce the economic burden for poors, proper aid of money should be contained in the policy. Another point to consider is people who are getting old. Some might think it is unfair to help elders, but all human beings become old. The government should care about their citizens'' future and continue to help elders. More specifically, as people get old, their abilities to work reduce, so they have to retire and they are not financially independent anymore. Also, they are vulnerable to diseases and medical conditions that require constant attention and medical intervention. Government should not left them in these poor conditions, because they have been contribute to society and still have a wealth of knowledge, skills, and experience that can be helpful for society. Therefore, government should provide seniors medical and economical supports for society as well as for individuals who are getting old. Last thing government should care about is stabilty of the society. If the government doesn''t focus on helping people in need, the differnce between people''s socioeconomic status will be get worse. As a result, the society might become more unstable. Historically, it is clear that there are more conflicts between people when the inequality of chances and unbalanced wealth are evident. For example, society may experience high rates of crime and violence as individuals compete for resources and power. Also, societies may suffer from a breakdown in social connections and trust, leading to societal disintegration and a loss of collective values. Government''s purpose is to maintain society''s peace and balanced state. So, they should help people in need more carefully to ensure their chance to learn and become sucessful. Also, for the citizen''s future, government should help elders. In conclusion, government''s role of helping people in need is essential for the society''s well-being.', '2025-02-14 10:24:00'),
(2, 18, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I want to know how to write results part at a scientific paper.', 'We investigated personality type depending on having siblings for the students in the F class of ‘scientific writing’. As shown in Fig 1., the percentage of only child and one who having siblings is 86.7% and 13.3%, respectively. The percentage of E (extroverted) and I (introverted) is 46.7% and 53.3%, respectively. Actually, this result couldn’t reflect the relationship between the existence of siblings and personality. We have difficult to evaluate hypotheses that having brothers and sisters has an extroverted personality than only child. For this reason, we retry to examine the individual results as you can see in Fig 2. The number of students of the introverted is 7 and the extroverted is 6 among having siblings, respectively, while the number of students of the introverted is 1 and the extroverted is 1 that exhibited the same number among only child. It is shown that the presence or absence of siblings is not directly related to the personality type (extroverted and introverted) As a result, it exhibited the hypothesis that having siblings is relatively extroverted than only child. It seems that there are many factors like the environment of growth. And thus, it could not conclude a person’s personality by having brothers and sisters. Also, considering that the subject of investigation is a very small standard group of class students, it is judged that the number of standard groups should be increased for a more accurate comparative analysis.', '2025-02-27 11:24:00'),
(3, 18, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I want to correct the grammatical errors related to adverbial Clauses.', 'Nowadays, tablets and laptops are used by most students. Most of students at KAIST also use them to listen lectures and taking notes for important information. Also, there are a lot of concerns of using tablets and laptops, because they lower the concentration of students or they make student''s eyes unhealthy. But I want to emphasize that despite of these problems, there are a lot of advantages of using tablets and laptops. There are 3 reasons. First of all, tablets and laptops permit students to save time. The functions of searching and recording could allow students to save their time. Specifically, searching function in the electronic devices allow us to fine the information, which we are not aware of or which are confused, quickly, Students just type the word that they want to know, and just for a moment, lots of useful information come out. When it comes to recording function, students could record the lecture. After that, they can play it 1.5 or twice time faster. So they can save their time using an efficient way. Second, using tablets and laptops, students can study more efficient. Let''s get back to the recording functions. students can listen again the lecture. This means they can pick up what they didn''t understand at that time when they are in the class, and they can study that part while they understand the information. Finally it will be helpful to space-efficiency. By using Zoom function of electronic devices, it is not necessary that all students have to come to class. If there is the class that too many students are existed, this will be more helpful. For these reasons, I want to emphasize using a tablet or laptop computer in class is good way for students.', '2025-03-13 09:54:00'),
(4, 18, 'I''m sorry, I think there might be a miscommunication. We just finished revising the last sentence. Is there anything else you need me to clarify or help you with?', 'I wonder if this sentence is correct grammar <sent>''In short, laptop and tablet have many advantages like weigh(for portability), infinite saving space, and increasing students’ academic achievements.''</sent>', 'In the past, almost all university students used textbooks and pens. Because of this, most students had to carry a load when they went to lectures. Nowadays, however, lots of students, including high school and university students, don''t have to carry heavy textbooks. They just take their laptop or tablet. Almost all KAIST students already have their own laptop, tablet, or both. Why many people use that in class? Let me explain why laptop/tablet are more convenient than textbooks and pens. First of all, it is light. Things which are light have many advantages. It is less hand to pick light things than heavy things. Because of this reason, It is convenient to take whenever students go. Second, laptop and tablet doesn’t have limit to include infinite files that are helpful to lessons or their own study. For example, many students use PDFs when they study or listen to lectures. PDF helps students not to take various textbooks when they have various lectures on only one day. Lastly, it can increase students’ academic achievements. Specifically, writing by hand has limitations when it comes to speed. But typing using laptop is faster than hand writing. In addition, laptops and tablets can search the internet with Google. Therefore, whenever students don''t know important information to understand their class, they can use their tablet or laptop to search for it. When students submit their homework to their professor, it is more convenient to use a laptop or tablet because online submission is faster and lower effort than offline submission. In short, laptops and tablets have many advantages such as portability, infinite saving space, and the ability to increase students'' academic achievements.', '2025-03-20 14:24:00'),
(5, 18, 'Yes, I understand that you learned about structuring the results section of a scientific paper in four ways, and the purposes of writing a results section. You also learned about the four basic components of a results section: revisiting the research aim or existing research, presenting specific key results with or without explanations, discussing problems with the results, and presenting possible implications of the results. Additionally, you learned that you should use language in a way that invites readers to check out your figures. Great job summarizing what you learned! Is there anything else you would like to discuss or ask me about in relation to this topic?', 'Accordong to what I learnt, can you tell me if the draft I have written is okay as a results section?', 'In the previous years, a trend of students enrolled in undergraduate or higher degrees moving farther away for education has been observed. Although having a bigger radius for university selection increases the number of opportunities, students who have close relationships with their families may experience homesickness. Paying frequent visits to the family may alleviate this issue. Furthermore, visiting their family for students often ends up with the benefit of receiving more supplies such as homemade food. We have hypothesized that students who visit their family more often are on average happier, and conducted a survey consisting of four questions. Before finding a relationship between the frequency of visiting family and happiness, we needed to check some factors which can affect the frequency. To this end, we first asked people about the distance they live from their families. Among our 16 respondents, the most frequent visitor was the person who lived the closest to their family (0-50km) with 16 visits on average within 4 months, while people living farther than 300km away showed the lowest results with two no visits and one 1 visit (Figure 1). However, between 100-200km, no significant trend was observed. We then questioned whether the closeness of the relationship between the respondents and their families affected the number of visits. As can be seen in Figure 1, no correlation was observed. Three people reported their closeness to their family as a 7 on a scale of 0 to 10. While one of them visited 16 times in the given period, the other two remained at the low numbers of 1 and 2. This could be attributed to the distance factor, as the respondent visiting their family 16 times lives the closest to their home at 0-50km; however, two people living in the same distance interval (100-200km) reported their closeness level as 8 and visited home 8 and 1 times. Overall, it can be observed in Figure 1 that at the closest and farthest ends of the scale (0-50km & 300km) distance plays a significant role in the frequency of home visits, while it shows variety in the middle range (100-200km). Emotional closeness, on the other hand, does not seem to factor into the results. Lastly, we compared the frequency of visiting family with perceived level of happiness to test our hypothesis (Figure 2). No correlation was observed between the two factors. While respondent 1 with an average of 16 home visits in 4 months reported 4 on their level of happiness, respondent 15 scored the highest score, 10, on the happiness chart and did not visit their family at all. However, no inverse correlation was observed, as respondents with high responses on both questions (see respondent 3) and low responses on both questions (see respondent 7) were also present. Overall, our data has shown that there is no direct correlation between students’ level of happiness and their amount of home visits.', '2025-04-03 16:24:00'),
(1, 19, '네, 그러면 이번 학기 동안 우리가 배운 것 중 결과 부분 작성에 관한 것을 보다 자세히 다룬 수업이었습니다. 당신이 작성한 이 Sample 결과 부분을 rubric에 따라 평가해보도록 하겠습니다.', '이게 rubric이야 Overview DOES NOT give a brief overview of the results. 0 점 Insufficient overview of results. Overview of results could be more detailed. 1 점 Good overview of the results. 2 점 Clarity Grammar and language use substantially impede the reader’s understanding of what is written. 0 점 Considerable effort is needed on the part of the reader to understand what is written. 1 점 Grammar and language use is clear so that readers do not need a great deal of effort to understand what is written. 2 점 Interpretation The data is incorrectly interpreted or incorrectly explained. 0 점 Some information could be added to aid the reader’s understanding of the author’s interpretation of the data. 1 점 The data is correctly interpreted and explained in appropriate depth. 2 점 Visuals referred to in the text The assignment does not contain text that refers to visuals. 0 점 The text contains descriptions of the visuals, though lacking clarity and detail. No invitation to view the visual is contained. 1 점 The text contains an invitation to view visuals as well as clear verbal descriptions of the information contained therein. 2 점 Visuals Figures are not referred to, axes are incorrectly labeled, and legends are missing. 0 점 Some errors in referring to the figures and/or in the labeling of the axes or providing of units. Otherwise, legend may be incomplete in some way. 1 점 Figures are present and referred to within the body of the results. Axes are correctly labeled and provide units where applicable (both x and y). Each figure contains a legend below the figure that is framed as a complete sentence summarizing the experimental results and basic information', 'First, we conducted a survey to test the hypothesis that people’s level of happiness is proportional to the variety and amount of leisure activities they do on the weekend. The data were collected from 13 KAIST graduate students through a survey. To analyze the results, the types of leisure activities used as key indicators, the time spent, and the level of happiness were visually displayed. Figure 1: Relationship between leisure activities (number of types and time Spent) and degree of happiness To investigate the relationship between leisure activities and the happiness index, a survey was conducted with 13 participants, collecting information on the time spent on leisure activities, the number of leisure activities experienced, and the respondents'' self-reported happiness index. A potential relationship between the number of leisure activities, the time spent on these activities, and the degree of happiness was observed (Fig. 1). The results show that respondents engaging in a single leisure activity mostly reported lower happiness levels, ranging from 1 to 3, with only one respondent reporting a happiness level of 4. Respondents engaging in a variety of activities (2-4) generally reported higher happiness levels, suggesting that participation in multiple leisure activities might positively impact happiness. However, the relationship between the amount of time spent on leisure activities and happiness is less clear, with most respondents who spent 5-6 hours or 7-8 hours on leisure activities reporting higher happiness levels. This could indicate an optimal time range for leisure activities that positively influences happiness, although more data is required to establish this relationship conclusively. Figure 2: Correlation Matrix of number of activity types, Time Spent on Leisure activities, and degree of happiness Based on the correlation matrix (Fig. 2), a moderate positive correlation (0.7) exists between the number of activity types and time spent on leisure activities, suggesting an increase in time spent as the number of activities increases. Meanwhile, a weak positive correlation (0.14) between the number of activity types and happiness levels indicates a slight tendency for happiness to increase with more activities, but the relationship is weak and may not be conclusive due to the small sample size. Additionally, a moderate positive correlation (0.57) exists between time spent on leisure activities and happiness levels, suggesting that happiness levels tend to increase with more time spent on leisure activities, although the relationship is not very strong. In summary, the results suggest that engaging in a variety of activities (2-4) might be positively associated with higher happiness levels. Additionally, spending 5-6 hours or 7-8 hours on leisure activities appears to yield higher happiness levels for most respondents, although the relationship between time spent on leisure activities and happiness is less clear. The correlation analysis revealed a moderate positive correlation (0.7) between the number of activity types and time spent on leisure activities, a weak positive correlation (0.14) between the number of activity types and happiness levels, and a moderate positive correlation (0.57) between time spent on leisure activities and happiness levels.', '2025-02-14 10:28:00'),
(2, 19, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I would like to learn please more about this paragraph: Active and Passive Voice Active Voice : You stole the cookie from the cookie jar. Passive voice : The cookie was stolen from the cookie jar. Passive voice: The cookie was eaten by Matthew. Active voice: I ate the cookie. Passive voice: Research will be presented by Matthew at the conference. Active voice: Matthew will present his research at the conference. Passive voice: Experiments have been conducted to test the hypothesis. Active voice: Scientists have conducted experiments to test the hypothesis. Active Vs. Passive (passive used in methodology section) Present Simple Researchers place an element in the control region. An element is placed in the control region. Simple past We collected various samples. Various samples were collected. Perfect tense : introduction section (background information) Present Perfect Science has made life easier. Life has been made easier by science. Past Perfect Scientists have researched this subject in great detail. This subject has been researched in great detail Future / Modal : applications, implications, future studies Future Scientists will research this further. This will be researched further. Modal You can use the model to predict problems. The model can be used to predict problems. Argument for the active voice Usually shorter than the passive voice 4 words vs. 6 in the cookie example. Passive is prone to abusive nominalization A data analysis was performed. Ambiguity less likely Usually preferred by journals Nature journals like authors to write in the active voice. The active voice appropriately expresses science. Scientists are an integral part of the research. Argument for the passive voice The performer is unknown, irrelevant, or obvious 1. Up to 90% of the energy in light bulbs is wasted in the form of heat. 2. The first edition of Freud’s earliest writings on dreams was published in 1899. 3. Drosophila melanogaster has been one of the most extensively studied species in genetics research. Emphasis on what was done We kept the honey bees in a humidified chamber at room temperature overnight. The honey bees were kept in a humidified chamber at room temperature overnight Less use of personal pronouns. Control of sentence structure We wish to suggest a structure for the salt of deoxyribose nucleic acid (D.N.A). This structure has novel features which are of considerable biological interest. Pauling and Carey have already proposed a structure for nucleic acid. A structure for nucleic acid has already been proposed by Pauling can Corey. Active vs. Passive Make sure your passive sentences are intentional and not habitual. Use the passive voice when necessary to maintain cohesion. When you use the passive voice, make sure the actor is not ambiguous and avoid abusive nominalizations.', 'Active and Passive Voice Active Voice : You stole the cookie from the cookie jar. Passive voice : The cookie was stolen from the cookie jar. Passive voice: The cookie was eaten by Matthew. Active voice: I ate the cookie. Passive voice: Research will be presented by Matthew at the conference. Active voice: Matthew will present his research at the conference. Passive voice: Experiments have been conducted to test the hypothesis. Active voice: Scientists have conducted experiments to test the hypothesis. Active Vs. Passive (passive used in methodology section) Present Simple Researchers place an element in the control region. An element is placed in the control region. Simple past We collected various samples. Various samples were collected. Perfect tense : introduction section (background information) Present Perfect Science has made life easier. Life has been made easier by science. Past Perfect Scientists have researched this subject in great detail. This subject has been researched in great detail Future / Modal : applications, implications, future studies Future Scientists will research this further. This will be researched further. Modal You can use the model to predict problems. The model can be used to predict problems. Argument for the active voice Usually shorter than the passive voice 4 words vs. 6 in the cookie example. Passive is prone to abusive nominalization A data analysis was performed. Ambiguity less likely Usually preferred by journals Nature journals like authors to write in the active voice. The active voice appropriately expresses science. Scientists are an integral part of the research. Argument for the passive voice The performer is unknown, irrelevant, or obvious 1. Up to 90% of the energy in light bulbs is wasted in the form of heat. 2. The first edition of Freud’s earliest writings on dreams was published in 1899. 3. Drosophila melanogaster has been one of the most extensively studied species in genetics research. Emphasis on what was done We kept the honey bees in a humidified chamber at room temperature overnight. The honey bees were kept in a humidified chamber at room temperature overnight Less use of personal pronouns. Control of sentence structure We wish to suggest a structure for the salt of deoxyribose nucleic acid (D.N.A). This structure has novel features which are of considerable biological interest. Pauling and Carey have already proposed a structure for nucleic acid. A structure for nucleic acid has already been proposed by Pauling can Corey. Active vs. Passive Make sure your passive sentences are intentional and not habitual. Use the passive voice when necessary to maintain cohesion. When you use the passive voice, make sure the actor is not ambiguous and avoid abusive nominalizations.', '2025-02-27 11:28:00'),
(3, 19, 'Great job on your essay! Let''s work on revising it based on the advice I gave you. First, let''s take a look at your introductory paragraph. You have a clear thesis statement at the end that tells the reader what the essay is going to compare. However, it would be helpful to add a sentence or two that provides some background information on the topic and why it is important to compare and contrast online and offline shopping. Next, let''s focus on the body paragraphs. You are using point-by-point organization to discuss similarities and differences. However, it would be helpful to add transition sentences between each point to help the reader follow your argument more easily. Finally, let''s take a look at your conclusion. You do a good job of summarizing the main points, but it would be helpful to add a sentence or two that provides some final thoughts on the topic and why it is important to consider both online and offline shopping. Here is a revised version of your essay: With the development of the internet, online shopping has become increasingly popular, challenging the traditional offline shopping way. In this essay, we will compare and contrast the advantages and disadvantages of online shopping and offline shopping, considering factors such as convenience, variety, interaction, and overall impact on consumers. Online shopping offers convenience and accessibility. With just a few clicks, consumers can browse through a vast array of products and make purchases from the comfort of their own homes. Online shopping eliminates the need for physical travel to stores, saving time and effort. Moreover, online shopping allows shoppers to make purchases at any time they want, as they are typically open 24/7. On the other hand, offline shopping provides an immediate shopping experience. Shoppers can physically examine and try on products before making a purchase, which is not possible with online shopping. Also, offline shopping offers instant gratification, as consumers can immediately take their purchases home. However, offline shopping requires individuals to visit physical stores during their operating hours, which can be restrictive and inconvenient for those with busy schedules. Next, online shopping offers unparalleled variety and selection. E-commerce platforms provide access to products from all around the world, allowing consumers to explore a wide range of options. Online retailers often have extensive inventories, ensuring that shoppers can find products in various sizes, colors, and styles. Also, consumers can easily compare prices, read reviews, and access detailed product information, empowering them to make informed purchasing decisions. In contrast, offline shopping has limited stock and selection, especially in smaller or specialized stores. However, offline shopping also has merits in providing the opportunity for consumers to personally inspect products and assess their quality, something that online shopping lacks. Shoppers can touch, feel, and try on items, ensuring their quality, fit, and suitability. This hands-on experience is particularly valuable for items such as clothes, furniture, or electronics. On the contrary, online shopping relies on product descriptions, images, and sometimes customer reviews, which may not always accurately convey the real-life experience of the product. In addition, interaction and customer service also differ between online and offline shopping. Offline stores provide face-to-face interaction with sales associates who can provide personalized assistance, answer questions, and offer recommendations. This personalized interaction enhances the shopping experience and can help customers make informed purchasing decisions. Offline shopping also provides the opportunity for social interaction, allowing shoppers to engage with friends or family while browsing stores. Online shopping, on the other hand, relies on digital communication channels. Even though customer service is available through online chat or email, the absence of immediate assistance may lead to delays in resolving queries or concerns. Price comparison is an area where both online and offline shopping have their merits. Online retailers often offer competitive prices due to lower overhead costs, and the ability to compare prices across different platforms is a breeze. In comparison, offline shopping can involve bargaining, taking advantage of sales or discounts, and immediate price negotiations, especially in smaller or local stores. Additionally, offline shopping allows shoppers to avoid shipping costs or waiting periods, which can sometimes be associated with online purchases. In terms of the overall impact on consumers, shopping experience and returns differ significantly between online and offline shopping. Online shopping offers a convenient and efficient experience, allowing consumers to quickly find products and compare prices. It has provided opportunities for small businesses and entrepreneurs to reach a wider market. However, it has led to concerns such as cybersecurity risks, potential frauds, and the loss of in-person social interaction. Also, it lacks the sensory experience that offline shopping provides, such as physically touching and trying on items. Offline shopping, while more traditional, still holds its value in terms of personal engagement, immediate gratification, and the ability to support local businesses. Offline shopping offers an immersive experience, allowing shoppers to engage their senses and assess product quality firsthand. Another aspect to consider is the return process. Online shopping often provides hassle-free returns, with easy-to-follow procedures and prepaid shipping labels. In contrast, returning items purchased offline may require visiting the store, waiting in line, and complying with specific return policies. In conclusion, online shopping and offline shopping both have their advantages and disadvantages. Online shopping offers convenience, an extensive variety of products, competitive prices, and the ability to shop anytime anywhere. On the other hand, offline shopping provides the opportunity for sensory engagement, face-to-face interaction between customers and staff, personalized customer service, and immediate gratification. Ultimately, the choice between online shopping and offline shopping depends on individual preferences, the type of product being purchased, and the overall shopping experience desired. As technology continues to advance, the future may see a blending of these two approaches, providing an even more seamless and immersive shopping experience for consumers.', 'Why do you think it is important to compare online shopping and offline shopping?', 'With the development of the internet, online shopping has become increasingly popular, challenging the traditional offline shopping way. Understanding the difference between online shopping and offline shopping is important because it helps consumers make informed decisions about how they want to shop. By understanding the advantages and disadvantages of each approach, consumers can choose the shopping method that best fits their needs and preference. Additionally, comparing online and offline shopping can help business understand the changing needs and expectations of their customers, and adapt their strategies accordingly. Finally, comparing two methods can help us understand the broader impact of technology on our society, and how it is changing the way we interact with each other and with the world around us. By these reasons, in this essay, we will compare and contrast the advantages and disadvantages of online shopping and offline shopping, considering factors such as convenience, variety, interaction, and overall impact on consumers. One of the key advantages of online shopping is convenience and accessibility. With just a few researching, consumers can browse through a vast array of products and make purchases from the comfort of their own homes. Online shopping eliminates the need for physical travel to stores, saving time and effort. Moreover, online shopping allows shoppers to make purchases at any time they want, as they are typically open 24/7. On the other hand, offline shopping provides an immediate shopping. Shoppers can physically examine and try on products before making a purchase, which is not possible with online shopping. Also, offline shopping offers instant gratification, as consumers can immediately take their purchases home. But, in a different sense, offline shopping requires individuals to visit physical stores during their operating hours, which can be restrictive and inconvenient for those with busy schedules. Next, Online shopping offers unparalleled variety and selection. E-commerce platforms provide access to products from all around the world, allowing consumers to explore a wide range of options. Online retailers often have extensive inventories, ensuring that shoppers can find products in various sizes, colors, and styles. Also, consumers can easily compare prices, read reviews, and access detailed product information, empowering them to make informed purchasing decisions. In contrast, offline shopping have limited stock and selection, especially in smaller or specialized stores. But offline shopping also have merits in providing the opportunity for consumers to personally inspect products and assess their quality, something that online shopping lacks. Shoppers can touch, feel, and try on items, ensuring their quality, fit, and suitability. This hands-on experience is particularly valuable for items such as clothes, furniture, or electronics. On the contrary, online shopping relies on product descriptions, image, and sometimes customer reviews, which may not always accurately convey the real-life experience of the product. In addition, interaction and customer service also differ between online and offline shopping. Offline stores provide face-to-face interaction with sales associates who can provide personalized assistance, answer questions, and offer recommendations. This personalized interaction enhances the shopping experience and can help customers make informed purchasing decisions. Offline shopping also provides the opportunity for social interaction, allowing shoppers to engage with friends or family while browsing stores. Online shopping, on the other hand, relies on digital communication channels. Even though customer service is available through online chat or email, the absence of immediate assistance may lead to delays in resolving queries or concerns. Next is about price comparison. Price comparison is an area where both online and offline shopping have their merits. Online retailers often offer competitive prices due to lower overhead costs, and the ability to compare prices across different platforms is a breeze. In comparison, offline shopping can involve bargaining, taking advantage of sales or discounts, and immediate price negotiations, especially in smaller or local stores. Additionally, offline shopping allows shoppers to avoid shipping costs or waiting periods, which can sometimes be associated with online purchases. In terms of the overall impact on consumers, shopping experience and returns differs significantly between online and offline shopping. Online shopping offers a convenient and efficient experience, allowing consumers to quickly find products and compare prices. It has provided opportunities for small business and entrepreneurs to reach a wider market. However, it has led to concerns such as cybersecurity risks, potential frauds, and the loss of in-person social interaction. Also, it lacks the sensor experience that offline shopping provides, such as physically touching and trying on items. Offline shopping, while more traditional, still holds its value in terms of personal engagement, immediate gratification, and the ability to support local businesses. Offline shopping offers an immersive experience, allowing shoppers to engage their senses and assess product quality firsthand. Another aspect to consider is the return process. Online shopping often provides hassle-free return, with easy-to-follow procedures and prepaid shipping labels. In contrast, returning items purchased offline may require visiting the store, waiting in line, and complying with specific return policies. In conclusion, online shopping and offline shopping both have their advantages and disadvantages. Online shopping offers convenience, a extensive variety of products, competitive prices, and the ability to shop anytime anywhere. On the other hand, offline shopping provides the opportunity for sensory engagement, face-to-face interaction between customers and staff, personalized customer service, and immediate gratification. Ultimately, the choice between online shopping and offline shopping depends on individual preferences, the type of product being purchased, and the overall shopping experience desired. As technology continues to advance, the future may see a blending of these two approaches, providing an even more seamless and immersive shopping experience for consumers.', '2025-03-13 09:58:00'),
(4, 19, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', '<essay>The government makes laws and protects its citizens from various problems, such as disasters, poverty, and crime. Citizens have their rights to be helped and protected by government. Each citizen has different situations and needs that may require assistance from the government. Therefore, the question arises: should the government help only those most in need rather than help all of its citizens? I want to say ''no'' to this question for several reasons;. While it may seem logical to provide aid only to those most in need, it can be discriminatory and demotivating. A more equitable approach is to provide aid to all citizens in need. First, limiting assistance to only those in need can create deeper discrimination and antagonism between groups. The government runs the country with tax money collected from its citizens. If only those in need receive benefits, it can create resentment among those who do not receive aid. Discrimination and stigmatization can arise, leading those who do not receive assistance to harbor ill will towards those who do. For example, when healthcare systems focus only on providing care to those who demonstrate financial need, it can create division and hatred. On the other hand, when assistance is provided to all citizens, accountability is shared and it fosters a sense of communal responsibility. Citizens are more invested in each other''s well-being, leading to a more cohesive society. The second reason is that people will lose their motivation to work if the government provides assistance to only those in need. They just have to get money from government and live with it. In such a system, those who do not benefit from government aid may feel disenfranchised and resentful towards those who do. They''re faced with paying for the income of others without receiving any benefits themselves. As a result, their motivation to work decreases. Some people might say that providing assistance only to those in need has potential for greater efficiency, as resources are concentrated where they are most needed. Additionally, the amount of funding needed for assistance programs may be lower, as it is targeted towards those in dire circumstances. However, Those who are ineligible for assistance due to their financial standing may feel that they are being left out of important government programs. They will lose their reason to pay taxes and their motivation to work hard, and consequently, government will lose efficiency gained by helping only those in need. A third problem of implementing a system of aid that targets only those most in need is that the process of determining who qualifies for aid can be highly subjective and prone to abuse. Determining who qualifies for government aid and who does not can be complex and time-consuming. Some people might intentionally misrepresent their situation in order to get assistance, while others might be unjustly excluded from aid due to administrative errors. Then there can be a moral issues. People with greater resources might not need government support, they may still benefit from it in various ways due to the error on determining who qualifies for government assistance. Another reason is that providing financial aid only to those who demonstrate financial need can create unintended consequences, such as discouraging students from pursuing their preferred paths of study based on cost. In contrast, a system that promotes providing assistance to all citizens based on merit and academic achievement ensures talented students have an equal opportunity to achieve their goals, thereby keeping the workforce competitive. Some argue that providing financial assistance to all students based on merit is a wasteful use of taxpayer dollars and that only those who demonstrate financial need or contribute to the public good should receive government funding. However, this argument fails to consider that limiting funding exclusively in this way may exclude many talented students from access to higher education, contributing to a less productive and innovative society overall. The cost to the taxpayer must be weighed against the benefits of investing in a more educated citizenry. In conclusion, the government must offer aid to all citizens to ensure a just and cohesive society. Providing assistance only to those most in need can intensify discrimination and breed resentment, ultimately eroding social solidarity. Additionally, such a system may disincentivize work by fostering resentment among those who do not qualify for aid. While some may argue that focusing aid only on those most in need can be more efficient, it can also exclude those who, despite not demonstrating obvious financial hardship, still require support. The process of determining who qualifies for aid can be complex and prone to errors, potentially leaving out deserving citizens. A system that promotes aid to all citizens is more inclusive and promotes social responsibility, while encouraging productivity and innovation. Therefore, it is imperative that the government consider equity and community investment when designing aid programs, rather than concentrating support on an exclusive group of people.</essay> can you help me revise this essay?', 'The government makes laws and protects its citizens from various problems, such as disasters, poverty, and crime. Citizens have their rights to be helped and protected by government. Each citizen has different situations and needs that may require assistance from the government. Therefore, the question arises: should the government help only those most in need rather than help all of its citizens? I want to say ''no'' to this question for several reasons;. While it may seem logical to provide aid only to those most in need, it can be discriminatory and demotivating. A more equitable approach is to provide aid to all citizens in need. First, limiting assistance to only those in need can create deeper discrimination and antagonism between groups. The government runs the country with tax money collected from its citizens. If only those in need receive benefits, it can create resentment among those who do not receive aid. Discrimination and stigmatization can arise, leading those who do not receive assistance to harbor ill will towards those who do. For example, when healthcare systems focus only on providing care to those who demonstrate financial need, it can create division and hatred. On the other hand, when assistance is provided to all citizens, accountability is shared and it fosters a sense of communal responsibility. Citizens are more invested in each other''s well-being, leading to a more cohesive society. The second reason is that people will lose their motivation to work if the government provides assistance to only those in need. They just have to get money from government and live with it. In such a system, those who do not benefit from government aid may feel disenfranchised and resentful towards those who do. They''re faced with paying for the income of others without receiving any benefits themselves. As a result, their motivation to work decreases. Some people might say that providing assistance only to those in need has potential for greater efficiency, as resources are concentrated where they are most needed. Additionally, the amount of funding needed for assistance programs may be lower, as it is targeted towards those in dire circumstances. However, Those who are ineligible for assistance due to their financial standing may feel that they are being left out of important government programs. They will lose their reason to pay taxes and their motivation to work hard, and consequently, government will lose efficiency gained by helping only those in need. A third problem of implementing a system of aid that targets only those most in need is that the process of determining who qualifies for aid can be highly subjective and prone to abuse. Determining who qualifies for government aid and who does not can be complex and time-consuming. Some people might intentionally misrepresent their situation in order to get assistance, while others might be unjustly excluded from aid due to administrative errors. Then there can be a moral issues. People with greater resources might not need government support, they may still benefit from it in various ways due to the error on determining who qualifies for government assistance. Another reason is that providing financial aid only to those who demonstrate financial need can create unintended consequences, such as discouraging students from pursuing their preferred paths of study based on cost. In contrast, a system that promotes providing assistance to all citizens based on merit and academic achievement ensures talented students have an equal opportunity to achieve their goals, thereby keeping the workforce competitive. Some argue that providing financial assistance to all students based on merit is a wasteful use of taxpayer dollars and that only those who demonstrate financial need or contribute to the public good should receive government funding. However, this argument fails to consider that limiting funding exclusively in this way may exclude many talented students from access to higher education, contributing to a less productive and innovative society overall. The cost to the taxpayer must be weighed against the benefits of investing in a more educated citizenry. In conclusion, the government must offer aid to all citizens to ensure a just and cohesive society. Providing assistance only to those most in need can intensify discrimination and breed resentment, ultimately eroding social solidarity. Additionally, such a system may disincentivize work by fostering resentment among those who do not qualify for aid. While some may argue that focusing aid only on those most in need can be more efficient, it can also exclude those who, despite not demonstrating obvious financial hardship, still require support. The process of determining who qualifies for aid can be complex and prone to errors, potentially leaving out deserving citizens. A system that promotes aid to all citizens is more inclusive and promotes social responsibility, while encouraging productivity and innovation. Therefore, it is imperative that the government consider equity and community investment when designing aid programs, rather than concentrating support on an exclusive group of people.', '2025-03-20 14:28:00'),
(5, 19, 'Can you please provide the English translation of the text so that I can understand what you are trying to convey?', 'Please translate <sent>정부가 취약계층만을 지원하는 정책을 펼친다면 시민들의 입장에서 화가 날 수 밖에 없다.</sent> to English.', 'Socioeconomically poor people usually lack conditions such as education, health care compare to the most. Caring socioeconomically poor people is natural in ethical view. However, it is quite controversial how much of people should be designated as socioeconomical poor. Although socioeconomically poor people are considered the most vulnerable citizens in our society, I believe government should help all of its citizens to ensure that everyone has access to basic necessities and resources. First, it is unfair for citizens to . Even though tax is a burden, citizens constantly paying their tax. If the government only implements policies that support the vulnerable population, citizens will have no choice but to be angry. Second, the budget have to be used properly for functioning economy. There are many things government should get attention. For instance, monitoring and functioning school like KAIST or helping people who are poored. Then why they assist those things? It is for Country''s power. Students in Kaist will lead science in the world, and structures will show the country''s well. I want to point out that there are many targets where budget should be used not only for poors. Third, standard for socioeconomically poor people are too arbitrary. During the Corona pandemic, it was controversial to define who to be received. If we give money by income percentile, people who are slightly better can''t get assistance. Otherwise, if we assist by job, usually we think self-employed people are in trouble. However, some self-employed people have earned more through delivery, while job seekers are in difficult circumstances. Helping socioeconomically solely might causes some problems. However, helping them also have their benefits too. For example, government can find out talented man newly. Even so, the decision looks unfair, inefficient and it looks easily be frauded. Conclusion, I think government should provide appropriate welfare to all of the citizens.', '2025-04-03 16:28:00'),
(1, 20, 'Before I revise it for you, I think it would be more helpful for you to tell me what specifically you''re struggling with or unsure about with regards to the Results and Discussion section of your paper. That way, we can work together to improve your writing skills and understanding of scientific research writing.', 'ok. can you give me feedback on this draft? this is the a description of an XRD analysis shown in the paper: <para>Figure 1 shows the characteristics of the synthesized composite. Figure 1a depicts the XRD analysis which implies that the composite formed shows the same chemical composition as that of the parent UiO-67. It is worth noting that the graphene oxide peak (2θ=26°) is not observed in the XRD peaks of the synthesized composites.2 This could be attributed to the small amount of GO present as compared to the amount of MOF and; thus, could not influence the overall diffraction pattern of the MOF. </para>', 'Figure 1 shows the characteristics of the synthesized composite. Figure 1a depicts the XRD analysis which implies that the composite formed shows the same chemical composition as that of the parent UiO-67. It is worth noting that the graphene oxide peak (2θ=26°) is not observed in the XRD peaks of the synthesized composites.2 This could be attributed to the small amount of GO present as compared to the amount of MOF and; thus, could not influence the overall diffraction pattern of the MOF.', '2025-02-14 10:32:00'),
(2, 20, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I write some result section based on survey. Here is the result section. please revise some grammatical error or any error. <essay>"In our survey, we want to investigate the correlation between sleeping hours and height. The result was analyzed based on answers from 19 participants, 15 men, and 4 women (Figure 1a). The survey consisted of three questions asking respondents’ average sleeping hours, height, and gender. As a result of the analysis, 68% of the respondents answered that they had slept 6-7 hr/per day, including all gender. The sleeping hour with the most responses was 7 hr/day, 31.6% of the population. The average height of the male participants was concentrated at 175 cm, while the height range of the female participants was variable from 158 cm to 175 cm. This discrepancy between males and females is understood as the difference in number of respondents. The correlation between height and sleeping hours was analyzed using a scatter plot shown in Figure 2. The result showed there is no direct relationship between sleeping hours and height. Furthermore, Pearson and Spearman''s indexes reflected that the correlation between these two variables (height and average of sleeping hours) is weak, as shown in the Table 1, and does not support the hypothesis that there is a dependency between sleeping time and height of students in both cases of men and women. In the future, we will survey a larger number of participants, especially female ones, for better generalization. In addition, to ensure that there is no external bias that might influence the result and diversity in the range of age, we will recruit participants outside KAIST."</essay>', 'In our survey, we want to investigate the correlation between sleeping hours and height. The result was analyzed based on answers from 19 participants, 15 men, and 4 women (Figure 1a). The survey consisted of three questions asking respondents’ average sleeping hours, height, and gender. As a result of the analysis, 68% of the respondents answered that they had slept 6-7 hr/per day, including all gender. The sleeping hour with the most responses was 7 hr/day, 31.6% of the population. The average height of the male participants was concentrated at 175 cm, while the height range of the female participants was variable from 158 cm to 175 cm. This discrepancy between males and females is understood as the difference in number of respondents. The correlation between height and sleeping hours was analyzed using a scatter plot shown in Figure 2. The result showed there is no direct relationship between sleeping hours and height. Furthermore, Pearson and Spearman''s indexes reflected that the correlation between these two variables (height and average of sleeping hours) is weak, as shown in the Table 1, and does not support the hypothesis that there is a dependency between sleeping time and height of students in both cases of men and women. In the future, we will survey a larger number of participants, especially female ones, for better generalization. In addition, to ensure that there is no external bias that might influence the result and diversity in the range of age, we will recruit participants outside KAIST.', '2025-02-27 11:32:00'),
(3, 20, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Can you find any grammar mistakes or awkward expressions in my draft?', 'The synthesis of blue quantum dots (QDs) has been studied with a variety of materials used. Blue quantum dots commonly have sizes of 2-6 nm and a peak wavelength of 400-500 nm. In order to have short wavelengths, these QDs are extremely small, so there exists difficulty in synthesizing them due to several factors such as Ostwald ripening, surface ligand effect, and quantum confinement effect. Depending on the precursors used, the photoluminescence quantum yield (PLQY) of these quantum dots may also vary. PLQY is the ratio of the number of photons emitted through photoluminescence to the number of photons absorbed by the material, and is an important criterion for determining the efficiency of QDs. In this section, three recent studies regarding the synthesis of blue quantum dots will be presented. Along with the efficiency of the quantum dots, the struggle for minimizing the use of harmful elements is also being emphasized, so studies about CdSe quantum dots which contain hazardous cadmium will be excluded for this section. One major example of blue quantum dot research is the use of indium and phosphorus precursors, resulting in indium phosphide (InP) QDs which are a type of III-V QDs. In 2020, Zhang et al.[1] reported the synthesis of blue InP quantum dots which have a structure of an InP core and a ZnS shell. For the core, (DMA)3P, ZnI2, and InI3 were used, while for the shell, zinc stearate and 1-dodecanethiol were used. The use of (DMA)3P is highly advantageous because it has high stability when exposed in the air and does not generate toxic PH3¬ gas. Since InP core by itself has low photoluminescence quantum yield (PLQY), ZnS which has a large bandgap as a shell can enhance the PLQY up to 45%. The resulting quantum dots had an emission wavelength of 468 nm, which grants the QD to have a blue emission. What is striking in this study was that this wavelength of 468 nm was the shortest wavelength among the reported InP quantum dots at the time. Moreover, full-width at half-maximum (FWHM) was 47 nm, which is considered narrow among blue InP quantum dots. Meanwhile, other groups of researchers focused on the use of metal halide perovskites for the synthesis of blue QDs, owing to their high stability and excellent photophysical. In 2019, Bi et al.[2] reported that CsPb1-xCuxX3 (X = Br, Br/Cl) perovskite QDs have a potential for being used as blue QDs that possess great optical properties. CsPb1-xCuxX3 perovskite QDs are synthesized by doping Cu2+ ions to the CsPbX3 quantum dots. The larger Pb2+ ions are substituted with smaller Cu2+ ions, leading to a contraction of the octahedral structure and eventually a much more stable lattice. These blue quantum dots show an emission peak in the range of 450-460 nm, accompanied by a narrow PL linewidth. The PLQY was as high as 95% when the x value was 0.07. In particular, these doped quantum dots had high thermal stability due to the stability of the modified lattice structure. The CsPb0.93Cu0.07Br3 QDs retained their PLQY value to 35% under annealing temperatures of 250oC, while the undoped QDs showed a sharp decrease in their PLQY value to 1% at same temperatures. The superb optical properties and high thermal stabilities with the use of metal halide perovskites may pave the way for developing blue-emitting optoelectronic devices with improved stability. Metal halide perovskites surely account for a crucial part in the blue quantum dot synthesis study. However, the problem with these quantum dots is the fact that metal halide perovskites mostly consist of lead ions, which are notorious for toxicity to human bodies. To cope with this issue, a number of researchers aimed to reduce or even eliminate the lead part of these perovskites by substituting lead with other components. For instance, in 2017, Zhang et al.[3] reported the synthesis of blue quantum dots using lead-free Cs3Sb2Br9. These inorganic antimony halide perovskite quantum dots are synthesized via modifying the structure of traditional CsSbBr3 perovskites, by moving every third Sb layer along <111> direction. The QDs resulted in an emission peak of 410 nm, and the PLQY of 46% could be obtained. This value of PLQY was notable in that it was much higher than that of the counterparts with similar emission peaks. The high value of PLQY can be attributed to the higher proportion of Br that reduces the surface trapper effect, and a large exciton binding energy. In addition, the FWHM value was 41 nm, which is also a much improved value compared to previous studies.', '2025-03-13 10:02:00'),
(4, 20, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about two kinds of parallelism that is important in eassy. One is organizational parallelism and another is syntatic parallelism. Oraganizational parallelism means it is important to provied well organized contents to readers. And syntatic parallelism means when we have parallel structure in the sentence, we should use same form of words or phrases.', 'In mordern society, it is important to ensure fair opportunites and a person''s well-being.To acheive this, government should concentrate on supporting people in need. First, the poors are not likely to get high quality education or supports than others. So, they get little chance for learning something and improving abilities. For instance, many universities and companies prefer a person who can perform well but the people who are in need can''t satisfy others need due to their insufficient learning and chances. As a result, to get a much better status and chances the poors need government''s help. Second, people might think it is unfair to help elders,but all human beings will get old and need helps to live. The government should care about their citizens'' future and continue to help elders. Therefore. the taxes and little unfairness you have to experience will return to you in the future. Lastly, if the government doesn''t focus on helping people in need, the differnce between people''s socioeconomic status will be get worse. As a result, the society might become more unstable. For example, historically, there are more conflict between the poor and the rich. It can be expected that there will be more comlaint, if the unbalanced chances and money are getting more bigger. Government''s purpose is to maintain society''s peace and balanced state. So, they should help people in need more carefully to ensure their chance to learn and become sucessful. Also, for the citizen''s future, government should help elders. In conclusion, government''s role of helping people in need is essential for the society''s well-being.', '2025-03-20 14:32:00'),
(5, 20, 'Great! Let''s start with the essay. Can you share the essay that you would like to revise? Please read it to me, out loud.', '<para>Last college can reduce the students who more to other major or getting out. As a reason from above, if students more satisfy about their major, they won’t move or change the school or major easily. This can be advantage to the college.</para>', 'In this days, most of the students choose the major and go to the proper university. Some students who strongly want that kind of work or job can get advantage about that, but others who don’t interest or it is not fun enough to them can be lose of time. So, for that I think universities should require that the first year of college be major free. It has a good point to both kinds of students and college. First, student can get a chance to know about major more. In high school, it is hard to get information about major because of school work and limitation of information pool. But if students go to universities and watch, ask or listen about the major by like major introduction class, they can choose what was really wanted to do. In my case, I had question what major I have to do. After listening two class, Bio & Brain Engineering and Brain Cognitive Science introduction, I could make my choose hard to BCS. Second, It can be a time to set a basic of major classes. Major classes mostly need previous knowledge. For example, in my Neuron Cell Biology needs General Biology class to hear more easily. Nor just for the biology, math also needs many basic steps. One year of major free could make more hard and strong basement of knowledge. Also It can be a time for own time or knowledge about other region. In Korea, high school study is mostly stricted. So, it is hard to learn other interesting class through the course. This major free can give a time to make more wide knowledge. Last college can reduce the students who more to other major or getting out. As a reason from above, if students more satisfy about their major, they won’t move or change the school or major easily. This can be advantage to the college. For those reason, major free will helpful to college and students. Student can know more about major and have a time for choose enough. Also, Learn more knowledge about other things or basic so that can make strong, wide basement. College can keep their students. So, universities should require that the first year of college be major free.', '2025-04-03 16:32:00'),
(1, 21, 'Yes, that''s absolutely right! Improper syntax can lead to ambiguity and confusion in your writing. It''s important to ensure that the words in your sentences are placed in the correct order and that your expressions are clear and concise. Misplacing or mislocating adverbs, adjectives or any other expression can alter the meaning of a sentence entirely. This could make it difficult or even impossible for the reader to understand what you are trying to communicate. Did you find any examples of this in the material we covered today?', 'Moreover I learned missing comma that makes subject in the sentence is unclear. Also the meaning of the sentence is unclear because of not using comma that can seperate different clauses.', 'Text-to-speech (TTS) systems synthesize raw speech waveforms from given text through several components. With the rapid development of deep neural networks, TTS system pipelines have been simplified to two-stage generative modeling apart from text preprocessing such as text normalization and phonemization. The first stage is to produce intermediate speech representations such as melspectrograms (Shen et al., 2018) or linguistic features (Oord et al., 2016) from the preprocessed text,1 and the second stage is to generate raw waveforms conditioned on the intermediate representations (Oord et al., 2016; Kalchbrenner et al., 2018). Models at each of the two-stage pipelines have been developed independently. Neural network-based autoregressive TTS systems have shown the capability of synthesizing realistic speech (Shen et al., 2018; Li et al., 2019), but their sequential generative process makes it difficult to fully utilize modern parallel processors. To overcome this limitation and improve synthesis speed, several non-autoregressive methods have been proposed. In the text-to-spectrogram generation step, extracting attention maps from pre-trained autoregressive teacher networks (Ren et al., 2019; Peng et al., 2020) is attempted to decrease the difficulty of learning alignments between text and spectrograms. More recently, likelihood-based methods further eliminate the dependency on external aligners by estimating or learning alignments that maximize the likelihood of target mel-spectrograms (Zeng et al., 2020; Miao et al., 2020; Kim et al., 2020). Meanwhile, generative adversarial networks (GANs) (Goodfellow et al., 2014) have been explored in second stage models. GAN-based feed-forward networks with multiple discriminators, each distinguishing samples at different scales or periods, achieve high-quality raw waveform synthesis (Kumar et al., 2019; Bi´nkowski et al., 2019; Kong et al., 2020). Despite the progress of parallel TTS systems, two-stage pipelines remain problematic because they require sequential training or fine-tuning (Shen et al., 2018; Weiss et al., 2020) for high-quality production wherein latter stage models are trained with the generated samples of earlier stage models. In addition, their dependency on predefined intermediate features precludes applying learned hidden representations to obtain further improvements in performance. Recently, several works, i.e., FastSpeech 2s (Ren et al., 2021) and EATS (Donahue et al., 2021), have proposed efficient end-to-end training methods such as training over short audio clips rather than entire waveforms, leveraging a mel-spectrogram decoder to aid text representation learning, and designing a specialized spectrogram loss to relax lengthmismatch between target and generated speech. However, despite potentially improving performance by utilizing the learned representations, their synthesis quality lags behind two-stage systems. In this work, we present a parallel end-to-end TTS method that generates more natural sounding audio than current two-stage models. Using a variational autoencoder (VAE) (Kingma & Welling, 2014), we connect two modules of TTS systems through latent variables to enable efficient end-to-end learning. To improve the expressive power of our method so that high-quality speech waveforms can be synthesized, we apply normalizing flows to our conditional prior distribution and adversarial training on the waveform domain. In addition to generating fine-grained audio, it is important for TTS systems to express the one-to-many relationship in which text input can be spoken in multiple ways with different variations (e.g., pitch and duration). To tackle the one-to-many problem, we also propose a stochastic duration predictor to synthesize speech with diverse rhythms from input text. With the uncertainty modeling over latent variables and the stochastic duration predictor, our method captures speech variations that cannot be represented by text. Our method obtains more natural sounding speech and higher sampling efficiency than the best publicly available TTS system, Glow-TTS (Kim et al., 2020) with HiFiGAN (Kong et al., 2020). We make both our demo page and source-code publicly available.', '2025-02-14 10:36:00'),
(2, 21, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about rewriting the thesis statements to include an opposing point of view. We can do this by using transition signals of contrast such as however, although, despite the fact that, and while.', 'Women''s mandatory military enlistment is a topic that raises questions about physical and social differences between men and women. While some may argue that women should have equal opportunities when it comes to serving in the military, I believe that these differences cannot be ignored. One of the primary considerations when it comes to the inclusion of women in the military is the significant gap in average muscle mass between men and women. According to studies, this gap is almost 20%, making it difficult to provide the same level of training for both genders. This means that women may be at a disadvantage when it comes to performing certain physical tasks required in the military. In addition, the military is no stranger to sexual assault and harassment. In fact, the military has been known to cover up such incidents, making it difficult for victims to report them. Recent statistics show that only 32.7% of sex crimes within the military are reported. This creates an environment where soldiers may not feel safe or protected. In addition, The military is no stranger to sexual assault and harassment. In fact, the military has been known to cover up such incidents, making it difficult for victims to report them. Recent statistics show that only 32.7% of sex crimes within the military are reported. This creates an environment where soldiers may not feel safe or protected. In other words, only 3 out of 10 people report it. 44% of victims who did not report sex crimes saids, "No action was likely to be taken." In other words, soldiers do not trust the military''s measures and do not even expected them. Unlike now situation, if two genders have to live in the military, there might be many problems that comes from the difference of two genders in the closed military society. As a result, the crime can be increased. Moreover, joining women to the military cannot resolve gender inequality. With women not being allowed in combat roles until recently, the facilities and conditions within the military are not suitable for women to join. There are shortages of women''s toilets and other facilities that make it difficult for women to serve alongside men. These limitations serve as a significant barrier to women''s participation in the military. Some argue that women''s mandatory military enlistment will help solve gender inequality and increase female participation in the military. However, simply allowing women to serve does not address systemic issues within society. Providing equal opportunities is only a small part of addressing gender inequality. It is a band-aid solution that fails to address the root causes of gender-based discrimination. In conclusion, I believe that women''s mandatory military enlistment is not an effective solution to the issue of gender inequality within the military. Physical, social, and cultural differences between men and women cannot be ignored. Until facilities and conditions are equalized for both genders, women''s participation in the military must remain voluntary. For this reason, I oppose women''s mandatory military enlistment. Of course, it is a pity that men go to the military to support their youth in their young and precious days in their 20s. I think women should live with more respect for men and a heart that contributes to the country.', '2025-02-27 11:36:00'),
(3, 21, 'Yes, using a comma can often help clarify a sentence and prevent ambiguity. Can you provide an example sentence from the class where adding a comma would have helped to remove ambiguity?', 'where there is multiple objects, you can use comma to remove ambiguity', 'While fuel consumption of internal combustion engine is determined according to the velocity planning, fuel consumption of hybrid vehicle is determined by both velocity planning and energy management strategy. Energy management strategy (EMS) of hybrid electric vehicle (HEV) is a critical factor in the control of HEV because loss of fuel consumption optimality can be more than 15% in heavy hilly road conditions due to selection of wrong EMS1). In the energy management problem, full information on future driving conditions is required to obtain the optimal solution, which is impossible. However, using available future information, a near-optimal performance can be achieved. This strategy, using available future information to achieve near-optimal performance is predictive EMS (p-EMS). Optimal velocity planning, just like energy management strategy, can also reduce fuel consumption without any change in the vehicle architecture, just within the change inside software. In this paper, a systematic control scheme that co-optimize velocity planning and p-EMS is proposed. The optimal velocity planning and proposed energy management strategy altogether shows significant effect on fuel consumption reduction without compromise on the travel time and safety.', '2025-03-13 10:06:00'),
(4, 21, 'Your introduction is on the right track. However, it is important to avoid repetition and ensure that your introduction flows smoothly. Here is an example of how you can refine your introduction: Governments have a crucial role to play in supporting their citizens, but they face significant challenges in doing so. With limited resources and budget constraints, it is essential that governments prioritize the allocation of resources to those in genuine need. By providing assistance only to those who require it, governments can ensure an efficient use of available resources. Moreover, this approach fosters social equity and reduces poverty, making it a win-win situation for both the government and its citizens. In this revised introduction, both the reasons for the thesis statement are merged into a coherent and connected format. What do you think of this introduction?', 'Can you give me some examples of support provided by goverments? I want to add some of these to the introduction.', 'Governments have responsibility to help citizens. However, due to the limited workforce and budget constraints, it is essential for goverments to use their resources in the most efficient manner. As such, it is imperative for goverments to extend their help only to those who are genuinely in need. Governments have a responsibility to provid assistance to their citizens, but because of limited resources, it is essential that they allocate support only to those in need. This approach not only ensures efficient use of available resources, but also fosters social equity and reduced poverty. Governments have a crucial role to play in supporting their citizens, but they face significant challenges in doing so. With limited resources and budget constraints, it is essential that governments prioritize the allocation of resources to those in genuine need. By providing assistance only to those who require it, governments can ensure an efficient use of available resources. Moreover, this approach fosters social equity and reduces poverty, making it a win-win situation for both the government and its citizens.', '2025-03-20 14:36:00'),
(5, 21, 'I apologize for the confusion. Based on your paragraph, it looks like you learned about the components of the discussion section. These three components include: 1. State and interpret key findings- In this component, you need to explain your results and provide an answer to the research question. You should analyze and interpret the data and explain how the findings are relevant to the research question. 2. Summarize and generalize - In this component, you need to link your findings with previous research and summarize your main results. You can make generalizations based on your findings and explain any limitations of the study. 3. Keep in mind who your potential readers will be - This component is a reminder that you should write for your intended audience. You should consider the knowledge level and background of your readers and ensure that your writing is clear and understandable. Overall, it appears that you have a good understanding of the key components of the discussion section. Do you have any questions or anything else you''d like to discuss?', 'Also, I leaned about the pyramid structure of the discussion section. The structure consists as follows: 1. First Paragraph: 1) Interpretation / Answer based on key findings. 2) Supporting evidence. 2. Middle Paragraphs: 1) Comparison/Contrasts to previous studies. 2) Limitations of your study. 3) Unexpected findings. 4) Hypotheses or models. 3. Last Paragraph: 1) Summary. 2) Significance/Implication. Could you revise <essay>" Our findings emphasize the need to continue to promote personal protection measures to reduce the risk of Lyme disease infection. We have identified three reasonable personal measures that may be protective against Lyme disease when practiced: tick checks, bathing, and insect repellents. Performing tick checks within 36 hr after spending time in the yard may reduce one’s risk by as much as 46%. In addition, bathing may reduce one’s risk by up to 57%, and the use of insect repellent may be protective against the disease up to 75%. Our results suggest that the part of the bindin responsible for species-specific eff agglutination lies in the region of residues 75-121. We showed that residues 18-74 and 122-136 can be deleted without loss of egg agglutination activity. All of the biologically active bindin deletion analogs were found to be species-specific by their ability to agglutinate exclusively S. purpuratus eggs. Deletion analogs that had any residues of region 75-121 deleted exhibited no significant activity above the bacterial control protein. We observed virtually no size classes of mtDNA molecules. Since the undegraded circular mtDNA molecules were entirely of heterogeneous size, this obser ed size heterogeneity probably reflects the real situation within plant mitochondria…In contrast to our observations, size classes of linear or circular molecules and species specific differences have been previously reported (24, 25). However, these studies were performed only with a fraction of supercoiled DNA (26), which most likely does not represent the complete set of molecules existing in organelle. Supercoiled DNA isolated from a C. album suspension culture, for example, consisted exclusively of small circular plasmid mp1 DNA. Its oligomers were found in the open circular form, thus appearing indeed as a few size classes. We have shown that annual canine vaccination campaigns achieving 67% coverage in Ngorongoro and 42% coverage in Serengeti should be sufficient to control rabies outbreaks with 95% confidence. These coverage levels are lower than the WHO-recommended annual target of 70% (26). We focused on annual coverage targets, since rabies vaccination in Tanzania is conducted through annual campaigns and since the WHO target is specified as such. However, we also calculated that 39% and 25% coverage consistently maintained in Ngorongoro and Serengeti, respectively, will control rabies outbreaks with 95% confidence. These estimates of required coverage are much lower than previous recommendations of 70% coverage on a consistent basis (1). The difference is possibly due to the fact that the parameters of the previous study were drawn from Asia and the Americas, whereas our model considers rabies dynamics in sub-Saharan Africa (19)." </essay>according to the previous sentence?', 'Our findings emphasize the need to continue to promote personal protection measures to reduce the risk of Lyme disease infection. We have identified three reasonable personal measures that may be protective against Lyme disease when practiced: tick checks, bathing, and insect repellents. Performing tick checks within 36 hr after spending time in the yard may reduce one’s risk by as much as 46%. In addition, bathing may reduce one’s risk by up to 57%, and the use of insect repellent may be protective against the disease up to 75%. Our results suggest that the part of the bindin responsible for species-specific eff agglutination lies in the region of residues 75-121. We showed that residues 18-74 and 122-136 can be deleted without loss of egg agglutination activity. All of the biologically active bindin deletion analogs were found to be species-specific by their ability to agglutinate exclusively S. purpuratus eggs. Deletion analogs that had any residues of region 75-121 deleted exhibited no significant activity above the bacterial control protein. We observed virtually no size classes of mtDNA molecules. Since the undegraded circular mtDNA molecules were entirely of heterogeneous size, this obser ed size heterogeneity probably reflects the real situation within plant mitochondria…In contrast to our observations, size classes of linear or circular molecules and species specific differences have been previously reported (24, 25). However, these studies were performed only with a fraction of supercoiled DNA (26), which most likely does not represent the complete set of molecules existing in organelle. Supercoiled DNA isolated from a C. album suspension culture, for example, consisted exclusively of small circular plasmid mp1 DNA. Its oligomers were found in the open circular form, thus appearing indeed as a few size classes. We have shown that annual canine vaccination campaigns achieving 67% coverage in Ngorongoro and 42% coverage in Serengeti should be sufficient to control rabies outbreaks with 95% confidence. These coverage levels are lower than the WHO-recommended annual target of 70% (26). We focused on annual coverage targets, since rabies vaccination in Tanzania is conducted through annual campaigns and since the WHO target is specified as such. However, we also calculated that 39% and 25% coverage consistently maintained in Ngorongoro and Serengeti, respectively, will control rabies outbreaks with 95% confidence. These estimates of required coverage are much lower than previous recommendations of 70% coverage on a consistent basis (1). The difference is possibly due to the fact that the parameters of the previous study were drawn from Asia and the Americas, whereas our model considers rabies dynamics in sub-Saharan Africa (19).', '2025-04-03 16:36:00'),
(1, 22, 'Good job on your essay! However, there are several areas where you can make improvements to clarify your points and make the content flow logically. Here are some steps you can take to revise your essay: 1. Introduction: Start with a clear and engaging hook that can grab the reader''s attention. You can begin with a statistic or an interesting fact that highlights the importance of the topic. For example, <sent>"In the 21st century, technology has transformed the way we learn, and tablets have become an essential tool in classrooms worldwide."</sent> 2. Thesis statement: Provide a clear and concise thesis statement that captures the main point of your essay. The thesis statement should be presented in the introduction, preferably as the last sentence. For example, <sent>"Tablets offer significant advantages over traditional textbooks such as access to the internet, portability, and efficient note-taking that can enhance learning outcomes for students."</sent> 3. Topic sentences: Ensure that each paragraph has a clear topic sentence that supports your thesis statement. The topic sentence should introduce the main idea of the paragraph, and the subsequent sentences should provide evidence to support it. For example, <sent>"The convenience of accessing the internet is one of the key advantages of using tablets in classrooms."</sent> 4. Evidence: Provide specific examples, data or statistics, to support your claims. Be sure to cite your sources appropriately. For example, <sent>"According to a recent survey conducted by the Pew Research Center, 80% of students use tablets in college, and 60% cite the ability to access the internet as the most significant benefit."</sent> 5. Conclusion: End your essay with a strong conclusion that summarizes the main points of your essay, reiterates your thesis statement and provides a final thought. For example, <sent>"In conclusion, tablets offer numerous advantages over traditional textbooks that can improve the learning experience for students. While there may be some initial costs, the benefits far outweigh the costs, making tablets a worthwhile investment in education."</sent> Good luck!', 'How about it? <essay>In the 21st century, technology has transformed the way we learn, and tablets have become an essential tool in classrooms worldwide. Most of students use lap top or tablet in class nowadays. However, someone stay at the transition porision and use paper note and textbook. Tablets offer significant advantages over traditional textbooks such as access to the internet, portability, and efficient note-taking that can enhance learning outcomes for students. I will write the 3 representataive advantages of tablet. The first advantage is internet. Tablets offer significant advantages over traditional textbooks such as access to the internet, portability, and efficient note-taking that can enhance learning outcomes for students. According to a recent survey conducted by the Pew Research Center, 80% of students use tablets in college, and 60% cite the ability to access the internet as the most significant benefit. Next advantage is weight. It might be illigal, but students can take all of the textbooks into tablet by the form of pdf. Univercity''s textbooks have large wight. Only 2 or 3 books can weight 5kg easily. However even if you download thousands of pdf, tablet''s weight doesn''t change just 0.001kg. Last one is note taking. There are many high quality of note applications. Compare the paper note, it takes significantly less time. Otherwise, many functions of application help you make a good note to study. In conclusion, tablets offer numerous advantages over traditional textbooks that can improve the learning experience for students. While there may be some initial costs, the benefits far outweigh the costs, making tablets a worthwhile investment in education.</essay>', 'Nowadays, most of students use lap top or tablet in class. Someone stay at the transition porision and use paper note and textbook. However, I think that there are big and lots of advantages on tablet. I will write the 3 representataive advantages of tablet. The first advantage is internet. We can find huge amount of informations on internet. For example, in univercity class, there are some words which is complecate and har do understand. We can know about these words by just one searching on internet. On the other hand, internet can show us the recently research related with the class. It makes students understand easily. Next advantage is weight. It might be illigal, but students can take all of the textbooks into tablet by the form of pdf. Univercity''s textbooks have large wight. Only 2 or 3 books can weight 5kg easily. However even if you download thousands of pdf, tablet''s weight doesn''t change just 0.001kg. Last one is note taking. There are many high quality of note applications. Compare the paper note, it takes significantly less time. Otherwise, many functions of application help you make a good note to study. To sum up, internet, weight, and note taking is the bid advantages of tablet. There are many other advantages on tablet not just these things. So, why don''t you prepare a nice table?', '2025-02-14 10:40:00'),
(2, 22, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Few month ago, I learned about comma rules. At that time, I thought that I understand about it. However I make many mistakes of comma rule.', 'The universities should be major free in first year of college. These days in Korea, lots of smart students who are in high scored universities like Seoul, Yonsei, or Kaist, leave their schools. It could be due to universities’ system that they should choose their major before they enter to universities. Instead of this, there are lots of problems in choosing major early. Thus, universities should be required to major-free in first year of college. At first, in high school, it is hard to choose the major. In universities, there are many major and classes. However, in high school, every students learn just few subjects like chemistry and physics. Also, they cannot get the information of major easily. Thus, there are less information of major, so students cannot choose major well. Un addition they do not have much time to think about major. Korea’s national exam ‘수능’ is very hard and it is hard to get good grade. Due to this, high school students have to study very hard than others. Thus, they do not have time to search their dream or major. In conclusion, high school students do not have sufficient information and time to choose major, so first grade of college should be major free. Second, the major-free year could be provide diverse experience to students. When we choose the major, we have to choose the course related to our major, so undergraduate student’s background information could be limited. Especially, these days, the collaboration of diverse major is important. It could be help people to be more creative and think diverse way. Thus, for more experiences, the first year in college should be major free. At next, the major-free policy could help the Korea’s education system changing. The past and current education system is not helpful to students’ future. For example, in high school students study hard for ‘수능’. But when they finished the exam, they forgot lots of things and did not study them again. Thus, the three years of students in high school is not that efficiency. On the other hand, some students who want to be a biologist of chemist, study the Earth science or East Asian history, because these subjects are easy to them. It is not good education. When, every college change the first year to major-free, students do not have to study for get the good major. In addition, students choose the major that are highest they can get with their grade. For example, in our school, student who want to be biologist go to mechanic school, and student who want to be a physicist go to medical school. Like this, most of students in Korea, they cannot study what they want tin college. So, the first year in college should be major-free. In conclusion, when the first year of college become major-free, it can help high school students who are hard to choose the major due to less information and time, undergraduate students to get many experiences, and education system in Korea. There are lots of benefit than disadvantages, so first year of college should be major-free.', '2025-02-27 11:40:00'),
(3, 22, 'Of course, I''d be happy to help you revise your essay''s vocabulary. First, let''s start by discussing what specific aspects of vocabulary you''d like help with. Do you want to improve the variety and complexity of words you use, or do you need help with specific words/phrases? Additionally, can you provide me with a copy of your essay so that I can better guide you through the revision process?', 'Let''s first start with spelling mistakes. Here is my essay: <essay>Advantages of making first year students major-free In Korea, most of the universities require the freshmen to choose their major before they start their first year. But very few of them including -IST universities like KAIST, let the first year students to be major-free. They choose their major in second year, or in the end of their first year. Even though there are many advantages and disadvantages with it, I think the first year students of college should be major-free. One of the most important benefit of first-year-major-free is that the freshmen can have chances to have contact with various fields of study. Some people may say major-free can make students stressed by forcing them to listen to unintersted subjects. But in the near future, we have to work on topics that are not only included to one field. We will need knowledges and perspectives of various fields, and the basic knowledge from the first year class will help overcoming it. Also, we can find unexpected interests. Learning about new fields of study may help them find their interests. Secondly, some other people say major-free is a waste of time for students who already decided their major, but it is not quite true. For example, despite my university is major-free in the first year, there are friends who listen to the classes for particular major. Some of them are accquiring organic, or biochemistry, and another friend is accquiring programming class for 3rd, or 4th years. Likewise, students with concrete dicision about their major can participate to such class, because it''s major-''free''. Lastly, major-free can help first-year students meet diverse people. In most universities that require their first students to choose their major usually divides the dormitory or class by major. This prevents students to meet people from other major, who have different point of view. Major-free can make students team-up with students of other majors, and help them grow abilities to cooperate with people who think different from them. In conclusion, letting first-year students of college to be major-free can help them find new interests, freely listen to their intersted subjects, meet diverse people. For these reasons, I strongly believe making first-year students of universities will help the students and the society.</essay>', 'Advantages of making first year students major-free In Korea, most of the universities require the freshmen to choose their major before they start their first year. But very few of them including -IST universities like KAIST, let the first year students to be major-free. They choose their major in second year, or in the end of their first year. Even though there are many advantages and disadvantages with it, I think the first year students of college should be major-free. One of the most important benefit of first-year-major-free is that the freshmen can have chances to have contact with various fields of study. Some people may say major-free can make students stressed by forcing them to listen to unintersted subjects. But in the near future, we have to work on topics that are not only included to one field. We will need knowledges and perspectives of various fields, and the basic knowledge from the first year class will help overcoming it. Also, we can find unexpected interests. Learning about new fields of study may help them find their interests. Secondly, some other people say major-free is a waste of time for students who already decided their major, but it is not quite true. For example, despite my university is major-free in the first year, there are friends who listen to the classes for particular major. Some of them are accquiring organic, or biochemistry, and another friend is accquiring programming class for 3rd, or 4th years. Likewise, students with concrete dicision about their major can participate to such class, because it''s major-''free''. Lastly, major-free can help first-year students meet diverse people. In most universities that require their first students to choose their major usually divides the dormitory or class by major. This prevents students to meet people from other major, who have different point of view. Major-free can make students team-up with students of other majors, and help them grow abilities to cooperate with people who think different from them. In conclusion, letting first-year students of college to be major-free can help them find new interests, freely listen to their intersted subjects, meet diverse people. For these reasons, I strongly believe making first-year students of universities will help the students and the society.', '2025-03-13 10:10:00'),
(4, 22, 'Sure! After reviewing it again, I am confident that the revised paragraph is grammatically correct in terms of verb tense. Let me know if you have any other questions or concerns!', 'can you suggest ways i can improve the structure of my paragraph? and please also check for any spelling or grammar mistakes', 'In the realm of open domain question answering, recent developments have led to increasingly sophisticated approaches to solving the task. For example, researchers have experimented with innovative methods, such as combining the strengths of the retrieve-read and retrieve-generate pipelines in one study. In another study, a deep learning model was developed that can generate natural language answers with high accuracy. Despite these advancements, significant challenges in open domain QA still exist, such as handling long-form questions and identifying reliable sources of information. As a result, future research will need to focus on overcoming these challenges to further improve the performance of open domain QA systems.', '2025-03-20 14:40:00'),
(5, 22, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about parallelism. It means that you are listing or comparing and contrasting items or ideas. Parallelism means that each item in a list or in a comparison follows the same grammatical pattern.', 'I believe that government should those most in need, not all of its citizens. There are two reasons for my opinion. First, when government helps all of its citizens, ore people who are in need will be neglected. Have you ever read an article about elderly people who live alone in a very poor environment because they don''t have money? These people desperately need help, but it is true that people in need don''t get enough help from the government. It will be worse when government expands the range of people who get supported. I think minority of people should get a concentrated help. Second, people who are very wealthy don''t need any help from the government. I believe it is right for people to help each other. Rich people shouldn''t receive benefits from the government. Rather, they have to pay more. It is a well-known fact that minority of super-rich people own majority of the wealth. To make our society a better place for everyone, people should be less selfish. These are two reasons why I believe government should help those most in need. We live in a society where the gap between the rich and the poor is very large. To overcome this, not only government but all of us should try hard, and take care of each other.', '2025-04-03 16:40:00'),
(1, 23, 'I''m sorry, but I still haven''t seen a paragraph or summary for me to review. Could you please provide me with a summary of what you learned during our class session or the paragraph you mentioned earlier so that we can discuss any potential problems or issues that may need to be addressed?', 'Method Porous carbon material derived from carbon dioxide as the reference material for identifying the active site of boron for 2 electron reduction, which is doped with heteroatoms (Boron, Oxygen). As this porous carbon material contains boron and oxygen, which are simultaneously generated when NaBH4 is used as a reducing agent, it would be a suitable reference. To further dope the carbon material with additional oxygen, we used a polymer containing O. The polymer and carbon material were heat-treated together, the polymer would decompose into fragments and oxygen could be doped into the carbon material. To efficiently confirm the effect of oxygen doping, we selected a similar structure polymer without oxygen as the compare group. 1. Synthesis of carbon materials by converting CO2 To obtain carbon materials by converting CO2, reducing agent, NaBH4 (Sigma-Aldrich, >99%), was prepared. Placed 2g of NaBH4 in an alumina boat and put in a furnace, raising the temperature to 520°C at a rate of 5°C/min. To prevent the reaction, we flowed inert gas, Ar, at a rate of 55 sccm. When the temperature reached 500°C, replaced Ar with CO2 as a carbon source and maintained the same flow rate of 55 sccm. We maintained the temperature at 500°C for 2 hours for sufficient reaction between CO2 and NaBH4. After waiting for the temperature to cool down, the carbon material was obtained. To remove impurities, washed the obtained carbon material with a 5M HCl solution by stirring at 80°C for 30 minutes and conducting filtration twice. Next, stirred the material in distilled water at 80°C for 30 minutes and filtered it three times. Finally, converted the material to a neutral condition by treating it with an ethanol solution twice. After washing, dried the material at 80°C overnight and obtained the basic carbon material, Boron doped porous carbon (BPC). 2. Heat treatment of carbon materials with oxygen-containing polymers Carbon material obtained from carbon dioxide was modified by conducting thermal treatment with a polymer, polyethylene oxide (PEO, Sigma-Aldrich), which contains oxygen for additional doping. The mixture of the carbon material, BPC, and PEO was prepared in a 1:4 mass ratio (0.1g:0.4g) by mixing with a vortex mixer for 5 minutes to ensure proper mixing. The mixture was then placed in an alumina boat and heated in a furnace with argon gas flowing at a 55sccm and heat rate of 5℃/min up to a temperature of 500°C, which was maintained for 3 hours after reached 500°C. Afterward, the temperature was gradually cooled lowered to room temperature to obtain the material BPC_PEO, which was the result of the thermal treatment of BPC and PEO. The obtained material was subjected to a washing and drying process, which involved placing it in a 5M HCl solution and stirring it for 30 minutes at 80°C, followed by filtration once. Then, the material was stirred in distilled water at 80°C for 30 minutes and filtered twice. Finally, to neutralize the carbon material, the same process was repeated with an ethanol solution once. The washed material was then dried overnight at 80°C and subjected to additional heat treatment to obtain the final carbon material, BPC_PEO. 3. Heat treatment of carbon materials with non oxygen-containing polymers To prepare a comparison group for carbon materials doped with oxygen, a polymer Polyethylene (PE, Sigma-Aldrich) and the basic carbon material BPC with the same structure with PEO but non oxygen polymer were processed together. The process of obtaining the materials including thermal treatment was the same as the previous process. BPC and PE were mixed in a 1:4 ratio (0.1g:0.4g) using a vortex mixer for 5 minutes to ensure proper mixing. The mixture was then placed in an alumina boat and put into a furnace. Argon gas was flowed through the furnace, and the temperature was raised to 500°C at a rate of 5℃/min. When the temperature reached 500°C, it was maintained for 3 hours before being lowered to room temperature to obtain the material BPC_PE, where BPC and PE were co-processed. The obtained material underwent a cleaning process and drying process as follows: it was placed in a 5M HCl solution and stirred at 80 °C for 30 minutes before being filtered once. Then, it was stirred in distilled water at 80 °C for 30 minutes and filtered twice. Finally, to neutralize the carbon material, the solution was converted to an ethanol solution and the same process was repeated once. After washing, the material was dried overnight at 80 °C to obtain the final carbon material, BPC_PE, which was subjected to additional heat treatment. 4. Electrochemical experiment The catalytic ability of the materials in producing hydrogen peroxide was measured using Rotating Ring Disk Electrode (RRDE) in a three-electrode cell. Ag/AgCl electrode was used as the reference electrode, and Pt coil electrode was used as the counter electrode and RRDE electrode. Solution consisting of 1 ml ethanol, 0.1 ml 5 wt% Nafion, and 4 mg catalyst was sonicated for 1 hour to disperse the catalyst well, and then 5 ul was dropped to load the catalyst. The electrode with the solution was rotated at 600 rpm for 30 minutes to dry and fix the catalyst on the electrode. LSV(Linear Sweep Voltammetry) measurements were then conducted underusing KOH 0.1M and Na2SO4 0.1M solutions as an electrolyte at a scan rate of 10 mV/s to test the performance of the catalyst with rotating 1600rpm. The actual current resulting from oxygen reduction was calculated as the difference between measurements taken in an argon-saturated solution initially and an oxygen-saturated solution subsequently. here', 'Method Porous carbon material derived from carbon dioxide as the reference material for identifying the active site of boron for 2 electron reduction, which is doped with heteroatoms (Boron, Oxygen). As this porous carbon material contains boron and oxygen, which are simultaneously generated when NaBH4 is used as a reducing agent, it would be a suitable reference. To further dope the carbon material with additional oxygen, we used a polymer containing O. The polymer and carbon material were heat-treated together, the polymer would decompose into fragments and oxygen could be doped into the carbon material. To efficiently confirm the effect of oxygen doping, we selected a similar structure polymer without oxygen as the compare group. 1. Synthesis of carbon materials by converting CO2 To obtain carbon materials by converting CO2, reducing agent, NaBH4 (Sigma-Aldrich, >99%), was prepared. Placed 2g of NaBH4 in an alumina boat and put in a furnace, raising the temperature to 520°C at a rate of 5°C/min. To prevent the reaction, we flowed inert gas, Ar, at a rate of 55 sccm. When the temperature reached 500°C, replaced Ar with CO2 as a carbon source and maintained the same flow rate of 55 sccm. We maintained the temperature at 500°C for 2 hours for sufficient reaction between CO2 and NaBH4. After waiting for the temperature to cool down, the carbon material was obtained. To remove impurities, washed the obtained carbon material with a 5M HCl solution by stirring at 80°C for 30 minutes and conducting filtration twice. Next, stirred the material in distilled water at 80°C for 30 minutes and filtered it three times. Finally, converted the material to a neutral condition by treating it with an ethanol solution twice. After washing, dried the material at 80°C overnight and obtained the basic carbon material, Boron doped porous carbon (BPC). 2. Heat treatment of carbon materials with oxygen-containing polymers Carbon material obtained from carbon dioxide was modified by conducting thermal treatment with a polymer, polyethylene oxide (PEO, Sigma-Aldrich), which contains oxygen for additional doping. The mixture of the carbon material, BPC, and PEO was prepared in a 1:4 mass ratio (0.1g:0.4g) by mixing with a vortex mixer for 5 minutes to ensure proper mixing. The mixture was then placed in an alumina boat and heated in a furnace with argon gas flowing at a 55sccm and heat rate of 5℃/min up to a temperature of 500°C, which was maintained for 3 hours after reached 500°C. Afterward, the temperature was gradually cooled lowered to room temperature to obtain the material BPC_PEO, which was the result of the thermal treatment of BPC and PEO. The obtained material was subjected to a washing and drying process, which involved placing it in a 5M HCl solution and stirring it for 30 minutes at 80°C, followed by filtration once. Then, the material was stirred in distilled water at 80°C for 30 minutes and filtered twice. Finally, to neutralize the carbon material, the same process was repeated with an ethanol solution once. The washed material was then dried overnight at 80°C and subjected to additional heat treatment to obtain the final carbon material, BPC_PEO. 3. Heat treatment of carbon materials with non oxygen-containing polymers To prepare a comparison group for carbon materials doped with oxygen, a polymer Polyethylene (PE, Sigma-Aldrich) and the basic carbon material BPC with the same structure with PEO but non oxygen polymer were processed together. The process of obtaining the materials including thermal treatment was the same as the previous process. BPC and PE were mixed in a 1:4 ratio (0.1g:0.4g) using a vortex mixer for 5 minutes to ensure proper mixing. The mixture was then placed in an alumina boat and put into a furnace. Argon gas was flowed through the furnace, and the temperature was raised to 500°C at a rate of 5℃/min. When the temperature reached 500°C, it was maintained for 3 hours before being lowered to room temperature to obtain the material BPC_PE, where BPC and PE were co-processed. The obtained material underwent a cleaning process and drying process as follows: it was placed in a 5M HCl solution and stirred at 80 °C for 30 minutes before being filtered once. Then, it was stirred in distilled water at 80 °C for 30 minutes and filtered twice. Finally, to neutralize the carbon material, the solution was converted to an ethanol solution and the same process was repeated once. After washing, the material was dried overnight at 80 °C to obtain the final carbon material, BPC_PE, which was subjected to additional heat treatment. 4. Electrochemical experiment The catalytic ability of the materials in producing hydrogen peroxide was measured using Rotating Ring Disk Electrode (RRDE) in a three-electrode cell. Ag/AgCl electrode was used as the reference electrode, and Pt coil electrode was used as the counter electrode and RRDE electrode. Solution consisting of 1 ml ethanol, 0.1 ml 5 wt% Nafion, and 4 mg catalyst was sonicated for 1 hour to disperse the catalyst well, and then 5 ul was dropped to load the catalyst. The electrode with the solution was rotated at 600 rpm for 30 minutes to dry and fix the catalyst on the electrode. LSV(Linear Sweep Voltammetry) measurements were then conducted underusing KOH 0.1M and Na2SO4 0.1M solutions as an electrolyte at a scan rate of 10 mV/s to test the performance of the catalyst with rotating 1600rpm. The actual current resulting from oxygen reduction was calculated as the difference between measurements taken in an argon-saturated solution initially and an oxygen-saturated solution subsequently.', '2025-02-14 10:44:00'),
(2, 23, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about the comma rules. When there is a list that contains two or more elements, we should use commas to separate them. Also I learned adjectives and adverbs. Subjects or objects can be described by adjectives and verbs can be described by adverbs.', 'In our university, KAIST, we are major-free in the first year. When other usual universities select a major before they come to university and keep on trach of it, we choose major in second year. This policy makes a lot of benefits to students and university. First, students can have a extra time to think about their dream. Since the university make a score of students high school work, it''s so important for students that they are afraid of changing their major area in the second or third year of high school. Instead, they choose the major in first grade of school and continuously work on it for three years, only for the college. How could a person make a decision of what to do in whole life, only in a age of 17? In the effect of policy about education in Korea, students don''t have enough time to experience largely, and widely. So ''the first year of college be major free'' can help students to have a time wondering what they will be in future, and experience lots of things as a adult. It could seen as wasting time (for 1 years) to study on their dream and major, but it could also seen as saving the time, because changing a major at the end of college Iwould take a time more than a year. Second, students can take a break after a hard time studying in high school for three years. Even though some students totally made a decision about major before college, it would be not a bad sounds to hear. Many people dream about campous life. Everyone knew that university is a place where we study about deeper knowledge of many things, but having a good time with college friends from the world (or just ofther city) can helpful to students. Not only taking a break, but also meeting much more people than school can improve their wideth and depth of thoughts and creativity. Third, as the time goes, many major areas share a same topic, like AI or argorithum. And if we plus the classes we have to listen like physics or math, their would be no time waste which some people are worried about. This could be the change of the study through years. A lot of time before, there was little subjects to share between different majors. And now, it''s the time we have to change. And last but not least, colleges can also less worry about enrolling student amount of each major. Some majors are more popular then others. Then do we have to change the people amout to enroll, Like hundred in chemistry and fifty in physics? By using this policy, colleges don''t need to think about that kind of enrollment, Students will change their major as they want. College would just have to see is they would study hard in college.', '2025-02-27 11:44:00'),
(3, 23, 'Certainly! Here are some examples of support that governments provide to their citizens: - Healthcare and medical services - Education and training - Financial assistance, such as social security or unemployment benefits - Public infrastructure, such as roads and bridges - Public housing - Environmental services, such as waste management - Emergency and disaster response services It''s important to note that the type of support provided by governments may vary depending on the country and its political system. Nonetheless, these examples can be used as a starting point to illustrate how governments help their citizens.', 'How about claiming some of the services or supports are provided to specific type of people who needs it? Can you try?', 'Governments have a crucial role to play in supporting their citizens, but they face significant challenges in doing so. With limited resources and budget constraints, it is essential that governments prioritize the allocation of resources to those in genuine need. By providing assistance only to those who require it, governments can ensure an efficient use of available resources. Moreover, this approach fosters social equity and reduces poverty, making it a win-win situation for both the government and its citizens. Governments play a vital role in providing assistance to their citizens, particularly those who are most vulnerable and disadvantaged. With finite resources, governments must allocate their budget and workforce effectively, prioritizing support for those in genuine need. For instance, governments may provide financial assistance to the unemployed, public infrastructure to remote or underprivileged regions, or public housing to those who are homeless or at risk of homelessness. By supporting these communities, governments help to reduce social inequality and create a stable and prosperous society for all.', '2025-03-13 10:14:00'),
(4, 23, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', '<essay>As the technology is getting more and more developed, various kinds of individual devices have invented. One of the results is the everyone in class uses some devices. However, some people suggested that using tablets and laptops will make students disatracted during class. Although the side effects exist, using tablet/laptop has so many advantages. The following reasons are the examples of the advantages. The first advantage is that students can use digital abilities needed for the class. Many professors make “lecture notes” for students and students need to use them right in class. Taking notes on laptops and tablets improves students’ abilities to learn new things and memorizing them. Except “lecture notes”, some classes such as programming, design, and composing, need students to use digital devices during class. Therefore using tablets and laptops makes students more effective in class. For the second reason, students can reduce their burdon during campus life. Digital devices can replace heavy textbooks, various types of notes, pencils and pen, and memo sheets. All equipments for studying are contained in a single tablet. Moreover, a single tablet can carry more functions like recording the sound from lectures, and submitting assignments on online. It means that students can use more equipments and functions that comes from smaller and lighter stuffs. Therefore tablets and laptops improves on each student’s campus life. For the third reason, the professors and TA(Teaching assistants)s can also perform effective work styles. By using electronic devices in class, they can get assignments online, automatically check grades and attendences, and provide lecture easily. A lot number of professors are already using digital systems during class. Therefore, using tablets and laptops in class can make not only students, but also professors and Tas comfortable. Although many advantages, there always exist some people using tablets and laptops in not appropriate ways. However the problem should be solved by the culture and self managing among students, not by making policies not allowing digital devices. Thus, Tablets and laptops should be used in class by above advantages.</essay> please find grammer errors in my essey', 'As technology continues to develope, various types of individual devices have been invented. One of the results is the everyone in class uses some devices. However, some people suggested that using tablets and laptops will make students distracted during class. Although the side effects exist, using tablet/laptop has so many advantages. The following reasons are examples of the advantages. The first advantage is that students can use digital abilities needed for the class. Many professors make “lecture notes” for students and students need to use them right in class. Taking notes on laptops and tablets improves students’ abilities to learn new things and memorize them. In addition to lecture notes, students in classes like programming, design, and composing, need to use digital devices during class. Therefore using tablets and laptops makes students more effective in class. For the second reason, students can reduce their burden during campus life. Digital devices can replace heavy textbooks, various types of notes, pencils and pen, and memo sheets. All equipments for studying are contained in a single tablet. Moreover, a single tablet can perform a range of functions like recording lectures and submitting assignments online. It means that students can use more equipments and functions that comes from smaller and lighter stuffs. Therefore tablets and laptops improves on each student’s campus life. For the third reason, the professors and TA(Teaching assistants)s can also perform effective work styles. By using electronic devices in class, they can recieve assignments online, automatically check grades and attendences, and present lecture more effectively. A lot number of professors are already using digital systems during class. Therefore, using tablets and laptops in class can make not only students, but also professors and Tas comfortable. Although there are many advantages, there are always some people who use tablets and laptops inappropriately. However the problem should be solved by the culture and self managing among students, not by making policies not allowing digital devices. Thus, Tablets and laptops should be used in class by above advantages.', '2025-03-20 14:44:00'),
(5, 23, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I wnat to find some reason source that can improve my opinion in internet.', 'Advantages of Using Tablets in Class Using tablets in class has become increasingly popular among students due to their numerous advantages. Firstly, using tablets can decrease the weight of your bag. If you don''t use a tablet, you would have to bring many textbooks and notes in your bag, which can be quite heavy and make you tired. However, if you use a tablet, you can save all textbook files on the tablet and take notes by using it, allowing you to travel lighter. Secondly, students can use the internet comfortably on a tablet. If you encounter something you don''t understand in class, a tablet''s internet capabilities allow you to figure it out immediately. Additionally, tablets provide access to online resources like digital versions of academic journals, research papers, and videos, which provide a wider range of resources to draw from, enhancing your understanding of the subject matter. Thirdly, using a tablet can help students study more efficiently. With interactive textbooks and educational apps, tablets provide a more immersive and interactive way of learning. Tablets also offer personalized learning opportunities by adapting their lessons and activities to the individual student''s learning style and ability level. This enables students to focus on their specific areas of weakness and improve their comprehension and retention of material. In summary, these are several reasons why using tablets in class can benefit students. By having access to a wealth of learning resources, the ability to engage with interactive learning tools, and the opportunity to receive personalized instruction, students can achieve better outcomes in their academic pursuits.', '2025-04-03 16:44:00'),
(1, 24, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about essay organization. There are formal langauge, tone, funnel introduction, and conclusion. Funnel introduction includes hook, narrow topic down, and thesis statement. Conclusion includes restating and final thoughts. Also we learned some transitions to use in essay.', 'In our university, KAIST, we are major-free in the first year. Unlike other universities, where students select their majors before starting college and continue to study it, we choose a major in the second year. This policy has several benefits for both students and university. The reason for this is because of various causes and effects. Firstly, being major-free in the first year allows students to have extra time to make decisions about their future. High school grades are very important when it comes to selecting majors, which puts a lot of pressure on students. Often, students choose their major solely based on their high school performance, which might not be a reliable indicator of interests or strengths. Since choosing a major at the early age of 17 is difficult, it is important to provide students with enough time to explore their options. Therefore, being major-free in the first year can provide students with time to experience different things as adults and have time to think about their dreams. This can help prevent students from feeling rushed to make such important decisions. Secondly, students can benefit from a break after a demanding high school experience that had lasted for three years. Despite having already decided on their major, students can benefit from taking time to meet people from all over the world and spend time with new friends. This time can help students to learn new perspectives, increase creativity, and improve their worldview. So, students can benefit by taking a break and having the freedom to explore college life without the constraints of a specific major. Furthermore, over time, many subjects within different majors have started overlapping, especially with the rise of artificial intelligence. As a result, giving students the opportunity to explore various subjects can improve their understanding of the shared topics and, in turn, improve their perspective on their major. Since many majors share similar course requirements like mathematics and physics, there would be no concern about wasting time on unrelated courses. Thus, students can benefit from a well-rounded education. Lastly, colleges can worry less about enrolling students for different majors, as not all majors are equally popular. By allowing students to change their major as they wish, colleges do not have to worry about involuntary enrolment in less popular majors or over-enrolling in popular ones. Instead, they can focus solely on ensuring that enrolled students are studying and meeting their academic obligations. As a result, the university can benefit from a more flexible system that can adapt to the needs of students without the burden of bureaucratic obstacles. Overall, being major-free in the first year of university can provide many benefits for both students and universities. Through the use of cause and effect paragraphs, we can better understand how this policy can benefit society as a whole.', '2025-02-14 10:48:00'),
(2, 24, 'Yes, that''s a good point. However, when you use an example that doesn''t fit neatly into your point, it can make your argument feel less clear or less convincing. Instead of using the pollution example, you could use a different example that is more clearly about someone in need of help, and that fits more closely with your argument that everyone needs help. This will help to make your argument more persuasive and concrete. For example, you could talk about people who are struggling with health problems, or people who have lost their jobs and are struggling financially.', 'Can you give me some examples that I can put in my grounds?', 'Many people wondered about how the government uses their taxes. There were many news about the usage of taxes for people that needed help like old people who live alone or orphans. However, news also told that taxes are used in ways that people think they don’t need, like rich people. Then, the taxes are used only for those most in need? I think it is not a good idea. I want to say three reasons for why the government should help all of its citizens. First, everyone needs help. Regardless of their background, people need help for many reasons. For example, those who are rich because of their restaurant. But if they have a problem about the pollution that is made by the building right next to restaurant, they can’t do anything regardless of their money. In this situation, the government has to help them. Like this, regardless of their background, everyone needs help in their situation. Also, during the COVID-19 pandemic, many small business owners struggled to keep their businesses afloat, regardless of their financial status, highlighting the need for government support to protect businesses and the economy. Second, the government and the country are made by the citizens. At Korean law, it says ‘the right of Korea lies with the citizens, and all the power comes from the citizens.’ Citizens contribute to make a government, and they should be the most important thing for the government. So, regardless of their background, the government has to protect all citizens. Also, in the world, The Universal Declaration of Human Rights states that "all human beings are born free and equal in dignity and rights," highlighting the importance of protecting the rights and welfare of all citizens. Finally, taxes are gained by all the citizens. Moreover, rich people pay more taxes. Of course, I think it''s fair and common sense that rich people pay more taxes. But the fact is that all citizens pay taxes. If they pay it but there''s no help, they will be confused about why they pay taxes. So, the government should help all people that pay taxes. To sum up, all citizen need help, and they pay taxes for government. And also, they are the most important thing for the government. I think it is fair that most taxes are used for people in need. But their system should be needed so that all citizens can get help.', '2025-02-27 11:48:00'),
(3, 24, 'Certainly, I''d be happy to review your writing and provide some feedback on its grammar. Please share it with me.', 'Summary: Generating natural Chitchat dialogues requires high-level decisions that neural language models (NLM) struggle to learn. Therefore, control; the ability to specify desired attributes of the text at test time, is important to fix errors. This paper investigated how controlling four low-level attributes (repetition, specificity, response-relatedness, question-asking) of generated text, changes human judgment on eight conversational quality aspects (avoiding repetition, interestingness, making sense, fluency, listening, inquisitiveness, humanness, engagingness). The paper used two methods Conditional Training (CT) and Weighted Decoding (WD) to control the four low-level attributes and found that while controlling question-asking, repetition had positive effects on human judgment aspects, increasing specificity decreased making sense and fluency while increasing response-relatedness decreased making sense, fluency, humanness, and engagingness. Therefore, though controlling can increase human engagement, we must have a careful balance between the four low-level attributes. Evaluation: The authors did a great job of exploring how low-level attributes affect human judgment factors. Their finding that humanness and engagingness can be very different was very interesting. Also, supplementary materials were very helpful in understanding the specific experimental procedures. However, how they came up with the four low-level attributes and why they evaluated the 8 human judgments is unclear which is a critical part of this study. For example, groundedness or trustworthiness is an important factor. Also, there is a limit that human evaluation is very subjective. Factors like interestingness are hard to measure and inherently dependent on each person.', 'Summary: Generating natural Chitchat dialogues requires high-level decisions that neural language models (NLM) struggle to learn. Therefore, control; the ability to specify desired attributes of the text at test time, is important to fix errors. This paper investigated how controlling four low-level attributes (repetition, specificity, response-relatedness, question-asking) of generated text, changes human judgment on eight conversational quality aspects (avoiding repetition, interestingness, making sense, fluency, listening, inquisitiveness, humanness, engagingness). The paper used two methods Conditional Training (CT) and Weighted Decoding (WD) to control the four low-level attributes and found that while controlling question-asking, repetition had positive effects on human judgment aspects, increasing specificity decreased making sense and fluency while increasing response-relatedness decreased making sense, fluency, humanness, and engagingness. Therefore, though controlling can increase human engagement, we must have a careful balance between the four low-level attributes. Evaluation: The authors did a great job of exploring how low-level attributes affect human judgment factors. Their finding that humanness and engagingness can be very different was very interesting. Also, supplementary materials were very helpful in understanding the specific experimental procedures. However, how they came up with the four low-level attributes and why they evaluated the 8 human judgments is unclear which is a critical part of this study. For example, groundedness or trustworthiness is an important factor. Also, there is a limit that human evaluation is very subjective. Factors like interestingness are hard to measure and inherently dependent on each person.', '2025-03-13 10:18:00'),
(4, 24, 'Sure, I would be happy to take a look at your paragraph and give you feedback on it. Please feel free to attach it here.', '<para>There are still many research questions involving the structure of modular groups with coefficients in other base rings that are not pursued in this paper. For instance, one may try to explore the structures of modular forms with coefficients in small ring of integers such as $\ZZ[\sqrt{N}]$ or $\ZZ[i]$. The solution to this problem may provide some insights to the structure of modular forms with coefficients in a more general ring of integers. Not only that, results on the structure of modular forms with coefficients in a larger ring of integers can be used to describe congruence relations on a larger class of modular forms.</para>', 'There are still many research questions involving the structure of modular groups with coefficients in other base rings that are not pursued in this paper. For instance, one may try to explore the structures of modular forms with coefficients in small ring of integers such as $\ZZ[\sqrt{N}]$ or $\ZZ[i]$. The solution to this problem may provide some insights to the structure of modular forms with coefficients in a more general ring of integers. Not only that, results on the structure of modular forms with coefficients in a larger ring of integers can be used to describe congruence relations on a larger class of modular forms.', '2025-03-20 14:48:00'),
(5, 24, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about writing compare and contrast essay. First, the introductory paragraph should be correctly organized, with the thesis statement at the end. The thesis statement makes it clear what the essay is going to compare. Second, the body paragraphs should use block or point-by-point organization to discuss similarities and differences. If the essay uses block organization, there is a transition sentence or transition paragraph between the two blocks. Finally, the conclusion has to summarize the main points or paraphrase the thesis statement.', 'With the development of the internet, online shopping has become increasingly popular, challenging the traditional offline shopping way. This essay is going to compare and contrast the advantages and disadvantages of online shopping and offline shopping, considering factors such as convenience, variety, interaction, and overall impact on consumers. One of the key advantages of online shopping is convenience and accessibility. With just a few researching, consumers can browse through a vast array of products and make purchases from the comfort of their own homes. Online shopping eliminates the need for physical travel to stores, saving time and effort. Moreover, online shopping allows shoppers to make purchases at any time they want, as they are typically open 24/7. On the other hand, offline shopping provides an immediate shopping. Shoppers can physically examine and try on products before making a purchase, which is not possible with online shopping. Also, offline shopping offers instant gratification, as consumers can immediately take their purchases home. But, in a different sense, offline shopping requires individuals to visit physical stores during their operating hours, which can be restrictive and inconvenient for those with busy schedules. Next, Online shopping offers unparalleled variety and selection. E-commerce platforms provide access to products from all around the world, allowing consumers to explore a wide range of options. Online retailers often have extensive inventories, ensuring that shoppers can find products in various sizes, colors, and styles. Also, consumers can easily compare prices, read reviews, and access detailed product information, empowering them to make informed purchasing decisions. In contrast, offline shopping have limited stock and selection, especially in smaller or specialized stores. But offline shopping also have merits in providing the opportunity for consumers to personally inspect products and assess their quality, something that online shopping lacks. Shoppers can touch, feel, and try on items, ensuring their quality, fit, and suitability. This hands-on experience is particularly valuable for items such as clothes, furniture, or electronics. On the contrary, online shopping relies on product descriptions, image, and sometimes customer reviews, which may not always accurately convey the real-life experience of the product. In addition, interaction and customer service also differ between online and offline shopping. Offline stores provide face-to-face interaction with sales associates who can provide personalized assistance, answer questions, and offer recommendations. This personalized interaction enhances the shopping experience and can help customers make informed purchasing decisions. Offline shopping also provides the opportunity for social interaction, allowing shoppers to engage with friends or family while browsing stores. Online shopping, on the other hand, relies on digital communication channels. Even though customer service is available through online chat or email, the absence of immediate assistance may lead to delays in resolving queries or concerns. Next is about price comparison. Price comparison is an area where both online and offline shopping have their merits. Online retailers often offer competitive prices due to lower overhead costs, and the ability to compare prices across different platforms is a breeze. In comparison, offline shopping can involve bargaining, taking advantage of sales or discounts, and immediate price negotiations, especially in smaller or local stores. Additionally, offline shopping allows shoppers to avoid shipping costs or waiting periods, which can sometimes be associated with online purchases. In terms of the overall impact on consumers, shopping experience and returns differs significantly between online and offline shopping. Online shopping offers a convenient and efficient experience, allowing consumers to quickly find products and compare prices. It has provided opportunities for small business and entrepreneurs to reach a wider market. However, it has led to concerns such as cybersecurity risks, potential frauds, and the loss of in-person social interaction. Also, it lacks the sensor experience that offline shopping provides, such as physically touching and trying on items. Offline shopping, while more traditional, still holds its value in terms of personal engagement, immediate gratification, and the ability to support local businesses. Offline shopping offers an immersive experience, allowing shoppers to engage their senses and assess product quality firsthand. Another aspect to consider is the return process. Online shopping often provides hassle-free return, with easy-to-follow procedures and prepaid shipping labels. In contrast, returning items purchased offline may require visiting the store, waiting in line, and complying with specific return policies. In conclusion, online shopping and offline shopping both have their advantages and disadvantages. Online shopping offers convenience, a extensive variety of products, competitive prices, and the ability to shop anytime anywhere. On the other hand, offline shopping provides the opportunity for sensory engagement, face-to-face interaction between customers and staff, personalized customer service, and immediate gratification. Ultimately, the choice between online shopping and offline shopping depends on individual preferences, the type of product being purchased, and the overall shopping experience desired. As technology continues to advance, the future may see a blending of these two approaches, providing an even more seamless and immersive shopping experience for consumers.', '2025-04-03 16:48:00'),
(1, 25, 'Certainly! Socioeconomically poor people refer to individuals or families who are economically and socially disadvantaged. They often lack education, adequate housing, health care, and other basic resources needed to live a decent quality of life. They may also experience social isolation, discrimination, and stigma due to their socioeconomic status. In short, socioeconomically poor people are those who struggle to meet their basic needs and face significant barriers to social and economic mobility.', 'I thought budget will not be used properly if government overpay for socioeconomical poor people. What else some other reasons might be occured if government assist only for the socioeconomical poor people?', 'Socioeconomically poor people usually lack conditions such as education, health care compare to the most. Caring socioeconomically poor people is natural in ethical view. However, it is quite controversial how much of people should be designated as socioeconomical poor. Although socioeconomically poor people are considered the most vulnerable citizens in our society, I believe government should help all of its citizens to ensure everyone has access to basic necessities and resources. First, the budget that will used was initially for all of us. We all citizens are paying tax, and they shout out many complaints such as ''It is too expensive.'' Even though, it is burden, they pay the tax for mandatory. Using the tax for all citizen is right. For this statement, helping only those most in need looks strange. It seems like the government overprotecting them. Majorities of citizens who are maintaining the country would deeply resent to the government that only helping minorities. Second, the budget have to be used properly for functioning economy. There are many things government should get attention. For instance, monitoring and functioning school like KAIST or helping people who are poored. Then why they assist those things? It is for Country''s power. Students in Kaist will lead science in the world, and structures will show the country''s well. I want to point out that there are many things where budget should be used not only for poors. Helping socioeconomically solely might causes some problems. However, helping them also have their benefits too. For example, government can find out talented man newly. Even so, the decision looks unfair, inefficient and it looks easily be frauded. Conclusion, I think government should provide appropriate welfare to all of the citizens.', '2025-02-14 10:52:00'),
(2, 25, 'Great! It sounds like you have a good understanding of introducing a thesis statement at the beginning and concluding with a final thought. Let''s start with the introduction. You should state your thesis clearly and concisely. A thesis statement acts as a roadmap for your essay, giving your readers a preview of the points you will cover. Can you write your thesis statement for this paper? Once you have that, we can focus on revising the body paragraphs. You have some good points, but we will need to organize them properly and include transitions between paragraphs to make your writing flow smoothly. Finally, we will work on your conclusion by summarizing your main points and ending with a final thought. Let''s get started on revising your essay!', 'Can you revise my essay with the above answer? Here''s my original essay. <essay>In recent years, the use of electronic devices in classrooms has become more prevalent, and there are both advantages and disadvantages to this trend. In terms of advantages, increased student participation and greater usefulness in the classroom are the most notable benefits. On the one hand, the use of tablets and laptops can increase student participation in class activities by providing engaging tools and incorporating online learning platforms. For example, playing Kahoot or Quizlet games about the course material can enhance understanding and retention of key concepts. Similarly, online platforms like Zoom or Google Meets can provide an opportunity for students to engage with professors and peers even if they are not physically present in the classroom. By using tablets and laptops, students can participate in class more actively and experience a more immersive learning environment. On the other hand, some critics argue that a reliance on electronic devices in the classroom can have negative consequences. For instance, it can foster a culture of distraction and undermine students'' ability to focus. Moreover, technology can sometimes fail, leading to disruptions in teaching and learning. In addition, while electronic documents are convenient, they can be easily lost if not properly saved or backed up. Despite these potential disadvantages, the advantages of using electronic devices in the classroom outweigh the disadvantages. In particular, electronic devices enable greater collaboration, productivity, and flexibility among students and professors. By taking advantage of these benefits, students can use their own tablet or laptop computers in class with more ease and productivity.</essay>', 'The prevalence of electronic devices in classrooms has surged in recent years, and while there are advantages and disadvantages to this trend, they can be managed effectively. The most notable benefits include increased student participation and greater usefulness in the classroom. On one hand, the use of tablets and laptops can increase student participation in activities by providing engaging tools and incorporating online learning platforms. For instance, playing Kahoot or Quizlet games enhances understanding and retention of key concepts. Similarly, online platforms like Zoom or Google Meets offer students the opportunity to engage with professors and peers, regardless of their physical location. These technologies allow for more active participation and a more immersive learning environment. On the opposite end, some critics argue that a dependence on electronic devices in the classroom has adverse effects, such as fostering a culture of distraction that undermines students'' ability to focus. Additionally, technology can sometimes fail, leading to disruptions in teaching and learning. Furthermore, while electronic documents are convenient, they can be easily lost if not properly saved or backed up. However, the benefits of using electronic devices in the classroom outweigh the disadvantages. In particular, these devices enable greater collaboration, productivity, and flexibility among students and professors. By taking advantage of these benefits, students can use their own tablet or laptop computers in class with more ease and productivity. In conclusion, while there are some downsides to the use of electronic devices in the classroom, there are many ways to overcome these challenges and maximize the advantages they offer. Ultimately, educators and students should work together to view these devices as a tool to enhance learning, and not as a distraction.', '2025-02-27 11:52:00'),
(3, 25, 'Yes, that''s a good start! You provide more detail and a clearer explanation of your results and the significance of your findings. You show how your study is unique from previous studies by being able to generate both PING and ING states in the same network and indicate how this finding has implications for information encoding. However, you should continue to outline the broader implications of the study and discuss the limitations of your study, as well as open up avenues for future research. Overall, it''s important to make sure that you provide a comprehensive discussion section that puts your results into context and advances the field''s understanding.', 'Thank you for your advice. But my targeting journal is closed to theoretical study, then do I need to wright about implication? Because it''s hard to talk about where this work can be used. I think it''s more related to engineering.', 'In this study, we found two types of synchronized states can be generated with synaptic I-E ratio in excitatory-inhibitory coupled neural network. The first synchronized state (state I) is similar with PING model, and the second synchronized state (state III) is similar with ING model. In the intermediate state (state II), the synchrony level is low. However, two types of oscillator states are emerged in this state. Thus, we showed that PING and ING model can be generated in the same network. In addition, in this state, the information encoding of neural network is maximized. This result implicates that with balanced I-E ratio, the information encoding can be maximized with emerging both PING and ING oscillatory state.', '2025-03-13 10:22:00'),
(4, 25, 'Sure, I can put the replaced words in bold. (Note: Some subtle changes have been made to improve the sentence flow.) As technology continues to develop, various kinds of individual devices have been invented. One of the outcomes is that everyone in class uses some form of technology. However, some suggest that using tablets and laptops can cause distractions during class. Despite the side effects, **the use of** tablet/laptop**s** has many benefits. Below are examples of these advantages. The first benefit is that digital devices allow students to use essential abilities required for their classes. Many professors provide “lecture notes” to students who need to use them during class. Taking notes on devices like laptops and tablets improves students’ learning abilities and enhances their ability to recall new information. Besides “lecture notes,” students in classes like programming, design, and composition need digital devices for effective learning. Therefore, **the** use of tablets and laptops makes students more productive in class. Secondly, digital devices help **reduce** students'' burden during campus life. Devices like tablets can replace heavy textbooks, various types of notes, pencils, pens, and memo sheets. All necessary equipment for studying is contained in a single tablet. Furthermore, a tablet can perform various functions like recording lectures and submitting assignments online. This means students can use more equipment and functions that come from smaller and lighter devices, enhancing their overall campus life. For the third benefit, professors and TAs can execute more efficient work styles. By using electronic devices in class, they can receive assignments online, automatically check grades and attendance, and present lectures more effectively. Most professors are already using digital systems during class. Thus, using tablets and laptops in class can make not **just** students but also professors and TAs comfortable. Although there are numerous advantages, some users may use tablets and laptops inappropriately. However, the problem should be solved by encouraging healthy habits and self-management among students rather than by implementing policies that prohibit digital devices. Thus, tablets and laptops should be used in class based on the advantages mentioned above.', 'As technology continues to develope, various types of individual devices have been invented. One of the results is the everyone in class uses some devices. However, some people suggested that using tablets and laptops will make students distracted during class. Despite the side effects, the use of tablet/laptop has so many advantages. The following reasons are examples of the advantages. The first advantage is that students can use digital abilities needed for the class. Many professors make “lecture notes” for students and students need to use them right in class. Taking notes on laptops and tablets improves students’ abilities to learn new things and memorize them. In addition to lecture notes, students in classes like programming, design, and composing, need to use digital devices during class. Therefore the use of tablets and laptops makes students more effective in class. Secondly, digital devices help reduce students'' burden during campus life. The devices can replace heavy textbooks, various types of notes, pencils and pen, and memo sheets. All equipments for studying are contained in a single tablet. Moreover, a single tablet can perform a range of functions like recording lectures and submitting assignments online. It means that students can use more equipments and functions that comes from smaller and lighter stuffs. Therefore tablets and laptops improves on each student’s campus life. For the third benefit, the professors and TA(Teaching assistants)s can also perform effective work styles. By using electronic devices in class, they can recieve assignments online, automatically check grades and attendences, and present lecture more effectively. A lot number of professors are already using digital systems during class. Therefore, using tablets and laptops in class can make not just students, but also professors and TAs comfortable. Although there are many advantages, there are always some people who use tablets and laptops inappropriately. However the problem should be solved by the culture and self managing among students, not by making policies not allowing digital devices. Thus, Tablets and laptops should be used in class by above advantages. is there any change of the contents in the writing needed?', 'As technology continues to develop, various types of individual devices have been invented. One of the results is that everyone in class tends to use some form of technology. However, some argue that using tablets and laptops can be distracting. Despite the potential side effects, the use of tablets/laptops has many advantages, which are highlighted below. The first benefit is that digital devices allow students to use the necessary digital abilities required for their classes. Many professors provide “lecture notes” to students, which they need to access during class time. Taking notes on laptops and tablets improves students’ learning and memorization abilities. Additionally, subjects such as programming, design, and composition often require the use of digital devices during class. Therefore, using tablets and laptops increases students'' productivity and engagement during class. Secondly, digital devices can help reduce the burden on students during campus life. Devices like tablets can replace bulky textbooks, various types of notes, pens/pencils, and memo sheets. All necessary equipment for studying is contained in a single portable device. Furthermore, students can perform various functions on a tablet, such as recording lectures and submitting assignments online, making studying more convenient and efficient. The third benefit is that professors and TAs can execute more efficient work styles by incorporating electronic devices into their classes. By using such devices, teachers can receive assignments online, automatically check grades and attendance, and present lectures more effectively. Many professors are already adopting digital systems in their classes. Thus, using tablets and laptops in class can make not just students but also professors and TAs comfortable and efficient. Although there are numerous advantages, some users may use tablets and laptops inappropriately. However, such issues can be tackled by encouraging healthy habits and self-discipline among students, rather than implementing policies that prohibit the use of digital devices. Therefore, tablets and laptops should be allowed in class, given the advantages mentioned above.', '2025-03-20 14:52:00'),
(5, 25, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about the comma rules. When there is a list that contains two or more elements, we should use commas to separate them.', 'Most of students use their electronic devices such as tablet or laptop in class. They use electronic devices because of advantages while using it in class. First, using electric devices could make our bag less heavier than before. When we use paper book or paper lecture note, the book is really thick and if we collect lecture note prints for several times then it makes our bag more heavier than before. However, when we use electronic devices, we could use pdf for book and write down lecture note on electronic note. Therefore even though we use a lot of books and lecture notes, the weight to our bag has only our electronic devices weight. Next, most of class use internet nowadays. As internet''s effect became larger and larger to our life, the use of internet became larger. We could take quiz on internet, or watch lecture on internet etc. Therefore, it makes student must use electronic devices while studying. Now few of class use zoom to make untact lecture and use google form to take quiz. Because of it, using electronic devices became necessary in class. In conclusion, there are two advantages that students use electronic devices in class. First, It makes student''s bag much lighter than before. Second, electronic devices could help to follow class using internet.', '2025-04-03 16:52:00'),
(1, 26, 'Yes, you are absolutely right that typing errors can have a negative impact on the reader''s understanding of the text. To correct a typing error, you can simply go back to the sentence where the error occurred and edit or replace the erroneous word or phrase. Using proofreading tools such as grammar and spell checkers can also help you to identify and correct any typing errors that you may have missed.', 'Also, at the review stage after you have finished writing, you should check if you have written the basics correctly, such as grammatical errors and the use of commas, so that the meaning of the sentence is conveyed well.', 'The Wisconsin Card Sorting Test (WCST) is a neuropsychological test of set-shifting, which is the capability to show flexibility when exposed to changes in reinforcement. In the WCST (Berg, 1948), test subjects have to correctly identify, implement, and remember sorting rules. The order of the test is as follows. Firstly, participants sorted cards according to color, shape, or number stimuli depicted on the card. Sorting the cards by color was initially verbally reinforced. After a participant responded correctly for 10 consecutive cards in that color category, the participant continued sorting by form and numbers without verbal stimuli or reinforcement. Subsequently, the ratio of correct responses to errors was computed, and the numbers of trials, errors was computed, and the numbers of trials, errors, perseverative responses, and perseverative errors were analyzed.', '2025-02-14 10:56:00'),
(2, 26, 'Great! Let''s apply what you''ve learned to your essay. Can you provide me with a copy of your essay, please? Also, let''s focus on one paragraph to make it more manageable. Which paragraph would you like to work on?', '<essay> I oppose women''s enlistment in the army. Physical conditions are not equal between a woman and a man. The physical difference between a woman and a man in their 20s is quite large. As a result, it is not easy to serve with the same level of training. In addition, the military is a closed society, and there is a possibility of crime in it. The military is busy hiding not only sex crimes but also incidents and accidents. If an accident occurs, if a soldier reports it to his or her superiors, they are in a hurry to cover up for fear of problems in their personnel review. In fact, there is data from the Minisstry of National Defense that only 32.7% reported sex crimes within the military. In other words, only 3 out of 10 people report it. 44% of victims who did not report sex crimes saids, "No action was likely to be taken." In other words, soldiers do not trust the military''s measures and do not even expected them. Unlike now situation, if two genders have to live in the military, there might be many problems that comes from the difference of two genders in the closed military society. As a result, the crime can be increased. Moreover, joining women to the military cannot resolve gender inequality. There are too many conditions that can cause other discriminatory perceptions even if a woman joins the military, such as facilities, hair length, and degree of training. There will be a shortage of women''s toilets in the military now, and it will take a long time to solve problems related to facilities. Therefore, it is difficult to judge that women''s enlistment in the army provides a fundamental solution. In a short, there is a risk of increased crime within women when they are required to join a closed army. Also, the current facilities are not suitable for women to join the army, and it will take a long time to solve them. In addition, there are many other conditions to consider, such as physical differences, the degree of training, and the length of the hair. For this reason, I oppose women''s mandatory military enlistment. Of course, it is a pity that men go to the military to support their youth in their young and precious days in their 20s. I think women should live with more respect for men and a heart that contributes to the country.</essay>', 'I object to women enlisting in the army because of the physical difference between men and women. Such differences are significant, with the gap in average muscle mass between them is almost 20%. As a result, it can be challenging to provide the same level of training for both genders. In addition, the military is a closed society that has beeon known to have an issue with crime, including sex crimes. The military is busy hiding not only sex crimes but also incidents and accidents. If an accident occurs, if a soldier reports it to his or her superiors, they are in a hurry to cover up for fear of problems in their personnel review. For instance, the Ministry of National Defense found that only 32.7% of sex crimes within the military are reported, with the majority of victims not expecting any action to be taken. In other words, only 3 out of 10 people report it. 44% of victims who did not report sex crimes saids, "No action was likely to be taken." In other words, soldiers do not trust the military''s measures and do not even expected them. Unlike now situation, if two genders have to live in the military, there might be many problems that comes from the difference of two genders in the closed military society. As a result, the crime can be increased. Moreover, joining women to the military cannot resolve gender inequality. There are too many conditions that can cause other discriminatory perceptions even if a woman joins the military, such as facilities, hair length, and degree of training. There will be a shortage of women''s toilets in the military now, and it will take a long time to solve problems related to facilities. Therefore, it is difficult to judge that women''s enlistment in the army provides a fundamental solution. In a short, there is a risk of increased crime within women when they are required to join a closed army. Also, the current facilities are not suitable for women to join the army, and it will take a long time to solve them. In addition, there are many other conditions to consider, such as physical differences, the degree of training, and the length of the hair. For this reason, I oppose women''s mandatory military enlistment. Of course, it is a pity that men go to the military to support their youth in their young and precious days in their 20s. I think women should live with more respect for men and a heart that contributes to the country.', '2025-02-27 11:56:00'),
(3, 26, 'Overall, the paragraph is very well-written and clearly conveys your objectives for your project. One suggestion for improvement is that you might offer more detail about how you plan to standardize the evaluation and comparison of debiasing methods. You could also consider adding some specific examples of biases that are common in contextual word embeddings or in NLP more broadly. Additionally, you might consider rearranging the sentence structure in a few places to create stronger flow between ideas. Are there any specific areas you would like me to review or help with in more detail?', 'can you please help me write a draft with the changes that you just suggested?', 'Contextual word embeddings have become a critical component in NLP due to their ability to capture important information based on the surrounding text. They are particularly useful for tasks such as language modeling, named entity recognition, and sentiment analysis. However, these embeddings also have the potential to encode various biases, such as those related to gender, age, and ethnicity. The issue of debiasing contextual word embeddings has thus become a critical topic in the field. We aim to survey different debiasing methods that have been proposed, such as retraining models on more diverse data, incorporating specific constraints into the training process, and using post-processing techniques to remove biases. While several such techniques have been proposed, there remains a lack of standardization in evaluating and comparing their effectiveness. Our project aims to propose a standardized approach for evaluating and comparing the effectiveness of these methods. This is essential to ensure more equitable and inclusive language models. By evaluating the strengths and weaknesses of these methods, we hope to develop a more comprehensive understanding of how these methods work and identify the most effective approach for debiasing contextual word embeddings. Our project also aims to investigate common biases that are present in contextual word embeddings and NLP models more broadly', '2025-03-13 10:26:00'),
(4, 26, 'Sure, I can make the requested changes: Introduction: <essay>Rhythm games are music-themed video games that challenge players to perform a series of pre-established actions to a specific rhythm. However, creating new beatmaps by hand can be challenging, time-consuming and requires significant attention to detail, which reduces the total number of songs a game can have. To address this, we propose the development of a deep learning algorithm that can automatically generate high-quality, fun beatmaps of various types and difficulty levels for any song. By doing so, we aim to achieve four main contributions: First, we aim to achieve better results than previous works in terms of beatmap quality by tokenizing the data in a MIDI-like fashion and conditioning the transformer on various features, such as the difficulty level, genre, etc. Second, we will define a model or a set of guidelines to evaluate beatmap quality more objectively, at least for a certain subset of beatmaps, since chart evaluation is largely subjective and there are no universal guidelines to follow. Third, we will generalize the algorithm’s application field from one game to many since many rhythm games have different ways of creating beatmaps. We will do this by, for instance, applying weight sharing techniques to the model when training it on different datasets. Lastly, we will find valuable training data for music annotation purposes which can, in turn, help in the development of new music-related tools and models going forward. By the end of this study, we hope to demonstrate that it is possible to automate the creation of beatmaps, which can significantly reduce the workload of developers and players alike.</essay>', '마지막 단락이 잘못되었습니다. it is already demonstrated, but we want to improve', 'Rhythm games are music-themed videogames in which players perform pre-established actions that follow a certain rhythm. A level of a rhythm game, called "beatmap" or "chart", is therefore a pattern of actions mapped on a sequence of musical beats that reflects the features of a song. Since the beatmaps are usually handcrafted, rhythm games come with a limited number of available songs, and the addition process takes a long time. Moreover, while many players want to try different charts for the same song when they master a pattern, most games don''t give this opportunity. To make up for the lack of their favorite songs, players use editors to manually create and share their own maps, but this task is very time-consuming and repetitive, and the alignment of beats and actions requires great attention to detail. The aim of this research is to automatically generate a high-quality, fun beatmap of the specified type and difficulty for any song using a deep learning algorithm, more specifically a transformer architecture. As chart evaluation is largely subjective, and there are no universal guidelines to follow, it is also necessary to define a set of rules to evaluate quality, while generalizing the algorithm''s application field from one game to many. - Achieve better results than the previous works, in terms of beatmap quality. - Define a model or a set of guidelines to evaluate beatmap quality more objectively, at least for a certain subset of beatmaps. - Generalize the algorithm’s application field from one game to many. - Find valuable training data for music annotation purposes.', '2025-03-20 14:56:00'),
(5, 26, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about run-on error: can''t join two sentences without punctuation and comma splice : can''t join two sentences with a comma. Also, I learned about coordinating conjunctions, too.', 'At least, in Korea, we have been wearing school uniforms at middle school and high school from 1950s. But lots of people saying that "school uniform have to be vanished". Also, I am the one who think that school uniform is not must-needed item at school. There are some reasons why school uniforms are made. The first reason is to make students feel they''re belong to the very group. About 90 years ago, Japan invaded Korea and tried to control Korean students not to use Korean language, not to learn Korean history, and so on. Japanese people tried to make all the people wear same clothes to feel they''re a part of the Japanese students, finally they started to wear school uniforms. The second reason is to control students easily. As a result of the research, when all the people in group are wearing same clothes, each person pretends to behave as the group members behave. By the same way, when all the students in school are wearing same clothes, they pretend to behave together or similarly. In this situation, teachers are easy to control them, so that it is efficient to the group which the number of students are a lot. But as time goes by, the situation of the school is changing continuously. The number of students is decreasing, teachers pretend to deliver their knowledge to each students, not overall students in class. What I want to say is there is no other reason to control students strictly and make them feel they''re members of the class. Also, school uniform is not designed to move freely, a lot of students are stressed out of wearing school uniforms. In conclusion, by circumstances of the school changes, school uniform must not be required for students.', '2025-04-03 16:56:00'),
(1, 27, 'That''s a great question. Let me take a look at your draft to see if there are ways we can address these common problems. Based on what we discussed in class, here are some suggestions for revising your draft: 1. Make sure all of the essential components of the results section are present, including the purpose of the experiment, the experimental approach, and the results themselves. If any of these are missing, make sure to include them. 2. Remove any irrelevant or peripheral information that doesn''t directly relate to your findings. Stick to the main points and avoid going off on tangents. 3. Be sure to include enough details to support your findings, but don''t include excessive experimental details that are not relevant or important to your results. If you find yourself providing too much detail, consider which details are essential and which can be shortened or removed. 4. Avoid making comparisons, speculations, or conclusions beyond what the results can support. Stick to what you have found and be clear about what your results do and do not imply. I hope this helps you revise your draft and avoid these common problems in your results section. Do you have any questions or further concerns I can help you with?', 'How can you revise the three paragraphs<essay> " To explore the forces behind the strong tendency of husbands to decrease their share of housework, and the low tendency to increase their share of housework in the course of marriage, we looked at the finds from the multivariate event-history models. We first explored the role of economic resources in changing couple’s division of housework in the course of marriage (Table 1). We investigate the impact of the spouse’s relative economic resources on the likelihood of dividing housework either more equally or less equally in the course of marriage. We find that husbands who work a similar number of hours (Husband = Wife), or lower number of hours (Husband < Wife) than their wives, are less likely to decrease their share in household labor, compared to husbands who work longer hours than their wives (Husband > Wife). Equal earning levels between the spouses also seem to reduce the likelihood for husbands to decrease their share of housework in the course of marriage (model 3b). For couples with an “atypical” female provider earnings ratio (Husband < Wife) the effect is not significant, however. It appears that a winning margin in economic resources does more for the husband than for the wife when housework is redistributed. We also looked at the effects of family formation on the gender division of household tasks to assess how shifts in economic resources play in this context (Table 2). We found a pronounced and significant effect for both directions of change. During the first year after childbirth, fathers seem to be about twice as likely to decrease their contribution to housework. In the same period, fathers’ likelihood to increase their share in housework is reduced by almost 50 percent, compared to childless men. This push towards a more traditional division of housework seems to come to a halt when the youngest child reaches age two. We found no indication, however, that parents readjust back to a more egalitarian division of housework when kids grow older and mothers return to their previous jobs. The time-varying economic indicators (models 2ab and 3ab) do not seem to explain these processes at all. Here, we need to be cautious not to interpret lack of significance in the economic indicators as lack of relevance, especially since the share of parents in the “non-traditional” resource categories is low. The number of mothers out-earning or working longer hours than their husbands is small in this sample, and the share of continuously working mothers is low. "</essay> in terms of removal of the four common problems?', 'To explore the forces behind the strong tendency of husbands to decrease their share of housework, and the low tendency to increase their share of housework in the course of marriage, we looked at the finds from the multivariate event-history models. We first explored the role of economic resources in changing couple’s division of housework in the course of marriage (Table 1). We investigate the impact of the spouse’s relative economic resources on the likelihood of dividing housework either more equally or less equally in the course of marriage. We find that husbands who work a similar number of hours (Husband = Wife), or lower number of hours (Husband < Wife) than their wives, are less likely to decrease their share in household labor, compared to husbands who work longer hours than their wives (Husband > Wife). Equal earning levels between the spouses also seem to reduce the likelihood for husbands to decrease their share of housework in the course of marriage (model 3b). For couples with an “atypical” female provider earnings ratio (Husband < Wife) the effect is not significant, however. It appears that a winning margin in economic resources does more for the husband than for the wife when housework is redistributed. We also looked at the effects of family formation on the gender division of household tasks to assess how shifts in economic resources play in this context (Table 2). We found a pronounced and significant effect for both directions of change. During the first year after childbirth, fathers seem to be about twice as likely to decrease their contribution to housework. In the same period, fathers’ likelihood to increase their share in housework is reduced by almost 50 percent, compared to childless men. This push towards a more traditional division of housework seems to come to a halt when the youngest child reaches age two. We found no indication, however, that parents readjust back to a more egalitarian division of housework when kids grow older and mothers return to their previous jobs. The time-varying economic indicators (models 2ab and 3ab) do not seem to explain these processes at all. Here, we need to be cautious not to interpret lack of significance in the economic indicators as lack of relevance, especially since the share of parents in the “non-traditional” resource categories is low. The number of mothers out-earning or working longer hours than their husbands is small in this sample, and the share of continuously working mothers is low.', '2025-02-14 11:00:00'),
(2, 27, 'Okay, how about this then: <sent>"Open domain question answering is an important area of research as it enables computers to understand and respond to natural language queries, facilitating more natural and efficient communication between humans and machines."</sent>', 'This feels more like the starting sentences for the introduction section, can you write it so that it''s suitable for the methodology scetion?', 'The field of open domain question answering has seen significant advancements in recent years, with the development of innovative approaches to tackling the challenging task of answering questions posed in natural language. In this review paper, we will focus on three key pipelines in open domain question answering: retrieve-read, retriever-generate, and generate-read. We will discuss the different methodologies used in each pipeline, their strengths and limitations, and promising directions for future research. Advancements in open domain question answering have the potential to revolutionize human-computer interaction and improve many aspects of our lives, from education to healthcare to entertainment', '2025-02-27 12:00:00'),
(3, 27, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'The below is my outline for my essay. I would like to get help writing the conclusion paragraph. <essay>Governments have a crucial role in the welfare of its citizens. First, providing assistance to all citizens can be inefficient and ineffective. Second, providing aid to those in need can help reduce inequality and improve social mobility. Third, focusing on those in need can help the government build trust and promote social cohesion.</essay>', 'Governments have a crucial role in the welfare of its citizens. First, providing assistance to all citizens can be inefficient and ineffective. Second, providing aid to those in need can help reduce inequality and improve social mobility. Third, focusing on those in need can help the government build trust and promote social cohesion. =================================================== responses =================================================== 1. Welfare programs - Governments often provide welfare programs such as food stamps, unemployment benefits, and housing assistance to low-income families and individuals who need financial assistance. These programs are designed to help those in need, and eligibility is often determined by income level and other factors that indicate economic hardship. 2. Education and training programs - Governments also offer education and training programs to help individuals gain the skills and knowledge needed to secure better-paying jobs and improve their economic prospects. These programs might include vocational training, adult education classes, and job placement services. 3. Healthcare - Access to healthcare is essential for everyone, but low-income families and individuals may face significant barriers to receiving quality care. Some governments provide healthcare options at little to no cost for those who cannot afford traditional healthcare plans. 4. Housing assistance - Governments can offer housing assistance to those who cannot afford safe and adequate housing. This assistance might take the form of rental vouchers, affordable housing developments, or subsidized mortgage programs. In all these programs, the primary focus is on helping those who are in need of assistance. By prioritizing those who require the most help, governments can ensure that resources are directed towards those who need them most and make the most impact on their well-being. ================================================ Body1 1. Limited government resources prevent the state from providing comprehensive assistance to every individual in need. 2. Universal assistance programs can benefit those who do not actually require financial assistance. 3. Providing assistance without proper scrutiny and targeted aid can lead to beneficiary fraud and abuse of resources. 4. Providing the same aid to all individuals can ignore specific circumstance and needs of each person. ================================================ How to write the conclusino paragraph 1. Start by summarizing your main points. You can say something like, "In conclusion, we have seen that governments play a crucial role in the welfare of their citizens by providing assistance to those in need, reducing inequality and improving social mobility, and promoting social cohesion." 2. Next, restate your thesis statement in a slightly different way. For example, you could say, "It is clear that governments have a responsibility to ensure the well-being of their citizens, and the strategies we have discussed today are just a few ways in which they can fulfill that duty." 3. Finally, end with a call to action or a thought-provoking statement. You could say something like, "As we move forward, it is important for us to remember the role that governments can play in creating a more just and equitable society. By holding our leaders accountable and advocating for policies that prioritize the needs of all citizens, we can work towards a brighter future for ourselves and future generations."', '2025-03-13 10:30:00'),
(4, 27, 'Yes, you have certainly grasped the core components of a well-written methodology section. A good methodology section must be informative, clear, and concise. You have pointed out that the methodology must carefully describe the selection process of sources and justification for those choices. It should also be well-written using proper language and grammar structure so that the information is easily understandable. Additionally, the methodology section should include the necessary details of the methods used to conduct the study. You did a great job summarizing what you learned in the class.', 'Please review my paper for any other things like clarification, grammar mistakes, etc.', 'In order to use intermediate representation, two questions need to be answered: how to use it with feature output extracted from the backbone and how much it involves training the classifier. The following subsections describe two auxiliary branches that address the above requirements. 2.1 Representation Summarization (RS) Vision models learn to summarize input into a dense representation with downsampling operation. More specifically, linearly embedded token [24] or feature map [18, 14] shrinks with downsampling operation as channel size C increases. In order for the intermediate representation to be dense and informative enough, we adapt the perspective from Hu et al. [15], which views a feature map as a collective of local descriptors whose summarized statistics express input. Thus, the Representation Summarization (RS) module is composed of 2d pooling to reduce channel-wise statistics and MLP to learn inter-dependencies between channels. The representation transformed by the MLP layer is activated by sigmoid throughout all experiments, but any other activation function can be applied. The transformed representation is denoted by zˆl = MLP(Pool2d(zl)). (2) Note. For patch representation in works such as [24], the spatial dimension is already mixed in the patch merging step. Therefore, we directly flatten the representation and apply pooling 1d. zˆl = Pool1d(z ′ l )) (3) where z ′ l denotes flattened zl . 2.2 Representation Mixup (RM) Previous works either use representation extracted from Yim et al. [36] or use weights from layers of pre-trained models by simple averaging [34] or partial selection algorithm [10]. Along the line of this belief, intermediate representation can act as hints for capturing hard false negative samples with simple aggregation methods such as weighted sum or concatenation. The most straightforward method is to mix them in proper portion. We are inspired by several works on data augmentation using interpolation for mixing up in input space or feature space for better representation learning [39, 31]. An interpolation of hidden representations zi , zk with respect to zi is expressed as z ′ = zi + α(zk − zi) (4) where α denotes the scaling factor. Given pre-trained backbone f, newly initialized linear classifier g, and input image x, the final output score s is s = g ◦ f(x). The final output representation from the pre-trained backbone is f(x) = zL. The pre-trained backbone can be expressed as two parts f(x) = f2 ◦ f1(x) and intermediate representation h can be retrieved while passing partial backbone f1. The final representation z ′ L passed to classifier g can be retrieved as follows: h = f1(x), hˆ = RS(h) ∈ R N , z′ L = hˆ · α + f2(h) · (1 − α) (5) . This means we mixup two elements: intermediate representation and final representation. In this paper, following the recent works, we design a learninable parameter α by summarizing the hidden representation into a single value between 0 and 1 as α = σ(W · zL + b). (6) While previous mixup-based works [41, 13] use a beta distribution for α, here we use an auxiliary linear layer to learn the level of mix in an instance-wise manner.', '2025-03-20 15:00:00'),
(5, 27, 'Of course, I''d be happy to help you with that. Can you please share your draft with me so that I can take a look at it and provide you with feedback?', '<essay>In this work, we have delved into some of the most prominent advancements in the development of quantum dots that emits blue light, with diverse materials being used as precursors. In each type of quantum dots, we have discussed the synthesis methods, the emission peak, the PLQY values, and the relative advantages of using the particular materials. InP, CsPb1-xCuxX3, and Cs3Sb2Br9 all showed an emission peak at 400-500 nm, and resulted in PLQY values over 40%. It can be estimated that blue quantum dot studies of each type had their own advantages. In the case of InP quantum dots, the research group was able to obtain blue quantum dots that are highly stable and do not generate toxic PH3¬ gas. For the researchers who synthesized CsPb1-xCuxX3 (X = Br, Br/Cl) perovskite QDs, a particularly high PLQY value of 95% can be obtained, which is more than twofold of their rival candidates. Lastly, Cs3Sb2Br9 perovskite QDs dealt with the issue of the inclusion of toxic lead in lead halide perovskite quantum dots. Therefore, it is promising that the ultimate goal of synthesizing blue quantum dots which possess high efficiency and do not contain any hazardous components can be achieved in various routes. These blue-emitting quantum dots may be further applied to the development of blue-light emitting devices such as QLEDs, and are promising for granting these devices of high EQE (external quantum efficiency) and long lifetimes. Still, the current development in blue quantum dots lag behind in the properties of the red and green counterparts. Hence, future studies may focus on the synthesis of blue quantum dots with a specific target peak wavelength, having much more improved values of PLQY and FWHM. In addition, the endeavor for minimizing the use of harmful chemicals should also be accompanied for the sake of protecting the environment and reducing health risks.</essay>', 'In this work, we have delved into some of the most prominent advancements in the development of quantum dots that emits blue light, with diverse materials being used as precursors. In each type of quantum dots, we have discussed the synthesis methods, the emission peak, the PLQY values, and the relative advantages of using the particular materials. InP, CsPb1-xCuxX3, and Cs3Sb2Br9 all showed an emission peak at 400-500 nm, and resulted in PLQY values over 40%. It can be estimated that blue quantum dot studies of each type had their own advantages. In the case of InP quantum dots, the research group was able to obtain blue quantum dots that are highly stable and do not generate toxic PH3¬ gas. For the researchers who synthesized CsPb1-xCuxX3 (X = Br, Br/Cl) perovskite QDs, a particularly high PLQY value of 95% can be obtained, which is more than twofold of their rival candidates. Lastly, Cs3Sb2Br9 perovskite QDs dealt with the issue of the inclusion of toxic lead in lead halide perovskite quantum dots. Therefore, it is promising that the ultimate goal of synthesizing blue quantum dots which possess high efficiency and do not contain any hazardous components can be achieved in various routes. These blue-emitting quantum dots may be further applied to the development of blue-light emitting devices such as QLEDs, and are promising for granting these devices of high EQE (external quantum efficiency) and long lifetimes. Still, the current development in blue quantum dots lag behind in the properties of the red and green counterparts. Hence, future studies may focus on the synthesis of blue quantum dots with a specific target peak wavelength, having much more improved values of PLQY and FWHM. In addition, the endeavor for minimizing the use of harmful chemicals should also be accompanied for the sake of protecting the environment and reducing health risks.', '2025-04-03 17:00:00'),
(1, 28, 'Of course! Before we dive into your current work, tell me, what are some of the key takeaways and skills you''ve learned in our scientific writing class so far?', 'i''ve actually learned quite a few valuable lessons in my scientific writing class. I learned how to write a research paper, how to review my own work and that of my peers and what mistakes to watchout for', 'This study presents a comparative evaluation of various Transformer-based architectures for open-domain question-answering (QA). Specifically, we examine the effectiveness of three popular approaches: Dense Passage Retrieval (DPR), Fusion in Decoder (FiD), and Generative Reader (GenRead). To evaluate these models, we conduct rigorous experiments on well-known benchmark datasets such as SQuAD, TriviaQA, and SearchQA. Our experiments focus on performance evaluation metrics, such as exact match accuracy and F1 score, as well as the efficiency and scalability of these models.', '2025-02-14 11:04:00'),
(2, 28, 'Yes, in scientific writing, it''s important to review the literature to see if there are any other studies that have been done on the same topic. This allows you to build on existing knowledge and understand the current state of the field. Additionally, it''s important to cite any sources that support the claims you make in your own work. Did we discuss how to do a literature review in class?', 'Yes we briefly talked about it. However, I would like to know how I can find research on the same topic', '“The effects of voluntary environmental programs on climate change disclosure quality" Han, Li, and Yang (2018): Data from the CDP climate change program, methodology involved regression analysis, and the analytical tool used was Stata. Research question - How do voluntary environmental programs affect the quality of climate change disclosures? Model - The authors used a two-stage least squares regression model. Variables – • Independent variable: Participation in a voluntary environmental program. • Dependent variable: Climate change disclosure quality. • Control variables: Firm size, industry, and other company characteristics. The quality of climate change disclosures was assessed using the disclosure score provided by CDP. • H1: The quality of climate change disclosures is positively related to CSR performance. • H2: The quality of climate change disclosures mediates the relationship between ownership structure and CSR performance. • H3: The relationship between ownership structure and CSR performance is moderated by the quality of climate change disclosures.', '2025-02-27 12:04:00'),
(3, 28, 'Yes, there are several other possible reasons that support your point. Here are a couple of additional reasons: - Helping only those in need ensures that the resources are directed towards those who are truly vulnerable and less fortunate. If resources are not allocated properly, those who actually require the most help may not receive support, while those who can take care of themselves may receive unnecessary assistance. - By providing assistance to those in need, governments can help to reduce poverty and promote social equity. This in turn can lead to a more cohesive and stable society, which benefits everyone. Would you like to include any of these reasons in your essay?', 'The second one looks good. Now I want to get some help writing thesis statement with the two main reasons.', 'Governments have responsibility to help citizens. However, due to the limited workforce and budget constraints, it is essential for goverments to use their resources in the most efficient manner. As such, it is imperative for goverments to extend their help only to those who are genuinely in need. Governments have a responsibility to provid assistance to their citizens, but because of limited resources, it is essential that they allocate support only to those in need. This approach not only ensures efficient use of available resources, but also fosters social equity and reduced poverty.', '2025-03-13 10:34:00'),
(4, 28, 'The opposite of living a passive life is living an active life.', 'Can you find any grammatical errors in my following essay? "First year in KAIST, undergraduates does not have a specific major. Many other universities opened majors that do not require a specific major in the first year, and some university even have undergraduates be free of majors until graduation. In my opinion, this trend is beneficial to the students and other universities should require the first year of college to be major-free. I have three supporting reason that no major on the first year of college is beneficial in different reasons. First, a year without major gives students more freedom to choose, and it enables them to live a more active life. Students can select what their lives and their first year on college would be like. For example, computer science student from the first year would not try to find what they are truly interested in but passively accept that leaning computer science is the only coarse they''ll take. On the other hand, freshmen with no major will consider carefully what they can choose and design their future on their own. *The process is likely to be painstaking, however actively choosing the path of life will help students build their identity and passion to motivate themselves. Another reason why major-free freshmen is beneficial is that they can create networks with more diverse people. Integration between fields is what makes a breakthrough in not only academic areas but also arts and businesses. Major-free freshmen will easily make bonds with people with diverse interests, abilities and histories. Students with major would also make bonds, but not as easily and strong, and not as diverse as students without a major would. Lastly, it''s hard to become interested in one major until high school graduation. Lacking life experience, high school students often choose majors by first look or without knowing what the major is actually about. Universities in South Korea grade high school students by their ''major compatible rate'' that cause high school student lie on their interests on the school records. First year without major will reduce this tendency and for the students who were not truly interested in the major they applied for a second chance. In conclusion, more universities and colleges should give their first year students the chance to search for their major. No major on first year gives chance to plan life on students'' own, encourages diverse social web creation, and makes students rethink the hastily chosen path of major they chose in high school. "', 'First year in KAIST, undergraduate students does not have a specific major. Many other universities offer majors that do not require a specific major in the first year, and some university even have undergraduates be free of majors until graduation. In my opinion, this trend is beneficial to the students and other universities should require the first year of college to be major-free. I have three supporting reasons that no major on the first year of college is beneficial. First, a year without major gives students more freedom to choose, and it enables them to live a more active life. Students can select what their life and their first year on college would be like. For example, computer science student from the first year would not try to find what they are truly interested in but passively accept that learning computer science is the only course they''ll take. On the other hand, freshmen with no major will consider carefully what they can choose and design their future for themselves. *The process is likely to be painstaking, however actively choosing the path of life will help students build their identity and passion to motivate them. Another reason why major-free freshmen is beneficial is that they can create networks with more diverse people. Integration between fields is what makes a breakthrough in not only academic areas but also arts and businesses. Major-free freshmen will easily make bonds with people with diverse interests, abilities and histories. Students with major would also make bonds, but not as easily and strongly, and not as diverse as students without a major would. Lastly, it''s difficult to become interested in one major until high school graduation. Lacking life experience, high school students often choose majors by first look or without knowing what the major is actually about. Universities in South Korea grade high school students by their ''major compatible rate'' that causes high school student lie on their interests on the school records. First year without major will reduce this tendency and for the students who were not truly interested in the major they applied for a second chance. In conclusion, more universities and colleges should give their first year students the chance to search for their major. Having no major on first year gives opportunity to plan their lives for themselves, encourages diverse social web creation, and makes students reconsider the major they chose hastily in high school.', '2025-03-20 15:04:00'),
(5, 28, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about paragraph structure. There are introduction, body, and conclusion. I''m curious about the appropriate length of each section.', 'Most of the nations around the world have their own policies to help their citizens. Some countries have policies aimed at supporting those who are most in need. For example, the Nordic countries and Canada have comprehensive welfare systems and employment insurance program. Although they have specific policies for those in need, they also has basic systems for all citizens. I think government should provide support all citizens regardless of socioeconomic background. Firstly, the government should ensure fundamental rights of citizens. The most important example is safety and healthcare. If nations help differently according to their socioeconomic background, it could be a non-just society. To make equitable society, nations should provide support equally. USA is now providing law enforcement, and fire emergency services, and disaster response, etc. Similarly, other nations are helping all citizens and ensure their safety. Furthermore, the government should make a just and equitable society. Socioeconomic status is a factor that is beyond on individual''s control, such as race, ethnicity, gender, or family background. Therefore, it is important for governments to provide support and assistance all citizens regardless of their socioeconomic status. If they treat differently, it can cause a lot of issues. For example, it can lead to discrimination problem and social problem. When individuals from disadvantaged backgrounds are treated differently than those from more privileged backgrounds, they may feel marginalized and excluded from society. To prevent these situations, government should support all citizens equally. All citizens have fundamental rights as a citizen of their nation. If the government treat differently according to their socioeconomic status, it could lead to lots of social problem, such as disparities, social exclusion. Therefore, the government should provide support for all citizens regardless of their socioeconomic backgrounds, and they have to make a just and equitable nations.', '2025-04-03 17:04:00'),
(1, 29, 'Yes, that''s a great summary! It seems like you''ve learned about the various components that make up the methods section of a scientific paper. These information elements are all important to include in the methods section because they ensure that the experiment can be properly understood and replicated by other researchers. By providing details on the sample size, location, experimental design, and statistical treatment, the reader can better understand the logic behind the experiment and evaluate the validity of the results. Great job! Do you have any questions about these information elements or any other topics we''ve covered in class?', 'Here is my method part in thesis. <para>"2.2 Methods 2.2.1 Problem description The most important concept of staff scheduling problems suggested in this paper is that all hotel rooms are divided into three parts, and each of them must be cleaned by different room attendants. In addition, all room attendants are not allowed to clean the different parts of the hotel room during the same day. Besides, there are three shifts, which are A-shift (00:00 to 08:00), B-shift (08:00 to 16:00), and C-shift (16:00 to 24:00), so there are total 10 kinds of duties including off-duty. They are A-shift & bathroom duty, A-shift & toilet duty, B-shift & bedroom duty, B-shift & bathroom duty, B-shift & toilet duty, C-shift & bedroom duty, C-shift & bathroom duty, C-shift & toilet duty, and off-duty. Meanwhile, the time required to clean each part of a room is different because of its size and spatial characteristics. Furthermore, because this paper considers several types of hotel rooms, the required time to clean the same part of a room is also different according to each type of hotel room. Therefore, the number of hotel rooms assigned to each room attendant should be determined considering the part of the hotel room and the type of hotel room. The whole process is performed by two mathematical models. The goal of mathematical model 1 is to minimize the sum of the total workforce levels. In order to do this, the sum of workforce levels required for each shift should be minimized. Based on the results of mathematical model 1, mathematical model 2 determines how to distribute the duties to the room attendants considering the fairness and the welfare conditions in perspective of minimizing the number of room attendants. Through this process, the minimized number of required room attendants is determined. This paper assumes that all rooms are available, and the total number of rooms is equal to the sum of occupied rooms, clean rooms, and dirty rooms. In addition, it is assumed that a sufficient number of rooms are always pre-cleaned, so that no situation occurs where customer waiting occurs. 2.2.2 Mathematical model 1: deriving minimum workforce level Mathematical model 1 aims to minimize the sum of the total workforce levels required to each shift. The workforce level required for each shift is determined by the number of rooms required to be cleaned, taking into account the number of check-in, check-out rooms, and clean rooms. The derived workforce levels have to be enough to clean the number of rooms required for check-in demand during the whole scheduling period. The result of mathematical model 1 is the least amount of duties that must be assigned to the room attendants in mathematical model 2."</para> In the provided paragraph, what kind of elements can you find?', '2.2 Methods 2.2.1 Problem description The most important concept of staff scheduling problems suggested in this paper is that all hotel rooms are divided into three parts, and each of them must be cleaned by different room attendants. In addition, all room attendants are not allowed to clean the different parts of the hotel room during the same day. Besides, there are three shifts, which are A-shift (00:00 to 08:00), B-shift (08:00 to 16:00), and C-shift (16:00 to 24:00), so there are total 10 kinds of duties including off-duty. They are A-shift & bathroom duty, A-shift & toilet duty, B-shift & bedroom duty, B-shift & bathroom duty, B-shift & toilet duty, C-shift & bedroom duty, C-shift & bathroom duty, C-shift & toilet duty, and off-duty. Meanwhile, the time required to clean each part of a room is different because of its size and spatial characteristics. Furthermore, because this paper considers several types of hotel rooms, the required time to clean the same part of a room is also different according to each type of hotel room. Therefore, the number of hotel rooms assigned to each room attendant should be determined considering the part of the hotel room and the type of hotel room. The whole process is performed by two mathematical models. The goal of mathematical model 1 is to minimize the sum of the total workforce levels. In order to do this, the sum of workforce levels required for each shift should be minimized. Based on the results of mathematical model 1, mathematical model 2 determines how to distribute the duties to the room attendants considering the fairness and the welfare conditions in perspective of minimizing the number of room attendants. Through this process, the minimized number of required room attendants is determined. This paper assumes that all rooms are available, and the total number of rooms is equal to the sum of occupied rooms, clean rooms, and dirty rooms. In addition, it is assumed that a sufficient number of rooms are always pre-cleaned, so that no situation occurs where customer waiting occurs. 2.2.2 Mathematical model 1: deriving minimum workforce level Mathematical model 1 aims to minimize the sum of the total workforce levels required to each shift. The workforce level required for each shift is determined by the number of rooms required to be cleaned, taking into account the number of check-in, check-out rooms, and clean rooms. The derived workforce levels have to be enough to clean the number of rooms required for check-in demand during the whole scheduling period. The result of mathematical model 1 is the least amount of duties that must be assigned to the room attendants in mathematical model 2.', '2025-02-14 11:08:00'),
(2, 29, 'Great, let''s start with your essay. Please point out the unclear pronouns and repetitive words and we will work on improving them. First, please read through your essay and circle them.', '<sent>We all citizens are paying tax, and they shout out many complaints such as ''It is too expensive.'' Even though, it is burden, they pay the tax for mandatory.</sent> In these sentences I think the word ''it'' is unclear. What about you?', 'Socioeconomically poor people usually lack conditions such as education, health care compare to the most. Caring socioeconomically poor people is natural in ethical view. However, it is quite controversial how much of people should be designated as socioeconomical poor. Although socioeconomically poor people are considered the most vulnerable citizens in our society, I believe government should help all of its citizens to ensure everyone has access to basic necessities and resources. First, the budget that will used was initially for all of us. We all citizens are paying tax, and they shout out many complaints such as ''It is too expensive.'' Even though, it is burden, they pay the tax for mandatory. Using the tax for all citizen is right. For this statement, helping only those most in need looks strange. It seems like the government overprotecting them. Majorities of citizens who are maintaining the country would deeply resent to the government that only helping minorities. Second, the budget have to be used properly for functioning economy. There are many things government should get attention. For instance, monitoring and functioning school like KAIST or helping people who are poored. Then why they assist those things? It is for Country''s power. Students in Kaist will lead science in the world, and structures will show the country''s well. I want to point out that there are many things where budget should be used not only for poors. Third, standard for socioeconomically poor people are too arbitrary. During the Corona pandemic, it was controversial to define target. If we give money by income percentile, people who are slightly better can''t get assistance. Otherwise, if we assist by job, usually we think self-employed people are in trouble. However, some self-employed people have earned more through delivery, while job seekers are in difficult circumstances. Helping socioeconomically solely might causes some problems. However, helping them also have their benefits too. For example, government can find out talented man newly. Even so, the decision looks unfair, inefficient and it looks easily be frauded. Conclusion, I think government should provide appropriate welfare to all of the citizens.', '2025-02-27 12:08:00'),
(3, 29, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I want to find outside sources for my essay. which part will be nice to add outside sources?', 'The relationship between the government and its citizens is a complex interplay of power, responsibility, and accountability. The government is responsible for providing its citizens with assistance and protection as a fundamental right. Additionally, each citizens possess diverse circumstances and needs that may require assistance from the government. Therefore, the question arises: should the government help only those most in need rather than help all of its citizens? This essay argues that the government should provide aid to all citizens, regardless of their financial status or demonstrated need, for several reasons; While it may seem logical to provide aid only to individuals most in need, it can be discriminatory and demotivating. Also, it creates a system that is prone to errors and fraud. Providing support to all citizens can promote social cohesion and responsibility. A more equitable approach is to provide aid to all citizens, regardless of financial status or demonstrated need. First, By restricting aid to those who demonstrate financial need, the government runs the risk of perpetuating division and animosity among different social and economic groups. The government runs the country with careful management of tax money. If only those in need receive benefits, it can create resentment among those who do not receive aid. Discrimination and stigmatization can arise, leading those who do not receive assistance to harbor ill will towards those who do. For instance, when healthcare systems focus care only on those individuals who exhibit dire financial need, it can create division and hatred. On the other hand, when assistance is offered to all citizens, accountability is shared, and it fosters a sense of communal responsibility. Citizens are more invested in each other''s well-being, leading to a more cohesive society. The second reason is that people will lose their motivation to work if the government provides assistance to only individuals in need. They could become reliant on government aid and lose motivation to work. In such a system, those who do not benefit from government aid may feel disenfranchised and resentful towards those who do. Those who do not receive aid may feel as though they are contributing to support others without receiving aid, without receiving any support themselves. As a result, their motivation to work decreases. Some people might say that providing assistance only to those in need has potential for greater efficiency, as resources are focused where they are most needed. Additionally, the amount of funding needed for assistance programs may be lower, as it is targeted towards those in dire circumstances. However, Those who are ineligible for assistance due to their financial standing may feel that they are being left out of important government programs. They will lose their reason to pay taxes and their motivation to work hard, and consequently, government will lose efficiency gained by helping only individuals in need. A third problem of implementing a system of aid that targets only those most in need is that the process of determining who qualifies for aid can be highly subjective and prone to abuse. Determining who qualifies for government aid and who does not can be complex and time-consuming. Some people might intentionally misrepresent their circumstance in order to get assistance, while others might be unjustly excluded from aid due to administrative errors. Then there can be a moral issues. People with greater resources might not need government support, they may still benefit from it in various ways due to the error on determining who qualifies for government assistance. Another reason is that providing financial aid only to individuals who demonstrate financial need can create unintended consequences, such as discouraging students from pursuing their preferred paths of study based on cost. In contrast, a system that promotes providing assistance to all citizens based on merit and academic achievement guarantees talented students have an equal opportunity to achieve their goals, thereby keeping the workforce competitive. Some argue that providing financial assistance to all students based on merit is a wasteful use of taxpayer dollars and that only those who demonstrate financial need or contribute to the public good should receive government funding. However, this argument fails to consider that limiting funding exclusively in this way may exclude many talented students from access to higher education, contributing to a less productive and innovative society overall. As a result, the cost to the taxpayer must be carefully balanced against the important benefits of promoting a more educated citizenry. In conclusion, the government must offer aid to all citizens to secure a just and cohesive society. Providing assistance only to those most in need can escalate discrimination and breed resentment, ultimately eroding social solidarity. Additionally, such a system may disincentivize work by fostering resentment among those who do not qualify for aid. While some may argue that focusing aid only on those most in need can be more efficient, it can also exclude those who, despite not demonstrating obvious financial hardship, still require support. The process of determining who qualifies for aid can be complex and prone to errors, potentially leaving out deserving citizens. A system that promotes aid to all citizens is more comprehensive and promotes social responsibility, while encouraging productivity and innovation. Therefore, it is imperative that the government consider equity and community investment when designing aid programs, rather than concentrating support on an exclusive group of people.', '2025-03-13 10:38:00'),
(4, 29, 'Your revised sentence is much clearer and concise! It correctly separates the adjectives used to modify the colleges and uses commas to separate the clauses, which helps to make the sentence grammatically correct. However, there''s one more revision you could make to further enhance your sentence''s clarity. In the final clause, you could add a comma after "same" to make it a parenthetical element, which would make the sentence clearer and easier to read. Here''s the revised sentence, "Let''s say that people are accepted to two colleges which are recognized as the same level, one is the first type, and the other is the second type. If properties of both of them are all the same but, except for the way to choose their major, I think most people, including me, would choose the latter one." Great work! You''ve applied your knowledge of comma usage effectively to revise your essay.', 'I think that it does not need a comma "If properties of both of them are all the same but, except for the way to choose their major"Isn''t it?', 'In Korea, there are two types of freshman. One is that people already get their major before they enter the college, and the other is that people choose their major after they are in college for 1 year. Let''s say that people are accepted to two colleges which are recognized as same level, one is the first type, and the other is the second type. If properties of both of them are all same but except for the way to choose their major, I think most people, including me, would choose latter one. Therefore, I think universities should require that the first year of college should be major free as possible as they can. There are some reasons. First one is that there are no certainty that people are interested in only one area forever. Before people enroll a university, they usually experienced just an elementary level of knowledge as universities see. Although it is good to have a dream their own just because if their simple interest, their interest can be changed as they study more deeply that area. Moreover, there are also people who don’t have their own dream until high school. Thus, choosing major before the first year of college is harsh. Nextly, freshman level subjects such as calculus, general physics, and general chemistry are not related deeply with majors. I do not mean such subjects are not helpful, but mean they are necessary to all freshman who are in any major. So, I think it is better that each major opens their own subject or seminar for freshman instead.', '2025-03-20 15:08:00'),
(5, 29, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about where should we use comma and quotation mark. Also, I learned it''s better to use verb form rather than noun form when we describe actions.', 'Government is different from past monarchy, because it tries to provide equal chances and resources to citzens . However, even in modern society, there are differences of economic and social status between people. Childern who are born into poor families will face difficulties. Also, elders need more help than others due to their reduced ablities. Therefore, to make a nation a better place, government should concentrate on supporting people in need. By providing education, resources, and aid to them, governments can contribute to a more equitable society. The most serious problem that government should consider is differences of background of a person''s childhood. The poors are not likely to get high quality education or supports than others. As a result, they get little chance for improving abilities to get a better status in society. For instance, university is important for a person''s various experience for success. However, many universities prefer a person who can perform well. Also, some elite universities require quite huge amount of money to register. But what people in need can''t satisfy are these external academic supports due to their environment. Government should make a policy that tries to improve public education to reduce the other external acardemic supports'' influence. In addition, to reduce the economic burden for poors, proper aid of money should be contained in the policy. Another point to consider is people who are getting old. Some might think it is unfair to help elders, but all human beings become old. The government should care about their citizens'' future and continue to help elders. More specifically, as people get old, their abilities to work reduce, so they have to retire and they are not financially independent anymore. Also, they are vulnerable to diseases and medical conditions that require constant attention and medical intervention. Government should not left them in these poor conditions, because they have been contribute to society and still have a wealth of knowledge, skills, and experience that can be helpful for society. Therefore, government should provide seniors with medical and economical supports that contribute to the well-being of both society and individuals who are aging. Last thing government should care about is stabilty of the society. If the government doesn''t focus on helping people in need, the differnce between people''s socioeconomic status will worsen. Consequently, the society might become more unstable. Historically, it is clear that there are more conflicts between people when the inequality of chances and unbalanced wealth are evident. For example, society may experience high rates of crime and violence as individuals compete for resources and power. Also, societies may suffer from a breakdown in social connections and trust, leading to societal disintegration and a loss of collective values. Hence, government have to care more about people in need for social benefits and stabilty. Nowadays, most governments around the world seems to function well, but there are major problems related to the inequality of social status and wealth. These are problems what democracy systems have to solve. One way to adress these problems is strengthening policies that support the social underprivileged. The government should help people in need more carefully to ensure their chance to learn and become sucessful. Moreover, for the citizen''s future, government should aid seniors with economical and medical supports that acknowledge the valuable contributions they have made to society. In conclusion, to achieve the critical role of government maintaining society''s peace and balanced state, they should concentrate on supporting minorities who have been historically dismissed and overlooked.', '2025-04-03 17:08:00'),
(1, 30, 'I found a few punctuation and grammar errors that need to be fixed in the paragraph: - In the sentence "While 68% and 53% of the students agree, only 21% and 37% strongly agree that they textbook is clearly understandable and the textbook tasks are helpful to develop their writing skills." - "they textbook" should be "the textbook." - In the sentence "Furthermore, 58% of the students either are neutral or disagree that the amount of reading each week is appropriate," - "either are" should be "are either." - In the sentence "On the other hand, most of the students strongly agree that the video content and classroom contents are satisfactory," - "classroom contents" should be "classroom content." - In the sentence "while they typically find the video and classroom contents to be satisfactory," - "contents" should be "content." Once those changes are made, the paragraph should read as follows: Table 1 summarizes the class content feedback from the student respondents. The results from Table 1 indicate that the students have mixed views regarding the effectiveness of the textbook content in developing their writing skills. While 68% and 53% of the students agree, only 21% and 37% strongly agree that the textbook is clearly understandable and the textbook tasks are helpful to develop their writing skills. Furthermore, 58% of the students are either neutral or disagree that the amount of reading each week is appropriate. On the other hand, most of the students strongly agree that the video content and classroom content is satisfactory. Approximately 68% of the students strongly agree that the videos are clearly understandable, and 63% strongly agree that the classroom content is clearly understandable. Furthermore, 74% of the students strongly agree that the videos are an appropriate length, while 58% strongly agree that the amount of time spent checking homework tasks is appropriate. Overall, the survey findings indicate that the students have mixed feelings regarding the efficacy of textbook content in developing their writing abilities, while they typically find the video and classroom content to be satisfactory. The findings may help the instructors adjust their teaching methods and course materials to better meet the needs and expectations of the students.', 'from my paragraph, it seems like it has too much details on the data description. can you help to make it shorter and concise?', 'Table 1 summarizes the class content feedback from the student respondents. The results from Table 1 indicate that the students have mixed views regarding the effectiveness of the textbook content in developing their writing skills. While 68% and 53% of the students agree, only 21% and 37% strongly agree that the textbook is clearly understandable and the textbook tasks are helpful to develop their writing skills. Furthermore, 58% of the students are either neutral or disagree that the amount of reading each week is appropriate. On the other hand, most of the students strongly agree that the video content and classroom content are satisfactory. Approximately 68% of the students strongly agree that the videos are clearly understandable, and 63% strongly agree that the classroom content is clearly understandable. Furthermore, 74% of the students strongly agree that the videos are an appropriate length, while 58% strongly agree that the amount of time spent checking homework tasks is appropriate. Overall, the survey findings indicate that the students have mixed feelings regarding the efficacy of textbook content in developing their writing abilities, while they typically find the video and classroom content to be satisfactory. The findings may help the instructors adjust their teaching methods and course materials to better meet the needs and expectations of the students.', '2025-02-14 11:12:00'),
(2, 30, 'Yes, I would be happy to take a look at your methodology section and provide you with feedback. Please share your work with me, and I''ll do my best to help you improve it.', '<essay>Apparatus The experimental apparatus used in this study consisted of a personal computer(PC) equipped with an NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3060 Ti graphics card, HTC Vive Pro Eye head-mounted display(HMD), two Vive Trackers (one for the participant’s left foot and one for the right foot), the Unity game engine, and the Ready Player Me software. The Unity game engine was used to create the virtual environment and the interactive scenarios. The Ready Player me software was used to generate virtual avatars. The experiment was conducted in a soundproof room. The room was equipped with a personal computer(PC) that was used to collect questionnaire answers. During the experiment, participants stood in front of two Vive base stations in the room, and were instructed to wear the VR headset and trackers, which allowed for head and body movement tracking in the virtual environment. Avatar set For the experiment, a total of 144 avatars were generated, with 72 avatars for male participants and another 72 avatars for female participants. The generated avatars’ sex was matched to the participants’ sex to ensure that participants were presented with avatars that matched their own gender. The avatars were further divided into six different experimental conditions, with each condition consisting of 12 avatars. Specifically, for each condition, 4 avatars had red hair, 4 avatars had black hair, and 4 avatars had gold hair, with different hairstyles for each avatar. In addition, 6 avatars within each condition had a comparatively darker skin color, while the remaining 6 had a comparatively lighter skin color. 12 avatars in the same condition wore the same clothing, and there were no duplicated avatars among the 144 total. (See appendix for the visual information.) Participants Participants were recruited within the KAIST community. 34 undergraduate and graduate students participated in the experiment (17 females, 17 males, mean age: 00, age SD = 0.00, age range: 00-00 years, 3 foreigners, 31 Koreans), all with normal or corrected-to-normal vision. All participants received 20,000won for their participation (duration: 60-90 min) Procedure Preparation Once participants arrived, consent agreement documents were provided to obtain their signature. Subsequently, instructions regarding the experiment were given to the participants, and after ensuring their comprehension of the experiment procedure, they were escorted to the experiment room to don the HMD and trackers. Eye calibration When the participant was ready to begin the experiment, an eye calibration process was performed. Avatar selection Following the eye calibration, a total of 12 avatars were presented to the participants in a grid format with 4 columns and 3 rows. Participants were then instructed to select an avatar as “My avatar”, while the researcher simultaneously selected an avatar as “Friend avatar”. Depending on the condition, participants either chose their own “My avatar” or it was chosen by the researcher. The hair color of the “Friend avatar” matched that of the participant’s “My avatar”, while their skin color differed from the “My avatar”. Avatar exposure After the avatar selection stage, “My avatar” and “Friend avatar” were sequentially presented in front of the participant for 3 seconds each. During this presentation, the avatar was rotated in a horizontal direction by 360 degrees, thereby enabling the participant to perceive the avatar’s distinguishing features from the back, side, and front of the avatar evenly. Avatar embodiment Following the avatar exposure, participants proceeded with the avatar embodiment process in which they were presented with a virtual mirror displaying “My avatar” and “Friend avatar”. Participants were then instructed to answer a series of questions regarding the mirror’s display of the avatars’ bodies and perform several movements, including clapping, touching their left shoulder with their right hand, and touching their friend avatar’s shoulder with their right hand. They were then asked to mimic the friend avatar’s pose and take a photo of themselves using the left-hand controller. The friend avatar posed in four different ways sequentially, with each pose involving lifting either the right arm, left arm, right foot, or left foot. Participants were asked to replicate each pose twice. The motion synchronization of “My avatar” with the participant was dependent on the condition, and could either be controlled by a button or remain still. The entire embodiment process was completed in an average of 3 minutes. Visual search task Next, the participant completed a visual search task involving the identification of either “My avatar” or “Friend avatar” within a grid of 12 avatars presented in a 4x3 format. At the start of each trial, a pop-up window displaying the target avatar was presented, which participants were required to click to initiate the search task. Once the target image was clicked, the pop-up window closed, and the 12 avatars were presented. Participants were instructed to locate the target avatar as quickly as possible and click on it using their right hand controller. The participants complete 40 trials for each condition, in total 240 trials. </essay> Data Collection During the visual search task, participants’ eye tracking data was collected as well as the reaction time and accuracy rate. After completing each condition, the participants were asked to answer the embodiment questionnaire with a PC in the experiment room. The standardized embodiment questionnaire utilized in this study was derived from Peck and Gonzalez-Franco’s (2021) research article titled “Avatar Embodiment: A Standardized Questionnaire” in Frontiers in Virtual Reality.', 'To Apparatus The experimental apparatus used in this study consisted of a personal computer(PC) equipped with an NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3060 Ti graphics card, HTC Vive Pro Eye head-mounted display(HMD), two Vive Trackers (one for the participant’s left foot and one for the right foot), the Unity game engine, and the Ready Player Me software. The Unity game engine was used to create the virtual environment and the interactive scenarios. The Ready Player me software was used to generate virtual avatars. The experiment was conducted in a soundproof room. The room was equipped with a personal computer(PC) that was used to collect questionnaire answers. During the experiment, participants stood in front of two Vive base stations in the room, and were instructed to wear the VR headset and trackers, which allowed for head and body movement tracking in the virtual environment. Avatar set For the experiment, a total of 144 avatars were generated, with 72 avatars for male participants and another 72 avatars for female participants. The generated avatars’ sex was matched to the participants’ sex to ensure that participants were presented with avatars that matched their own gender. The avatars were further divided into six different experimental conditions, with each condition consisting of 12 avatars. Specifically, for each condition, 4 avatars had red hair, 4 avatars had black hair, and 4 avatars had gold hair, with different hairstyles for each avatar. In addition, 6 avatars within each condition had a comparatively darker skin color, while the remaining 6 had a comparatively lighter skin color. 12 avatars in the same condition wore the same clothing, and there were no duplicated avatars among the 144 total. (See appendix for the visual information.) Participants Participants were recruited within the KAIST community. 34 undergraduate and graduate students participated in the experiment (17 females, 17 males, mean age: 00, age SD = 0.00, age range: 00-00 years, 3 foreigners, 31 Koreans), all with normal or corrected-to-normal vision. All participants received 20,000won for their participation (duration: 60-90 min) Procedure Preparation Once participants arrived, consent agreement documents were provided to obtain their signature. Subsequently, instructions regarding the experiment were given to the participants, and after ensuring their comprehension of the experiment procedure, they were escorted to the experiment room to don the HMD and trackers. Eye calibration When the participant was ready to begin the experiment, an eye calibration process was performed. Avatar selection Following the eye calibration, a total of 12 avatars were presented to the participants in a grid format with 4 columns and 3 rows. Participants were then instructed to select an avatar as “My avatar”, while the researcher simultaneously selected an avatar as “Friend avatar”. Depending on the condition, participants either chose their own “My avatar” or it was chosen by the researcher. The hair color of the “Friend avatar” matched that of the participant’s “My avatar”, while their skin color differed from the “My avatar”. Avatar exposure After the avatar selection stage, “My avatar” and “Friend avatar” were sequentially presented in front of the participant for 3 seconds each. During this presentation, the avatar was rotated in a horizontal direction by 360 degrees, thereby enabling the participant to perceive the avatar’s distinguishing features from the back, side, and front of the avatar evenly. Avatar embodiment Following the avatar exposure, participants proceeded with the avatar embodiment process in which they were presented with a virtual mirror displaying “My avatar” and “Friend avatar”. Participants were then instructed to answer a series of questions regarding the mirror’s display of the avatars’ bodies and perform several movements, including clapping, touching their left shoulder with their right hand, and touching their friend avatar’s shoulder with their right hand. They were then asked to mimic the friend avatar’s pose and take a photo of themselves using the left-hand controller. The friend avatar posed in four different ways sequentially, with each pose involving lifting either the right arm, left arm, right foot, or left foot. Participants were asked to replicate each pose twice. The motion synchronization of “My avatar” with the participant was dependent on the condition, and could either be controlled by a button or remain still. The entire embodiment process was completed in an average of 3 minutes. Visual search task Next, the participant completed a visual search task involving the identification of either “My avatar” or “Friend avatar” within a grid of 12 avatars presented in a 4x3 format. At the start of each trial, a pop-up window displaying the target avatar was presented, which participants were required to click to initiate the search task. Once the target image was clicked, the pop-up window closed, and the 12 avatars were presented. Participants were instructed to locate the target avatar as quickly as possible and click on it using their right hand controller. The participants complete 40 trials for each condition, in total 240 trials. Data Collection During the visual search task, participants’ eye tracking data was collected as well as the reaction time and accuracy rate. After completing each condition, the participants were asked to answer the embodiment questionnaire with a PC in the experiment room. The standardized embodiment questionnaire utilized in this study was derived from Peck and Gonzalez-Franco’s (2021) research article titled “Avatar Embodiment: A Standardized Questionnaire” in Frontiers in Virtual Reality.', '2025-02-27 12:12:00'),
(3, 30, 'One way to improve your opening paragraph is to make it more concise. While you provide a good overview of the topic, it can be a bit wordy and difficult to follow at times. Here''s one possible way to revise the paragraph: "Smart Livestock Farming (SLF) is a new concept in the livestock industry that uses computer vision (CV) technology to monitor the health and welfare of animals. By automatically tracking parameters like behavior, activity, and pose information, SLF reduces the need for human intervention, which can be cost-effective and less stressful for the animals. CV technology offers a range of tools for monitoring pigs, including image processing, image classification, object detection, and segmentation. Researchers have used these tools to classify pig behaviors, detect abnormal behavior or disease, estimate body composition traits and body weights for regression, and obtain pose information for individual pigs in an image. Overall, CV technology has the potential to greatly enhance the management of pig health and welfare in SLF systems." This revision cuts out some of the unnecessary detail from the original paragraph while still conveying all the key information. It also clarifies the relationship between SLF and CV technology and presents the information in a more organized and easy-to-follow way.', 'In the original paragraph I mentioned about low-level CV and high-level CV. Do I need to briefly elaborate about the definition of both? Or is it already a standard term in computer vision field?', 'With the advancement of technology, the concept of Smart Livestock Farming (SLF) has emerged in the livestock industry [ 1]. SLF technologies enable non-manual and non-invasive supervision by automatically monitoring animal’s body parameters, behavior, activity level and pose information etc. This is cost-effective and less stressful for the animals due to less human intervention. Among SLF’s tools, computer vision (CV) has made many improvements in livestock operations [ 2]. Many studies have used low-level CV, such as image processing [3] and high-level CV technology, such as image classification [4– 6 ], object detection [7, 8] and segmentation [ 9,10 ], to monitor the health and welfare of pig. Image classification has been used to classify pig behaviors [ 4 ], detect abnormal behavior [ 5] or disease on body parts [ 6 ]. Studies have also been conducted to estimate the body composition traits [ 11 ] and their body weights [12 ] for regression. On the other hand, as object detection and segmentation have evolved, researchers have focused on the pose information of individual pig in an image [ 7 ]. CV technology provides a variety of tools to efficiently manage the health and welfare of pig.', '2025-03-13 10:42:00'),
(4, 30, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned that I should be cautious of use of pronoun indiscreetly when writing a paper.', 'The main use of the English present subjunctive, called the mandative or jussive subjunctive, occurs in that clauses (declarative content clauses; the word that is sometimes omitted in informal and conversational usage) expressing a circumstance which is desired, demanded, recommended, necessary, or similar. Such a clause may be dependent on verbs like insist, suggest, demand, prefer, adjectives like necessary, desirable, or nouns like recommendation, necessity; it may be part of the expression in order that... (or some formal uses of so that...); it may also stand independently as the subject of a clause or as a predicative expression.', '2025-03-20 15:12:00'),
(5, 30, 'Yes, I can certainly help you with that. Please go ahead and provide me with the paragraph you would like me to revise.', '<para>Offensive language exchanged between chatbots and human users can have detrimental consequences on users, chatbot services, and society. Despite notable advancements in autonomous offensive language detection, extending these efforts to chat data remains challenging due to the chat messages'' inherent briefness and contextual complexity. In this paper, we introduce a novel offensive language dataset based on real-world chatbot-human conversations, annotated with a focus on context-awareness. Our dataset distinguishes context- dependent offensive lanquage, which is an offensive expression under a specific context. To address this nuanced task, we propose a neural network model named CALIOPER (Context-Aware modeL for Identifying Offensive language using Pre-trained Encoder and Retrieval). CALIOPER leverages a context-aware encoder and attention mechanism to incorporate previous messages and retrieve relevant information from them for detecting offensiveness. Experimental results show that CALIOPER outperforms existing offensive language detection models on multi-turn datasets, particularly for context-dependent offensive language. This work provides a direction in offensive language detection in chat data, contributing to safer chatbot ecosystems. *This paper contains profanity due to the nature of the study topic.</para>', 'Offensive language exchanged between chatbots and human users can have detrimental consequences on users, chatbot services, and society. Despite notable advancements in autonomous offensive language detection, extending these efforts to chat data remains challenging due to the chat messages'' inherent briefness and contextual complexity. In this paper, we introduce a novel offensive language dataset based on real-world chatbot-human conversations, annotated with a focus on context-awareness. Our dataset distinguishes context- dependent offensive lanquage, which is an offensive expression under a specific context. To address this nuanced task, we propose a neural network model named CALIOPER (Context-Aware modeL for Identifying Offensive language using Pre-trained Encoder and Retrieval). CALIOPER leverages a context-aware encoder and attention mechanism to incorporate previous messages and retrieve relevant information from them for detecting offensiveness. Experimental results show that CALIOPER outperforms existing offensive language detection models on multi-turn datasets, particularly for context-dependent offensive language. This work provides a direction in offensive language detection in chat data, contributing to safer chatbot ecosystems. *This paper contains profanity due to the nature of the study topic.', '2025-04-03 17:12:00'),
(1, 31, 'Of course! Please provide me with your essay, and I will check it over.', '<essay> A lot of schools, even some middle schools, let students use their private tablets and laptop computers, and sometimes teachers even provide them. However, this has been controversial because people were not sure whether it is effective for education or not. The reason why governments still allow them to use such electric devices, even though there are some controversies, is because it has some advantages that can not be taken only with general books or notebooks. First, it is easier to write and erase letters. Erasers should be used to remove words that are written as a mistake, and the size of the letters can be changed easily while it is difficult with paper notebooks. Furthermore, digital notebooks have more color options so users can use various color pens. Second, they are useful to search for necessary information. It is hard to find some concepts on books during class; however, it will be much faster to look for them with online services. Therefore, the extra time after the particular class to understand what the teachers taught would not be required since the students can discover more documents that can help them learn specific concepts. Third, each of the students of a certain class can be connected. Accordingly, they can share the useful information and have some debates about what they learned during the day, which could offer high school students the opportunity to experience teamwork or the cooperation projects that are usually shown in colleges earlier.</essay>', 'A lot of schools, even some middle schools, let students use their private tablets and laptop computers, and sometimes teachers even provide them. However, this has been controversial because people were not sure whether it is effective for education or not. The reason why governments still allow them to use such electric devices, even though there are some controversies, is because it has some advantages that can not be taken only with general books or notebooks. First, it is easier to write and erase letters since digital notebooks allow one to remove words that are written as a mistake, and the size of the letters can be changed easily, unlike paper notebooks. Furthermore, digital notebooks have more color options, allowing users to include various color pens. Second, they are useful to search for necessary information. It is hard to find some concepts in books during class; however, it will be much faster to look for them online. Therefore, extra time after a particular class to help students understand what the teachers taught would not be required since they can discover more documents that can help them learn specific concepts. Third, each of the students in a certain class can be connected. As a result, they can share useful information and have debates about what they learned during the day, offering high school students the opportunity to experience teamwork or the cooperation projects usually shown in colleges earlier.', '2025-02-14 11:16:00'),
(2, 31, 'Yes, that is correct! Colons are a powerful tool for scientific writers. Specifically, they are used to introduce lists, explanations, or clarifications. When you are presenting a list of items, or a series of concepts, you can use a colon to introduce or highlight them. This can be particularly useful when you want to make sure your readers understand the relationship between items in a list, or when you want to emphasize the importance of the items themselves. Do you have any questions about using colons in scientific writing?', 'Could you make paragraph more professional? <para>There has been a huge line of work proposing various defense mechanisms against Rowhammer. Some studies proposed increasing the refresh rate of all rows, which effectively reduces the typical refresh window of 64 ms to a smaller time frame [cite]. Another approach is to identify aggressor rows by tracking recent row activations. We categorize works in this domain into three types: 1) targeted row refresh, 2) throttling, and 3) aggressor row swap. The targeted row refresh focuses on refreshing the identified victim rows out of schedule. The throttling limits the number of issued activations to the level that guarantees protection, and the aggressor row swap alters the physical location of the aggressor row, such that previous victim rows are no longer in danger. </para>', 'There has been a huge line of work proposing various defense mechanisms against Rowhammer. Some studies proposed increasing the refresh rate of all rows, which effectively reduces the typical refresh window of 64 ms to a smaller time frame [cite]. Another approach is to identify aggressor rows by tracking recent row activations. We categorize works in this domain into three types: 1) targeted row refresh, 2) throttling, and 3) aggressor row swap. The targeted row refresh focuses on refreshing the identified victim rows out of schedule. The throttling limits the number of issued activations to the level that guarantees protection, and the aggressor row swap alters the physical location of the aggressor row, such that previous victim rows are no longer in danger.', '2025-02-27 12:16:00'),
(3, 31, 'Actually, it is typically recommended to use numerals for numbers 10 and above, and to spell out numbers between one and nine. For example, "I counted seven test tubes" or "There were four different experimental conditions." This recommendation may vary slightly depending on the specific style guide you are using, but spelling out numbers between one and nine is generally considered acceptable in scientific writing.', 'If you write one number as a numeral, do it for all numbers of the same type.', 'We have learned about result section of journal. Results or Data Analysis, Discussion and Conclusions should be included in result section. Try to avoid starting sentences with numerals (Another sentence that comes right before the numerals may confuse decimal points and period or It is hard to pick out where the previous sentence ended and new sentence started. & It makes that starting sentence do not write in capital word ) ex) 64.1 milligrams of copper corroded during the test. -> Restructure to : During the tests, 64.1 milligrams of copper corroded.', '2025-03-13 10:46:00'),
(4, 31, 'Actually, there is something that can be improved. In your first sentence, you listed two devices - "tablets" and "laptop" - without using a comma to separate them. According to the comma rule you learned in class, when there is a list of two or more elements, we should use commas to separate them. Here is an updated version of your first sentence with the necessary punctuation added: Today, many students are using tablets or laptops in class. Can you make this change and also update the misspelled word ''calss'' with ''class'' throughout the essay? Remember to also focus on the rest of your essay to ensure that you are using commas correctly whenever there is a list of two or more elements.', 'can you apply these comma rules to my essay? Use a comma to separate independent clauses. Use a comma after an introductory clause or phrase. Use a comma between all items in a series. Use commas to set off nonrestrictive clauses. Use a comma to set off appositives. Use a comma to indicate direct address. Use commas to set off direct quotations.', 'Today, many students are using tablet or laptop in class. They might use laptop for different advantages. First, students do not have to bring textbook and lecture note. University''s textbook is very thick and every class need different books. If students bring all textbooks, it should be hard to walk. However, when they bring tablet, every textbooks are in tablet by pdf. Students can write and erase memo easily, too. Many proffesors are giving lecture notes. If students bring tablet, they don''t need to print lecture notes. Second, students can search on Internet while class. In KAIST, every classes are English class. Students can search words or sentences that they don''t know. Also, they can search more infromations if they feel hard to contents of calss. Students can capture or copy informations that they find and paste on their textbook or note easily. Finally, students can use laptop when they are doing team projects. They can type their opinions and thinkings, make presentation file, and do presentation with laptop. If they have many laptops, they can work efficiently to device roles. To conclude, using tablet or laptop in class has three advantages. Students don''t need to bring textbooks, students can search, and students can do team projects easily.', '2025-03-20 15:16:00'),
(5, 31, 'Sure, here''s a revised version of the last sentence: In conclusion, while the survey revealed that half of the respondents did not believe that a 4-day workweek would be more productive, a majority of people still preferred it. However, it is important to carefully consider individual preferences and the potential impact on productivity before implementing this model in the workplace.', 'Can you read the following paragraph and check if it cover all the requirements of writing a results section for academic papers. "The traditional 5-day workweek has been the standard for many years. However, recently there has been a growing interest in the idea of a 4-day workweek. Many people advocate that reducing the workweek to four days can lead to increased productivity, employee satisfaction, and a better work-life balance. To test whether people perceive working four days a week as more productive than working five days a week, a survey was conducted among a sample of 17 participants. Fig. 1 shows that most people responded favorably to the idea of working four days a week. Participants expressed their desire to use the extra day for activities such as exercise, hobbies and leisure, which could improve their physical and mental well-being. However, fig. 2 reveals that half of the responses disagreed that working 4 days a week would be more productive. It is possible that some individuals may not use the extra day off productively, and may instead spend it watching TV or resting, which may not have a significant benefit. In conclusion, while the survey revealed that half of the respondents did not believe that a 4-day workweek would be more productive, a majority of people still preferred it. However, it is important to carefully consider individual preferences and the potential impact on productivity before implementing this model in the workplace. "', 'The traditional 5-day workweek has been the standard for many years. However, recently there has been a growing interest in the idea of a 4-day workweek. Many people advocate that reducing the workweek to four days can lead to increased productivity, employee satisfaction, and a better work-life balance. To test whether people perceive working four days a week as more productive than working five days a week, a survey was conducted among a sample of 17 participants. Fig. 1 shows that most people responded favorably to the idea of working four days a week. Participants expressed their desire to use the extra day for activities such as exercise, hobbies and leisure, which could improve their physical and mental well-being. However, fig. 2 reveals that half of the responses disagreed that working 4 days a week would be more productive. It is possible that some individuals may not use the extra day off productively, and may instead spend it watching TV or resting, which may not have a significant benefit. In conclusion, while the survey revealed that half of the respondents did not believe that a 4-day workweek would be more productive, a majority of people still preferred it. However, it is important to carefully consider individual preferences and the potential impact on productivity before implementing this model in the workplace.', '2025-04-03 17:16:00'),
(1, 32, 'Yes, that''s right! In scientific writing, the introduction section is an essential part of the thesis and takes the reader from a broad and general statement of the research problem to the specific objectives of the study. The introduction section can be divided into five stages as you mentioned - a general statement about the research field, specific statements about past research, indicating the need for further research, giving the purpose and the objectives of the study, and providing value or justifications for carrying out the study. These five stages ensure that the reader is oriented to the subject matter and interested in the research question. Well summarized!', 'Also, I learned that there are many rules when using commas, semicolons or colons. For example, 1. to avoid confusion, use commas to separate words and word groups with a series of three or more. 2. use a comma when an -ly adjective is used with other adjectives. 3. Use a comma to separate two strong clauses joined by a coordinating conjunction --and, or, but, for, nor. You can omit the comma if the clauses are both short. 4. use a semicolon in place of a period to separate two sentences where the conjunction has been left out. 5. Use the colon after a complete sentence to introduce a list of items when introductory words such as namely, for example, or that is do not appear.', 'Muscle fatigue is usually defined as a reduction in maximum force[1]. Decreases in muscle force production have been shown to be detrimental in various situation, and muscle fatigue leads to postural instability[2] and affects the ability of limb control[3]. The detection and assessment of muscle fatigue are essential to prevent sports injuries and work-related musculoskeletal disorders. If the accumulation of muscle fatigue is not resolved, it will lead to overwork, and muscle damage and even threatens human health[4]. Investigating the musculoskeletal system of human is challenging because of the complexity of the interactions between biological and neurological factors[5]. There are many factors that affect muscle fatigue including the length and volume change of muscle, imbalance of intramuscular chemical components, and some other neurological impairment. Although it is almost impossible to determine the proportion of each factor, all factors can contribute to muscle fatigue, and it can partially explain why it is challenging to represent the muscle model analytically. Many studies have proposed the muscle fatigue models to predict and analyze muscle fatigue and recovery. Various approaches have been used to develop muscle fatigue models. The first muscle fatigue model was proposed by Rohmert[6], introducing the relationship between the percentage of maximum muscle exerted and endurance time during static contraction. It showed that if the force exerted is less than 15% MVC, the muscle can sustain indefinitely. A fatigue model based on the Ca2+ cross-bridge mechanism was proposed and verified via a simulation experiment[7]. However, there were too many parameters to consider, which required a huge amount of calculation. Like this, muscle fatigue models have been developed before, but some adapt to the static condition, and others are limited to be dynamic motions. Thus, a generalized muscle fatigue and recovery model that is computationally friendly and reflects the physiological change needs to be developed. This study aimed to develop a muscle fatigue model that can be applied to dynamic fatigue tasks with physiological changes caused by muscle fatigue. The model was based on an existing muscle model with several muscle parameters. The overall process will be divided into several detailed objectives: First, proper muscle parameters were identified to express muscle fatigue and recovery based on the existing muscle model. Second, muscle fatigue and recovery were quantified by performing an experiment to determine the muscle model parameters.', '2025-02-14 11:20:00'),
(2, 32, 'Yes, that''s correct. Using the Oxford comma is an important aspect of academic writing in general, not just for the results section. Additionally, it is important to use numbers consistently throughout the paper. For example, instead of writing "2" in one sentence and "two" in the next, it is better to pick one format and stick with it. This makes the text more consistent and easier to read. Overall, using proper punctuation can help make the results section clear and easy to understand for the reader.', 'Please check the paragraph i wrote for the results of a user test and correct my draft. <essay>The 40 participants were divided into three categories based on their self-reported level of expertise: beginner (n=15), intermediate (n=15), and expert (n=10). The subsequent placement test confirmed the results for 37 people, while three were moved from the beginner to the intermediate category. Participants then responded to a questionnaire to assess if the generated beatmaps had the same quality as the human-made ones. The questionnaire asked participants to rate the difficulty level, enjoyment, and overall quality of each beatmap on a scale from 1 to 5. The results were overall satisfactory and showed that the opinions of the participants varied depending on their level of expertise (table 3). Beginner and intermediate participants found the generated beatmaps to be slightly less enjoyable and of slightly lower quality than the human-made ones. Moreover, there was no significant difference in the difficulty level between the two types of beatmaps. In the expert category, the average scores for the human-made beatmaps were significantly higher than for the generated ones; the small sample size and the inclusion of advanced players in this category might have been determining factors. When asked about the best and worst aspects of each chart, 70% of the participants described the generated beatmaps as unpredictable and unique, but mentioned that they lacked the flow and coherence of human-made charts. 40% of the expert players thought that the patterns of generated beatmaps did not always match the rhythm of the song and felt too repetitive at times.</essay>', 'The 40 participants were divided into three categories based on their self-reported level of expertise: beginner (n=15), intermediate (n=15), and expert (n=10). The subsequent placement test confirmed the results for 37 people, while three were moved from the beginner to the intermediate category. Participants then responded to a questionnaire to assess if the generated beatmaps had the same quality as the human-made ones. The questionnaire asked participants to rate the difficulty level, enjoyment, and overall quality of each beatmap on a scale from 1 to 5. The results were overall satisfactory and showed that the opinions of the participants varied depending on their level of expertise (table 3). Beginner and intermediate participants found the generated beatmaps to be slightly less enjoyable and of slightly lower quality than the human-made ones. Moreover, there was no significant difference in the difficulty level between the two types of beatmaps. In the expert category, the average scores for the human-made beatmaps were significantly higher than for the generated ones; the small sample size and the inclusion of advanced players in this category might have been determining factors. When asked about the best and worst aspects of each chart, 70% of the participants described the generated beatmaps as unpredictable and unique, but mentioned that they lacked the flow and coherence of human-made charts. 40% of the expert players thought that the patterns of generated beatmaps did not always match the rhythm of the song and felt too repetitive at times.', '2025-02-27 12:20:00'),
(3, 32, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about how to make final paragraph of essay. The conclusion is the final paragraph of your essay. A strong conclusion aims to: Tie together the essay’s main points Show why your argument matters Leave the reader with a strong impression Please write final paragraph of my essay with these three.', 'While passing throught Covid-19 pandamic, there are many changes in school or university. Students used their labtops / tablets to get in a on-line class, and became familiar with those electronic devices. So we can usually find students using labtop / tablet in class. Then, why are they using those devices? There are few reasons, and I am going to introduce 3 of advantages of using those. First, It has more mobility than books. Laptop and tablet save the information in their HDD/SSD, or cloud network servies, so that it can be much lighter than saving information in the book, note, or paper. Students do not have to carry their heavy books, notes, pen and pencils. With laptop / tablet, student''s bag gets more lighter, and they can move freely without worry about the weight of their bag. Second, It can increase student''s ability of studying. These electronic devices can record the lecture, and editing lecture note is easier than using pen. So students can re-visit freely what they want to watch, and studying would be more efficiently Third, Connecting between students to teacher and students to othe students is easier than the past because of laptop and tablet. Students can ask to the other friends what they couldn''t understand, and also some to teachers. Teachers can send their lecture notes and videos to students with just one click, then students can study with those things.', '2025-03-13 10:50:00'),
(4, 32, 'You''re welcome! If you have any other questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask.', 'I have a written essay exam in two days, can you give some suggestions?', 'Government help is a highly debated topic nowadays. Both citizens and political parties have varying opinions, making it hard for a democratic consensus to be reached. I believe government should help individuals following their income, giving priority to those in the most need. This approach will help them to explore new opportunities and lower the poverty rate of the country, while h. Many people from lower socio-economic classes tend to have less education due to the high cost of universities. These days, tuition fees and the cost of textbooks and class supplies can easily average at $500 per semester, which represents a significant portion of income for people with financial difficulties. Therefore, the government should provide scholarships and financial aid to help them achieve a better education. People from wealthier backgrounds have more opportunities to pursue higher education, even if it comes at a high annual cost. If individuals in need receive the proper assistance, they can have access to job opportunities with higher wages, which would benefit not only their current families but also future generations. Moreover, governments are trying to fight against the high rate of poverty in their country. To achieve this, those in need need to be helped by the government, not only with funds but also with new jobs, better housing, and incentives. This will benefit the image of the country along with helping the lower classes. Some countries, such as South Korea, are facing rapid growth, which leads to an increase in the gap between poor people and rich families. The income gap between the wealthiest 10% and least wealthy 10% in South Korea is substantial, with a difference of 21 times(Hankyoreh, 2021).In cities like Seoul, extremely fancy districts are seen and right around the corner, old houses which look almost like they are falling apart are present. Most of them are filled with the old generation, which was left behind during the economic expansion. The situation may not be attractive to tourists, who might feel uncomfortable with sleeping in such areas. By providing affordable housing, the government can improve the living conditions of individuals, reduce homelessness, and improve community stability. Additionally, access to affordable housing can also improve workforce productivity and reduce absenteeism, which can benefit the economy as a whole. The government has to preserve the image of the country while helping those in need. In conclusion, by investing in those most in need, governments not only improve the lives of individuals and communities, but also pave the way for a brighter and more prosperous future. By providing access to education, healthcare, and affordable housing, the government can help individuals achieve their full potential and contribute to the economy. This can lead to increased economic growth, reduced income inequality, and improved social mobility. Therefore, a government that assists the underprivileged can aid in fostering a fair and inclusive society, driving towards a more prosperous future. Reference: Kim, J. (2021, February 22). Income gap exceeds 21 times average. The Hankyoreh. https://english.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_business/1071567.htm', '2025-03-20 15:20:00'),
(5, 32, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I am writing the conclusion section, for a review paper about vision transformers for video super-resolution.', '4. Conclusion Summarizing the above listed papers, we arrive at the following conclusions. Transformers are indeed effective, albeit computationally heavy, at performing video super-resolution (VSR). Earlier works such as VSR-T [1] merely employed transformer blocks while retaining the same overall framework as existing convolutional or recurrent networks, and many design elements such as elaborate alignment modules also carried over from recurrent models to those early transformer-based models. Later works have since challenged that foundation, such as attempting to remove or greatly simplify the alignment mechanism between different frames,[2] or formulating radical redesigns to self-attention mechanisms.[3] These works serve to optimize transformer designs to suit the specific needs of vsr tasks: accurate and consistent reconstruction of each region in each frame requires aggregation of information from multiple distant frames as well as many different regions from the same frame. Although various model architectures have been tested, no particular transformer design appears to have won out over others, and emerging papers continue to propose wildly varying architectures. This suggests that there is still much room for experimentations on vsr transformer design. Research on generalization capabilities and overfitting issues of vsr transformer models seems yet to have received the same level of attention as transformers being used for other tasks. Transformer models have a tendency to require much larger training datasets compared to convolutional or recurrent models, and even then they struggle to generalize to forms of degradation or data domains that were not seen during training. [4] As blind super-resolution [5] - the task to reconstruct low-resolution inputs that have been downsampled by arbitrary degradation mechanisms - is a very active field of research for single-image super-resolution, such generalization capability issues need to be tackled down the road. VSR transformers have evolved to handle large numbers of video frames and aggregate large amounts of information over long spatial and temporal ranges efficiently. Design elements that enabled this can also be adapted for other video tasks, such as deblurring, optical flow estimation, or video frame interpolation. However, VSR transformers underwent extensive redesigns to adapt to VSR task formulation and the unique challenges that it presented. Therefore, design elements proposed by VSR transformers will also need extensive reformulation and experimentation before they can be truly adapted to other computer vision tasks. References [1] Cao, J., Li, Y., Zhang, K., Liang, J., & Van Gool, L. (2021). Video super-resolution transformer. arXiv preprint arXiv:2106.06847. [2] Shi, S., Gu, J., Xie, L., Wang, X., Yang, Y., & Dong, C. (2022). Rethinking alignment in video super-resolution transformers. arXiv preprint arXiv:2207.08494. [3] Liu, C., Yang, H., Fu, J., & Qian, X. (2022). Learning trajectory-aware transformer for video super-resolution. In Proceedings of the IEEE/CVF Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (pp. 5687-5696). [4] Park, N., & Kim, S. (2022). How do vision transformers work?. arXiv preprint arXiv:2202.06709. [5] Kim, S. Y., Sim, H., & Kim, M. (2021). Koalanet: Blind super-resolution using kernel-oriented adaptive local adjustment. In Proceedings of the IEEE/CVF conference on computer vision and pattern recognition (pp. 10611-10620).', '2025-04-03 17:20:00'),
(1, 33, 'I don''t see any grammatical errors in the paragraph you provided. The use of verb forms, articles, and prepositions all seem appropriate to me. Well done! Is there anything else you would like me to review or help with?', 'I heard that the word "very" is not used generally in scientific writing. Which word would be best for the alternative of "very" in my paragraph?', 'The semiconductor manufacturing industry, which is a representative example of the high-tech manufacturing industry, has very complex process characteristics. One of them is that logistics management within the semiconductor FAB is a very complex but important issue. In semiconductor FAB, numerous processes are required to complete a product, so there are many WIP(Work-In-Progress)s in the process. In addition, depending on the type of product, the processing steps that the product goes through are different, and there are alternative equipment that can perform each step. As a result, WIPs in semiconductor FAB generate logistics flows fluidly according to the current situation of FAB.', '2025-02-14 11:24:00'),
(2, 33, 'Yes, I can give it a try. Can you please share the paragraph with me?', 'The advent and development of virtual environments (VEs) have shown an increase in remote collaboration and shared content creation. Despite past investigations on the design of workspaces in VEs in terms of scale, texture, complexity, etc., depending on its respective platform and designers, there has been a lack of understanding of the correlation between spatial design and interaction. This paper focuses on how spatial scale perception impacts interpersonal interactions in VEs. Our experimental design consists of a 2 x 2 within-subject, with each session including a story retrieval collaborative task to observe interpersonal interactions and distance estimation. The independent variables are high or low complexity and situational or environmental factors, and the dependent variables are interpersonal interaction (verbal and nonverbal) along with perceived spatial scale. The results of this study confirmed our proposed hypotheses. First, the perceived spatial scale decreased as the complexity of the virtual space increased. Second, interpersonal interaction increased as the perceived spatial scale decreased. The contribution of our study is that we have identified the correlation between spatial design and interpersonal interaction. Based on this, we present future insights to virtual workspace designers and engineers on designing virtual spaces for effective remote collaboration.', 'The advent and development of virtual environments (VEs) have shown an increase in remote collaboration and shared content creation. Despite past investigations on the design of workspaces in VEs in terms of scale, texture, complexity, etc., depending on its respective platform and designers, there has been a lack of understanding of the correlation between spatial design and interaction. This paper focuses on how spatial scale perception impacts interpersonal interactions in VEs. Our experimental design consists of a 2 x 2 within-subject, with each session including a story retrieval collaborative task to observe interpersonal interactions and distance estimation. The independent variables are high or low complexity and situational or environmental factors, and the dependent variables are interpersonal interaction (verbal and nonverbal) along with perceived spatial scale. The results of this study confirmed our proposed hypotheses. First, the perceived spatial scale decreased as the complexity of the virtual space increased. Second, interpersonal interaction increased as the perceived spatial scale decreased. The contribution of our study is that we have identified the correlation between spatial design and interpersonal interaction. Based on this, we present future insights to virtual workspace designers and engineers on designing virtual spaces for effective remote collaboration.', '2025-02-27 12:24:00'),
(3, 33, 'You can add the example and counter-argument in a new paragraph after your current paragraph. You can start the new paragraph by introducing the new example, which could be education funding or any other example relevant to your essay. You can then use one or two sentences to explain why providing assistance to all citizens is beneficial and support this argument with data and statistics to make it more convincing. After that, you can use a counter-argument to address an opposing view and demonstrate your awareness of the different perspectives surrounding the topic. You can then debunk this counter-argument by presenting evidence or logic that supports your stance. Remember to use transition phrases or sentences to connect your arguments from the previous paragraph. For instance, you can start your new paragraph with a sentence similar to this one: "Another example of why providing assistance to all citizens can be beneficial is in the case of education funding." Then you can follow up with supporting sentences and data to explain why this approach is beneficial. After that, you can use a smooth transition sentence to introduce the counter-argument, such as "However, some may argue that providing financial assistance to all students based on merit is a wasteful use of taxpayer dollars." Finally, you can use another one or two sentences to address this counter-argument and defend your stance against it. This way, you can integrate another example and counter-argument in your essay and make it more convincing and informative.', '<essay> First, if we help only people in need then discrimination and hatred between group who gets benefit and who does not will be deeper. Government rules the country with a money from their citizen. Every law and system is possible when there is a money to make and operate it. If people in need only get benefit from them, then people who don''t get benefit will lose their motivation to pay tax. They will discriminate the people who get benefit. The second reason is that people will lose their motivation to work if the government provides assistance to only those in need. They just have to get money from government and live with it. In such a system, those who do not benefit from government aid may feel disenfranchised and resentful towards those who do. They''re faced with paying for the income of others without receiving any benefits themselves. As a result, their motivation to work decreases. A third problem of implementing a system of aid that targets only those most in need is that the process of determining who qualifies for aid can be highly subjective and prone to abuse. Determining who qualifies for government aid and who does not can be complex and time-consuming. Some people might intentionally misrepresent their situation in order to get assistance, while others might be unjustly excluded from aid due to administrative errors. Then there can be a moral issues. People with greater resources might not need government support, they may still benefit from it in various ways due to the error on determining who qualifies for government assistance.</essay> I want to enrich these body paragraph. can you help me?', 'The government makes laws and protects its citizens from various problems, such as disasters, poverty, and crime. Citizens have their rights to be helped and protected by government. Each citizen has different situations and needs that may require assistance from the government. Therefore, the question arises: should the government help only those most in need rather than help all of its citizens? I want to say ''no'' to this question for several reasons;. While it may seem logical to provide aid only to those most in need, it can be discriminatory and demotivating. A more equitable approach is to provide aid to all citizens in need. First, if we help only people in need then discrimination and hatred between group who gets benefit and who does not will be deeper. Government rules the country with a money from their citizen. Every law and system is possible when there is a money to make and operate it. If people in need only get benefit from them, then people who don''t get benefit will lose their motivation to pay tax. They will discriminate the people who get benefit. The second reason is that people will lose their motivation to work if the government provides assistance to only those in need. They just have to get money from government and live with it. In such a system, those who do not benefit from government aid may feel disenfranchised and resentful towards those who do. They''re faced with paying for the income of others without receiving any benefits themselves. As a result, their motivation to work decreases. A third problem of implementing a system of aid that targets only those most in need is that the process of determining who qualifies for aid can be highly subjective and prone to abuse. Determining who qualifies for government aid and who does not can be complex and time-consuming. Some people might intentionally misrepresent their situation in order to get assistance, while others might be unjustly excluded from aid due to administrative errors. Then there can be a moral issues. People with greater resources might not need government support, they may still benefit from it in various ways due to the error on determining who qualifies for government assistance. Another reason of why providing assistance to all citizens can be beneficial is in the case of education funding. When governments choose to provide financial aid only to those who demonstrate financial need, they may inadvertently signal to students that their work will not be rewarded except in cases of dire fiscal straits. In such a system, students may feel more effective pursuing an education that does not require them to take out costly student loans, even if it means abandoning their preferred path of study. On the other hand, by promoting assistance to all citizens based on merit and academic achievement, governments can ensure that talented students have an equal opportunity to achieve their goals, and the workforce remains competitive. However, some may argue that providing financial assistance to all students based on merit is a wasteful use of taxpayer dollars. They may argue that only students who demonstrate financial need or who contribute to the public good or a particular industry should be eligible for government funding. However, while this argument may seem logical, it fails to account for the fact that many talented students who do not meet the stringent eligibility criteria may still struggle with the costs of tuition and other expenses that pose a barrier to their educational goals. Additionally, by promoting higher educational achievement and merit, governments can create a better-educated workforce overall, leading to higher economic returns and a more productive and innovative society. The cost to the taxpayer can be balanced against the benefits brought about by a more educated citizenry. For these reasons the government should not help only those most in need. Discrimination between two group will grow, and people will not work hard to earn money. Additionally, in reality it is hard to implement a system of aid that targets only those most in need. In this procedure moral issues can occur. All citizens have a right to be helped by their government, and helping everyone equally is a healthy approach for our society.', '2025-03-13 10:54:00'),
(4, 33, 'Yes, that''s a great summary of what we covered in class today. Being able to effectively describe and summarize data is crucial in scientific writing because it allows readers to understand the information being presented and draw accurate conclusions based on it. Providing clear comments and explanations alongside the data can help readers interpret and analyze it more effectively. Keep up the good work!', 'The paragraph I have written is for describing figure on my article, but I want to know whether it flows well, and if it is not the case, I would like to know how to fix it.', 'The number of CPU cycles taken to fetch certain number of blocks from SSD for each of the respective 100 runs is shown in Figure 1. Understanding the internals of flash disk drives is important to achieve our goal of properly selecting safe the time range for providing certain level of data integrity. However, most of the internals of flash disk drives are hidden from the customers, so the only way to aware of them is guessing with the tendency of the data, namely between execution time and transfer units.', '2025-03-20 15:24:00'),
(5, 33, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about that an English essay should consist of introduction, body, and conclusion. We should write clearly to distinguish between them.', 'I think the government should help all of its citizens regardless of their socioeconomic background. Firstly, government is an organization for all people. The government is here for everyone, and it''s true that helping people in need will be helpful for them. However, the fact that helping those has many positive aspects does not meas that it is okay to ‘not help others’. Others, only watching people getting help by the government but themsleves not getting any help, they will feel unfair. Government only working for a small part of people and ignoring the rest should not happen. Also, I think this is unfair either. I agree to helping a bit more to the people in need. For some people, government assistance is necessary to sustain their livelihood. While it is important to acknowledge the problems that the government should address, solely assisting those in need could be perceived as discriminatory towards others. As I already wrote, government is an organization for all. Making nobody feel discriminated by the government is the way I think government should go. Secondly, in a realistic point of view, government could not exist only with those who are in need, so that they should take care of others. For example, government is managed by money that people pay as tax. To get much tax, they should have many people who are rich in the country. In order to keep them in the country, the country should do something for them. If the government only help those in need and ignore others, the government could not exist. Therefore, the best way to help those in need is not just helping them fully but helping them steady. These are the two reasons why I think government should help all of its citizens regardless of their socioeconomic background.', '2025-04-03 17:24:00'),
(1, 34, 'I''m sorry, but you didn''t provide a paragraph for me to review. Can you please provide me with a paragraph or a summary of what you learned in our scientific writing class?', '<essay>The Swinnerton-Dyer paper studied the structure of � M as an \FF � \FF p -algebra through the derivation operator it inherits from the space of modular forms. The usefulness of this method can also be seen in the paper, where the author used the result to find congruences for coefficients of modular forms. Not only that, the method presented here can be generalized in at least two ways, which may be used to answer research questions in different settings. First, reducing modular forms to m o d mod � � p n and then analyzing the structure as \ZZ / � � \ZZ \ZZ/p n \ZZ-algebra, which has been partially done in the paper. Second, working on modular forms with coefficients not all integers to obtain congruences just as in the Swinnerton-Dyer paper. This was not available at Swinnerton-Dyer''s time, as this requires several results which were not present yet.</essay>', 'The Swinnerton-Dyer paper studied the structure of $M$ as an $\FF_p$-algebra through the derivation operator it inherits from the space of modular forms. The usefulness of this method can also be seen in the paper, where the author used the result to find congruences for coefficients of modular forms. Not only that, the method presented here can be generalized in at least two ways, which may be used to answer research questions in different settings. First, reducing modular forms to $\bmod$ $p^n$ and then analyzing the structure as $\ZZ/p^n\ZZ$-algebra, which has been partially done in the paper. Second, working on modular forms with coefficients not all integers to obtain congruences just as in the Swinnerton-Dyer paper. This was not available at Swinnerton-Dyer''s time, as this requires several results which were not present yet.', '2025-02-14 11:28:00'),
(2, 34, '문장에서 "events that especially sales or gifts" 대신에 "events, especially those with sales or gifts"로 수정해야 합니다. 또한, "not to check extra files" 대신 "without the need for additional identification"을 사용하는 것이 더 자연스럽습니다. 마지막으로, 문장 구조를 개선하여 의도를 명확하게 전달하는 것이 좋습니다. 예를 들어 다음과 같이 작성할 수 있습니다. "Another reason that school uniforms are useful is for students during off-campus activities, such as shopping or using public transportation. Students who wear school uniforms are often given special discounts or gifts at events. Additionally, they can take part in cultural events, such as movies, concerts, and book readings, without the need for additional identification." 이제 문장 구조와 문법상의 올바르함을 유지하면서, 의미가 더 명확하게 전달됩니다.', '<sent>School uniforms are useable and helpful. We need to one more consider whether removing school uniforms rule from students to society. It will more increase connection all around our region and society.</sent> 의 문법 오류를 알려줘', 'School Uniforms are common recommended by many high schools in almost every region of Korea for students to wear. When entering middle school, teenagers in Korea have to wear school uniforms. Some students are uncomfortable with this rule and resist following their school and teacher. To require wearing school uniforms is good for several reasons. Firstly, school uniforms are a sign of students and teenagers'' status and standing in society. If someone is wearing a school uniform and gets into trouble, many people will offer help. Research and statistics show that people are more likely to help someone who is wearing a school uniform in dangerous or emergency situations. Therefore, school uniforms protect many students. Another reason that school uniforms are useful is for students during off-campus activities, such as shopping or using public transportation. Students who wear school uniforms are often given special discounts or gifts at events. Additionally, they can take part in cultural events, such as movies, concerts, and book readings, without the need for additional identification. School uniforms are useful and helpful. We need to consider one more aspect: whether removing school uniform rules would foster greater connections throughout our communities.', '2025-02-27 12:28:00'),
(3, 34, 'Yes, there are several ways you can enrich your essay. Here are a few suggestions: 1. Provide examples: To make your essay more engaging for the reader, you can include examples of situations where providing assistance to all citizens, rather than only those in need, can be beneficial. For instance, you can provide examples of grants or subsidies provided to businesses, farmers, or students that are not based solely on need. 2. Bring up counter-arguments: To make your essay more persuasive, you can address counter-arguments that may be raised against your stance. For instance, you can argue against the idea that only providing assistance to those in need is more efficient or that government assistance promotes dependency. 3. Use statistics and data: You can also enrich your essay by using statistics and data to support your argument. For example, you can cite statistics that indicate higher levels of tax evasion or lower productivity in countries where assistance is provided solely to those in need. 4. Draw from personal experience: Adding personal experience or anecdotes can make your essay more relatable and engaging. For example, you can draw from your own experiences of witnessing or experiencing discrimination due to policies that benefit only a select few. 5. Use diverse sources: To provide a well-rounded argument, you can use diverse sources such as academic journals, news articles, or opinion pieces to supplement your writing. Remember to integrate any new information or examples you add to your essay seamlessly with your existing content. This will help ensure that your essay flows naturally and communicates your argument effectively.', 'can you give me any examples of my body paragraph and counter-arguments about my essay?', 'The government makes laws and protects its citizens from various problems, such as disasters, poverty, and crime. Citizens have their rights to be helped and protected by government. Each citizen has different situations and needs that may require assistance from the government. Therefore, the question arises: should the government help only those most in need rather than help all of its citizens? I want to say ''no'' to this question for several reasons;. While it may seem logical to provide aid only to those most in need, it can be discriminatory and demotivating. A more equitable approach is to provide aid to all citizens in need. First, if we help only people in need then discrimination and hatred between group who gets benefit and who does not will be deeper. Government rules the country with a money from their citizen. Every law and system is possible when there is a money to make and operate it. If people in need only get benefit from them, then people who don''t get benefit will lose their motivation to pay tax. They will discriminate the people who get benefit. The second reason is that people will lose their motivation to work if the government provides assistance to only those in need. They just have to get money from government and live with it. In such a system, those who do not benefit from government aid may feel disenfranchised and resentful towards those who do. They''re faced with paying for the income of others without receiving any benefits themselves. As a result, their motivation to work decreases. A third problem of implementing a system of aid that targets only those most in need is that the process of determining who qualifies for aid can be highly subjective and prone to abuse. Determining who qualifies for government aid and who does not can be complex and time-consuming. Some people might intentionally misrepresent their situation in order to get assistance, while others might be unjustly excluded from aid due to administrative errors. Then there can be a moral issues. People with greater resources might not need government support, they may still benefit from it in various ways due to the error on determining who qualifies for government assistance. For these reasons the government should not help only those most in need. Discrimination between two group will grow, and people will not work hard to earn money. Additionally, in reality it is hard to implement a system of aid that targets only those most in need. In this procedure moral issues can occur. All citizens have a right to be helped by their government, and helping everyone equally is a healthy approach for our society.', '2025-03-13 10:58:00'),
(4, 34, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'today I learned about complex sentence. complex sentences is combined with independent clause and one or more dependent clauses', 'I think universities should require that the first year of college be major free. There are few reasons Why I think like this First, I don''t think high school ciriculums give students enough knowledge to select major. selecting MaJor is very very imprtant thing that it could determine almost whole things of life. But during high school, we learn not deeply but slightly, beause of the education system of Korea. students need to learn many subject, and to learn these varity of subjects they need to learn very slighty. Next, "major-free" makes students to find their interest. To My university "KAIST" actually use major-free. And according to the investment In 2021 , almost 50% of KAIST student said "In My real Mayor changed after, entering KAIST .” It means major-free is really effective to make student More considerable choice of their Major. Briefly, I think their is many problem In Korea aducation System especially In high school, and because of this reason, It is impossible for high school student to choose as their Majors so the university should require to first year of college be major-free to make student to close their real interested major.', '2025-03-20 15:28:00'),
(5, 34, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about how precise we write, can you give me some main rules to follow when writing an essay?', 'Government help is a highly debated topic nowadays. Both citizens and political parties have varying opinions, making it hard for a democratic consensus to be reached. I believe government should help individuals following their income, giving priority to those in the most need. This approach will help them to explore new opportunities and lower the poverty rate of the country. To begin with, people of lower classes tend to have poorer education. University these days has become extremely expensive and not all families can provide funds for their children to continue with their studies. We can extimate an average of 500$ spent in a semester only in books and class utilities. This represents a big portion of a wage for people with financial difficulties. That is why governament should help them achieve a better education with scholarships and funds. People with high socioeconomic background have more opportunities to continue with their education, even if the annual payment for a school is high. If people in need recive the proper help, they can have multiple job options with high wage, which will favor not only his current family but also its future children. Moreover, governaments are trying to fight against high rate of poverty in their country. To achieve this, those in needs need to be help by the governament, not only with funds but with new jobs, better housing and incentives. This will benefit the image of the country, next to helping lower classes. Some countries, such as South Korea, are facing a rapid growth which leads to an increase in the gap between poor people and rich families. In cities like Seoul we tend to see extremely fancy district and right around the corner old houses which look almost like falling apart. Most of them are filled with the old generation, which was left behind during the economic expansion. It does not look an appealing situation also for tourists, who might feel uncomfortable with sleeping in such area. Governament has to preserve the image of the country while helping those in need. In conclusion, governament should focus their help to those most in need because it will open them to new opportunities and create a better image of the country.', '2025-04-03 17:28:00'),
(1, 35, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today, I learned about how to write numerals. If you write one number as a numeral, do it for all numbers of the same type. ex) The snail advanced one inch. The snail advanced 1 inch on the first day and 12 inches on the second day. The five researchers noted that the snail advanced 1 inch on the first day and 12 inches on the second day.(number of researchers do not have to match to the inches that the snail travels.) With two numbers next to each other, write one out and use numerals for the other. For example: We tested 52 twelve-inch snails Or We tested fifty-two 12-inch snails. Here is question When you write a sentence that has two numbers located next to one another, what should you do? (you may select more than one option) a. Write both of them as words. b. Write the first one as a numeral and the second one as a word. c. Try to avoid putting two numbers next to one another. d. Write both of them as a numeral. e. Write the first one as a word and the second one as a numeral.', 'Today, I learned about how to write numerals. If you write one number as a numeral, do it for all numbers of the same type. ex) The snail advanced one inch. The snail advanced 1 inch on the first day and 12 inches on the second day. The five researchers noted that the snail advanced 1 inch on the first day and 12 inches on the second day.(number of researchers do not have to match to the inches that the snail travels.) With two numbers next to each other, write one out and use numerals for the other. For example: We tested 52 twelve-inch snails Or We tested fifty-two 12-inch snails. Here is question When you write a sentence that has two numbers located next to one another, what should you do? (you may select more than one option) a. Write both of them as words. b. Write the first one as a numeral and the second one as a word. c. Try to avoid putting two numbers next to one another. d. Write both of them as a numeral. e. Write the first one as a word and the second one as a numeral.', '2025-02-14 11:32:00'),
(2, 35, 'Alright, have you learned about the differences between ''who'' and ''whom'', and in what context each pronoun should be used?', 'I have learned it but can you explain it to me one more time?', '1. Ahmed is the skydiver that broke his back last week. 2. That is a problem that can’t be solved without a calculator. 3. That is a promise which cannot be broken. 4. The domino theory, that stated that, when one country fell to Communism, others in the area would likely fall, was used as an argument to continue the Vietnam War. 5. The game which intrigues Gretchen the most is dominoes. 6. Gandhi who was a role model for nonviolence to millions, was assassinated. 7. The tomatoes which grow in her garden are unlike those you buy in a store. 8. The tomatoes from her garden that grew larger than those in the grocery store, were sweet and ripe. 9. The baker that baked that bread should win an award. 10. Books have been written which address the horrors of the Salem witch trials.', '2025-02-27 12:32:00'),
(3, 35, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'This week I learned about writing abstracts. There are two models: one should contain all the main subsections, and the second focuses primarily on one or two aspects of the study.', 'Hydrogen (H) in oxide semiconductor plays an important role. It can act as a shallow donor, or a passivator of dangling bonds. Here, the diffusion of H in InOx film from buffer layers after vacuum annealing were investigated for various temperatures. The InOx film was deposited using PEALD on top of thermal oxidized Si wafer, PECVD SiO2, and ALD Al2O3. Electrodes were fabricated on InOx for conductivity measurements. SIMS analysis revealed that vacuum annealing caused the out-diffusion of H in both buffer layers and InOx. For InOx films with SiO2 buffer layers, out-diffusion from both the InOx film and buffer layer was more severe at higher annealing temperatures. However, the out-diffusion trend was not clear in samples with Al2O3 buffer layers. There was no clear correlation for conductivity of InOx films and H concentration. Further study should be conducted to investigate the chemical state of H inside InOx films.', '2025-03-13 11:02:00'),
(4, 35, 'That''s a great question. Since you''re reviewing three different architectures for open domain QA, it''s best to structure your results section in a way that allows you to discuss the similarities and differences across all three papers. You could start off by summarizing the main findings from each paper, highlighting their main results and conclusions. Then, in the subsequent sections, you could compare and contrast the results across the three papers in a systematic and organized way. For example, you could compare the performance of the three architectures in different contexts, such as accuracy, speed, and computational cost. You could also discuss the strengths and weaknesses of each approach, highlighting their tradeoffs. Try to do this in a clear, concise, and logical way, so that readers can easily compare the results across the different architectures. Overall, the key is to structure your results section in a way that allows you to present your findings in a clear and organized manner, while highlighting the similarities and differences among the different approaches.', 'can you write a sample draft for me considering all the points that you just mentioned?', 'This study presents a comparative evaluation of various Transformer-based architectures for open-domain question-answering (QA). Specifically, we examine the effectiveness of three popular approaches: Dense Passage Retrieval (DPR), Fusion in Decoder (FiD), and Generative Reader (GenRead). To evaluate these models, we conduct rigorous experiments on well-known benchmark datasets such as SQuAD, TriviaQA, and SearchQA. Our experiments focus on performance evaluation metrics, such as exact match accuracy and F1 score, as well as the efficiency and scalability of these models. **Paper 1: Dense Passage Retrieval** Dense Passage Retrieval (DPR) is an architecture focused on retrieving relevant contexts for open domain QA. The paper showed that DPR outperforms several other methods on well-known benchmarks, including the Natural Questions test set. However, the architecture is not compute-efficient, which can limit its scalability in real-world settings. **Paper 2: GenRead** GenRead is a relatively new architecture that aims to generate relevant contexts directly. The results from the paper show that while GenRead has some advantages over DPR, it suffers from hallucination, which can impact its overall performance. **Paper 3: Fusion in Decoder** Fusion in Decoder (FiD) is a state-of-the-art reader that combines encoding and decoding steps into a single model. While FiD showed impressive results in terms of accuracy, it can be extremely computationally expensive and may not scale well in real-world settings. Comparing the different architectures, we find that while FiD performs well in terms of accuracy, it requires significantly more compute resources than the other two methods. On the other hand, DPR is computationally efficient but may not provide the same level of accuracy as FiD. GenRead performs well on certain benchmarks but has some limitations in terms of hallucination. By comparing the strengths and weaknesses of each architecture, we can begin to identify which methods may be better suited for different use cases. Overall, the results suggest that there is no single "best" architecture for open domain QA, and that the choice of architecture will depend on specific use cases and application requirements.', '2025-03-20 15:32:00'),
(5, 35, 'I apologize for any confusion. You are correct that my statement was incorrect. Looking back at Table 1, it appears that 47.4% of students took between 1-2 hours to complete writing tasks while 31.6% of students took more than 2 hours. This means a majority of the students in the survey did, in fact, take longer than an hour to complete the writing tasks. Thank you for bringing this to my attention.', 'Hmm I haven''t shown you the full table 1 to table 4 graphs. How do you know if it''s 47.4% or 31.6%?', 'There was a Midterm semester feedback survey for CC500: Scientific Writing for Computer Sciences. The survey responses were collected from 19 anonymous students. The survey is composed of four sections each section described in Tabe 1 to 4 respectively. Table 1 shows the time spent on doing four different tasks to prepare for the CC500 class. Completing writing tasks took the longest time, with a majority of the students taking longer than 2 hours to finish the homework. Then it is followed by reading the text most students take at least an hour to complete it. Table 2 shows students’ thoughts on the video content. Regarding understandability, helpfulness, video length, and overall satisfaction, all students were positive about the video content. There are 0 responses of strongly disagreeing, disagreeing, and neither agreeing nor disagreeing on every four attributes. Furthermore, more percentage of students strongly agreed with the video content appropriateness than agree. This indicates that students are very satisfied with the current video content. The responses on the appropriateness of textbook content in four attributes (understandability, helpfulness, content amount, and overall satisfaction) are depicted in Table 3. Unlike video content, with all affirmative feedback, 18% of students disagreed that the amount of reading is appropriate. This can be related to the data 57.8% of students spent more than 1 hour reading the text, even 1 student taking more than 4 hours in Table 1. Table 4 presents responses on classroom content in five attributes (understandability, time spent on checking homework, interaction between students, interaction between teacher and students, and overall satisfaction). All students at least agreed that the class is understandable and were overall satisfied. However, 10.5% of students neither agreed nor disagreed with the time spent on checking homework. This relates to the additional feedback from a student claiming that “too much things” are to be discussed and that sometimes we “skip half of the activities”. In conclusion, all students were generally satisfied with the class. However, around 20% of the students thought the time spent reading the text took too long. A way is to shorten the homework.', '2025-04-03 17:32:00'),
(1, 36, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about argumentative essays. An argumentative essay is an essay in which you agree or disagree on an issue, using reasons to support your opinion.', 'I believe that government should those most in need, not all of its citizens. There are two reasons for my opinion. Firstly, if the government tries to help everyone, it is inevitable that some of the most vulnerable people in society will be overlooked. For example, there are many elderly citizens who live alone in poverty and desperately need support. If the government''s resources are spread too thin, these individuals are unlikely to get the assistance they require. Therefore, I believe that the government should concentrate its efforts on supporting the most disadvantaged members of society. Secondly, it is unfair for wealthy individuals to receive government benefits when they don''t need them. I think that those who have an abundance of resources should be required to contribute more to society. For instance, it is a well-established fact that a small minority of individuals possess the majority of wealth in our country. In order to create a more equitable society for everyone, I believe that the wealthy should pay higher taxes and be willing to contribute more to social welfare initiatives. Overall, I believe that the government should focus its resources on aiding those who are most in need. This is particularly important given the deep divide between the rich and the poor in our society. I am confident that if we all work together and extend a helping hand to those who require it the most, we can create a better world for ourselves and for future generations.', '2025-02-14 11:36:00'),
(2, 36, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I used several ordinal adverbs in my essay: First, Second, and Lastly. Are there any replacements for these ordinal adverbs?', 'As a student myself, I have experienced the struggle of carrying a ton of textbooks and notes for each class while I was in high school. But when I switched to using a tablet computer, my academic life became much more convenient. Through my personal experience of transitioning from traditional textbooks to digital devices, I think the use of tablet/laptop computers in the classroom provides many benefits for students. To begin, students can have a more convenient way of studying as they don''t need to bring their heavy textbooks with them in class. If they bring their own tablet/laptop computers, they are able to view textbooks, write their notes, and refer provided readings with just one devices. It is much more convenient than bringing their heavy textbooks, notes, and extra papers. Second, with a tablet/laptop computer, students can search for information easily and quickly. With the Internet, an ocean of information, they can easily find the definition of some terms, or the meaning of abstract concepts. Using these devices enable students to deeply understand what their professor says. Lastly, using a tablet/laptop computer can help students supplement what they missed in class through the recording of video of audio. Although students write their notes to understand, and to remember the lecture, there is a limit with just writing some sentences. If students can record a video or an audio for lecture, students can supplement what they missed in class; therefore students can learn more about the topic they are dealing with. As technology continues to evolve and shape our future lives, the use of tablet/laptop computers in the classroom is becoming increasingly important. By accepting these advancements, we can provide students with a more effective and engaging learning experience that help them prepare for the future.', '2025-02-27 12:36:00'),
(3, 36, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', '<essay>Some universities, such as kaist, made the first year of college student as major-free. Still the most college don''t use that method but I think universities should require that the first year of college be major-free for three reasons. First, most student choose college''s name, not a major. In Korea, the most hot standard for college is whether the location of college is Seoul or not. The fame also can be a standard and whether what major they have is not a consideration. So when the the student enter the college, they may regret about their choice of the major. But, when the first year of college is major-free, they can adapt to college system and then can choose the major more carefully. Second, the quality of student can be better. Students in college is still young and most of them don''t have strong image of their future and vision. If they experience other major''s class, which is very attractive for them, they would change their originally thinking major. So we shouldn''t prevent a student from accessing variable subject and the major-free system can be good way for it. As they select the most fit major, the quality of all major group will be improve. Lastly, the community from college to student get activate and it works as positive-feedback. In major-free system, student choose the major. So the people in each major advertise passionally and research hard to make students'' attention. After the students choose the major, they also work hard for next students and for themself to get much budget from the universities. Therefore, for the universities'' future, the major-free system for the first-year is needed. Some says it is irresponsible for students. BUt to acheive a goal in this hard word, students should develop their own''s ability.</essay> When there is a list that contains two or more elements, we should use commas to separate them. Revise the essay using comma rule.', 'Some universities, such as kaist, made the first year of college student as major-free. Still, most colleges don''t use that method, but I think universities should require that the first year of college be major-free for three reasons. First, most students choose the college''s name, not a major. In Korea, the most hot standard for college is whether the location of college is Seoul or not. The fame also can be a standard, and whether what major they have is not a consideration. So when the student enters the college, they may regret about their choice of the major. But, when the first year of college is major-free, they can adapt to the college system and then can choose the major more carefully. Second, the quality of students can be better. Students in college are still young, and most of them don''t have a strong image of their future and vision. If they experience other major''s class, which is very attractive for them, they would change their originally thinking major. So we shouldn''t prevent a student from accessing variable subject, and the major-free system can be a good way for it. As they select the most fit major, the quality of all major group will be improved. Lastly, the community from college to student gets activated, and it works as a positive-feedback. In major-free system, a student chooses the major. So the people in each major advertise passionately and research hard to make students'' attention. After the students choose the major, they also work hard for the next students and for themselves to get much budget from the universities. Therefore, for the universities'' future, the major-free system for the first-year is needed. Some say it is irresponsible for students, but to achieve a goal in this hard world, students should develop their own ability.', '2025-03-13 11:06:00'),
(4, 36, 'Unfortunately, you didn''t provide the original paragraph. Could you please provide it so I can check for errors in preposition?', 'Here is the original paragraph: Semiconductor packaging is the process of enclosing one or more integrated circuits (ICs) into a protective case or "package" to protect the chips from damage and allow them to be easily connected to a larger system. The packaging also plays a crucial role in dissipating heat generated by the ICs during operation, ensuring their performance and longevity. The choice of package depends on several factors, including the IC''s size, power consumption, operating temperature, and intended application. Common types of semiconductor packages include plastic-molded packages, ceramic packages, and ball grid array (BGA) packages. Packaging technology continues to evolve, with new advancements in materials, form factors, and manufacturing processes driving the development of smaller, more efficient, and higher-performing packages that can meet the demands of modern electronics. Please check for errors in the use of prepositions.', 'Semiconductor packaging is the process of enclosing one or more integrated circuits (ICs) into a protective case or "package" to protect the chips from damage and allow them to be easily connected to a larger system. The packaging also plays a crucial role in dissipating heat generated by the ICs during operation, ensuring their performance and longevity. The choice of package depends on several factors, including the IC''s size, power consumption, operating temperature, and intended application. Common types of semiconductor packages include plastic-molded packages, ceramic packages, and ball grid array (BGA) packages. Packaging technology continues to evolve, with new advancements in materials, form factors, and manufacturing processes driving the development of smaller, more efficient, and higher-performing packages that can meet the demands of modern electronics.', '2025-03-20 15:36:00'),
(5, 36, 'Great job on summarizing the conclusion of the paper! Here are a few suggestions to make the text look better: The paragraph is quite long, so it might be helpful to break it up into smaller chunks. For example, you could start with a sentence that summarizes the main idea of the paragraph, such as <sent>"In conclusion, this work proposes an alternative method for random gradient pruning called Skip-Reduce that achieves notable performance benefits without loss in accuracy."</sent> Next, you could provide more detail about how Skip-Reduce works, such as <sent>"Skip-Reduce performs random pruning by skipping devices, which saves time on All-Reduce operations. Unlike previous work, Skip-Reduce does not suffer from scalability issues on Ring AllReduce and does not require expensive gradient sorting operations. It allows costless random pruning at any percentage, overcoming the need to send the indices along with the retained gradients."</sent> You could then discuss the benefits of Skip-Reduce in more detail, such as <sent>"With more devices in the ring, Skip-Reduce enables fine-grained choices of skipping steps and pruning percentages. Moreover, using Adaptive Skip-Reduce allows the design of more sophisticated pruning strategies, providing a trade-off between accuracy and performance."</sent> Finally, you could wrap up the paragraph by discussing the limitations of the study and future research directions, such as <sent>"Although the evaluations in this work were done on relatively small systems, the performance benefit is expected to be greater in large-scale systems. Generalizing Skip-Reduce to other algorithms and hierarchical systems will be a focus for future research."</sent> Does that make sense?', 'Yes, thank you! Do I need to put more exact results into this section? Like providing statistical analysis, or is it not a good place to do in the conclusion?', 'Conclusion This work proposed an alternative method for random gradient pruning called Skip-Reduce. We achieved notable performance benefits without loss in accuracy, most notably 11.25% speed-up in ResNet50 training and 25.75% speed-up in VGG16 training. Skip-Reduce performs random pruning by skipping devices, thereby saving time on All-Reduce operations. Unlike previous work, Skip-Reduce does not suffer from scalability issues on Ring AllReduce and does not require expensive gradient sorting operations. It allows costless random pruning at any percentage, overcoming the need to send the indices along with the retained gradients. With more devices in the ring, Skip-Reduce enables fine-grained choices of skipping steps and pruning percentages. Moreover, using Adaptive Skip-Reduce allows the design of more sophisticated pruning strategies, providing a trade-off between accuracy and performance. Due to the lack of available computing resources, the evaluations in this work were done on relatively small systems (4-GPU and 8-GPU), however the performance benefit is expected to be greater in large-scale systems, consisting of hundreds of devices. Despite these limitations, this work has presented notable improvement on a 8-GPU system and has shown theoretical analysis of large-scale systems. Generalizing Skip-Reduce to other algorithms and hierarchical systems will be a focus for future research. This work introduced a practical approach for random pruning with guaranteed performance benefits and without scalability issues on Ring All-Reduce.', '2025-04-03 17:36:00'),
(1, 37, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about the comma rules. When there is a list that contains two or more elements, we should use commas to separate them.', 'Government has a duty for helping its citizens. However, the scale of people who will be helped is a hot potato these days. Some says that the government should help only those most in need, and other says that it should help all of its citizens, regardless of their socioeconomic background. I think it is better to help only those most in need. So from now on, I''ll talk about my opinion with specific reasons. First, it will help to make a balanced society. Since resources that government can use for citizens are limited, it would be better to help people who really needs help, rather than helping every citizens. These days, many society''s wealth gap between the top and the bottom are tremendous, which means it is very unbalanced. I think a good society should be balanced in everything, so I''d choose to help only those most in need. Secondly, I think it is a social duty. Have you ever heard about the word ''Noblesse Oblige''? It is a word which has a long history and it is about some duties that rich people should follow for others. So, we can know that it was trivial for rich people to help other people for a long time. From this perspective, helping only those most in need seems trivial. Of course, there are some people who really worked hard and got a high socioeconomic background, but in many cases the socioeconomic background depends on their luck, such as parent''s background. So, I think it is right for high class people to turn back the benefits to society they have had, and giving up the government''s help for those most in need will be a idea of it. So, I think the government should help only those most in need, rather than helping all the citizens regardless of their socioeconomic background for two reasons. First it will help to make a balanced society, and second, it is a social duty such as ''Noblesse Oblige''. Thank you.', '2025-02-14 11:40:00'),
(2, 37, 'Great job on writing your essay! Here are some suggestions to improve your writing: 1. In the first paragraph, try to add more details to the story or anecdote that you provide to help grab the reader''s attention. Make it a little more engaging. Additionally, make sure you clearly state the topic at the end of your introduction so the reader knows what to expect in your essay. 2. In the second paragraph, instead of saying "First," try starting the sentence with a transitional phrase like "To begin with," or "The first reason why..." This will make your essay flow better. Additionally, try re-reading your sentences to make them more clear. For example, the sentence <sent>"Even individuals who encounter challenging circumstances should be given equal opportunities to improve their situation through hard work" could be rephrased as "Individuals who face difficult circumstances should be provided with equal opportunities to improve their situation by working hard."</sent> 3. In the third paragraph, it''s important to explain why over-helping can lead to neglect of duty. Try expanding on this idea with an example or a specific scenario. Also, consider rephrasing the sentence <sent>"This rule make strange society that faithful people live difficult life and lazy people live peaceful life." to make it more clear. For instance, it could be rephrased as "This can create a society where hardworking individuals lead difficult lives in comparison to those who do not work."</sent> 4. In the final paragraph, make sure to reiterate your thesis statement and follow it up with a clear conclusion. Consider wrapping up your essay by tying together all the points you''ve made and leaving the reader with something to think about. Overall, your essay has good ideas and potential, but it could benefit from clearer and more concise writing. Keep practicing and refining your writing skills, and I''m sure you will improve!', 'Then, how can I make interesting introduction? Please give me a example story.', 'Have you ever had to face a difficult situation where you needed help but were denied because of factors beyond your control? When I was growing up, my family struggled through tough financial times, and we often had to rely on government assistance to make ends meet. However, I noticed that those who were seemingly worse off than us were not always receiving aid. This made me question the fairness of the government''s support system. Shouldn''t those who are truly in need receive assistance regardless of their economic status? In this essay, I argue that the government should provide support based on individual circumstances, and not just economic status. First, Korea help poor people to date but in other people, there are people who are in trouble with working because of disease, privacy condition, ete... When they work in order to overcome difficulty, government do not support them for reason that they have ability to be responsible for living family. Eventually, bad circumstance will be continued. Even individuals who encounter challenging circumstances should be given equal opportunities to improve their situation through hard work. Second, overhelping can bring neglect of duty. If people who do not have money, because they do not live hard and working. This rule make strange society that faithful people live difficult life and lazy people live peaceful life. Finally, someone who just works hard and earns a lot money is required to be sacrified is unfair. Among the rich, some inherit their wealth while others earn it through labor or investments. Even though they work hard in order to live enough life, government required them to sacrify. It can be lower desire. For these three reasons, the government should not only provide support based on economic status but must also consider the individual''s situation in order to provide equitable assistance to those who are in need. Of course, the criteria of circumstance is not obvious, situations must be considered. I hope to change the rule and provide opportunitied to people who live hardly.', '2025-02-27 12:40:00'),
(3, 37, 'Of course! I''d be happy to take a look at your conclusion writing and provide you with some feedback. Can you please share your writing with me?', '<essay>We have developed the platform of a novel bile acid-based liposome loaded doxorubicin for effective oral anti-cancer therapy. Our nanoplatform is designed with conjugation of taurocholic acid polymer to drug-loaded cationic liposome via electrostatic attraction. This developed nanoparticle demonstrated increased absorption ability, which is one of the limitations for oral delivery, compared to other non-coating groups and showed powerful anti-cancer efficacy through apoptosis test. Furthermore, the tocofersolan modification on liposome for p-gp inhibition also proved the synergistic effect by inhibiting drug efflux from cancer cell resulting in maximizing the cytotoxicity of doxorubicin on cancer cell. The development of the effective oral nanoplatform implies that it might provide an innovatory and convenient quality of anti-cancer treatment for cancer patients. Also, this nanoplatform can apply to other intravenous drugs of bacterial diseases as well as other cancer types for conversion to oral administration. Its possibilities are endless due to the properties of lipid platform synthesized microfluidic device. Though this research has used taurocholic acid which is one type of secondary bile acids for oral ability of nanoparticle, other secondary bile acid like glycocholic acid might have superior ability to apply on drug delivery platform. We found the targeting efficacy of taurocholic acid in this paper so the next step for commercialization of oral administration is optimization of the bile acids. These efforts might open the opportunities for improved quality of life to suffering cancer patients. </essay> This is my writing.', 'We have developed the platform of a novel bile acid-based liposome loaded doxorubicin for effective oral anti-cancer therapy. Our nanoplatform is designed with conjugation of taurocholic acid polymer to drug-loaded cationic liposome via electrostatic attraction. This developed nanoparticle demonstrated increased absorption ability, which is one of the limitations for oral delivery, compared to other non-coating groups and showed powerful anti-cancer efficacy through apoptosis test. Furthermore, the tocofersolan modification on liposome for p-gp inhibition also proved the synergistic effect by inhibiting drug efflux from cancer cell resulting in maximizing the cytotoxicity of doxorubicin on cancer cell. The development of the effective oral nanoplatform implies that it might provide an innovatory and convenient quality of anti-cancer treatment for cancer patients. Also, this nanoplatform can apply to other intravenous drugs of bacterial diseases as well as other cancer types for conversion to oral administration. Its possibilities are endless due to the properties of lipid platform synthesized microfluidic device. Though this research has used taurocholic acid which is one type of secondary bile acids for oral ability of nanoparticle, other secondary bile acid like glycocholic acid might have superior ability to apply on drug delivery platform. We found the targeting efficacy of taurocholic acid in this paper so the next step for commercialization of oral administration is optimization of the bile acids. These efforts might open the opportunities for improved quality of life to suffering cancer patients.', '2025-03-13 11:10:00'),
(4, 37, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I had to write my results section following this rubric: Overview DOES NOT give a brief overview of the results. Insufficient overview of results. Overview of results could be more detailed. Good overview of the results. Clarity Grammar and language use substantially impede the reader’s understanding of what is written. Considerable effort is needed on the part of the reader to understand what is written. Grammar and language use is clear so that readers do not need a great deal of effort to understand what is written. Interpretation The data is incorrectly interpreted or incorrectly explained. Some information could be added to aid the reader’s understanding of the author’s interpretation of the data. The data is correctly interpreted and explained in appropriate depth. Visuals referred to in the text The assignment does not contain text that refers to visuals. The text contains descriptions of the visuals, though lacking clarity and detail. No invitation to view the visual is contained. The text contains an invitation to view visuals as well as clear verbal descriptions of the information contained therein. Visuals Figures are not referred to, axes are incorrectly labeled, and legends are missing. Some errors in referring to the figures and/or in the labeling of the axes or providing of units. Otherwise, legend may be incomplete in some way. Figures are present and referred to within the body of the results. Axes are correctly labeled and provide units where applicable (both x and y). Each figure contains a legend below the figure that is framed as a complete sentence summarizing the experimental results and basic information', 'Overview DOES NOT give a brief overview of the results. Insufficient overview of results. Overview of results could be more detailed. Good overview of the results. Clarity Grammar and language use substantially impede the reader’s understanding of what is written. Considerable effort is needed on the part of the reader to understand what is written. Grammar and language use is clear so that readers do not need a great deal of effort to understand what is written. Interpretation The data is incorrectly interpreted or incorrectly explained. Some information could be added to aid the reader’s understanding of the author’s interpretation of the data. The data is correctly interpreted and explained in appropriate depth. Visuals referred to in the text The assignment does not contain text that refers to visuals. The text contains descriptions of the visuals, though lacking clarity and detail. No invitation to view the visual is contained. The text contains an invitation to view visuals as well as clear verbal descriptions of the information contained therein. Visuals Figures are not referred to, axes are incorrectly labeled, and legends are missing. Some errors in referring to the figures and/or in the labeling of the axes or providing of units. Otherwise, legend may be incomplete in some way. Figures are present and referred to within the body of the results. Axes are correctly labeled and provide units where applicable (both x and y). Each figure contains a legend below the figure that is framed as a complete sentence summarizing the experimental results and basic information', '2025-03-20 15:40:00'),
(5, 37, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about results overview, language conventions & informational elements, illustrations, and writing with numbers.', 'Our survey results show that roughly 70% of respondents reported having experience using ChatGPT in mathematical proofs (Figure 1). Of those who have used ChatGPT, 76.9% reported that ChatGPT’s answer was not mathematically appropriate (Figure 2). Figure 1. The experience of using ChatGPT. About 70% of respondents have experienced ChatGPT. Figure 2. The mathematical appropriateness of ChatGPT. Respondents who have used ChatGPT answered that ChatGPT’s answer is not mathematrically appropriate. The most frequently mentioned strength of ChatGPT was “Its ability to apply existing theorems” (50% of respondents), followed by “Its ability of mathematical inference” (29% of respondents) (Figure 3). Figure 3. The strength of ChatGPT in terms of a mathematical proof. Most frequent reply was “Application of existing theorems”, which was 50% among all repliers. Second-most frequent reply was its “Ability of mathematical inference”. Respondents who thought ChatGPT did not perform well in mathematical proofs cited logical errors, computational errors, and mathematical inference as its weaknesses. Additionally, regarding the degree of hallucination that feedback should be given to ChatGPT to reinforce its frequency, a very small percentage of people chose 10%, while the majority chose 20% or more (Figure 4). Figure 4. The degree of experiencing a hallucination that had to give feedback to ChatGPT to reinforce.', '2025-04-03 17:40:00'),
(1, 38, 'Yes, it is acceptable to use parentheses in academic writing. However, it is important to use them appropriately and sparingly. Parentheses should be used to provide additional information or clarification that is not essential to the main point of the sentence. It is also important to ensure that the information within the parentheses is grammatically correct and properly punctuated.', 'can you make an example when it works okay or when it is wrong to use them?', 'Government help is a highly debated topic nowadays. Both citizens and political parties have varying opinions, making it hard for a democratic consensus to be reached. I believe government should help individuals following their income, giving priority to those in the most need. This approach will help them to explore new opportunities and lower the poverty rate of the country. Many people from lower socio-economic classes tend to have less education due to the high cost of universities. These days, tuition fees and the cost of textbooks and class supplies can easily average at $500 per semester, which represents a significant portion of income for people with financial difficulties. Therefore, the government should provide scholarships and financial aid to help them achieve a better education. People from wealthier backgrounds have more opportunities to pursue higher education, even if it comes at a high annual cost. If individuals in need receive the proper assistance, they can have access to job opportunities with higher wages, which would benefit not only their current families but also future generations. Moreover, governments are trying to fight against the high rate of poverty in their country. To achieve this, those in need need to be helped by the government, not only with funds but also with new jobs, better housing, and incentives. This will benefit the image of the country along with helping the lower classes. Some countries, such as South Korea, are facing rapid growth, which leads to an increase in the gap between poor people and rich families. The income gap between the wealthiest 10% and least wealthy 10% in South Korea is substantial, with a difference of 21 times(Hankyoreh, 2021).In cities like Seoul, extremely fancy districts are seen and right around the corner, old houses which look almost like they are falling apart are present. Most of them are filled with the old generation, which was left behind during the economic expansion. The situation may not be attractive to tourists, who might feel uncomfortable with sleeping in such areas. The government has to preserve the image of the country while helping those in need. In conclusion, by investing in those most in need, governments not only improve the lives of individuals and communities, but also pave the way for a brighter and more prosperous future. Therefore, a government that assists the underprivileged can aid in fostering a fair and inclusive society, driving towards a more prosperous future. Reference: Kim, J. (2021, February 22). Income gap exceeds 21 times average. The Hankyoreh. https://english.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_business/1071567.htm', '2025-02-14 11:44:00'),
(2, 38, 'Of course! Please provide me with the first paragraph of your essay, and I will assist you in identifying any grammar errors.', '<para>Nowadays, an economic inequality became serious problem in world. According to 2019 Oxfam report, only 26 richest people own as much wealth as the poorest 50% of the global population. In addition, income inequality, gender inequality, education inequailty became more seriously. In this situation, most of people have different level of socioeconomic backgrounds. Therefore, the government should help only those most in need.</para>', 'Nowadays, economic inequality has became serious problem in world. According to Oxfam report, only 26 richest people own as much wealth as the poorest 50% of the global population. In addition, income inequality, gender inequality, education inequality have became more seriously. In this situation, most people have different level of socioeconomic backgrounds. Therefore, the government should focus on helping those who are in the most need. First of all, resources are limited. As I mentioned before, richest people own almost of resources, Because of that, if the government help all of the citizens, then the economic inequality will be getting worse. To solve this inequality, the government has to help who doesn''t have enough resources. We have to focus on prioritizing the redistribution of wealth and resources to support those who are vulnerable. Second, wealthy individuals do not feel that they need the government''s help in the same way. According to chatGPT, they are only interested in government policies and regulations that can affect the ability of wealthy to them. For instance, tax policies, trade policies, etc. Additionally, wealthy people may have motivation to support government helping community, In this situation, the government don''t need to help wealthy people, and wealthy people may agree with this idea, Some might be think it can make another inequality, but this kind of inequality can be helpful to our society. Trough this way, we can give more resources to poor people. In conclusion, the government don''t need to help all citizens, because of resource limit, agree from wealthy people. If the government help people most in need, a lot of inequality in our society will be solved in future.', '2025-02-27 12:44:00'),
(3, 38, 'Yes, of course! I''m happy to help you revise your draft. Please send it over and we can go through it together.', 'first can you check if there are any spelling mistakes or grammatical errors in this paragraph and point them out for me please. <para>"The traditional 5-day workweek has been the standard for many years, but recently, there has been a growing interest in the idea of a 4-day workweek. many people advocate that a shorter workweek can lead to increased productivity, employee satisfaction and better work-life balance. To test whether people perceive working four days a week as more productive than working five days a week, a survey was conducted among a sample of 17 participants. From the responses we observed that most of the people think that they would prefer working four days a week as shown in figure 1. Many individuals would use the extra time to engage in activities such as exercise, hobbies, and leisure activities, which could improve their physical and mental well-being. However, figure 2 shows that half of the responses disagree that working 4 days a week would be more productive. There are some individuals who may not use the extra day off productively and may just spend it watching TV or resting, which may not have a significant benefit. In conclusion, the result of this study indicate a majority of people perceive working four days a week as more productive than working five days a week. While there are benefits to a 4-day workweek, it''s essential to consider individual preferences and the impact on productivity before implementing this model in the workplace."</para>', 'The traditional 5-day workweek has been the standard for many years, but recently, there has been a growing interest in the idea of a 4-day workweek. many people advocate that a shorter workweek can lead to increased productivity, employee satisfaction and better work-life balance. To test whether people perceive working four days a week as more productive than working five days a week, a survey was conducted among a sample of 17 participants. From the responses it was observed that most people think that they would prefer working four days a week as shown in figure 1. Many individuals would use the extra time to engage in activities such as exercise, hobbies, and leisure activities, which could improve their physical and mental well-being. However, figure 2 shows that half of the responses disagree that working 4 days a week would be more productive. Some individuals may not use the extra day off productively and may just spend it watching TV or resting, which may not have a significant benefit. In conclusion, the result of this study indicate a majority of people perceive working four days a week as more productive than working five days a week. While there are benefits to a 4-day workweek, it''s essential to consider individual preferences and the impact on productivity before implementing this model in the workplace.', '2025-03-13 11:14:00'),
(4, 38, 'Sure! Before we begin, can you please provide me with the essay so I can review it?', '<essay>Advantages of Using Tablets in Class Using tablets in class has become increasingly popular among students due to their numerous advantages. Firstly, using tablets can decrease the weight of your bag. If you don''t use a tablet, you would have to bring many textbooks and notes in your bag. That can become quite heavy and can make you tired. However, if you use a tablet, you can save all textbook files on the tablet and take notes by using it. This means that you would only have to bring your tablet with you to class, which will make your bag lighter. Secondly, students can use the internet comfortably on a tablet. There may be times when you don''t understand something in class, and by using a tablet, you can figure it out immediately. Thirdly, using a tablet can help students study more efficiently. You can take notes, do research, and read books by using a tablet. You can handle many tasks with a tablet, and it helps you finish your work quickly. In summary, these are three reasons why students use tablets in class, and they are advantages. Using tablets in class can help students in many ways.</essay>', 'Advantages of Using Tablets in Class Using tablets in class has become increasingly popular among students due to their numerous advantages. Firstly, using tablets can decrease the weight of your bag. If you don''t use a tablet, you would have to bring many textbooks and notes in your bag. That can become quite heavy and can make you tired. However, if you use a tablet, you can save all textbook files on the tablet and take notes by using it. This means that you would only have to bring your tablet with you to class, which will make your bag lighter. Secondly, students can use the internet comfortably on a tablet. There may be times when you don''t understand something in class, and by using a tablet, you can figure it out immediately. Thirdly, using a tablet can help students study more efficiently. You can take notes, do research, and read books by using a tablet. You can handle many tasks with a tablet, and it helps you finish your work quickly. In summary, these are three reasons why students use tablets in class, and they are advantages. Using tablets in class can help students in many ways.', '2025-03-20 15:44:00'),
(5, 38, 'Of course! Let''s take a look at your introduction and see how we can make it stronger. Can you please share your current introduction with me?', 'Governments have responsibility to help citizens. However, since resources and money which belong to governments are limited, they must use them wisely. Thus, governments should help only those in need for following resons: governments must use their resources efficiently, and those citizens in need may not need help all the time. First, as mentioned before, governments do not have infinite resources. They can not help all of the citizens most of cases. Thus, governments should distinguish citizens whether they need help or not, but also how much support is needed to be sufficient for them.', 'Governments have responsibility to help citizens. However, since resources and money which belong to governments are limited, they must use them wisely. Thus, governments should help only those in need for following resons: governments must use their resources efficiently, and those citizens in need may not need help all the time. First, as mentioned before, governments do not have infinite resources. They can not help all of the citizens most of cases. Thus, governments should distinguish citizens whether they need help or not, but also how much support is needed to be sufficient for them. Second, not everyone received support from government will need another support next time. In short, those in need are not fixed group of citizens. For every cases, governments must investigate and choose who are in need and who are not. In conclusion,', '2025-04-03 17:44:00'),
(1, 39, 'Excellent! And how about the use of colons and semicolons? What did you learn about them?', 'learned about the role of colon and semicolon, especially through exmples of its use.', 'In this lecture, I learned about paraphrasing, colon & semicolon, hyphens, and so on. Through this lecture, it was an opportunity to learn more about how to write a paper. I learn 5 tools to paraphrasing : replace some of the words with synonyms, make a positive verb into a negative verb, change active constructions to passive and vice versa, change words into other parts of speech, move parts of sentences around. learned about the role of colon and semicolon, especially through exmples of its use. A colon introduces a formal list, long quotation, equation, or definition. A semi-colon either joins two independent clauses or separates complex itmes in a list.', '2025-02-14 11:48:00'),
(2, 39, 'Good evening. Could you please provide me with a summary of what you learned in our English writing class, so we can begin the revision process?', 'Below is an outline of my essay. Governments have a crucial role in the welfare of its citizens. First, providing assistance to all citizens can be inefficient and ineffective. Second, providing aid to those in need can help reduce inequality and improve social mobility. Third, focusing on those in need can help the government build trust and promote social cohesion.', 'Governments have a crucial role in the welfare of its citizens. First, providing assistance to all citizens can be inefficient and ineffective. Second, providing aid to those in need can help reduce inequality and improve social mobility. Third, focusing on those in need can help the government build trust and promote social cohesion. =================================================== responses ===================================================== 1. Welfare programs - Governments often provide welfare programs such as food stamps, unemployment benefits, and housing assistance to low-income families and individuals who need financial assistance. These programs are designed to help those in need, and eligibility is often determined by income level and other factors that indicate economic hardship. 2. Education and training programs - Governments also offer education and training programs to help individuals gain the skills and knowledge needed to secure better-paying jobs and improve their economic prospects. These programs might include vocational training, adult education classes, and job placement services. 3. Healthcare - Access to healthcare is essential for everyone, but low-income families and individuals may face significant barriers to receiving quality care. Some governments provide healthcare options at little to no cost for those who cannot afford traditional healthcare plans. 4. Housing assistance - Governments can offer housing assistance to those who cannot afford safe and adequate housing. This assistance might take the form of rental vouchers, affordable housing developments, or subsidized mortgage programs. In all these programs, the primary focus is on helping those who are in need of assistance. By prioritizing those who require the most help, governments can ensure that resources are directed towards those who need them most and make the most impact on their well-being.', '2025-02-27 12:48:00'),
(3, 39, 'Sure, I can take a look at the revised methodology section you worked on in class. Can you please share the revised version with me?', '<sent>The current investigation involved the preparation of chicken and further heating of the chicken. The chicken is collected in an environment where air and water pollution rating is A+. Five samples were utilized in order to analyze the relationship between sterilization and the heating temperature. All the samples were thoroughly rinsed with tap water, and 5 independent ovens are set to 150, 175, 200, 225, 250 degrees Celsius, respectively. The samples were then covered with a seasoning called BBQ seasoning from National Pork Institute (NPI), an authoritative organization related to processed pork products. The samples were cut into 5 pieces according to the conventional method of subdividing the whole chicken for an equal distribution of heat in the oven. Subsequently the samples were placed on a stainless-steel plate which is known as a good heat conductor. The chicken-oven system was placed in the ovens and heated for 30 minutes.</sent>', 'The current investigation involved the preparation of chicken and further heating of the chicken. The chicken is collected in an environment where air and water pollution rating is A+. Five samples were utilized in order to analyze the relationship between sterilization and the heating temperature. All the samples were thoroughly rinsed with tap water, and 5 independent ovens are set to 150, 175, 200, 225, 250 degrees Celsius, respectively. The samples were then covered with a seasoning called BBQ seasoning from National Pork Institute (NPI), an authoritative organization related to processed pork products. The samples were cut into 5 pieces according to the conventional method of subdividing the whole chicken for an equal distribution of heat in the oven. Subsequently the samples were placed on a stainless-steel plate which is known as a good heat conductor. The chicken-oven system was placed in the ovens and heated for 30 minutes.', '2025-03-13 11:18:00'),
(4, 39, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Is there any problem about improper syntax (incorrect or inappropriate word order), missing comma, unclear pronoun reference (pronouns should always have clear antecedents), and grouping of conflicting words (combing words that are often opposite in meaning, ensuing in oxymorons) that can cause confusion in readers. Once you have found them, please correct them whenever possible?', 'By uncovering, the reactor core was exposed, allowing radioactive isotopes to escape. We propose, providing the above engineering services hourly, based on the following estimates. The thermal pollution of a nuclear power plant is less than 2 percent of the pollution of the average coal-fired plant. As airplane designs change, the anti-ice systems also have to change. Most people, who are diagnosed with phenylketonuria, are newborns shortly after birth. The thermal storage unit can only supply low-pressure auxiliary steam due to insufficient excess energy from the undersized collector. At this time, the Department of Energy is only considering Yucca Mountain as a possible storage site for nuclear waste. Other possible sites are excluded from candidates. If the airplane waits too long to take off, the de-ice fluid can dissipate. The Lunar Module was only designed to hold two astronauts, and to have a life time of forty-five hours. The beams are positioned with respect to the chopper blade so that, while one beam passes, the output of the opposite beam is completely blocked. The Hindenburg was filled with hydrogen because the gas is lighter than air. The report claimed that a hull wire could have ruptured a gas cell if it fractured. The equations come from fundamental definitions of mass flow, work, and efficiency, to avoid complex multi-ordered calculations. To provide spill protection, all tanks were equipped with basins and automatic shutoff devices, or overfill alarms, or ball float valves. As the first step in introducing CFD, Jones had to set up conservative assumptions. As with any system, errors occur in localization. Having a model would help designers predict the effects of engine operation over all speeds of engine.', '2025-03-20 15:48:00'),
(5, 39, 'Yes, you are correct! Today''s lesson was about ways to introduce experimental data in a scientific paper. There are two common ways to do this - you can either first present the figures or tables with the data, and then interpret it, or you can first provide an interpretation of the data, then introduce the relevant figure or table. Based on what we have discussed in class, I suggest that you try to modify the order of the introduction based on what you believe will be most effective in terms of explaining your data to your reader. You can consider factors like the complexity of the experiments, the clarity of the results, and what you want to draw the reader''s attention to. By doing this, you can make sure that the flow of information enhances the understanding of your reader and presents your research results in the best possible way. Does that make sense to you?', 'Furthermore, I learned that the purpose, background, experimental approach, results and interpretation of results are needed in the result section. In this situation, how can I make this paragraph better by indicating precisely the 6 things in the previous sentence?', 'Data obtained in previous research has already reported the increase in sightings of UFOs prior to earthquakes. According to Kim et al. (2005), the median average of UFO appearance numbers increased by about 50% before the earthquake occurrence. In our study, our data were collected using the UFO observation model (UOM) mentioned in our methodology section. Modelled results were compared with UFO sightings for 7 days prior to the earthquake, earthquake magnitude, average weekly UFO sightings, and descriptions of UFOs in 5 countries. Table 1 shows the UFO sightings within 300 km of the epicenter using UOM. Kim et al had reported only about the increasing magnitude of earthquakes according to the increased average weekly UFO sightings. However, the modeled data could not predict when an earthquake is likely to occur. We added the UFO sightings for 7 days prior to the earthquake and the descriptions of UFOs were also considered. If the number of UFO sightings for 7 days prior to the earthquake increased than average weekly UFO sightings, the earthquake had occurred. Although most UFOs had a light or color, if the UFO did not have a light or color such as in India, the earthquake occurred even though the number of UFO sighting for 7 days prior to the earthquake was similar to the average weekly UFO sightings. Magnitude of earthquakes increased as average weekly UFO sightings increased, the exception was the USA which had high-speed. Therefore, the criteria of the description of UFO should be more organized. Nevertheless, these results suggest that our theory to interpret the collected data may provide more affordable information for predicting the time and magnitude of earthquakes.', '2025-04-03 17:48:00'),
(1, 40, 'Sure, here are some examples that you could use to support your second main idea: - In some cases, people who are wealthy or have connections may receive government assistance even if they don''t truly need it. This can happen if they know how to work the system or have access to resources that others don''t. This means that people who are truly in need may be denied assistance because the resources are being used by those who don''t need them. - On the other hand, people who are truly in need may be denied assistance because they don''t meet certain criteria or don''t fit into a specific category. For example, someone who is struggling to make ends meet because of a medical condition may not qualify for assistance because they don''t meet the income requirements, even though they are facing significant financial hardship. - Another issue with providing assistance based solely on economic status is that it can create a culture of dependency. If people know that they will receive assistance regardless of their efforts to improve their situation, they may be less motivated to work hard or take responsibility for their own lives. This can lead to a cycle of poverty and dependence that is difficult to break. - Finally, providing assistance based solely on economic status can be unfair to those who work hard and earn a good income. These individuals may be required to pay higher taxes or contribute more to social programs, even if they are already struggling to make ends meet. This can create resentment and a sense of injustice, which can lead to social unrest and division. These are just a few examples, but you can use them as a starting point to develop your own ideas and arguments. Remember to provide specific examples and evidence to support your position, and to address counterarguments to your position.', 'Thank you for advice. I revise my essay. <essay>Have you ever had to face a difficult situation where you needed help but were denied because of factors beyond your control? When I was growing up, my family struggled through tough financial times, and we often had to rely on government assistance to make ends meet. However, I noticed that those who were seemingly worse off than us were not always receiving aid. This made me question the fairness of the government''s support system. Shouldn''t those who are truly in need receive assistance regardless of their economic status? In this essay, I argue that the government should provide support based on individual circumstances, and not just economic status. First, Korea help poor people to date but in other people, there are people who are in trouble with working because of disease, privacy condition, ete... When they work in order to overcome difficulty, government do not support them for reason that they have ability to be responsible for living family. Eventually, bad circumstance will be continued. Even individuals who encounter challenging circumstances should be given equal opportunities to improve their situation through hard work. Second, overhelping can bring neglect of duty. If people who do not have money, because they do not live hard and working. This rule make strange society that faithful people live difficult life and lazy people live peaceful life. Another issue with providing assistance based solely on economic status is that it can create a culture of dependency. If people know that they will receive assistance regardless of their efforts to improve their situation, they may be less motivated to work hard or take responsibility for their own lives. This can lead to a cycle of poverty and dependence that is difficult to break. Finally, someone who just works hard and earns a lot money is required to be sacrified is unfair. Among the rich, some inherit their wealth while others earn it through labor or investments. Even though they work hard in order to live enough life, government required them to sacrify. It can be lower desire. In conclusion, the government should not base their support solely on economic status, but rather take into consideration the individual''s circumstances and needs. By doing so, those who truly need support can receive it, and those who are capable of standing on their own two feet can do so without hinderance. It is crucial to provide equitable assistance to those in need to ensure a just and fair society. Through hard work and dedication, individuals should be allowed the opportunity to improve their situation. Let us work together to create a society that values and supports its citizens, regardless of their background or economic status.</essay>', 'Have you ever had to face a difficult situation where you needed help but were denied because of factors beyond your control? When I was growing up, my family struggled through tough financial times, and we often had to rely on government assistance to make ends meet. However, I noticed that those who were seemingly worse off than us were not always receiving aid. This made me question the fairness of the government''s support system. Shouldn''t those who are truly in need receive assistance regardless of their economic status? In this essay, I argue that the government should provide support based on individual circumstances, and not just economic status. First, Korea help poor people to date but in other people, there are people who are in trouble with working because of disease, privacy condition, ete... When they work in order to overcome difficulty, government do not support them for reason that they have ability to be responsible for living family. Eventually, bad circumstance will be continued. Even individuals who encounter challenging circumstances should be given equal opportunities to improve their situation through hard work. Second, overhelping can bring neglect of duty. If people who do not have money, because they do not live hard and working. This rule make strange society that faithful people live difficult life and lazy people live peaceful life. Another issue with providing assistance based solely on economic status is that it can create a culture of dependency. If people know that they will receive assistance regardless of their efforts to improve their situation, they may be less motivated to work hard or take responsibility for their own lives. This can lead to a cycle of poverty and dependence that is difficult to break. Finally, someone who just works hard and earns a lot money is required to be sacrified is unfair. Among the rich, some inherit their wealth while others earn it through labor or investments. Even though they work hard in order to live enough life, government required them to sacrify. It can be lower desire. In conclusion, the government should not base their support solely on economic status, but rather take into consideration the individual''s circumstances and needs. By doing so, those who truly need support can receive it, and those who are capable of standing on their own two feet can do so without hinderance. It is crucial to provide equitable assistance to those in need to ensure a just and fair society. Through hard work and dedication, individuals should be allowed the opportunity to improve their situation. Let us work together to create a society that values and supports its citizens, regardless of their background or economic status.', '2025-02-14 11:52:00'),
(2, 40, 'Certainly! Here are a few different types of hooks that you may find helpful: 1. Start with a question: Asking a question is a great way to grab the reader''s attention and make them curious about the rest of your essay. For example, <sent>"How many college students use tablet/laptop computers in class each day? You may be surprised to learn that the majority of students prefer to use digital devices rather than traditional textbooks."</sent> 2. Use a startling fact or statistic: Sharing a surprising or shocking piece of information can help to pique the reader''s interest. For example, <sent>"Did you know that research indicates students who use tablet/laptop computers in the classroom achieve higher grades than those who solely use traditional textbooks?".</sent> 3. Tell an anecdote or story: An engaging story or personal anecdote can help to create a connection with the reader and provide context for your essay. For example, <sent>"As a student myself, I have experienced the struggle of carrying multiple heavy textbooks for each class. But when I switched to using a digital device, my academic life became much more manageable."</sent> 4. Use a quote: A well-chosen quote from an expert, famous person, or even a student can help to spark interest in your topic. For example, <sent>"As Steve Jobs once said, ''Technology is nothing. What''s important is that you have a faith in people, that they''re basically good and smart, and if you give them tools, they''ll do wonderful things with them.''"</sent> Remember, the purpose of your hook is to draw the reader in and make them interested in your essay. You should choose one that is relevant to your topic and makes sense within the context of your essay.', 'Can you make this sentence more natural in English? <sent>As a student myself, I have experienced the struggle of carrying a ton of textbooks and notes for each class in my high school.</sent>', 'As a student myself, I have experienced the struggle of carrying a ton of textbooks and notes for each class while I was in high school. But when I switched to using a tablet computer, my academic life became much more convenient. The use of tablet/laptop computers in the classroom provides many benefits for students. First, students can have a more convenient way of studying as they don''t need to bring their heavy textbooks with them in class. If they bring their own tablet/laptop computers, they are able to view textbooks, write their notes, and refer provided readings with just one devices. It is much more convenient than bringing their heavy textbooks, notes, and extra papers. Second, with a tablet/laptop computer, students can search for information easily and quickly. With the Internet, an ocean of information, they can easily find the definition of some terms, or the meaning of abstract concepts. Using these devices enable students to deeply understand what their professor says. Lastly, using a tablet/laptop computer can help students supplement what they missed in class through the recording of video of audio. Although students write their notes to understand, and to remember the lecture, there is a limit with just writing some sentences. If students can record a video or an audio for lecture, students can supplement what they missed in class; therefore students can learn more about the topic they are dealing with. In conclusion, the use of tablet/laptop computers in the classroom is a practical and effective way to enhance student''s learning experiences.', '2025-02-27 12:52:00'),
(3, 40, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about articles today. The definite article "the" should be used in a sentence when I want to mention some specific words.', 'In the famous Korean movie "parasite", there are some rich people who do not have any worry about their economic budget. On the other hand, there are some people who have trouble living their lives due to their poor situation. Is it reasonable for the wealthy people to be helped by the government with the people who live in an underground floor? It is obviously not desirable. The government should focus on helping only those most in need. One of the reasons why the government needs to help the poor only is it is a way to save a budget of the government. The budget of a country is limited to some extent depending on its economic level. In addition to that, the contemporary society has to try to save its budget for the future generation, which will have lots of difficulty on their lives. As a result, a leader of the country has to control its budget carefully. If all of the citizens in the country get economic merits by some policies, there will be some situations where the government cannot use the budget to the parts that are needed really. By focusing on the needed, the government can also reinforce the quality of support to them. It will help the government to save the budget for the future. Also, the quality of support will be upgraded because the distribution of the limited budget is dependent on the number of people. The cases of private insurance focusing on only small number of people guarantee that the quality of support is related to the number of people who are supported. The second reason is that there can be a positive effect about solving the economic inequality by helping only those most in need. The government gets its income mainly by a tax, which is from the wealthy. If the administration needs tax to help the poor, the wealthy need to pay more tax naturally that makes their wealth reduced. In this way, the poor can enhance their economic level by the support made from the wealthy''s tax. Because it is obvious that the economic inequality will be worsen as the technology, such as AI, develops fast, the effort to prevent the unbalance is important. In conclusion, the government should focus on helping only those most in need. The first reason is it can save the budget which can be used efficiently for other purposes. There is another advantage, which is an increase of the quality of the support. The other reason is focusing on the needed can help solving the problem about the economic inequality. The government can make the country to grow by just helping only the needed, not every citizens.', '2025-03-13 11:22:00'),
(4, 40, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', '<para>"The cohesin complex has an essential role in maintaining genome organization. However, its role in gene regulation remains largely unresolved. Here we report that the cohesin release factor WAPL creates a pool of free cohesin, in a process known as cohesin turnover, which reloads it to cell-type-specific binding sites. Paradoxically, stabilization of cohesin binding, following WAPL ablation, results in depletion of cohesin from these cell-type-specific regions, loss of gene expression and differentiation. Chromosome conformation capture experiments show that cohesin turnover is important for maintaining promoter–enhancer loops. Binding of cohesin to cell-type-specific sites is dependent on the pioneer transcription factors OCT4 (POU5F1) and SOX2, but not NANOG. We show the importance of cohesin turnover in controlling transcription and propose that a cycle of cohesin loading and off-loading, instead of static cohesin binding, mediates promoter and enhancer interactions critical for gene regulation."</para> This paragraph is an abstract of a scientific paper. Can I have which sentence is the turnover part to emphasize the topic?', 'The cohesin complex has an essential role in maintaining genome organization. However, its role in gene regulation remains largely unresolved. Here we report that the cohesin release factor WAPL creates a pool of free cohesin, in a process known as cohesin turnover, which reloads it to cell-type-specific binding sites. Paradoxically, stabilization of cohesin binding, following WAPL ablation, results in depletion of cohesin from these cell-type-specific regions, loss of gene expression and differentiation. Chromosome conformation capture experiments show that cohesin turnover is important for maintaining promoter–enhancer loops. Binding of cohesin to cell-type-specific sites is dependent on the pioneer transcription factors OCT4 (POU5F1) and SOX2, but not NANOG. We show the importance of cohesin turnover in controlling transcription and propose that a cycle of cohesin loading and off-loading, instead of static cohesin binding, mediates promoter and enhancer interactions critical for gene regulation.', '2025-03-20 15:52:00'),
(5, 40, 'Great! Let''s start with the essay you''ve written. Can you please provide me with a copy of your essay? We can then go through it together and identify areas that need improvement.', 'Some people in Korean question about military service. Why only men should go to military? Why only man spand their precious time in military? They even say this military system of men''s are one of the gender discriminatory. So, they say also women go to military like men''s do. Is it right thinking? Is tihs true that military system is discriminatory about gender? I don''t think so. Of course, it is hard to go military, but it can''t be reason that military service should be expanded to encompass female Korean. This essay will explain some reasons that encourage my opinion. First, the problem of man''s military service is not gender discrimination. It is just the problem of differences from men and women. In fact, men usually are stronger and have greater health. It is physical difference from men and women. The military, as you known as have a lot of time that exercise, training, etc. Some military''s hard training is difficult to women to sucess them. Because of women''s physical weak, the military service is hard to be expanded to women. Of course, there are some strong women that can work more that men. But this is not good in terms of efficiency. Also, there are some problems if the military service is expanded to Korean women. For example, the army must build new dormitary for women. Moreover, they have to prepare some place that need to wemen, like women''s toilets, women''s shower system, and also women''s hospitals. Those preparing steps need a lot of moneys. This is not good for us. Lastly, because of women military service, the tax on military will increase. These days, already Korean have to pay lots of tax in military. If the military service is expanded on women, this military tax will be increased much more, and it makes us hard to live. The tax problem is not simple problem. The expanded military serviece lead to rebuild some dormitary and pay money to military women. These all the tax. Do you have enough money to pay it? To sum up, extending military service to women is not good for us because lots of money like tax and false asspect that military serviece of men is discrimination of gender. Men have their works, and also women. Men and women must care eash other. I hope you understanding my opinion. Thank you for reading my essay.', 'Some people in Korean question about military service. Why only men should go to military? Why only man spand their precious time in military? They even say this military system of men''s are one of the gender discriminatory. So, they say also women go to military like men''s do. Is it right thinking? Is tihs true that military system is discriminatory about gender? I don''t think so. Of course, it is hard to go military, but it can''t be reason that military service should be expanded to encompass female Korean. This essay will explain some reasons that encourage my opinion. First, the problem of man''s military service is not gender discrimination. It is just the problem of differences from men and women. In fact, men usually are stronger and have greater health. It is physical difference from men and women. The military, as you known as have a lot of time that exercise, training, etc. Some military''s hard training is difficult to women to sucess them. Because of women''s physical weak, the military service is hard to be expanded to women. Of course, there are some strong women that can work more that men. But this is not good in terms of efficiency. Also, there are some problems if the military service is expanded to Korean women. For example, the army must build new dormitary for women. Moreover, they have to prepare some place that need to wemen, like women''s toilets, women''s shower system, and also women''s hospitals. Those preparing steps need a lot of moneys. This is not good for us. Lastly, because of women military service, the tax on military will increase. These days, already Korean have to pay lots of tax in military. If the military service is expanded on women, this military tax will be increased much more, and it makes us hard to live. The tax problem is not simple problem. The expanded military serviece lead to rebuild some dormitary and pay money to military women. These all the tax. Do you have enough money to pay it? To sum up, extending military service to women is not good for us because lots of money like tax and false asspect that military serviece of men is discrimination of gender. Men have their works, and also women. Men and women must care eash other. I hope you understanding my opinion. Thank you for reading my essay.', '2025-04-03 17:52:00'),
(1, 41, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned that the last part of essay must contain the content that summary and emphasize the whole essay.', 'I think that goverment must help citizen according to criteria about not import but situation. First, Korea help poor people to date but in other people, there are people who are in trouble with working because of disease, privacy situation, ete... When they work in order to overcome difficulty, government do not help them for reason that they have ability to be responsible for living family. Eventually, bad situation will be continued. Someone who does his best must be given more opportunity to out of poor, although they have bad situation and condition. Second, overhelping can bring neglect of duty. If people who do not have money, because they do not live hard and working. This rule make strange society that faithful people live difficult life and lazy people live peaceful life. Finally, someone who just works hard and earns a lot money is required to be sacrified is unfair. In rich people, some are naturally rich thanks to their parents, others earn the money for working. Even though they work hard in order to live enough life, government required them to sacrify. It can be lower desire. For these three reasons, help must not provided for economic criteria.Of course, the criteria of situation is not obvious, situations must be considered. I hope to change the rule and provide opportunitied to people who live hardly.', '2025-02-14 11:56:00'),
(2, 41, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about thesis sentences. It is mostly the last sentence of the introductory paragraph. Could you check my thesis sentence in my essay whether it is proper?', 'Majority of people has experienced wearing their school uniform. The traditional notion that students should wear school uniforms has persisted for a long time, even today. However, some schools allow students to wear regular clothes when they attend school. While student freedom is important, I believe that high schools should control students'' clothing and require them to wear a consistent school uniform. There are two main reasons why I assert this statement. Firstly, wearing school uniforms is very economical. It''s a well-known fact that young people are usually interested in fashion or trends, so they buy new clothes or accessories that are popular among their friends. For example, in the 2000s, some students in South Korea were known as "backbone brokers" and required expensive jackets, such as Goose down, from their parents. If high schools controlled what students wore with a uniform, they would not need to buy expensive and high-quality clothes to wear to school. Moreover, since students wear the same school uniform for five days a week, they don''t need a large amount of clothes for everyday life. With this in mind, wearing school uniforms can reduce the cost of clothing and is therefore an economical choice. Secondly, school uniforms are able to represent a school''s identity. Once a school selects a uniform, it usually remains unchanged for a long time. In other words, many people who graduated from a school wore the same uniform. Therefore, a school uniform becomes a symbol of the school. For instance, if you see some students wearing a particular school uniform on the street, you can recognize the name of the school they are attending. Furthermore, wearing a school uniform may also foster a sense of unity and integration among students, as they all wear the same design. Unity of a school may make students passionate and of course it would help learning or communicating with other students in same school. I believe that school uniforms can create a unified image and identity for each school. In conclusion, wearing school uniforms helps to reduce economic burden and creates a sense of identity at school. Therefore, I believe that school uniforms should be required for high school students. By wearing uniforms, students avoid the need to buy expensive clothing and can represent their school''s identity. This fosters a sense of unity, which is valuable for academic and social success.', '2025-02-27 12:56:00'),
(3, 41, 'School uniforms bring uniformity among students and create a sense of harmony.', '<sent>그 누구도 차별받거나 다르다는 느낌을 들지 않게 한다.</sent> 를 번역해줘', 'School Uniforms are common recommended by many high schools in almost every region of Korea for students to wear. When entering middle school, teenagers in Korea have to wear school uniforms. Some students are uncomfortable with this rule and resist following their school and teacher. To require wearing school uniforms is good for several reasons. Firstly, school uniforms are a sign of students and teenagers'' status and standing in society. If someone is wearing a school uniform and gets into trouble, many people will offer help. Research and statistics show that people are more likely to help someone who is wearing a school uniform in dangerous or emergency situations. Therefore, school uniforms protect many students. Another reason that school uniforms are useful is for students during off-campus activities, such as shopping or using public transportation. Students who wear school uniforms are often given special discounts or gifts at events. Additionally, they can take part in cultural events, such as movies, concerts, and book readings, without the need for additional identification. Lastely, School uniforms bring uniformity among students and create a sense of harmony. It prevents anyone from feeling discriminated or different. School uniforms are useful and helpful. We need to consider one more aspect: whether removing school uniform rules would foster greater connections throughout our communities.', '2025-03-13 11:26:00'),
(4, 41, 'No, it is not appropriate to write a discussion in the results part of a scientific paper. As I mentioned earlier, the results section simply presents the raw data that you have collected, often in the form of tables, graphs, or figures. This section does not offer any interpretation or analysis of the data that you have collected. In contrast, the discussion section is where you can interpret and analyze the results, and discuss their implications. It is important that you keep these two sections separate in your paper.', 'Then what is the difference between discussion part and conclusion? Because I usually read the paper in order of results following conclusion, not discussion part.', 'Introduction and discussion Introduction: write about the work of other researcher; describe what type of work existed in the field, Locate a gap in the research; describe a problem associated with existing research., Write about the present paper, creating an interface with content of work so you could move the reader to the central section of paper. Discussion: Describe your study in relation to what is already in the field. Describe to what extent you have responded to that gap in the research field or how you have solved that problem., Revisit aspects of your study and guide readers away from your current report to future research.', '2025-03-20 15:56:00'),
(5, 41, 'Sure, I can certainly help clarify the sentence. However, to do so, I''ll need a bit more context. Can you please provide the sentence in the context of the essay, or tell me what the author is attempting to convey with this sentence?', 'i am trying to explain why government should help people only in need.', 'I think the government should help only in need. It’s because people who don’t need help is OK without help. However, government help is critical for people who need help. If the government gave aid to every citizen, they would not be able to help everyone sufficiently. To provide assistance requires the recipients to also play their part by being in genuine need of help, as helping individuals who don''t require assistance would detract from the aid provided to those who genuinely do need it. First, I think the government should provide sufficient help for people who need help because government help is critical for their lives. For example, if a poor man with no family got an accident and need money for the surgery nobody else could borrow him money except for the government. As shown in the example since the government has a permission to help every citizen to live a healthy and pleasure life. Helping only people in need would be a key to maintain the whole citizen live better lives. Second helping for every citizen will make help for each person too small since the government has limited money and material. Perhaps nobody will be satisfied after getting such a small help. some might think it’s unfair to have only some people not everybody it is still the best choice to keep most people well as possible. These are some reasons I think the government should help some people in need. By helping only people in need the government can use limited facility efficiently and people who need help we can get much more help than helping everyone in the society.', '2025-04-03 17:56:00'),
(1, 42, 'Yes, that''s great! Can you tell me more about what you learned specifically about paraphrasing?', 'I learn 5 tools to paraphrasing : replace some of the words with synonyms, make a positive verb into a negative verb, change active constructions to passive and vice versa, change words into other parts of speech, move parts of sentences around.', 'In this lecture, I learned about paraphrasing, colon & semicolon, hyphens, and so on. Through this lecture, it was an opportunity to learn more about how to write a paper. I learn 5 tools to paraphrasing : replace some of the words with synonyms, make a positive verb into a negative verb, change active constructions to passive and vice versa, change words into other parts of speech, move parts of sentences around. learned about the role of colon and semicolon, especially through exmples of its use.', '2025-02-14 12:00:00'),
(2, 42, 'Hello! The paragraph you shared looks great. Here is my revised version with some minor changes: "While the proposed algorithm showed promising results, there are still some limitations to consider. Firstly, the percentage of unique patterns in the generated beatmaps greatly increased, but it was still significantly lower than that of human-made beatmaps, especially for higher difficulty levels. Secondly, although the proposed algorithm outperformed the DDC baseline in every aspect of the task, it performed slightly worse than the GN baseline for the beginner charts. Future research may focus on investigating ways to improve consistency across all difficulty levels and incorporate the spatial placement of actions for specific game interfaces. Additionally, the research could examine the variations in beatmaps created by different authors for the same song and develop a metric to quantify them and refine evaluation guidelines. Obtaining feedback from experienced beatmap creators in these areas may be necessary. The algorithm has practical applications, particularly for amateur video game developers who don''t have the resources or expertise to create precise and engaging beatmaps from scratch. Additionally, it could be used for motor and cognitive skill recovery rhythm-based games in healthcare and rehabilitation settings." Let me know if you have any further questions or concerns.', 'thanks that sounds great. what about this part? <para>The results of the study indicated that the proposed algorithm was effective in generating beatmaps that accurately reflected the timing and rhythm patterns of the input music tracks. Specifically, the model achieved an overall step placement F1-score of 0.83 and a step selection accuracy of 73% with an end-to-end approach. Moreover, the Over P-Space score of the generated charts increased by 15% compared to the baseline algorithms. Since there are several valid ways to interpret the same song, resulting in multiple possible beatmaps, evaluating the output correctly can be challenging. The achieved scores indicate that the algorithm can produce charts comparable to those created manually. The user test results showed that the generated beatmaps were similar in terms of difficulty level and enjoyment to the human-made ones, but the expert players rated the latter as significantly better in terms of overall quality. The feedback received highlights the importance of considering the level of expertise of the intended users when evaluating quality. Beginner and intermediate players may be less critical than experienced players with higher standards. Since some participants described the generated beatmaps as unpredictable and unique but lacking flow and coherence, there may be room for improvement in the generation of more consistent and intuitive patterns that follow the structure and melody of the song. This could be achieved through incorporating low-level audio features into the model.</para>', 'The results of the study indicated that the proposed algorithm was effective in generating beatmaps that accurately reflected the timing and rhythm patterns of the input music tracks. Specifically, the model achieved an overall step placement F1-score of 0.83 and a step selection accuracy of 73% with an end-to-end approach. Moreover, the Over P-Space score of the generated charts increased by 15% compared to the baseline algorithms. Since there are several valid ways to interpret the same song, resulting in multiple possible beatmaps, evaluating the output correctly can be challenging. The achieved scores indicate that the algorithm can produce charts comparable to those created manually. The user test results showed that the generated beatmaps were similar in terms of difficulty level and enjoyment to the human-made ones, but the expert players rated the latter as significantly better in terms of overall quality. The feedback received highlights the importance of considering the level of expertise of the intended users when evaluating quality. Beginner and intermediate players may be less critical than experienced players with higher standards. Since some participants described the generated beatmaps as unpredictable and unique but lacking flow and coherence, there may be room for improvement in the generation of more consistent and intuitive patterns that follow the structure and melody of the song. This could be achieved through incorporating low-level audio features into the model.', '2025-02-27 13:00:00'),
(3, 42, 'Yes, you can definitely write a conclusion for your essay. The conclusion should summarize the main points of your essay and provide a final thought or reflection on the topic. It should leave a lasting impression on the reader and tie together all the ideas presented in the essay.', 'Can you recommend what should be included in the conclusion of my essay?', 'In today''s digital age, tablets and laptops have become ubiquitous tools for students, and most of students in KAIST also use them to listen lectures and taking notes for important information. While concerns have been raised about the potential negative effects of these devices on student concentration and eye health, it is important to recognize the many benefits that they offer for academic success. This essay will explore three key advantages of using tablets and laptops in the classroom: time savings, increased learning efficiency, and improved space efficiency. First of all, tablets and laptops permit students to save time. The functions of searching and recording could allow students to save their time. Specifically, searching function in the electronic devices allow us to fine the information, which we are not aware of or which are confused, quickly, Students just type the word that they want to know, and just for a moment, lots of useful information come out. When it comes to recording function, students could record the lecture. After that, they can play it 1.5 or twice time faster. So they can save their time using an efficient way. Another key advantage of using tablets and laptops in the classroom is that they can make studying more efficient by allowing students to review lecture content at their own pace. For example, recording functions can help students pick up on information they may have missed during class or that did not make sense to them at the time. By listening to recordings multiple times and studying challenging material more closely, students are better able to grasp course concepts and improve their grades. Finally, the use of tablets and laptops in the classroom can have a positive effect on space efficiency. With the advent of video conferencing technologies like Zoom, electronic devices can allow students to participate in classes and collaborate with their peers from anywhere. For example, if a class is oversubscribed and too many students are present physically, electronic devices can be used to provide remote access and allow everyone to participate equally. Additionally, eBooks and online course materials can greatly reduce the physical space requirements for traditional textbooks and other teaching materials, resulting in more effective use of classroom resources. For these reasons, I want to emphasize using a tablet or laptop computer in class is good way for students.', '2025-03-13 11:30:00'),
(4, 42, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about the language conventions and information elements used for result section.', 'By analyzing participants’ think-aloud scripts, we found out that all participants had three primary goals for their ideation: relevant design, aesthetically pleasing design, and novel design. They aimed to create a design that aligned well with the given topic, looked visually appealing, and stood out from existing designs. Based on these three goals, we analyzed how participants accomplish these goals using visual references in three separate ideation stages, which are reference search, idea generation, and narrowing down. During the reference search stage, we observed various strategies to stimulate novelty and creativity. Two of the six participants intentionally used general search terms to discover diverse results instead of topic-specific keywords. A different participant obtained references from a field unrelated to brand design, specifically interior design. Three participants used generative models in the hopes that the randomness of AI would lead to new ideas. As visual styles are difficult to explain in words, three out of six participants used recommendation functions for styles instead of formulate them as search keywords. They discovered one of the random images with a style they liked, and then proceeded with the further exploration by getting recommended images similar to the original image. After searching for references, all participants categorized them using their own criteria. These criteria were frequently divided into two categories: style-related keywords and topic-related keywords. In the idea generation stage, participants employed two primary strategies. The first is to extract the commonness from multiple references. Five participants grouped the topic-related references and discover effective ways to convey topics by extracting common objects. For example, P3 said, “Looking at various references related to travel, I discovered that travel hats appeared frequently, and I decided to use this.” Three participants discovered the specific design elements (e.g., font, color) from the group of references that they liked, and decided to use this for their own design as well. However, this commonness sometimes affects their design in an opposite way. Two of the participants said that they aimed to identify and avoid design styles that were too common. The second strategy was to merge multiple references. Participants divided the topic into keywords, found references for each of them, and merged them together. They changed particular elements from a favorite reference to another element that can highlight the topic more effectively. They also combined references for different design elements, such as typography and color, and applied design elements from other references to a favorite reference. After generating a range of design concepts, the participants utilized visual references to build prototypes quickly and narrow their choices down. We observed that four participants utilized their references to validate their design concepts by confirming if several references complemented each other and if the design would appear visually appealing after developing this design concept. Additionally, two participants mentioned utilizing references to compare diverse design concepts by taking distinct design elements and implementing them interchangeably. Based on the interview after the ideation task, we identified various needs when utilizing references in design ideation. In terms of reference search, designers expressed a desire for a search function based on reference groups, rather than recommendations from single references. They also sought a tool to provide references for non-existent or abstract concepts, in addition to a recommendation system for specific design elements, like font, layout, and color. During the idea generation phases, designers desired a tool to automatically extract common design elements from their reference groups, as well as to modify specific parts of references to create new design variations. However, during the narrowing-down phase, we observed a lack of systems to support this aspect of the ideation process. These observations suggest an opportunity for developing computational tools to aid designers in the different stages of ideation. In summary, this formative study aimed to investigate the strategies employed by designers when using different references together to generate creative ideas. The study found that designers tend to group multiple references according to their own criteria and utilize them as a collective source of inspiration rather than relying on a single reference. During the ideation process, designers extract common elements from their reference groups to guide their design direction, or merge multiple references to create new and creative design ideas. References are used as both a source of direction and stimulus for generating divergent ideas and as a material for making design decisions during the convergent phase. The study also revealed a need for a reference search tool that can provide references for non-existent or abstract concepts, as well as a recommendation system that can provide granular suggestions for different design elements. Finally, it was found that designers currently utilize generative models as reference providers.', '2025-03-20 16:00:00'),
(5, 42, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about puctuations. You must add a comma where the context changes.', 'Gold nanoparticles have unique optical and electronic properties that make them attractive for a wide range of applications, from biomedical imaging to catalysis. The surface of gold nanoparticles can be functionalized with thiol groups, which can form strong covalent bonds with the gold surface. This thiol-gold interaction is widely used in bioconjugation and sensing applications, where thiolated molecules can be attached to the gold surface to create stable and functionalized nanoparticles. Moreover, the strong binding affinity of thiol groups to gold surfaces has been exploited for the formation of self-assembled monolayers (SAMs) on gold nanoparticles. By carefully selecting the thiol molecules and controlling their assembly on the gold surface, SAMs with tailored properties can be created. Overall, the thiol-gold interaction is a powerful tool for controlling the surface chemistry of gold nanoparticles and enhancing their functionality.', '2025-04-03 18:00:00'),
(1, 43, '<para>The responsibilities of governments include ensuring the safety of their citizens, protecting their basic human rights, and promoting economic growth and stability. This includes providing healthcare, education, social services, and maintaining critical infrastructure such as transportation and utility systems. Governments also have the responsibility to maintain a fair and just legal system, protect the environment and natural resources, and engage in diplomacy with other countries to promote peace and security.</para>', 'I think governments should focus on helping those in need preferentially, but I can not come up with any basis or instance. Can you help me?', 'Governments have a responsibility to =================================================== Sure, I can help you with that. One instance where governments should focus on helping those in need is during times of national disasters such as floods, hurricanes, or earthquakes. In such critical situations, governments should prioritize the aid to those who require it the most, including the elderly, children, and low-income households. Another example where governments should preferentially help those in need is in the area of healthcare. The government should work to provide universal access to quality healthcare services, regardless of individual financial resources. This is crucial because low-income households are disadvantaged when it comes to accessing quality healthcare and require special attention. Finally, governments should focus on providing educational opportunities to marginalized communities. Education is a crucial aspect of empowering individuals from disadvantaged backgrounds and providing them with the tools needed to achieve long-term financial stability. In conclusion, supporting those in need is an essential responsibility of governments and ensures equitable opportunities for all citizens. ===================================================== The responsibilities of governments include ensuring the safety of their citizens, protecting their basic human rights, and promoting economic growth and stability. This includes providing healthcare, education, social services, and maintaining critical infrastructure such as transportation and utility systems. Governments also have the responsibility to maintain a fair and just legal system, protect the environment and natural resources, and engage in diplomacy with other countries to promote peace and security.', '2025-02-14 12:04:00'),
(2, 43, 'Yes, I can suggest some improvements to the paragraph you provided. First, it would be helpful to provide more context about what Rowhammer is, as some readers may not be familiar with the term. You could provide a brief explanation or link to a resource for readers who need more information. Second, it would be helpful to provide more specific examples and citations for the proposed mechanisms of defense against Rowhammer. For example, instead of just citing "cite" for each approach, you could include the specific studies that propose each approach and provide more detail about how they work. Third, you could consider breaking up the paragraph into smaller sections, each focused on a specific approach to defending against Rowhammer. This would make the information easier to read and digest for readers. Overall, the paragraph you provided contains good information, but could benefit from some additional context and detail.', 'Can you suggest possible changes to the paragraph below? <para>A considerable amount of effort has been directed towards developing various mechanisms to defend against the Rowhammer. Some studies proposed increasing the refresh rate of all rows, which effectively reduces the typical refresh window of 64 ms to a smaller time frame [cite]. Alternatively, some researchers have suggested identifying aggressor rows by tracking recent row activations. These efforts can be grouped into three categories: targeted row refresh, throttling, and aggressor row swap. The targeted row refresh focuses on scheduling refresh operations for identified victim rows outside of the regular schedule. The throttling approach limits the number of issued row activations to a predetermined level that ensures protection [cite]. Finally, the aggressor row swap approach involves changing the physical location of the aggressor row [cite]. By doing so, previously victimized rows are no longer in danger. </para>', 'A considerable amount of effort has been directed towards developing various mechanisms to defend against the Rowhammer. Some studies proposed increasing the refresh rate of all rows, which effectively reduces the typical refresh window of 64 ms to a smaller time frame [cite]. Alternatively, some researchers have suggested identifying aggressor rows by tracking recent row activations. These efforts can be grouped into three categories: targeted row refresh, throttling, and aggressor row swap. The targeted row refresh focuses on scheduling refresh operations for identified victim rows outside of the regular schedule. The throttling approach limits the number of issued row activations to a predetermined level that ensures protection [cite]. Finally, the aggressor row swap approach involves changing the physical location of the aggressor row [cite]. By doing so, previously victimized rows are no longer in danger.', '2025-02-27 13:04:00'),
(3, 43, 'Ok! Here''s the next sentence: Original: For example, lots of students use PDF when they study or listen their lectures. Revised: For example, many students use PDFs when they study or listen to lectures. Explanation: No change in comma usage is necessary for this sentence.', 'Is there no error in the comma rule before the sentence I just corrected?', 'In the past, almost all university students used textbooks and pens. Because of this, most students had to carry a load when they went to lectures. Nowadays, however, lots of students, including high school and university students, don''t have to carry heavy textbooks. They just take their laptop or tablet. Almost all KAIST students already have their own laptop, tablet, or both. Why many people use that in class? Let me explain why laptop/tablet are more convenient than textbooks and pens. First of all, it is light. Things which are light have many advantages. It is less hand to pick light things than heavy things. Because of this reason, It is convenient to take whenever students go. Second, laptop and tablet doesn’t have limit to include infinite files that are helpful to lessons or their own study. For example, many students use PDFs when they study or listen to lectures. PDF helps students not to take various textbooks when they have various lectures on only one day. Lastly, it can increase students’ academic achievements. Specifically, just writing using their own hands have limit to write fastly. But typing using laptop is faster than hand writing. In addition, laptop and tablet can search internet like Google. Therefore, whenever students doesn’t know any informations that are important to understand their class, they can search the information by using tablet and laptop. When students sumit their homeworks to professor, laptop and tablet are convenient, because offline sumit request more time, more effort than online sumit. In short, laptop and tablet have many advantages like weigh(for portability), infinite saving space, and increasing students’ academic achievements.', '2025-03-13 11:34:00'),
(4, 43, 'Certainly! The distribution of a country''s budget is important because it determines how resources are allocated to various sectors and programs. A well-planned budget can help a country maintain its economic stability, promote growth, and improve the quality of life for its citizens. For example, investing in education can lead to a more skilled workforce, which can attract businesses and stimulate economic growth. Similarly, investing in infrastructure projects such as roads, bridges, and public transportation can improve transportation efficiency, reduce traffic congestion, and increase access to goods and services. On the other hand, if a country''s budget is not distributed properly, it can lead to economic instability, social inequality, and political unrest. For instance, if too much of the budget is allocated to military spending, it can leave other important sectors underfunded, such as education, healthcare, and social welfare programs. This can lead to a lack of opportunities for citizens, which can cause frustration and unrest. Therefore, it''s important for governments to carefully consider how they allocate their budgets to ensure that resources are distributed in a way that benefits the country as a whole.', '<para>Second, to assume government assist socioeconomically poor people with money, the budget has to be used properly and reasonable. While it''s important to assist those in need, such as the poor, there are other areas that require attention as well. Especially for Korea, military and education are most important part to compete with others. R&D is important to run after advanced country. However assisting poor are not crucial in developing country. It is hard to maintain country without countermeasure.</para> Can you assess my paragraph?', 'Socioeconomically poor people usually lack conditions such as education, health care compare to the most. Caring socioeconomically poor people is natural in ethical view. However, it is quite controversial how much of people should be designated as socioeconomical poor. Although socioeconomically poor people are considered the most vulnerable citizens in our society, I believe government should help all of its citizens to ensure that everyone has access to basic necessities and resources. First, government policies that only focus on the socially vulnerable can lead to citizens feeling aggrieved and ignored. The concept of citizenship involves both fulfilling duties to the country and holding rights that the government should uphold. For example, male join the army mandatory. Even though tax is a burden, citizens constantly paying their tax. Instead, citizens get the right to vote for the country. Blindly taking care of the socially vulnerable is ignoring the rights of citizens. Second, proper and reasonable use of the budget is crucial for a functioning economy. While it''s important to assist those in need, such as the poor, there are other areas that require attention as well. In Korea, for example, military and education are crucial for maintaning social stability and competeing with other countries. Investing R&D is also important to keep up with advanced countries. Without caring development and addressing poverty, it can lead to social unrest and hinder economic growth. Therefore, it''s important for the government to distribute resources in a way that benefits the country as a whole. Third, standard for socioeconomically poor people are too arbitrary. During the Corona pandemic, it was controversial to define who to be received. If we give money by income percentile, people who are slightly better can''t get assistance. Otherwise, if we assist by job, usually we think self-employed people are in trouble. However, some self-employed people have earned more through delivery, while job seekers are in difficult circumstances. Helping socioeconomically solely might causes some problems. However, helping them also have their benefits too. For example, government can find out talented man newly. Even so, the decision looks unfair, inefficient and it looks easily be frauded. Conclusion, I think government should provide appropriate welfare to all of the citizens.', '2025-03-20 16:04:00'),
(5, 43, 'Sure, go ahead and share your paragraph, and I''ll be happy to check it for correct comma usage.', '<essay>METHODS This study focuses on the role of anterior cingulate Cortex (ACC) in audiovisual multisensory integration and its potential involvement in auditory dominance in mice facing cognitive conflict scenarios. Experimental Model Details Approval from KAIST Institutional Animal Care and Use Committee was obtained for all procedures. Mice of both sexes aged P40-P120 were used for this study. Experiments were performed on wild type (WT, C57BL/6J n=[number]) male and female mice. Subjects were housed under light (starting at 8am) and dark (starting at 8 pm) cycle in single cages with food (mouse chow) available at will. Weight loss of no more than 10% of the initial weight was approved for experiments. Dual Retrograde Tracing Mice of age P50-90 were lightly anesthesized with isoflurane and set on a stereotaxic device (David Kopf Instruments). Throughout the surgery the mice were kept under 1.0-1.5% isoflurane in oxygen, and on a heating pad to maintain the body temperature. After ensuring proper anaesthesia through toe pinch reflex, the mice were head fixed with ear bars and eyes were covered in Vaseline to avoid dryness. The hair on the head was removed with hair removal cream, and the scalp was opened with a single cut down the middle. After removal of periosteum and cleaning of the skull (with ethanol and 1X phosphate buffered saline (PBS)) the target areas were marked on the right hemisphere in reference to Bregma and Lambda. The coordinates used were AP +0.50 ML -0.20 DV -1.00 for ACC and AP -1.94 ML -.1.90 DV -0.40 for posterior parietal cortex (PPC), decided using Paxinos Atlas and Allen Brain Atlas (1, 2). Small craniotomies of 0.1 mm diameter were made over the target coordinates. Injections were done with Nanoliter injector (World Precision Instruments), 400 nl per area, both at 0.3 nl/sec speed. PPC was injected with pseudotyped AAV virus containing red fluorescence (PAAV-CAG-tdTomato), and ACC was injected with pseudotyped AAV virus containing green fluorescence (PAAV-CAG-tdTomato). Neurons projecting to PPC were expected to show red signals, and neurons projecting to ACC were expected to show green signals, while neurons projecting to both areas would be observed in yellow. After the injections the incision was close by suturing, and mice were sacrificed after 2 weeks for histology. Histology Dual retrograde tracing mice were sacrificed after 2 weeks of virus incubation. The mice were anesthesized deeply with isoflurane and perfused with 1X PBS followed by 4% paraformaldehyde (PFA). The brains were extracted from the skull and left for postfixation in 4% PFA either for 1 hour in room temperature (RT) or overnight in 4C. After fixation, brain samples were transferred into 30% sucrose in RT on a shaker for 2-3 days. After the brains sunk to the bottom of the tube, they were embedded into optimal cutting temperature (OCT) medium (Tissue Tek) and stored at -80C freezer. Cryosectioning was performed at 30 nm thickness at the cryostat (Leica), from posterior areas to PPC to anterior areas to ACC, collecting one section and discarding the next. Sections were collected on microscope slides, washed in 1X PBS 3 times for 10 minutes each, and mounted in DAPI. Slides were imaged at the scanning microscope, in the channels DAPI, EGFP, and TdTomato. Behavioural experiment Surgery P40-60 mice were fixed at the stereotaxic device and kept at the same conditions as mentioned in the Dual Retrograde Tracing surgery. The scalp skin was cut and removed from between the eyes to the ears to expose the skull. Neck muscles were cut and removed. Skull was cleaned and PPC and ACC were marked. Headplates were attached to the skull with Loctite and dental cement. Head-fixed training Head-fixed training was performed to later test the mice in multisensory decision making. Training was done in soundproof chambers, fixed in a head-fixed tube apparatus. The mice were set in licking distance from a water port, a 7 inch gamma-corrected LCD monitor 10 cm away from the left eye (minimum & maximum luminance set as 1 & 120Lux), and a speaker 10 cm away from the left ear. In an attempt to provide a sound proof environment, the wooden chambers were covered with insulating foam on the inside. The mice were trained in a Go/No-Go task for auditory and visual modalities simultaneously. Black and white gradient horizontal/vertical drifting gratings were used for visual stimuli. 5 kHz and 10 kHz pure tones were used for auditory stimuli. Vertical left-to-right drifting gratings and 5 kHz pure tone were trained as Go stimuli and horizontal bottom-to-top drifting gratings and 10 kHz pure tone were trained as No-Go stimuli. The animals were water deprived for 2 days before the training. The first days were free-water period, where the mouse would get 4ul water reward with every lick, with no stimuli present. When the lick rate reached 200 licks/20 min, the mouse was advanced to conditioning period. In this period the mouse was given 1 ul water reward for Go trials regardless of lick response for the association of the stimuli to the reward. No punishment was present at this stage. When the Hit Rate ((Hit x 100)/(Hit+Miss)) reached 70%, the animal would be moved onto the training period. Training period consisted of hit, miss, false alarm and correct rejection according to the mouse’s licking the lick port within the response window after stimulus presentation. Hit trials were rewarded with 1 ul of water if mice licked within the response window. False Alarm trials were punished with a 200 ms airpuff. Miss and Correct rejection trials were neither rewarded nor punished. If animals did not get 1 ml water in total from training in a day, it was given the amount of water to complete the consumption to 1 ml after the training. The training was regarded complete when the Correct Rate (((Hit+Correct Rejection) x 100)/Number of Trials)) reached 80%. In the case of one modality reaching the treshold faster, the mouse was trained in single modality until they were on the same level. There were going to be more subsections but I ran out of time I’m sorry:’) REFERENCES 1. Paxinos G, J. FKB. The Mouse Brain in stereotaxic coordinates. Academic Press; 2019. 2. Allen Mouse Brain Atlas [dataset] [Internet]. 2011. Available from: http://mouse.brain-map.org/ </essay>', 'METHODS This study focuses on the role of anterior cingulate Cortex (ACC) in audiovisual multisensory integration and its potential involvement in auditory dominance in mice facing cognitive conflict scenarios. Experimental Model Details Approval from KAIST Institutional Animal Care and Use Committee was obtained for all procedures. Mice of both sexes aged P40-P120 were used for this study. Experiments were performed on wild type (WT, C57BL/6J n=[number]) male and female mice. Subjects were housed under light (starting at 8am) and dark (starting at 8 pm) cycle in single cages with food (mouse chow) available at will. Weight loss of no more than 10% of the initial weight was approved for experiments. Dual Retrograde Tracing Mice of age P50-90 were lightly anesthesized with isoflurane and set on a stereotaxic device (David Kopf Instruments). Throughout the surgery the mice were kept under 1.0-1.5% isoflurane in oxygen, and on a heating pad to maintain the body temperature. After ensuring proper anaesthesia through toe pinch reflex, the mice were head fixed with ear bars and eyes were covered in Vaseline to avoid dryness. The hair on the head was removed with hair removal cream, and the scalp was opened with a single cut down the middle. After removal of periosteum and cleaning of the skull (with ethanol and 1X phosphate buffered saline (PBS)) the target areas were marked on the right hemisphere in reference to Bregma and Lambda. The coordinates used were AP +0.50 ML -0.20 DV -1.00 for ACC and AP -1.94 ML -.1.90 DV -0.40 for posterior parietal cortex (PPC), decided using Paxinos Atlas and Allen Brain Atlas (1, 2). Small craniotomies of 0.1 mm diameter were made over the target coordinates. Injections were done with Nanoliter injector (World Precision Instruments), 400 nl per area, both at 0.3 nl/sec speed. PPC was injected with pseudotyped AAV virus containing red fluorescence (PAAV-CAG-tdTomato), and ACC was injected with pseudotyped AAV virus containing green fluorescence (PAAV-CAG-tdTomato). Neurons projecting to PPC were expected to show red signals, and neurons projecting to ACC were expected to show green signals, while neurons projecting to both areas would be observed in yellow. After the injections the incision was close by suturing, and mice were sacrificed after 2 weeks for histology. Histology Dual retrograde tracing mice were sacrificed after 2 weeks of virus incubation. The mice were anesthesized deeply with isoflurane and perfused with 1X PBS followed by 4% paraformaldehyde (PFA). The brains were extracted from the skull and left for postfixation in 4% PFA either for 1 hour in room temperature (RT) or overnight in 4C. After fixation, brain samples were transferred into 30% sucrose in RT on a shaker for 2-3 days. After the brains sunk to the bottom of the tube, they were embedded into optimal cutting temperature (OCT) medium (Tissue Tek) and stored at -80C freezer. Cryosectioning was performed at 30 nm thickness at the cryostat (Leica), from posterior areas to PPC to anterior areas to ACC, collecting one section and discarding the next. Sections were collected on microscope slides, washed in 1X PBS 3 times for 10 minutes each, and mounted in DAPI. Slides were imaged at the scanning microscope, in the channels DAPI, EGFP, and TdTomato. Behavioural experiment Surgery P40-60 mice were fixed at the stereotaxic device and kept at the same conditions as mentioned in the Dual Retrograde Tracing surgery. The scalp skin was cut and removed from between the eyes to the ears to expose the skull. Neck muscles were cut and removed. Skull was cleaned and PPC and ACC were marked. Headplates were attached to the skull with Loctite and dental cement. Head-fixed training Head-fixed training was performed to later test the mice in multisensory decision making. Training was done in soundproof chambers, fixed in a head-fixed tube apparatus. The mice were set in licking distance from a water port, a 7 inch gamma-corrected LCD monitor 10 cm away from the left eye (minimum & maximum luminance set as 1 & 120Lux), and a speaker 10 cm away from the left ear. In an attempt to provide a sound proof environment, the wooden chambers were covered with insulating foam on the inside. The mice were trained in a Go/No-Go task for auditory and visual modalities simultaneously. Black and white gradient horizontal/vertical drifting gratings were used for visual stimuli. 5 kHz and 10 kHz pure tones were used for auditory stimuli. Vertical left-to-right drifting gratings and 5 kHz pure tone were trained as Go stimuli and horizontal bottom-to-top drifting gratings and 10 kHz pure tone were trained as No-Go stimuli. The animals were water deprived for 2 days before the training. The first days were free-water period, where the mouse would get 4ul water reward with every lick, with no stimuli present. When the lick rate reached 200 licks/20 min, the mouse was advanced to conditioning period. In this period the mouse was given 1 ul water reward for Go trials regardless of lick response for the association of the stimuli to the reward. No punishment was present at this stage. When the Hit Rate ((Hit x 100)/(Hit+Miss)) reached 70%, the animal would be moved onto the training period. Training period consisted of hit, miss, false alarm and correct rejection according to the mouse’s licking the lick port within the response window after stimulus presentation. Hit trials were rewarded with 1 ul of water if mice licked within the response window. False Alarm trials were punished with a 200 ms airpuff. Miss and Correct rejection trials were neither rewarded nor punished. If animals did not get 1 ml water in total from training in a day, it was given the amount of water to complete the consumption to 1 ml after the training. The training was regarded complete when the Correct Rate (((Hit+Correct Rejection) x 100)/Number of Trials)) reached 80%. In the case of one modality reaching the treshold faster, the mouse was trained in single modality until they were on the same level. There were going to be more subsections but I ran out of time I’m sorry:’) REFERENCES 1. Paxinos G, J. FKB. The Mouse Brain in stereotaxic coordinates. Academic Press; 2019. 2. Allen Mouse Brain Atlas [dataset] [Internet]. 2011. Available from: http://mouse.brain-map.org/', '2025-04-03 18:04:00'),
(1, 44, 'I''m sorry, but that does not appear to be a summary of what you learned in my scientific writing class. Can you please provide me with a brief explanation of what you learned in class, so that we can discuss it?', '<sent>Q3) 3D reconstruction using Stereo Vision has the disadvantage that it is difficult to accurately find corresponding pairs and is greatly affected by external environmental factors such as ambient light. If you could add a digital projector to project both fringe and binary patterns onto the target to be measured, explain how you could use it to find corresponding pairs with the stereo vision system.</sent>', 'Adding a digital projector to a stereo vision system can improve the accuracy of 3D reconstruction by projecting both fringe and binary patterns onto the object to be measured. To find corresponding pairs, we can project fringe and binary patterns onto the object''s surface and capture two images of the object from different viewpoints. The fringe pattern is used to calculate the disparity map and identify corresponding pairs, while the binary pattern is used to refine the matching in regions where the disparity map may not be accurate. By combining the 3D positions obtained from both the fringe and binary patterns, we can obtain a more accurate and robust reconstruction of the object''s surface. Projecting patterns also helps reduce the impact of external environmental factors such as ambient light. The unwrapped phase information can be used to calculate the absolute depth value of each point on the object''s surface.', '2025-02-14 12:08:00'),
(2, 44, 'Yes, of course! Compare and contrast is a common type of essay where the writer analyzes similarities and differences between two or more things. This could be anything from two different books, two different characters, or even two different historical events. The goal is to provide a thoughtful and well-researched analysis that highlights the similarities and differences between the subjects you are comparing.', 'Can you please revise my essay with compare and contrast? Here''s the original one. <essay>In recent years, the increased use of tablets, laptops, and other internet technology devices in classrooms has brought about two significant advantages: increased student participation and greater usefulness of these devices in the classroom. As a result, the use of tablets and laptops can lead to increased student participation in class activities by providing engaging tools and incorporating online learning platforms. For example, playing Kahoot quiz about what students have learned increases understanding of the concept they have learned, and using QR codes to join some activity in class will rise interest of students. In addition, students and professors can contact each other online via Zoom or Google Meets, which can also increase participation of students who are far away. By using tablets and laptops, students can participate in class more actively. Furthermore, the second advantage is the usefulness of using such devices. In class, professors do their class using lecture notes, and sometimes they write down some letters on the whiteboard. Students who use tablets or laptops can easily download the lecture note, write what they understand down on it, take some pictures of the whiteboard, and share some copy of their online notes. Also, by using some internet platforms such as KLMS or Google Classroom, students can upload their homework or handouts more comfortably. The most important part of the advantages, usefulness, is that students can do those things with only one electronic device; they need no paper, no pencil, no erasers. In conclusion, the use of electronic devices in the classroom has significant advantages, such as increased student participation and greater usefulness. By taking advantage of these benefits, students can use their own tablet or laptop computers in class with more ease and productivity.</essay>', 'In recent years, the use of electronic devices in classrooms has become more prevalent, and there are both advantages and disadvantages to this trend. In terms of advantages, increased student participation and greater usefulness in the classroom are the most notable benefits. On the one hand, the use of tablets and laptops can increase student participation in class activities by providing engaging tools and incorporating online learning platforms. For example, playing Kahoot or Quizlet games about the course material can enhance understanding and retention of key concepts. Similarly, online platforms like Zoom or Google Meets can provide an opportunity for students to engage with professors and peers even if they are not physically present in the classroom. By using tablets and laptops, students can participate in class more actively and experience a more immersive learning environment. On the other hand, some critics argue that a reliance on electronic devices in the classroom can have negative consequences. For instance, it can foster a culture of distraction and undermine students'' ability to focus. Moreover, technology can sometimes fail, leading to disruptions in teaching and learning. In addition, while electronic documents are convenient, they can be easily lost if not properly saved or backed up. Despite these potential disadvantages, the advantages of using electronic devices in the classroom outweigh the disadvantages. In particular, electronic devices enable greater collaboration, productivity, and flexibility among students and professors. By taking advantage of these benefits, students can use their own tablet or laptop computers in class with more ease and productivity.', '2025-02-27 13:08:00'),
(3, 44, 'Great, here''s the revised version with the verb tense errors corrected: "Recent developments in open domain question answering have become more sophisticated, and researchers have been experimenting with innovative approaches to solve the task. In one study, a new approach was proposed that combines the strengths of the retrieve-read and retrieve-generate pipelines. Another research group has developed a deep learning model that can generate natural language answers with high accuracy. Despite these advancements, there are still challenges to be addressed in open domain QA, such as handling long-form questions and identifying reliable sources of information. Future research is likely to focus on overcoming these challenges to improve the performance of open domain QA systems." I changed the first sentence from "is becoming" to "have become" since developments are ongoing and have progressed so far, they are no longer developing. In the second sentence, "is proposed" was changed to "was proposed" since the study was completed in the past. The next sentence, "has developed" was correct, but I kept it for consistency. The fourth sentence, "will likely focus" was corrected since future research is an activity that has yet to happen, making "will likely focus" a more suitable verb tense.', 'can you check one more time to make sure there aren''t any other mistakes in there?', '"Recent developments in open domain question answering have become more sophisticated, and researchers have been experimenting with innovative approaches to solve the task. In one study, a new approach was proposed that combines the strengths of the retrieve-read and retrieve-generate pipelines. Another research group has developed a deep learning model that can generate natural language answers with high accuracy. Despite these advancements, there are still challenges to be addressed in open domain QA, such as handling long-form questions and identifying reliable sources of information. Future research is likely to focus on overcoming these challenges to improve the performance of open domain QA systems."', '2025-03-13 11:38:00'),
(4, 44, 'Error', 'Do you think my draft effectively conveys my own interpretation of, or insights into, the primary issues of the topic?', 'Summarizing the above listed papers, we arrive at the following conclusions. Transformers are indeed effective, albeit computationally heavy, at performing video super-resolution (VSR). Earlier works such as VSR-T [1] merely employed transformer blocks while retaining the same overall framework as existing convolutional or recurrent networks, and many design elements such as elaborate alignment modules also carried over from recurrent models to those early transformer-based models. Later works have since challenged that foundation, such as attempting to remove or greatly simplify the alignment mechanism between different frames,[2] or formulating radical redesigns to self-attention mechanisms.[3] These works serve to optimize transformer designs to suit the characteristics of vsr tasks specifically, where information from multiple distant frames as well as many different regions from the same frame needs to be aggregated for accurate and smooth reconstruction. Although various model architectures have been tested, no particular transformer design appears to have won out over others, and emerging papers continue to propose wildly varying architectures. This suggests that there is still much room for experimentations on vsr transformer design. Research on generalization capabilities and overfitting issues of vsr transformer models seems yet to have received the same level of attention as transformers being used for other tasks. Transformer models have a tendency to require much larger training datasets compared to convolutional or recurrent models, and even then they struggle to generalize to forms of degradation or data domains that were not seen during training. [4] As blind super-resolution [5] - the task to reconstruct low-resolution inputs that have been downsampled by arbitrary degradation mechanisms - is a very active field of research for single-image super-resolution, such generalization capability issues need to be tackled down the road. VSR transformers have evolved to handle large numbers of video frames and aggregate large amounts of information over long spatial and temporal ranges. Design elements that enabled this can also be adapted for other video tasks, such as deblurring, optical flow estimation, or video frame interpolation. However, many design elements will need to be greatly altered to accommodate for their respective target tasks’ own specific needs, like vsr transformers evolved to accommodate for vsr specific characteristics.', '2025-03-20 16:08:00'),
(5, 44, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about choppy sentences. When too short sentences are overused, the writing could be considered poor styled. Therefor, It is important to combine them using soordination and subordination.', 'I think the government should help all of its citizens regardless of their socioeconomic background. Firstly, government is an organization for all people. Government is here for everyone. It is true that when the government help people in need, it will be able to help people as much as possible, which will be very helpful for them. However, the fact that helping people in need has many positive aspects does not meas that it is okay to ‘not help others’. Government only working for a small part of people and ignoring the rest should not happen. Also, I think it is unfair either. I agree to helping a bit more to the people in need. There are people who can’t live without some help of the government. There are problems that government should deal with in order to help people. However, only helping those who need help could be viewed as discriminating others. As I already wrote, government is an organization for all. Making nobody feel discriminated by the government is the way I think government should go. Secondly, in a realistic point of view, government could not exist only with those who are in need, so that they should take care of others. For example, government is managed by money that people pay as tax. To get much tax, they should have many people who are rich in the country. In order to keep them in the country, the country should do something for them. If the government only help those in need and ignore others, the government could not exist. Therefore, the best way to help those in need is not just helping them fully but helping them steady. These are the reasons why I think government should help all of its citizens regardless of their socioeconomic background.', '2025-04-03 18:08:00'),
(1, 45, 'Great! Let''s revise your essay together. Can you please provide me with a copy of your essay?', '<essay>I''m against women joining the army. There are some reasons that supporting my idea. First, physical conditions are not equal between a woman and a man. The physical difference between a woman and a man in their 20s is quite large. As a result, it is not easy to serve with the same level of training. Second, the military is a closed society, and there is a possibility of crime in it. Unlike now situation, if two genders have to live in the military, there might be many problems that comes from the difference of two genders. As a result, the crime can be increased, Third, joining women to the military cannot resolve gender inequality. There are too many conditions that can cause other discriminatory perceptions even if a woman joins the military, such as facilities, hair length, and degree of training. Therefore, it is difficult to judge that women''s enlistment in the army provides a fundamental solution. Of course, it is a pity that men go to the military to support their youth in their young and precious days in their 20s. I think women should live with more respect for men and a heart that contributes to the country.</essay>', 'I oppose women''s enlistment in the army. Physical conditions are not equal between a woman and a man. The physical difference between a woman and a man in their 20s is quite large. As a result, it is not easy to serve with the same level of training. In addition, the military is a closed society, and there is a possibility of crime in it. Unlike now situation, if two genders have to live in the military, there might be many problems that comes from the difference of two genders. As a result, the crime can be increased, Moreover, joining women to the military cannot resolve gender inequality. There are too many conditions that can cause other discriminatory perceptions even if a woman joins the military, such as facilities, hair length, and degree of training. Therefore, it is difficult to judge that women''s enlistment in the army provides a fundamental solution. Of course, it is a pity that men go to the military to support their youth in their young and precious days in their 20s. I think women should live with more respect for men and a heart that contributes to the country.', '2025-02-14 12:12:00'),
(2, 45, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about the comma rules. When there is a list that contains two or more elements, we should use commas to separate them.', 'Development Trend and Performance Analysis of Hypergolic Propellant Developed countries that have researched space for a long time ago are sending satellites, probes into the space for exploration of resources and future habitat. Such explorations were largely led by national agencies/organizations due to astronomical cost, but in recent years, the exploration market has grown larger and more private companies are entering the space industry. For example, SpaceX, a leader of the private sector in the market, has developed Falcon series reusable rocket. They also send a number of payloads(satellites, probes etc.) into space every year. The most vital element in space exploration is a satellite’s lifetime. For satellites, long-period/distance operation to explore various places and fine thrust control and re-ignition for orbit modification are much more important factors than the magnitude of thrust. Typical methods used to generate thrust of satellites include using propellants(combination of fuels and oxidizers), solar energy, and molecular ionization etc. Solar energy is disadvantageous for long-distance exploration because satellites cannot always receive energy as they move behind the sun and if they go far from source that can receive, it is also difficult to operate. However, hypergolic propellant have no constraints needed to generate thrust(solar energy must need source). Hypergolic propellant is a propellant that spontaneously combusts when fuel and oxidizer make contact, resulting in a simple engine structure(no igniter). Moreover, it exists in a liquid state at room temperature(298K), so it has long-period storage. Hypergolic propellants used the past include hydrazine-based fuels(hydrazine, MMH, UDMH) and nitrogen tetraoxide(N2O4) or hydrazine-based fuels and NTO combinations. These combinations have been widely used in developed countries since the beginning of space development due to their high efficiency and long-period storage characteristics. For example, the European Union''s Ariane 1, Russia''s Proton launcher''s RD-253 ,and China''s Jangjeong 1 to 4 all used N2O4-UDMH or NTO-UDMH as propellants, and the fuel A-50 used in Titan or Delta rocket top engines was a combination of 50% UDMH and 50% MMH. However, these propellant combinations are highly toxic carcinogens and absorb moisture when exposed to the air, so advanced technologies and special equipment are required for handling, and protective clothing and gas masks must be worn. Also, the high cost of technology and equipment prohibits practical use. A possible solution to solve these shortcomings is low toxicity and eco-friendly hypergolic propellants. Representative eco-friendly low-toxic hypergolic propellants are combinations of the low-toxic fuel-hydrogen peroxide(H2O2). This paper reviews the advantages of eco-friendly low-toxic hypergolic propellants and compares the rocket performance such as ignition delay, thrust, specific impulse, specific velocity with original hypergolic propellants. Finally, it suggests about the future directions of hypergolic propellant research.', '2025-02-27 13:12:00'),
(3, 45, 'Okay. Let me give you a quick rundown of the basic structure of a Cause and Effect essay. Introduction: - In the introduction, you introduce the topic and provide background information or context to the reader. - You can also provide a thesis statement or a clear statement of your position on the topic. Body paragraphs: - The body of the essay should be organized into paragraphs, with each paragraph focusing on a different cause or effect. - Each paragraph should have a topic sentence that clearly states the cause or effect you are discussing. - You can use evidence or examples to support your points. - It''s important to use transitions to connect your ideas and show the relationship between the causes or effects. Conclusion: - In the conclusion, you summarize your main points and restate your thesis in a different way, without simply repeating it. - You can also provide some final thoughts or recommendations. Now, let''s turn our attention to your essay. Can you please provide me with a copy of your essay so we can go over it together?', '<essay> Numerous jobs are easily replaced by AI nowdays. This phenomenon leads to a drastic decline in employment. As a result, many people will be expected to lost their jobs. In this situation, one solution is considered which is universal basic income. However, this solution needs to be excluded because of many side effects and unsustainability. This essay will explore why UBI is not an appropriate solution and suggest things to consider in order to create better solution. UBI can be implemented in two main ways. One way is giving UBI every person in same amount, and the other is giving that differently based on income level. If goverment give UBI every person in the same amount, the product price will increase. Moreover, the money which goverment has will decreases, and the money have to be used in public policy will be insufficient. As a result, UBI can''t ensure people''s life quality. The other hand, UBI can be given differently based on income level. But, this leads to the other problems. Think about two people. One works hard to earn sufficient money for family, and the other does nothing. The person working hard would get less money than person do nothing. This removes the reason working hard, and It leads to decreasing productivity in society. In this respect, UBI can cause many side effects. It can be also seen in terms of the efficient use of funds by the government. People who benefit from AI would earn many money by AI development, but the other lose their job. As a result, many amount of money would be bias to people who related with AI. However, the government does not have to inject money into society because the total amount of money is constant. The proper role of the government is to establish policies to create jobs and encourage employment in society. In terms of sustainability, UBI is a short-term solution. Therefore, UBI has many risks to make it difficult to maintain society in the long run. If UBI is started, it is difficult to decide when to stop this policy. There is a high possibility that UBI support will be decreased or stopped due to economic factors. And, such a situation would cause social and economic turmoil. Since employment problem due to AI will get worse in the future as technology advances, the solution about that has to be sustainable and stable. But, UBI has many risks and side effects. Therefore, UBI should not be considered as a solution. More stable and sustainable solutions has to be founded to solve this problem.</essay>', 'Numerous jobs are easily replaced by AI nowdays. This phenomenon leads to a drastic decline in employment. As a result, many people will be expected to lost their jobs. In this situation, one solution is considered which is universal basic income. However, this solution needs to be excluded because of many side effects and unsustainability. This essay will explore why UBI is not an appropriate solution and suggest things to consider in order to create better solution. UBI can be implemented in two main ways. One way is giving UBI every person in same amount, and the other is giving that differently based on income level. If government give UBI every person in the same amount, the product price will increase. Moreover, the money which government has will decreases, and the money have to be used in public policy will be insufficient. As a result, UBI can''t ensure people''s life quality. The other hand, UBI can be given differently based on income level. But, this leads to the other problems. Think about two people. One works hard to earn sufficient money for family, and the other does nothing. The person working hard would get less money than person do nothing. This removes the reason working hard, and It leads to decreasing productivity in society. In this respect, UBI can cause many side effects. It can be also seen in terms of the efficient use of funds by the government. People who benefit from AI would earn many money by AI development, but the other lose their job. As a result, many amount of money would be bias to people who related with AI. However, the government does not have to inject money into society because the total amount of money is constant. The proper role of the government is to establish policies to create jobs and encourage employment in society. In terms of sustainability, UBI is a short-term solution. Therefore, UBI has many risks to make it difficult to maintain society in the long run. If UBI is started, it is difficult to decide when to stop this policy. There is a high possibility that UBI support will be decreased or stopped due to economic factors. And, such a situation would cause social and economic turmoil. Since employment problem due to AI will get worse in the future as technology advances, the solution about that has to be sustainable and stable. But, UBI has many risks and side effects. Therefore, UBI should not be considered as a solution. More stable and sustainable solutions has to be founded to solve this problem.', '2025-03-13 11:42:00'),
(4, 45, 'Great! Let''s start by reviewing your essay. Can you please provide me with a copy of your essay? We can then go through it step by step and make the necessary revisions.', 'I believe that government should help those most in need, not all of its citizens. There are two reasons for my opinion. Firstly, if the government tries to help everyone, it is inevitable that some of the most vulnerable people in society will be overlooked. For example, there are many elderly citizens who live alone in poverty and desperately need support. If the government''s resources are spread too thin, these individuals are unlikely to get the assistance they require. Therefore, I believe that the government should concentrate its efforts on supporting the most disadvantaged members of society. Secondly, it is unfair for wealthy individuals to receive government benefits when they don''t need them. I think that those who have an abundance of resources should be required to contribute more to society. For instance, it is a well-established fact that a small minority of individuals possess the majority of wealth in our country. In order to create a more equitable society for everyone, I believe that the wealthy should pay higher taxes and be willing to contribute more to social welfare initiatives. Overall, I believe that the government should focus its resources on aiding those who are most in need. This is particularly important given the deep divide between the rich and the poor in our society. I am confident that if we all work together and extend a helping hand to those who require it the most, we can create a better world for ourselves and for future generations.', 'The issue of government assistance is a contentious one, with many people arguing that the government should help all citizens, while others believe that resources should be focused on those who are most in need. In this essay, I will argue that the government should prioritize helping the most vulnerable members of society. By doing so, we can create a more equitable society that benefits everyone. Firstly, it is important to recognize that there are many vulnerable members of society who require government assistance. For example, elderly citizens who live alone in poverty often struggle to make ends meet and require support to maintain a decent standard of living. However, if the government tries to help everyone, it is inevitable that some of these individuals will be overlooked. This is because resources are limited, and it is difficult to provide comprehensive support to everyone. Therefore, it is essential that the government focuses its efforts on supporting the most disadvantaged members of society. Secondly, it is unfair for wealthy individuals to receive government benefits when they don''t need them. While some argue that everyone should receive equal treatment, this ignores the fact that some people have more resources than others. In order to create a more equitable society, it is important that those who have an abundance of resources contribute more to social welfare initiatives. This can be achieved through higher taxes and other measures that ensure that the burden of supporting those in need is shared more equitably. In conclusion, the government should prioritize helping the most vulnerable members of society. By doing so, we can create a more equitable society that benefits everyone. This can be achieved through targeted support for those in need, as well as measures that ensure that the burden of supporting those in need is shared more equitably. I urge everyone to consider the importance of this issue and to take action to support those who require assistance. Together, we can create a better world for ourselves and for future generations.', '2025-03-20 16:12:00'),
(5, 45, 'Sure, here is a slightly longer and more detailed version while still incorporating percentages: Table 1 summarizes the feedback from students on the class content. Overall, the results indicate that students have mixed feelings about the effectiveness of the textbook content in developing their writing skills. While 68% of the students agree that the textbook is helpful to develop their writing skills, only 21% strongly agreed. Similarly, while 53% of the students agreed that the textbook is clearly understandable, only 37% strongly agreed. In contrast, most students found the video and classroom content satisfactory. 63% and 68% of the students strongly agreed that the classroom content and videos were clearly understandable, respectively. Additionally, 74% of the students agreed that the videos were an appropriate length, while 58% strongly agreed that the amount of time spent checking homework tasks is appropriate. However, the data also revealed that 58% of the students either are neutral or disagree that the amount of reading each week is appropriate. Thus, the findings suggest that instructors should consider adjusting the amount of reading assigned in the course. Overall, the survey results indicate that students have mixed feelings regarding the efficacy of textbook content in developing their writing abilities. The feedback on classroom content and videos was more positive, suggesting instructors should focus more on these methods of instruction.', 'is it okay to have number of percentage at the beginning of the sentence?', 'Table 1 summarizes the class content feedback from the student respondents. The results from Table 1 indicate that the students have mixed views regarding the effectiveness of the textbook content in developing their writing skills. While 68% of the students agree that the textbook is clearly understandable, only 21% strongly agreed. Similarly, while 53% of the students agreed that the textbook is helpful to develop their writing skills, only 37% strongly agreed. In contrast, most students found the video and classroom content satisfactory. Additionally, 74% of the students agreed that the videos were an appropriate length, while 58% strongly agreed that the amount of time spent checking homework tasks is appropriate. However, the data also revealed that 58% of the students either are neutral or disagree that the amount of reading each week is appropriate. Thus, the findings suggest that instructors should consider adjusting the amount of reading assigned in the course. Overall, the survey findings indicate that the students have mixed feelings regarding the efficacy of textbook content in developing their writing abilities, while they typically find the video and classroom content to be more positive. The findings may help the instructors adjust their teaching methods and course materials to better meet the needs and expectations of the students.', '2025-04-03 18:12:00'),
(1, 46, 'Great, it sounds like we covered a lot of important topics today! Can you explain to me how to properly use paraphrasing in scientific writing? And also, do you mind giving me an example of how to correctly use a colon and a semicolon in a sentence?Lastly, can you tell me what some common mistakes are when it comes to unclear pronoun reference and how we can avoid them?', 'First of all, I learned the 5 tools for paraphrasing: replace some of the words with synonyms, make a positive verb into a negative verb, change active constructions to passive, and vice versa, change words into other parts of speech, and move parts of sentences around. Next, a colon introduces a formal list, long quotation, equation, or definition. And a semicolon can join two independent clauses and separate items in a complex list. Third, there are several rules of using hyphens. Especially, when there is a compound modifier ending in -ly or to stack modifiers too much, we should not use hyphen. Finally, anticipatory reference and ambiguous antecendent are the common mistakes to unclear pronoun reference. To avoid them, we use pronoun right after the target noun and specify the noun which we used for pronoun.', 'Applications of directed hypergraphs (DHs): DHs have been used in various domains to model chemical reactions [5], metabolism [37], bitcoin transactions [40], citation networks [50], road networks [32], and email communications [26]. A number of works address machine learning problems on DHs, including node classification [44], hyperarc prediction [22, 32, 51], and hypergraph generation [26], and question answering [49]. Structural properties of real-world DHs: The wide applicability of DHs has led to the study of the structural properties of realworld DHs, i.e., DHs that model real-world complex systems. Kim et al. [26] examined how reciprocal hyperarcs in real-world DHs are. To this end, they defined a principled measure of reciprocity of DHs, and using it, they revealed that hyperarcs in real-world DHs tend to be more reciprocal than those in random DHs. They also showed that the reciprocal structures can be reproduced by a simple preferential-attachment-like mechanism. Moyano and Jose [35] analyzed the strongly connected components (SCCs)1 of OWL ontologies after modeling them as DHs, and to this end, they proposed fast algorithms for finding SCCs in DHs. In addition, a number of studies have focused on structural properties of undirected hypergraphs [7, 9, 16, 17, 27]. Graphlet analysis of (directed) graphs: There exists a long line of research on local structures of (directed) graphs using (directed) graphlets [33, 34, 41], which are induced isomorphism classes of subgraphs with a fixed number of nodes. A typical procedure, which we also extend to DHs in Section 3.2, is to (a) count the instances of each graphlet in a given graph and (b) measure its significance by comparing it with the count in a randomized graph. The significances of all graphlets, which we call the characteristic profile (CP), summarize the local structures of the graph and using CPs, we can directly compare (e.g., measure the similarity between) the local structures of two graphs of different sizes. In addition to graph characterization, graphlets have been used for various applications, including clustering [8], link prediction [3, 20], malware detection [21]. Counting the instance of each graphlet is computationally challenging, and thus a large number of exact and approximate counting algorithms have been developed [4, 10–12, 24, 39]. It should be noticed that the computational challenge that these algorithms address comes from the increase of the size of each graphlet, and this is different from the challenge (see Section 4.3) in counting the instances of DHGs, whose size (i.e., the number of hyperarcs) is fixed, and thus their ideas are not directly applicable to our problem. Graphlet analysis of undirected hypergraphs: Lotito et al. [31] directly extended the notion of graphlets to undirected hypergraphs. They defined higher-order motifs, which are isomorphic classes of connected sub-hypergraphs composed of 𝑛 (spec., 3 or 4) nodes. However, this notion is not appropriate when the size of a hyperedge is unbounded or at least can be greater than 𝑛. Discarding the hyperedges of size bigger than 𝑛 or generating new hyperedges through the intersection with a set of 𝑛 nodes leads to distortion and loss of information that original hypergraphs contain. In order to overcome such an issue, Lee et al. [28] defined h-motifs (a.k.a., hypergraph motifs) based on (the emptiness of seven regions occurred by) three overlapping hyperedges (i.e., node sets), independently of the sizes of hyperedges, and the notion was later extended to temporal hypergrahps [29]. They also provided approximate counting algorithms, based on which the baseline counting algorithm in Section 5.4 is designed. If we ignore directional information in DHs, h-motifs can be applied to DHs, but the characterization power is limited, as shown in Sections 5.2 and 5.3.', '2025-02-14 12:16:00'),
(2, 46, 'Yes, your paragraph includes all six essential components of an abstract. You have provided background information on the topic, stated the research question, described the experimental approach, presented the results, discussed the conclusion, and highlighted the significance of the study. Well done!', 'Also, I lerned about the signal for these six main components. The examples of the signals are 1) Our finding, 2) To elucidate, 3) We determined, etc.. Can you find signals similar to thay I mentioned in the examples? Please find the signals in my paragraph <para>"Many insects possess a sexual communication system that is vulnerable to chemical espionage by parasitic wasps. We recently discovered that a hitch-hiking (H) egg parasitoid exploits the antiaphrodisiac pheromone benzyl cyanide (BC) of the Large Cabbage White butterfly Pieris brassicae. This pheromone is passed from male butterflies to females during mating to render them less attractive to conspecific males. When the tiny parasitic wasp Trochogramma brassicae detects the antiaphrodisiac, it rides on a mated female butterfly to a host plant and then parasitizes her freshly laid eggs. The present study demonstrates that a closely related generalist wasp, Trichogramma evanescens, exploits BC in a similar way, but only after learning. Interestingly, the wasp learns to associate an H response to the odors of a mater femalr P. brassicae butterfly with reinforcement by parasitizing freshly laid butterfly effs. Behavioral assays, before which we specifically inhibited long-term memory (LTM) formation with a translation inhibitor, reveal that the wasp has formed protein synthesis-dependent LTM at 24 h after learning. To our knowledge, the combination of associatively learning to exploit the sexual communication system of a host and the formation of protein synthesis-dependent LTM after a single learning event has not been documented before. We expect it to be widespread in nature, because it is highly adaptive in many species of egg parasitoids. Our finding of the exploitation of an antiaphrodisiac by multiple species of parasitic wasps suggests its use by Pieris butterflies to be under strong selective pressure. "</para>.', 'Many insects possess a sexual communication system that is vulnerable to chemical espionage by parasitic wasps. We recently discovered that a hitch-hiking (H) egg parasitoid exploits the antiaphrodisiac pheromone benzyl cyanide (BC) of the Large Cabbage White butterfly Pieris brassicae. This pheromone is passed from male butterflies to females during mating to render them less attractive to conspecific males. When the tiny parasitic wasp Trochogramma brassicae detects the antiaphrodisiac, it rides on a mated female butterfly to a host plant and then parasitizes her freshly laid eggs. The present study demonstrates that a closely related generalist wasp, Trichogramma evanescens, exploits BC in a similar way, but only after learning. Interestingly, the wasp learns to associate an H response to the odors of a mater femalr P. brassicae butterfly with reinforcement by parasitizing freshly laid butterfly effs. Behavioral assays, before which we specifically inhibited long-term memory (LTM) formation with a translation inhibitor, reveal that the wasp has formed protein synthesis-dependent LTM at 24 h after learning. To our knowledge, the combination of associatively learning to exploit the sexual communication system of a host and the formation of protein synthesis-dependent LTM after a single learning event has not been documented before. We expect it to be widespread in nature, because it is highly adaptive in many species of egg parasitoids. Our finding of the exploitation of an antiaphrodisiac by multiple species of parasitic wasps suggests its use by Pieris butterflies to be under strong selective pressure.', '2025-02-27 13:16:00'),
(3, 46, 'Great! It''s important to begin with a strong introduction that captures the reader''s attention. Have you thought about any specific story or anecdote that relates to your topic? It''s important to choose a story that is relevant and interesting, and that will make the reader want to read more. Additionally, it should set up the rest of your essay and provide context for your discussion.', '<essay>I think that goverment must help citizen according to criteria about not import but situation. First, Korea help poor people to date but in other people, there are people who are in trouble with working because of disease, privacy condition, ete... When they work in order to overcome difficulty, government do not support them for reason that they have ability to be responsible for living family. Eventually, bad circumstance will be continued. Even individuals who encounter challenging circumstances should be given equal opportunities to improve their situation through hard work. Second, overhelping can bring neglect of duty. If people who do not have money, because they do not live hard and working. This rule make strange society that faithful people live difficult life and lazy people live peaceful life. Finally, someone who just works hard and earns a lot money is required to be sacrified is unfair. Among the rich, some inherit their wealth while others earn it through labor or investments. Even though they work hard in order to live enough life, government required them to sacrify. It can be lower desire. For these three reasons, the government should not only provide support based on economic status but must also consider the individual''s situation in order to provide equitable assistance to those who are in need. Of course, the criteria of circumstance is not obvious, situations must be considered. I hope to change the rule and provide opportunitied to people who live hardly.<essay> This is my essay.', 'I think that goverment must help citizen according to criteria about not import but situation. First, Korea help poor people to date but in other people, there are people who are in trouble with working because of disease, privacy condition, ete... When they work in order to overcome difficulty, government do not support them for reason that they have ability to be responsible for living family. Eventually, bad circumstance will be continued. Even individuals who encounter challenging circumstances should be given equal opportunities to improve their situation through hard work. Second, overhelping can bring neglect of duty. If people who do not have money, because they do not live hard and working. This rule make strange society that faithful people live difficult life and lazy people live peaceful life. Finally, someone who just works hard and earns a lot money is required to be sacrified is unfair. Among the rich, some inherit their wealth while others earn it through labor or investments. Even though they work hard in order to live enough life, government required them to sacrify. It can be lower desire. For these three reasons, the government should not only provide support based on economic status but must also consider the individual''s situation in order to provide equitable assistance to those who are in need. Of course, the criteria of circumstance is not obvious, situations must be considered. I hope to change the rule and provide opportunitied to people who live hardly.', '2025-03-13 11:46:00'),
(4, 46, 'Great! Let''s begin by reviewing your essay to see how you have used commas in your writing. 1. Start by reading your essay carefully several times. 2. Look for places where you have used lists or multiple items in a sentence. 3. Check to see if you have used commas to separate the items in the list. 4. If you have, make sure that the commas are placed correctly. They should be placed after each item except for the last one, which should be followed by ''and'' or ''or''. 5. If you have not used commas, identify the places where they need to be added and add them accordingly. 6. Finally, read the revised essay once again to ensure that the commas are used correctly and do not create any confusion in the sentence. If you have any questions or need further guidance, feel free to ask!', 'Today I learned about synonyms, words that share the same or almost the same basic meaning. The writer use these synonyms to avoid repetition.', 'Majority of people may have experienced to wear their school uniform. This traditional thought that students should wear school uniform may last very long time, even for these days. However, recently there are some schools which allow students to wear free clothes when they go to school. Of course freedom of students is important, but I think that high school should control student''s clothes and they should wear constant clothes as school uniform. There are two big reasons that I asserts with this statement. Firstly, wearing school uniform is very economical. It is needless to say that young people are usually interested in fashion or trend. So they buy new clothes or accessories that are famous for their friends. For example, in 2000s, there were some students so-called "backbone broker" in South Korean that required a kind of expensive jackets such as "Goose down" for their parents. If high school control students to wear school uniform, students do not have to buy expensive and high-quality clothes to wear in school. Moreover, It is worth pointing that as they wear school uniform for 5 days a week, they don''t need large amount of clothes on daily life. As I pointed out, wearing school uniform can reduce payment on clothes, so it is economical. Secondly, I would like to say that school uniform is able to represent school''s identity. Obviously, once school uniform select for specific school, usually it would not change for very long term. In other words, many people who graduated those school wore the school uniform. The point is that such school uniform could be a symbol of school. For instance, if you walk along that street and see some students wearing school uniform, you could recognize the name of school students are in. Furthermore, wearing school uniform may integret student''s mind, because it provide same design for all of students. I think that school uniform is capable of making an image and identity of each school. In conclusion, wearing school uniform is helpful in reducing economcal burden. Also, it could make a kind of identity in school. Thus, I think that school uniform should be required for high school students.', '2025-03-20 16:16:00'),
(5, 46, 'Great! Let''s start by taking a look at your essay and identifying any opportunities to further enhance your use of cause and effect. Can you please provide me with a copy of your essay? I can then review it and give you some specific feedback.', '<sent>By focusing on the needed, the government can also reinforce the quality of support to them. the number of people needed to help matters, for the distribution of the limited budget is dependent on the number of people.</sent>', 'In the famous Korean movie "parasite", there are some people who do not worry about economic problem, but there are some people who have trouble living their lives due to their poor situation. Is it reasonable for the wealthy people to be helped by the government with the people who live in an underground floor? I think it is not desirable. The government should focus on helping only those most in need. The first reason why the government needs to help the poor only is it is a way to save a budget of the government. A leader of the country has to control its budget carefully, for it is not infinite, but has maximum limitation. If all of its citizens get economic merits by some policies, there will be some situations where the government cannot use the budget to the parts which are needed really. By focusing on the needed, the government can also reinforce the quality of support to them. the number of people needed to help matters, for the distribution of the limited budget is dependent on the number of people. The smaller the number is, the greater the quality of support becomes. The second reason is that there can be a positive effect about solving the economic inequality by helping only those most in need. The government gets its income mainly by the tax, which is from the wealthy. If it needs tax to help the poor, the wealthy need to pay more tax naturally, which makes their wealth reduced. In this way, the poor can enhance their economic level by the support made from the wealthy''s tax. In conclusion, the government should focus on helping only those most in need. The first reason is saving the budget, and the second reason is solving the problem about the economic inequality. Although there may be some problems about it, it is the best way to help the poor.', '2025-04-03 18:16:00'),
(1, 47, 'Sure, go ahead and share your essay with me. Let''s take it one step at a time and work on sentence forms.', '<essay>Advantages of Using Tablet in Class Now days, in many lasses, we use tablet or laptop. There are three reasons why students use tablet in their class. The first reason that students use tablet in their class is that using tablet can decrease bag weight, but If you don''t use tablet, you should bring many textbooks and notes in your bag. It''s really heavy and it will make you tired. However, if you use tablet, you can save all textbooks file in tablet, and you can take notes by tablet. It means that you can bring only tablet to class. It will make your bag more lighter. Second reason that students use tablet in their class is that students can use internet comfortably by tablet. In class, there must be something you can''t understand, so by using tablet, you can find out that intermediately. Third reason that students use tablet in their class is that using tablet can help student''s effecient study. Students can take notes, doing research, and reading books by tablet. Students can handle many works by tablet, and it helps students finish their work fastly. These are three reasons why students using tablet in class, and it''s advantage. Using tablet in class can help students in many ways.</essay>', 'Advantages of Using Tablet in Class These days, many students use tablets or laptops in their classes. There are several reasons why using a tablet has become a popular choice for students. Firstly, using tablets can decrease the weight of your bag. If you don''t use a tablet, you would have to bring many textbooks and notes in your bag. That can become quite heavy and can make you tired. However, if you use a tablet, you can save all textbook files on the tablet and take notes by using it. This means that you would only have to bring your tablet with you to class, which will make your bag lighter. Secondly, students can use the internet comfortably on a tablet. There may be times when you don''t understand something in class, and by using a tablet, you can figure it out immediately. Thirdly, using a tablet can help students study more efficiently. You can take notes, do research, and read books by using a tablet. You can handle many tasks with a tablet, and it helps you finish your work quickly. In summary, these are three reasons why students use tablets in class, and it''s an advantage. Using a tablet in class can help students in many ways.', '2025-02-14 12:20:00'),
(2, 47, 'Based on your previous revisions to the methodology section, the complete revised paragraph could look like this: The methodology section is a critical component of a research paper that outlines the procedures and methods used to conduct the study. In this section, it is important to provide a detailed description of the materials and methods used to ensure reproducibility and reliability of the study''s findings. The structure our group made is a tree with a black stem and green leaves standing on a yellow surface. Firstly, to create the base, a square (2x2) form was made using 4 yellow full blocks. Next, 5 black full blocks were used to form a straight pillar that went in the center of the base. Afterwards, the 3x3 table was filled with green blocks except for numbers 1 and 9. Finally, the green full cap block was put on top of block 5. The center of three structures were then stacked in order from the bottom up. The choice of blocks used in the construction of the tree structure was based on prior research indicating the importance of color and size in visual perception. Specifically, the use of green blocks with a black stem was intended to increase the visual appeal of the tree and attract attention. The yellow blocks were selected to provide contrast to the green of the leaves and make the structure more visible. By using these specific blocks, we aimed to create a visually appealing and memorable structure. Based on this revised paragraph, I would rate the following scores for each subsection of the rubric: - Overview: 2 (Provides a general introduction and overview of the materials/methods section that helps to clearly orient the reader to the section.) - Repeatability: 2 (Contains all information needed to replicate the structure, making it possible for others to reproduce it.) - Precision: 2 (Provides specific and precise details on the size, color, and placement of the blocks.) - Clarity: 2 (It is well-written and easy to understand without considerable effort on the reader''s part.) - Justification: 2 (Justifies methods and materials used and relates this to prior studies by indicating the importance of color and size in visual perception.) Therefore, the final score for the methodology section is 10 out of 10. Well done!', 'methodology section의 overview 부분이 block building activity에 대한 내용이 아닌 것 같아서 글이 좀 어색한것 같은데', 'The structure our group made is a tree with a black stem and green leaves standing on a yellow surface. Firstly, put a base block on the floor, by using 4 yellow full blocks, make a square (2X2) form. Next, use 5 black full blocks and stack them vertically to form a straight pillar. Next, fill the 3x3 table with green blocks except for numbers 1 and 9. Then put a green full cap block on top of block 5. Stack the center of three structures in order from the bottom up.', '2025-02-27 13:20:00'),
(3, 47, 'Please share your essay so we can start working on it.', 'clearify the following sentence. Also if the government give aids to every citizen government won’t be able to help sufficiently for neither to help requires the citizen nor the help non-required citizen.', 'I think the government should help only in need. It’s because people who don’t need help is OK without help. However, government help is critical for people who need help. Also if the government give aids to every citizen government won’t be able to help sufficiently for neither to help requires the citizen nor the help non-required citizen. First, I think the government should provide sufficient help for people who need help because government help is critical for their lives. For example, if a poor man with no family got an accident and need money for the surgery nobody else could borrow him money except for the government. As shown in the example since the government has a permission to help every citizen to live a healthy and pleasure life. Helping only people in need would be a key to maintain the whole citizen live better lives. Second helping for every citizen will make help for each person too small since the government has limited money and material. Perhaps nobody will be satisfied after getting such a small help. some might think it’s unfair to have only some people not everybody it is still the best choice to keep most people well as possible. These are some reasons I think the government should help some people in need. By helping only people in need the government can use limited facility efficiently and people who need help we can get much more help than helping everyone in the society.', '2025-03-13 11:50:00'),
(4, 47, 'Very good, it sounds like you learned about the importance of modeling a conclusion in scientific writing. Could you provide an example from the text you read which illustrates how the author modeled a conclusion?', 'Our results provide compelling evidence for long-term involvement with such patients and suggest that this approach appears to be effective in counteracting stress that may exacerbate the disorder.', 'Hybrid electric vehicles (HEVs) have gained popularity as a sustainable transportation option due to their ability to reduce fuel consumption and greenhouse gas emissions compared to conventional ve- hicles. HEVs utilize multiple power sources, typically an internal combustion engine and an electric motor, to provide propulsion. However, to achieve optimal performance and eﬀiciency, HEVs require advanced control strategies, including optimal velocity planning and energy management. Optimal ve- locity planning involves determining the most eﬀicient speed trajectory for a vehicle based on various factors such as road conditions, traﬀic, and vehicle characteristics.', '2025-03-20 16:20:00'),
(5, 47, 'Great job! I can see that you''ve effectively used modal verbs in the paragraph you''ve shared with me. You used "indicated" in the first sentence to show the possibility that the data suggests. Similarly, you used "demonstrated" to imply that the anatomical tracing experiments showed a certain connection. Additionally, you used "can be seen" to show possibility and "were found" to imply discovery. Lastly, you used "may have been" to indicate a possibility, which is apt as you are uncertain of the exact volume of injection in that case. Overall, you have effectively used modal verbs as appropriate in your writing.', 'I learnt that in results section of the article we need to have sentence calling the reader to check the figure such as ''In Figure 1, ...''. Can you tell me if I called the readers to check my figures effectively?', 'RESULTS Data obtained in a previous study by Song et al. indicated that Posterior Parietal Cortex (PPC) is involved in multisensory integration of audiovisual stimuli in mice performing a head-fixed discrimination task, modulating auditory dominance (1). Furthermore, anatomical tracing experiments in mice demonstrated that auditory cortex (AC) and visual cortex (VC) are connected not only to PPC, but also anterior cingulate cortex (ACC) (2). We performed dual retrograde tracing to examine this anatomical connectivity, and chemical deactivation of ACC and PPC in head-fixed trained mice performing an audiovisual Go/No-Go discrimination task (see Methods). Dual-retrograde tracing (Figure 1a) has shown that VC projects onto both association areas. As can be seen on Figure 1b, these projections were found to be from segregated neuron populations. Red and green signals were clearly observed in segregated groups in the primary visual cortex (V1), no convergent yellow signal being observed. ACC also received projections from secondary visual areas (V2L, V2M). It is evident that the projections from VC to PPC and ACC are not of the same origin. Furthermore, robust AC projections to ACC were not observed. The signal in AC was mainly red and concentrated in the auditory dorsal (AuD) area, showing projections from AC to PPC. The volume of retrograde virus injection in ACC may have been a bit more in volume than optimal; however, as the injection center appears to be in the correct target (cingulate cortex area 1; Cg1), this should not have created a significant deviation on the results (Figure 1c). The injection in PPC seemed to be confined within the borders of the area according to Paxinos Atlas (3) (Figure 1d). Chemical deactivation of ACC, and training and testing stimuli were shown on Figure 2a, b. Muscimol injection on ACC has not shown any significant change in the correct rates in the audiovisual Go/No-Go test compared to the control injection of PBS (Figure 2c, d). However, the results can be less than ideal, as the correct rates for both modalities are below the trained 80% in both animals. Although the task training period was finished at a correct rate of over 80% for both auditory and visual stimuli, the results are suboptimal for both in the testing condition. For example, as can be seen on Figure 2d, Mouse F#2 has shown 51.6 and 58.6% visual correct rates for muscimol and PBS injections respectively, which is drastically low compared to the trained 80% threshold. Furthermore, the muscimol injection trials seem to have lower visual correct rates for both mice, which was not expected. These may have been caused by the unpredicted stress the injection surgery put on the animals on the day of testing. Overall, ACC seems to be anatomically connected to VC, through a segregated population of neurons when compared to PPC. ACC does not seem to modulate decision making in audiovisual conflict resolution task, at least in our specific head-fixed task paradigm. However, the testing conditions were not optimal, which makes it difficult to draw strong conclusions from the current data. REFERENCES 1. Song Y-H, Kim J-H, Jeong H-W, Choi I, Jeong D, Kim K, et al. A neural circuit for auditory dominance over visual perception. Neuron. 2017;93(5):1236–7. 2. Zingg B, Hintiryan H, Gou L, Song MY, Bay M, Bienkowski MS, et al. Neural networks of the mouse neocortex. Cell. 2014;156(5):1096–111. 3. Paxinos G, J. FKB. The Mouse Brain in stereotaxic coordinates. Academic Press; 2019.', '2025-04-03 18:20:00'),
(1, 48, 'Great, let''s start by taking a look at your essay and making sure that you have properly used commas when listing items. Let''s focus on the body paragraph where you present your arguments. Please re-read the paragraph and identify the places where you have used a list of items.', 'Can I show u my essay and would u check if I used comma rules correctly?', 'A lot of schools, even some middle schools, let students use their private tablets and laptop computers and sometimes teachers even provide them. However, this has been controversial because people were not sure whether it is effective for education or not. The reason why governments still allow them to use such electric devices even though there are some controversies is because it has some advantages that can not be taken only with general books or notebooks. First, it is easier to write and erase letters. Erasers should be used to remove words that are written as a mistake. The size of the letters can be changed easily while it is difficult with paper notebooks. Furthermore, digital notebooks have more color options so users can use various color pens. Second, they are useful to search for necessary information. It is hard to find some concepts on books during class. However it will be much faster to look for them with online services. Therefore, the extra time after the particular class to understand what the teachers taught would not be required since the students can discover more documents that can help them learn specific concepts. Third, each of the students of a certain class can be connected. Accordingly, they can share the useful informations and have some debates about what they learned during the day. There could be a possibility for highschool students to experience the teamworks or the cooperation projects that is usually shown in colleges earlier.', '2025-02-14 12:24:00'),
(2, 48, 'Yes, I can definitely help you with that. Here''s a revised version of the paragraph that follows the guideline of providing key findings in the first paragraph: <para>"Our study on fertilization among sea urchins revealed that it is intraspecies specific and involves surface components of both gametes. We found that the fertilization success varied among different individuals of the species S. purpuratus, with approximately one third of the examined individuals showing significant differences in fertilization. Interestingly, we observed that crosses for gametes of an individual that yield significantly reduced fertilization in one cross reached normal levels with other individuals of the opposite sex, suggesting that a low fertilization success is not due to immature or defective gametes. Our findings suggest that the molecules that mediate sperm-egg interactions may play an important role in speciation, and that mutations in these elements may result in reproductive isolation and speciation."</para>', '<para>Also, for second guideline to avoid these common problems is that you have to describe the importance and significance of the study clearly. Can you revise "Our findings indicate that fertilization among sea urchins is intraspecies specific and that surface components of both gametes are involved in the fertilization specificity. Results of intraspecies specific fertilization between different gametes of several different individuals of the species S. purpuratus displayed varying degrees of fertilization success. Approximately one third of the examined individuals show significant differences in fertilization. The percent of individual crosses of gametes yielding significantly reduced fertilization specificity corresponds to the previously reported amount of “defective” gametes encountered during fertilization (5) and egg agglutination experiments (9) However, in our study, crosses for gametes of an individual that yield significantly reduced fertilization in one cross reached normal levels with other individual of the opposite sex, suggesting that a low fertilization success is not due to immature or defective gametes. It seems intuitive that the molecules that mediate sperm-egg interactions may play an important role in speciation since individuals are in separate gene pools if the sperm and egg cannot interact to form a zygote. How these systems evolve so that once common ancestors become reproductively isolate is not so obvious. Geographic isolation is believed to be the principal mechanism of speciation of marine animals (6). However, speciation does not have to be accompanied by major genomic reorganization (5, 7). A few mutations in bindin and its receptor can be sufficient to accomplish reproductive isolation because these proteins are major components of the fertilization mechanism. The hypothesis that bindins and their receptors contain multiple adhesive elements would allow mutations to occur within an individual element of bindin without catastrophic consequences for mutant individuals in the absence of a simultaneous compensating mutation in the receptor. In summary, fertilization among sea urchins appears intraspecies specific due to surface components of both gametes. It is conceivable that these surface components contain multiple adhesive elements. Based on our hypothesis, mutations in these elements may result in reproductive isolation and speciation."</para> in terms of the second guideline?', 'Our findings indicate that fertilization among sea urchins is intraspecies specific and that surface components of both gametes are involved in the fertilization specificity. Results of intraspecies specific fertilization between different gametes of several different individuals of the species S. purpuratus displayed varying degrees of fertilization success. Approximately one third of the examined individuals show significant differences in fertilization. The percent of individual crosses of gametes yielding significantly reduced fertilization specificity corresponds to the previously reported amount of “defective” gametes encountered during fertilization (5) and egg agglutination experiments (9) However, in our study, crosses for gametes of an individual that yield significantly reduced fertilization in one cross reached normal levels with other individual of the opposite sex, suggesting that a low fertilization success is not due to immature or defective gametes. It seems intuitive that the molecules that mediate sperm-egg interactions may play an important role in speciation since individuals are in separate gene pools if the sperm and egg cannot interact to form a zygote. How these systems evolve so that once common ancestors become reproductively isolate is not so obvious. Geographic isolation is believed to be the principal mechanism of speciation of marine animals (6). However, speciation does not have to be accompanied by major genomic reorganization (5, 7). A few mutations in bindin and its receptor can be sufficient to accomplish reproductive isolation because these proteins are major components of the fertilization mechanism. The hypothesis that bindins and their receptors contain multiple adhesive elements would allow mutations to occur within an individual element of bindin without catastrophic consequences for mutant individuals in the absence of a simultaneous compensating mutation in the receptor. In summary, fertilization among sea urchins appears intraspecies specific due to surface components of both gametes. It is conceivable that these surface components contain multiple adhesive elements. Based on our hypothesis, mutations in these elements may result in reproductive isolation and speciation.', '2025-02-27 13:24:00'),
(3, 48, 'Error', 'For these reasons, I want to emphasize using a tablet or laptop computer in class is good way for students. Do you think this sentence is appropriate for the conclusion part of my essay?', 'In today''s digital age, tablets and laptops have become ubiquitous tools for students, and most of students in KAIST also use them to listen lectures and taking notes for important information. While concerns have been raised about the potential negative effects of these devices on student concentration and eye health, it is important to recognize the many benefits that they offer for academic success. This essay will explore three key advantages of using tablets and laptops in the classroom: time savings, increased learning efficiency, and improved space efficiency. First of all, tablets and laptops permit students to save time. The functions of searching and recording could allow students to save their time. Specifically, searching function in the electronic devices allow us to fine the information, which we are not aware of or which are confused, quickly, Students just type the word that they want to know, and just for a moment, lots of useful information come out. When it comes to recording function, students could record the lecture. After that, they can play it 1.5 or twice time faster. So they can save their time using an efficient way. Another key advantage of using tablets and laptops in the classroom is that they can make studying more efficient by allowing students to review lecture content at their own pace. For example, recording functions can help students pick up on information they may have missed during class or that did not make sense to them at the time. By listening to recordings multiple times and studying challenging material more closely, students are better able to grasp course concepts and improve their grades. Finally, the use of tablets and laptops in the classroom can have a positive effect on space efficiency. With the advent of video conferencing technologies like Zoom, electronic devices can allow students to participate in classes and collaborate with their peers from anywhere. For example, if a class is oversubscribed and too many students are present physically, electronic devices can be used to provide remote access and allow everyone to participate equally. Additionally, eBooks and online course materials can greatly reduce the physical space requirements for traditional textbooks and other teaching materials, resulting in more effective use of classroom resources. In conclusion, while there are concerns about the potential negative effects of using tablets and laptops in the classroom, the benefits they offer for academic success cannot be ignored. By allowing students to save time, increase learning efficiency, and improve space efficiency, these devices have become essential tools for modern-day learning. Therefore, I strongly recommend the use of tablets and laptops in the classroom as a way to enhance the learning experience and improve academic performance.', '2025-03-13 11:54:00'),
(4, 48, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about the below sentences. Review Writing Tips for Methods - Most of this section will be written in the past tense. → If you are describing something that you did, use the past tense. → If you need to describe currently accepted practices, use the present tense. - Write any procedure in chronological order. → Try to give the old information first and the new information second. - The passive voice is usually used to avoid I / We; However, active voice is not forbidden. Try to make passive structures using short passive forms. (short and concise!) ※ Trend for using voice - Many fields (especially Engineering) : tend to abstain from using the first person pronounced like I or We. - Natural science (especially Biology or Chemistry journal) : active voice becomes quite a lot more popular and common - High impact journal (Nature, Science…) : a lot of instances for I or We → Recommendation : Look at the journal and question, and see what is common in terms of language usage, (active or passive) then decide for yourself which one you think would be appropriate for the journal you will submit to. = Case by Case!', 'Construction of Training Dataset The specimens are divided into data collection specimens, which are used for training, and validation specimens, which are not used for training. To obtain accurate normal and defect data from both specimens, Micro-CT was used. CT images were obtained using the X-ray Microscope ZEISS Xradia 520 Versa model (Sample resolution: 50 μm) at KAIST Analysis Center for Research Advancement (KARA). The collected CT images were processed using Dragonfly software from Object Research Study (ORS). The Minimum Intensity Projection (MIP) technique was used to obtain a depth-wise single projection image from the surface, and global thresholding and binarization were performed using the Otsu method. This allowed us to obtain a single image with defective pixels corresponding to areas where Onyx and Carbon fiber had debonded or delaminated during the printing process and normal pixels corresponding to well-printed areas. These images were matched one-to-one with Ultrasonic Wave Propagation Imaging (UWPI) laser ultrasonic testing results to obtain robust normal and defect data. The data generated from 3D printing is imbalanced, and therefore, data augmentation is necessary to prevent the overfitting of the training dataset. The Synthetic Minority Over-Sampling Technique (SMOTE) was used for data augmentation. SMOTE is an oversampling technique commonly used in machine learning, which involves extracting one data point from the minority class data, computing the differences between it and the k-nearest neighbors, multiplying these differences by random numbers between 0 and 1, and subsequently adding these values to the original data. This operation generates new data points that resemble the original ones, thereby increasing the number of samples in the dataset. This technique has the advantage of preventing overfitting better than simple oversampling. After data augmentation, the entire dataset was divided into five sets to perform 5-fold cross-validation, with four sets used for training and one set for validation to evaluate the accuracy of the CNN.', '2025-03-20 16:24:00'),
(5, 48, 'Yes, "long-ranged interaction" is not correct because it violates the rules of hyphenation for compound modifiers. The correct form should be "long-range interaction" that is hyphenated since "long-range" acts as a single descriptive unit that modifies "interaction" as a compound modifier. The problem with "long-ranged" is that it contains an adjective, "long," and a verb, "ranged." This creates confusion and makes it difficult for readers to understand the intended meaning. So, we should use the correct form of "long-range interaction" to convey clear meaning.', 'Thanks I understand. I want to ask another question. I want to explain an experimental protocol like this: amicon concentration was conducted at 8000xg 20 min twice. Is the grammer of this expression correct?', 'Conventional cationic liposome was prepared by microfluidic device mixing ethanol phase and aqueous phase rather than the film hydration method. At ethanol phase, DOPC, cholesterol, DOTAP and TPGS were used with 4: 2: 3: 1 ratio. 123mM ammonium sulfate solution in distilled water was used at aqueous phase. Total flow rate (TFR) and Flow rate ratio (FFR) are 10 and 3:1, respectively. After the liposome nanoparticles were synthesized, desalting step was followed. Then, 5% w/w DOX-HCl was inserted and stirred at 250 rpm for an hour at 60℃. The amicon concentration was conducted twice, each for 20 minutes, at 8000xg to purify liposome from left doxorubicin. Finally, liposomes were coated with one-fifth concentration CSA or TCSA solution dissolved in DW for 3 hours at room temperature with 180 rpm. The whole procedures after inserting doxorubicin were conducted under blocking lights conditions. Because doxorubicin has intrinsic fluorescence at 595nm, light can weaken its property.', '2025-04-03 18:24:00'),
(1, 49, 'I''m happy to help! Go ahead and share your paragraph with me, and I''ll take a look.', 'Meanwhile, those who replied they are not satisfied with the cafeteria at KAIST came up with a number of reasons. The largest portion that accounted for the students’ dissatisfaction was the limitation in choosing the menu, with 62.5% of students responding. What is intriguing is that from those who are unsatisfied with the cafeteria because of the limited menu, 80% were staying at KAIST for more than four years. This suggests that having similar meals for a long period of time may result in an adverse effect on the level of satisfaction of the cafeteria. Another major reason for students’ dissatisfaction towards the cafeteria at KAIST was because of the taste. Here, all of the respondents were staying in KAIST for 1~2 years, implying that students evaluate the taste of food in cafeterias relatively quickly.', 'Meanwhile, those who replied they are not satisfied with the cafeteria at KAIST came up with a number of reasons. The largest portion that accounted for the students’ dissatisfaction was the limitation in choosing the menu, with 62.5% of students responding. What is intriguing is that from those who are unsatisfied with the cafeteria because of the limited menu, 80% were staying at KAIST for more than four years. This suggests that having similar meals for a long period of time may result in an adverse effect on the level of satisfaction of the cafeteria. Another major reason for students’ dissatisfaction towards the cafeteria at KAIST was because of the taste. Here, all of the respondents were staying in KAIST for 1~2 years, implying that students evaluate the taste of food in cafeterias relatively quickly.', '2025-02-14 12:28:00'),
(2, 49, 'I''m sorry, but I cannot determine that yet as you haven''t shared the essay with me. Can you please provide me with the essay so we can start the revision process?', '<essay>In these days, there are a lot of things that attracts people, and most of people can choose one of them to study or work for. However, in Korea, almost all of universities make hard for student to change their major. Even, students try to re-enter other universities to change their major. So I think that universities should require that the first year of college be major-free. As I said before, there are many interesting things in these days. Although students have already chosen their major to study, ohter major can attract them so they can want to study other things. Someone can say that they can change their major, but if that two majors are completely different, students have to study much more new subjects so their graduation will be delayed. Even in KAIST, which is well known for easy major changing, they are afraid of changing major because their graduation could be delayed a lot. To prevent these problems, universities should make students select their major at least in second year of college. In KAIST, students are major-free in first year. they can study subjects of the major that they are interested in, though they''re not in that major. They can test their interest about major, and they can consider whether they will be in the major or not. In this system, students will make less mistake to select their major and it will be decreased that students change their major. For these reasons, I believe universities shoud make their first year student be major-free.</essay> Is there any grammatical errors in my essay?', 'These days, there are many things that attracts people, and most people can choose one of them to study or work for. However, in Korea, almost all of universities make it hard for students to change their major. Furthermore, students try to enroll in other universities to change their major. I think that universities should make the first year of college major-free. As I said before, there are many interesting things in these days. Although students have already chosen their major, they may still bew interested in other fields and want to explore other subjects. Someone may argue that they can change their major, but if that two majors are completely different, students have to study much more new subjects so their graduation will be delayed. Even in KAIST, which is well known for easy major changing, they are afraid of changing major because their graduation could be delayed a lot. To prevent these problems, universities should make students select their major at least in second year of college. In KAIST, students are major-free in first year. they can study subjects of the major that they are interested in, though they''re not in that major. They can test their interest about major, and they can consider whether they will be in the major or not. In this system, students will make less mistake to select their major and it will be decreased that students change their major. For these reasons, I believe universities shoud make their first year student be major-free.', '2025-02-27 13:28:00'),
(3, 49, '이 훅은 보통의 훅과는 다릅니다. 일반적인 훅은 독자들의 호기심과 그들의 관심을 최대한 끌어들일 수 있는 것이 필요하지만, 이 훅은 반대의 방향으로 나아가며 독자들의 관점에서 부정적인 주장을 내세우는 것입니다. 따라서 대상 독자층과 해당 토픽과 관련하여 적절한 훅을 고려해야 합니다. 만약 저희가 작성하려는 에세이가 의견을 주장하고, 비판적인 글이 아니라면 이 훅은 적절하지 않을 수 있습니다. 일반적인 훅의 경우에는 독자의 참여를 높이는 데에 좋은 효과를 발휘하므로, 더 좋은 대안이 있을 수 있습니다.', '<sent>There are some reasearch and stastics that teamwork and harmony made by people wearing same uniform.</sent> 는 문법적으로 옳은 표현이야?', 'Title: Shoud we wear a school uniform? Have you ever hesitate to wear a school uniform? School Uniforms are common recommended by many high schools in almost every region of Korea for students to wear. When entering middle school, teenagers in Korea have to wear school uniforms. Some students are uncomfortable with this rule and resist their school and teacher. To require wearing school uniforms is good for several reasons. Firstly, school uniforms are a sign of students and teenagers'' status and standing in society. If someone is wearing a school uniform and gets into trouble, many people will offer help. Research and statistics show that people are more likely to help someone who is wearing a school uniform in dangerous or emergency situations. Therefore, school uniforms protect many students. Another reason that school uniforms are useful is for students during off-campus activities, such as shopping or using public transportation. Students who wear school uniforms are often given special discounts or gifts at events. Additionally, they can take part in cultural events, such as movies, concerts, and book readings, without the need for additional identification. Lastely, School uniforms bring uniformity among students and create a sense of harmony. It prevents anyone from feeling discriminated or different. There are some reasearch and stastics that teamwork and harmony made by people wearing same uniform. School uniforms are useful and helpful in many ways. We need to consider one more aspect: whether removing school uniform rules would foster greater connections throughout our communities.', '2025-03-13 11:58:00'),
(4, 49, 'Based on the introduction, methodology, and results of your research, it seems that you have conducted a comprehensive review of recent developments in open-domain question answering (QA). You have identified three prominent approaches to open-domain QA, including retrieve then read (DPR), retrieve then generate (FiD), and generate then read (GenRead) pipelines. You have also highlighted the key differences between these approaches, including their reliance on retrieval versus generation, their use of pre-trained models, and their focus on efficiency versus accuracy. In the methodology section, you have described the systematic process employed to identify and select relevant research articles for the review. Finally, in the results section, you have presented the key findings and results obtained from a comprehensive review of three influential papers in the field of open domain question answering. You have critically analyzed the methodologies and experimental results of each paper, providing valuable insights into the current state-of-the-art methods in this rapidly evolving field. Based on your research, you have identified that there is no single best model for open-domain QA, and further research is necessary to refine and improve each of these models before a final, optimal solution can be determined.', 'can you help write a draft for a discussions and conclusion section based on this?', 'Open-domain Question Answering (QA) [1] is the task of answering questions posed by users without relying on a specific database or knowledge graph. Instead, open-domain QA systems must be able to process and analyze a wide range of text sources to provide accurate and relevant answers to queries. Open domain QA has the potential to enhance information access and utilization by allowing users to input queries in natural language, and obtaining accurate and pertinent answers. Open-domain QA systems can improve the capacity to locate, process and apply knowledge on various domains. However, despite the significant progress in recent years, open-domain QA remains a challenging problem due to several factors, including the vast amount of information available online, the diversity of sources like Wikipedia and web crawl, and the need to understand and interpret natural language. To tackle this challenge, researchers have explored various approaches to open-domain QA, ranging from traditional retrieval-based methods to more recent generative models. In recent years, there has been substantial progress in the field with 3 prominent approaches to open domain QA. The retrieve then read (DPR) [2], retrieve then generate (FiD) [3] and the generate then read (GenRead) [4] pipelines where each of these has its own benefits and drawbacks. DPR [2] relies on a retrieval-based method where the system first retrieves relevant documents based on the question and then extracts the answer from the retrieved documents. This approach can tackle the challenge of diversity of sources by leveraging multiple sources of information to find relevant documents. However, it may struggle with understanding complex questions or generating more nuanced answers. FiD [3] also relies on a retrieval-based method to retrieve relevant documents but then it generates an answer based on these retrieved documents using a generative model. This approach can handle the challenge of generating more accurate and nuanced answers, but it may require a large amount of training data and be computationally expensive. GenRead [4] on the other hand is based on a generative model that directly generates context which is then used to find the answer without relying on retrieval. While this approach has the potential to generate more intuitive and informative answers, the accuracy of the answers is highly dependent on the ability of the model to generate appropriate context. Additionally, generative models may be slower than the retrieval models, as they require additional time for context generation. Key differences between these approaches include their reliance on retrieval versus generation, their use of pre-trained models, and their focus on efficiency versus accuracy. While generative models may provide more accurate answers, they can be computationally expensive and require a large amount of training data. Retrieval-based approaches, on the other hand, may be more efficient, but may struggle with understanding complex questions or generating more nuanced answers., Given the complexity and diversity of approaches to open-domain QA, there is a need for a comprehensive survey paper that can provide a comparative analysis of recent developments, and identify promising directions for future research. Our survey paper aims to fill this gap by systematically reviewing and comparing the three papers mentioned earlier, highlighting their strengths and weaknesses, and providing insights into their potential for improving open-domain QA. By doing so, we hope to provide a roadmap for future research in this exciting and rapidly evolving field. In addition, our survey paper may help to identify new research questions and challenges that have not yet been addressed, and may inspire new approaches and techniques for tackling the open-domain QA problem. Our goal is to provide a comprehensive overview of the most recent developments, and to highlight the key trends and challenges in the field. The methodology section of this review paper on the recent studies in open domain Question Answering (QA) outlines the systematic process employed to identify and select relevant research articles for the review. Open domain QA is an essential task in natural language processing (NLP) that involves answering questions based on a given context without any specific domain knowledge. The area of open domain QA is constantly evolving, with new approaches and techniques being proposed and evaluated regularly. Therefore, it is essential to conduct a rigorous and comprehensive review to identify the most effective and promising approaches, and highlight areas of research that require further investigation. In this section, we describe the search strategy, inclusion and exclusion criteria, and data extraction process used to select and analyze relevant research articles. The methodology employed for this review paper was highly selective, and aimed to focus on three main publications that cover different pipelines for open domain QA. A comprehensive literature search was initially conducted on major scientific databases, such as Google Scholar, ACM Digital Library, IEEE Xplore, and ScienceDirect, to identify relevant research articles published from 2018 to 2023. The search terms used were "open domain question answering", "open-domain QA", "information retrieval", "natural language processing", and "generative retrieval". The search was conducted in March 2023, and yielded a total of 568 articles. Inclusion and exclusion criteria: The inclusion criteria were as follows: (1) studies that proposed innovative approaches for open domain QA; (2) studies that showed promising improvements in the existing benchmarks of Trivia-QA [6], Natural Questions [5], Web-Q [7], and SQuAD datasets [1]; (3) studies published in English; (4) studies published in peer-reviewed journals or conferences. The exclusion criteria were as follows: (1) studies that focused on domain-specific QA; (2) studies that did not provide sufficient details on the proposed approach; (3) studies that were not published in English; (4) studies that were not peer-reviewed. To finalize the selection of articles for this review, a rigorous screening process was employed. After screening the titles and abstracts of the identified articles, relevant studies were selected based on the inclusion and exclusion criteria. The full texts of the selected articles were then reviewed, and relevant data was extracted, including the year of publication, datasets used, evaluation metrics, proposed approach, and results. The selection process was highly selective, and only three publications were included in the review paper based on their relevance, originality, and contribution to the field of open domain QA. The extracted data was analyzed to identify trends and patterns in recent approaches for open domain QA. The proposed approaches were categorized based on their underlying pipelines, including retrieve-read [4], retrieve-generate [3], and generate-read [2]. The evaluation metrics used in the studies were also analyzed to identify the most commonly used metrics, and highlight the challenges in evaluating open domain QA systems. Finally, the quality of the selected articles was assessed based on the following criteria: relevance, validity, reliability, and usability. The final three publications selected for this review paper were deemed to be of high quality, demonstrate originality, and provide a significant contribution to the field of open domain QA. In this section, we present the key findings and results obtained from a comprehensive review of three influential papers in the field of open domain question answering. The papers under examination are, “Dense Passage Retrieval”,” Fusion in Decoder,” and” Generate Rather than Retrieve!” These papers explore different approaches and techniques aimed at improving the effectiveness and efficiency of open domain question answering systems. By critically analysing the methodologies and experimental results of each paper, this review aims to provide valuable insights into the current state-of-the-art methods in this rapidly evolving field. Table 1 provides an overview of the performance of all three models on NQ (Kwiatkowski et.al, 2019, TriviaQA A (Joshi et al., 2017), and WebQ (Berant et al., 2013) datasets, showcasing their comparative strengths and weaknesses. “Dense Passage Retrieval” introduces a novel approach to open domain question answering by leveraging dense representations of passages instead of traditional sparse retrievals (Robertson and Zaragoza, 2009). The key findings of this study demonstrate that dense passage retrieval methods significantly outperform sparse retrievals in terms of retrieval accuracy and efficiency. By employing pre-trained language models and utilizing dense vector representations, the authors showcase the potential of this approach for improving information retrieval and subsequent question answering performance. “Fusion in Decoder” investigates the integration of fusion techniques within the decoding phase of open domain question answering models. The primary objective of this research is to enhance the integration of multi-modal information (Karpukhin et al., 2020; Robertson and Zaragoza, 2009) during the generation of answers. The key findings reveal that incorporating fusion mechanisms, such as attention-based fusion and cross-modal gating, leads to improved answer quality, better alignment between questions and answers, and enhanced overall performance of the system. This work highlights the significance of fusion techniques in capturing diverse sources of information and effectively leveraging them during the decoding process. “Generate Rather than Retrieve!” explores an alternative paradigm for open domain question answering by focusing on generating answers directly instead of relying on retrieval-based approaches (Karpukhin et al., 2020; Lewis et al., 2020; Chen et al., 2017). This approach employs sequence-to-sequence models to generate relevant contexts, which are then utilized by the reader to find or generate an answer. The key findings of this study demonstrate that generating answers without explicit retrieval can yield competitive performance, especially in scenarios where retrieval-based methods face challenges, such as long-tail queries or out-of-domain questions. This work emphasizes the potential of generative models as a promising avenue for open domain question answering. While all three papers contribute to the advancement of open domain question answering, they approach the problem from different angles. “Dense Passage Retrieval” (DPR) was the first to be introduced among the three, serving as a solid baseline and providing a starting point for comparison. Although its results may lag behind” Fusion in Decoder” (FiD) and” Generate Rather than Retrieve!” (GenRead), DPR establishes a strong foundation in the field. FiD, while showcasing impressive results, is computationally expensive, which limits its practical use in certain scenarios. On the other hand, GenRead demonstrates results that appear superior to the other two approaches. However, being a generative model, it can suffer from the challenge of extreme hallucination, where it confidently generates answers that may not be accurate or relevant. It becomes evident that there is no single best model, as each approach excels in certain aspects while lagging behind in others. Therefore, further research is necessary to refine and improve each of these models before a final, optimal solution can be determined.', '2025-03-20 16:28:00'),
(5, 49, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Can you re-write this paragraph to understand more easily for non-majors?', 'Gene regulation is a highly coordinated process that requires not only ordered recruitment of various transcription factors, but also the alterations in chromatin structure. Chromatin remodelers play an important role in regulating the compaction of chromatin to organize genomic DNA. These conserved enzymes can be divided in 4 families: SWI/SNF, ISWI, CHD, and INO80, depending on what characteristic domains they have. These chromatin remodelers mediate post-translational histone modification or utilize energy derived from ATP hydrolysis to alter the histone-DNA contacts within the nucleosome.', '2025-04-03 18:28:00'),
(1, 50, 'I''d be happy to do that. If you can send me your discussion and conclusion section, I''d be happy to review it and provide feedback on the sentence length.', '<essay>Discussion Overview We have proposed iStooge, a robot classroom attendance device that could help students efficiently do their school work by spending less time attending class and focusing more on extracurricular activities. The result showed that iStooge could be beneficial for both fooling instructors to get the attendance credit and get better average grades compared to the previous research. In this discussion section, we’ll elaborate more on the potential, limitations, and future improvements of iStooge. Findings We conducted an experiment to measure the relationship between this robot and actual grades. Table 1 shows the relative effectiveness of robot surrogate in varying conditions. The results of iStooge were generally better than the other two robots. Especially in math lectures, the efficiency is 100% in every robot. And in Table 2, we can see that the average grade is not too bad either. However, we can find performance differences between subjects. It shows that the performance of the English lecture is much worse than the Engineering lecture and the Math lecture. The reason for this is that the robot’s training data was significantly less for English than for Math and Engineering. Another reason may be that English lecture requires students more subjective and creative answers rather than a uniform correct answer, so it requires more advanced natural language processing techniques than Math and Engineering. Limitation Our work has several limitations which could be addressed in future works. First, iStooge has a limited set of error recovery methods. Currently, iStooge plays a pre-recorded apology to the instructor when it gives an incorrect answer. However, this approach may not seem natural to them as students do not typically apologize for incorrect answers during these classes. Therefore, this approach might be less effective. Instead of an apology, iStooge could use an embarrassing facial expression or an awkward laugh as an alternative method to recover from errors. Another critical limitation is that no matter how much the effectiveness of the robots improves, it doesn''t give students better grades than when they attend the class without robots. Therefore in future research, a novel robot function that allows students to get better grades than they attend the class themselves should be proposed. For example, since robots are good at memorizing things in the short-term better than humans, we can use this ability to help students score better on quizzes and other assessments. Conclusion Attending class to get good grades is a significant problem for busy students. And the effect of low attendance on student grades has a negative aspect on the social life and work obligations of the student. So we proposed iStooge, a robot classroom attendance device that helps students efficiently do their school work by spending less time attending class and focusing more on extracurricular activities. It can attend class and answer the instructor’s questions, finally, it can fake student’s attendance. Then we conducted lab study using iStooge. The results showed that we are able to fool the instructor with fairly high performance and get a good grade, providing that it is possible to get a good grade without sufficient attendance. </essay> Here you go', 'Discussion Overview We have proposed iStooge, a robot classroom attendance device that could help students efficiently do their school work by spending less time attending class and focusing more on extracurricular activities. The result showed that iStooge could be beneficial for both fooling instructors to get the attendance credit and get better average grades compared to the previous research. In this discussion section, we’ll elaborate more on the potential, limitations, and future improvements of iStooge. Findings We conducted an experiment to measure the relationship between this robot and actual grades. Table 1 shows the relative effectiveness of robot surrogate in varying conditions. The results of iStooge were generally better than the other two robots. Especially in math lectures, the efficiency is 100% in every robot. And in Table 2, we can see that the average grade is not too bad either. However, we can find performance differences between subjects. It shows that the performance of the English lecture is much worse than the Engineering lecture and the Math lecture. The reason for this is that the robot’s training data was significantly less for English than for Math and Engineering. Another reason may be that English lecture requires students more subjective and creative answers rather than a uniform correct answer, so it requires more advanced natural language processing techniques than Math and Engineering. Limitation Our work has several limitations which could be addressed in future works. First, iStooge has a limited set of error recovery methods. Currently, iStooge plays a pre-recorded apology to the instructor when it gives an incorrect answer. However, this approach may not seem natural to them as students do not typically apologize for incorrect answers during these classes. Therefore, this approach might be less effective. Instead of an apology, iStooge could use an embarrassing facial expression or an awkward laugh as an alternative method to recover from errors. Another critical limitation is that no matter how much the effectiveness of the robots improves, it doesn''t give students better grades than when they attend the class without robots. Therefore in future research, a novel robot function that allows students to get better grades than they attend the class themselves should be proposed. For example, since robots are good at memorizing things in the short-term better than humans, we can use this ability to help students score better on quizzes and other assessments. Conclusion Attending class to get good grades is a significant problem for busy students. And the effect of low attendance on student grades has a negative aspect on the social life and work obligations of the student. So we proposed iStooge, a robot classroom attendance device that helps students efficiently do their school work by spending less time attending class and focusing more on extracurricular activities. It can attend class and answer the instructor’s questions, finally, it can fake student’s attendance. Then we conducted lab study using iStooge. The results showed that we are able to fool the instructor with fairly high performance and get a good grade, providing that it is possible to get a good grade without sufficient attendance.', '2025-02-14 12:32:00'),
(2, 50, 'That''s a good point. Justifying your methods is an important part of the methodology section. If you''re not sure whether you provided the right justifications or not, I suggest you go back through your work and review each justification carefully. Make sure that the reasons you gave for choosing a particular method are clear and logical. It''s also helpful to have someone else review your work and provide feedback. That way, you can get a fresh perspective and make any necessary revisions. If you''d like, I can take a look at your paragraph and provide some feedback to help you improve it.', 'THIS IS MY PARAGRAPH? CAN YOU TAKE A LOOK AT IT AND GIVE ME FEEDBACK, PLEASE? <para>Methodology Overview The study is testing the company’s ESG commitment and the attributes of the CEO while controlling some variables that could affect this relationship, mainly the supervising board and CEO’s respective responsibilities regarding ESG matters of the firm. Sample The sample used for this study is collected from the Carbon Disclosure Project database of 2020 (CDP 2020). CDP collected data about the CEO’s responsibilities, board positions, and carbon emissions from over 4000 companies from several countries. The details about the CEO education attributes not included in the CDP database are collected from public sources, including companies'' annual reports or LinkedIn profiles. Survey Structure The companies were asked to fill out a form with questions about their carbon emissions, governance structure, and the CEO’s responsibility. For the governance structure, companies were asked to provide details about the department supervising the ESG-related matters, whether it is a specific board or an executive member. This data helps us control the influence of other executive members on CEO decisions. As for the CEO’s responsibility, the questionnaire included inquiries about the CEO’s role in ESG-related matters and whether they are directly or indirectly reported to him. Regarding carbon emissions, the companies were asked to report their yearly emissions number and indicate their level of engagement in reducing them. This data helps measure the dependent variable of our model. The CDP database did not include details about the CEO education attributes our study focuses on. Therefore, we had to collect them individually through publicly available sources. We quantified whether the CEO studied abroad and the presence or absence of ESG awareness in their educational background. This helps us measure the independent variable of our study.</para>', 'Methodology Overview The study is testing the company’s ESG commitment and the attributes of the CEO while controlling some variables that could affect this relationship, mainly the supervising board and CEO’s respective responsibilities regarding ESG matters of the firm. Sample The sample used for this study is collected from the Carbon Disclosure Project database of 2020 (CDP 2020). CDP collected data about the CEO’s responsibilities, board positions, and carbon emissions from over 4000 companies from several countries. The details about the CEO education attributes not included in the CDP database are collected from public sources, including companies'' annual reports or LinkedIn profiles. Survey Structure The companies were asked to fill out a form with questions about their carbon emissions, governance structure, and the CEO’s responsibility. For the governance structure, companies were asked to provide details about the department supervising the ESG-related matters, whether it is a specific board or an executive member. This data helps us control the influence of other executive members on CEO decisions. As for the CEO’s responsibility, the questionnaire included inquiries about the CEO’s role in ESG-related matters and whether they are directly or indirectly reported to him. Regarding carbon emissions, the companies were asked to report their yearly emissions number and indicate their level of engagement in reducing them. This data helps measure the dependent variable of our model. The CDP database did not include details about the CEO education attributes our study focuses on. Therefore, we had to collect them individually through publicly available sources. We quantified whether the CEO studied abroad and the presence or absence of ESG awareness in their educational background. This helps us measure the independent variable of our study.', '2025-02-27 13:32:00'),
(3, 50, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'In the last month, I learned about the comma rules. When there is a list that contains two or more elements, we should use commas to separate them.', 'In the KAIST, freshmen can take any class without limits. It is able because they are major-free at the first year of KAIST. But I think this is not helpful to students. This major-free system makes students to lose focusing of their likes, and students will be stressed by studying other subjects, and they can''t use time efficiently. Firstly, major-free year of first disturbs students from studying their favorite subjects. Most of students go to the college to study about deep knowledge or useful skill and creativity. They can learn these things before changing their focusing and mind. If the college change the first year to be major-free, then the students should take classes of all major subjects. They should study hard to earn a good grade. This can give disturbing to students who don''t like other subjects or are not good at other subjects than their favorite subjects. Also, because of studying subjects that students actually don''t have curiocity, they can feel stressful. Students are already exhausted by learning their major. More neccessary classes for graduation of college only gives more painful labor to students. They already study other subjects at the high school, though it was little, so they don''t want to study more about them. Lastly, the time is limited, but using one year for studying minor subjects is not efficient to students and universities. If all of universities have a lot of support and money from government and people, first year of being major-free can be good choice. But, this system makes students to graduate later and spends money to use more professors and more classrooms. I this is not efficient at all. So, I think major-free system at first year is not efficient. I think instead of using this system, universities should more lighten their limits and graduation level.', '2025-03-13 12:02:00'),
(4, 50, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned how to write a collaborative essay covering causes and effects. The essay must not use imperative mood, such as "I" and "you". Also, I need not to use ''cliche'' for the interest of readers.', 'In the famous Korean movie "parasite", there are some people who do not worry about economic problem, but there are some people who have trouble living their lives due to their poor situation. Is it reasonable for the wealthy people to be helped by the government with the people who live in an underground floor? I think it is not desirable. The government should focus on helping only those most in need. The first reason why the government needs to help the poor only is it is a way to save a budget of the government. The budget of a country is limited to some extent depending on its economic level. In addition to that, the contemporary society has to try to save its budget for the future generation, which will have lots of difficulty on their lives. As a result, a leader of the country has to control its budget carefully. If all of its citizens get economic merits by some policies, there will be some situations where the government cannot use the budget to the parts which are needed really. By focusing on the needed, the government can also reinforce the quality of support to them. It will help the government to save the budget for the future. Also, the quality of support will be upgraded because the distribution of the limited budget is dependent on the number of people. The cases of private insurance focusing on only small number of people guarantee that the quality of support is related to the number of people who are supported. The second reason is that there can be a positive effect about solving the economic inequality by helping only those most in need. The government gets its income mainly by the tax, which is from the wealthy. If it needs tax to help the poor, the wealthy need to pay more tax naturally, which makes their wealth reduced. In this way, the poor can enhance their economic level by the support made from the wealthy''s tax. In conclusion, the government should focus on helping only those most in need. The first reason is saving the budget, and the second reason is solving the problem about the economic inequality. Although there may be some problems about it, it is the best way to help the poor.', '2025-03-20 16:32:00'),
(5, 50, 'Certainly! The idea behind using an end-to-end approach instead of separating the problem into multiple subtasks is that it may simplify the overall problem and potentially produce more accurate results. By feeding raw audio data through a neural network that generates a complete sequence of time-action pairs, the model may be able to generate beatmaps that are more closely aligned with the musical characteristics of the song without having to split the task into separate stages. This can save time and computational resources, and may also improve the overall quality of the generated beatmaps.', 'Who said that transformers have been successful in a variety of tasks, including sequence-to-sequence tasks, and that encoder-decoder transformer implementations can handle longer sequences of data than LSTM-based networks?', 'The neural network, taking a 1D tensor representing the characteristics of a single audio file as input, produces a sequence of synchronized time-action pairs ready to be converted into the chosen beatmap format. This end-to-end approach was preferred over the separation of the problem into multiple subtasks, namely action placement and action selection, which is commonly used in the beatmap generation domain. Since transformers have obtained incredible results in many sequence-to-sequence tasks in terms of quality and parallelization potential, and are able to handle long sequences of data better than LSTM-based networks, a standard encoder-decoder transformer implementation was chosen as a generation model.', '2025-04-03 18:32:00'),
(1, 51, 'Great, thank you for the summary. Let''s take a look at your essay. Can you please provide me with your essay, and we can work through it together to revise your use of outside sources?', '<essay> I oppose women''s enlistment in the army. Physical conditions are not equal between a woman and a man. The physical difference between a woman and a man in their 20s is quite large. As a result, it is not easy to serve with the same level of training. In addition, the military is a closed society, and there is a possibility of crime in it. Unlike now situation, if two genders have to live in the military, there might be many problems that comes from the difference of two genders. As a result, the crime can be increased, Moreover, joining women to the military cannot resolve gender inequality. There are too many conditions that can cause other discriminatory perceptions even if a woman joins the military, such as facilities, hair length, and degree of training. Therefore, it is difficult to judge that women''s enlistment in the army provides a fundamental solution. Of course, it is a pity that men go to the military to support their youth in their young and precious days in their 20s. I think women should live with more respect for men and a heart that contributes to the country.</essay>', 'I oppose women''s enlistment in the army. Physical conditions are not equal between a woman and a man. The physical difference between a woman and a man in their 20s is quite large. As a result, it is not easy to serve with the same level of training. In addition, the military is a closed society, and there is a possibility of crime in it. The military is busy hiding not only sex crimes but also incidents and accidents. If an accident occurs, if a soldier reports it to his or her superiors, they are in a hurry to cover up for fear of problems in their personnel review. In fact, there is data from the Minisstry of National Defense that only 32.7% reported sex crimes within the military. In other words, only 3 out of 10 people report it. 44% of victims who did not report sex crimes saids, "No action was likely to be taken." In other words, soldiers do not trust the military''s measures and do not even expected them. Unlike now situation, if two genders have to live in the military, there might be many problems that comes from the difference of two genders in the closed military society. As a result, the crime can be increased. Moreover, joining women to the military cannot resolve gender inequality. There are too many conditions that can cause other discriminatory perceptions even if a woman joins the military, such as facilities, hair length, and degree of training. There will be a shortage of women''s toilets in the military now, and it will take a long time to solve problems related to facilities. Therefore, it is difficult to judge that women''s enlistment in the army provides a fundamental solution. In a short, there is a risk of increased crime within women when they are required to join a closed army. Also, the current facilities are not suitable for women to join the army, and it will take a long time to solve them. In addition, there are many other conditions to consider, such as physical differences, the degree of training, and the length of the hair. For this reason, I oppose women''s mandatory military enlistment. Of course, it is a pity that men go to the military to support their youth in their young and precious days in their 20s. I think women should live with more respect for men and a heart that contributes to the country.', '2025-02-14 12:36:00'),
(2, 51, 'Yes, that''s an important aspect of scientific writing. Can you tell me a bit more about what you learned specifically?', 'we just learned different ways of writing it. can you help me with an assignment of mine?', 'Contextual word embeddings have become a critical component in NLP due to their ability to capture important information based on the surrounding text, which makes them particularly useful for tasks such as language modeling, sentiment analysis, and named entity recognition. However, these embeddings not only capture word meaning but also encode real-world biases related to gender, age, and ethnicity. Recent work has shown pre-trained language models capture social biases from their training data and as a result, debiasing these embeddings has become a critical topic in the field. While various debiasing methods for word embeddings, such as retraining models on more diverse data, incorporating specific constraints into the training process, and using post-processing techniques to remove biases, have been proposed, there remains a lack of standardization in evaluating and comparing their effectiveness. Therefore, standardizing the evaluation and comparison of these debiasing methods is essential to ensure more equitable and inclusive language models. The main objective of this project is to investigate the current debiasing techniques for contextual word embeddings and propose a standardized approach to evaluate their performance. By evaluating the strengths and weaknesses of these methods, we aim to develop a more comprehensive understanding of how they work and identify the most effective approach for debiasing contextual word embeddings.', '2025-02-27 13:36:00'),
(3, 51, 'Great. Then the sentence is correctly punctuated. Let''s move onto the next sentence.', 'can you show me next sentence that i can identify to adjective clauses', 'There are some reasons why I am using a tablet in class. I am going to explain some advantages by using a tablet in class First, I can take the class by using a tablet. I do not need to carry many books to take the class. So It is more easy for me to take the class. Furthermore, It is more convenicence to carry a tablet than books. Second, I can take find anything directly by using a tablet. For major classes or difficult classes, there are many points that I can not understand. Using a tablet, I can find the answer of my question or figure out what I do not know. Therefore, I can easily follow the classes. for me, I forget the '' Voltage distributinon '' . It is very elementary idea about physics . So I got shocked. But soon, I found it by my tablet . I can follow the lecture without any blank. Third, Tablet Notetaking gives me many benefits. When I am notetaking at the paper, It is little bit hard to draw a flat line or circle or highlight the important part. But ata the tablet environment , I can easily do notetaking by a few click. I can choose the color of the pen or thickness of the pen and there are tools such as ruler, triangle , rectangule, circle If I want and accessed, I can record some part of lecture. So It is more easy to notetake by listening the lecture. In summary , It is more portable to carry tablet, directly something, It is more easy to take note. In these reasons , they are the advantages of using tablet.', '2025-03-13 12:06:00'),
(4, 51, 'Yes, we can definitely work on revising your sentences to address some of these common issues. First, can you provide me with a copy of the essay you would like to work on? From there, we can go sentence by sentence to identify any issues and revise them accordingly.', '<essay>Government makes laws and protects their citizens from various probelms such as disasters, poverties and crimes. Citizens have their rights to be helped and protected by government. Each citizens will hve different situations and different needs to be helped by government. Then should the government help only those most in need rather than helping all of its citizens? I want to say ''no'' to this question for several reasons. First, if we help only people in need then discrimination and hatred between group who gets benefit and who does not will be deeper. Government rules the country with a money from their citizen. Every law and system is possible when there is a money to make and operate it. If people in need only gets benefit from them, then people who don''t get benefit will loose their motivation to pay tax. They will discriminate the people who get benefit. Second reason is that peolpe will loose their motivation to work. If government helps every people in need, then they don''t have to work. They just have to get money from government and live with it. On the other hand people who have to pay for that money and don''t get benefit don''t have reason to earn more money. Their motivation to work will decrease. For these reason the government should not help only those most in need. Discrimination between two group will grow, and people will not work hard to earn money. All citizens have their right to be helped by their givernment. Helping equally is healthy way for our society than helping only people in need.</essay>', 'The government makes laws and protects its citizens from various problems, such as disasters, poverty, and crime. Citizens have their rights to be helped and protected by government. Each citizen has different situations and needs that may require assistance from the government. Therefore, the question arises: should the government help only those most in need rather than helping all of its citizens? I want to say ''no'' to this question for several reasons; First, if we help only people in need then discrimination and hatred between group who gets benefit and who does not will be deeper. Government rules the country with a money from their citizen. Every law and system is possible when there is a money to make and operate it. If people in need only gets benefit from them, then people who don''t get benefit will loose their motivation to pay tax. They will discriminate the people who get benefit. The second reason is that people will lose their motivation to work if the government provides assistance to only those in need. They just have to get money from government and live with it. In such a system, those who do not benefit from government aid may feel disenfranchised and resentful towards those who do. They''re faced with paying for the income of others without receiving any benefits themselves. As a result, their motivation to work decreases. For these reason the government should not help only those most in need. Discrimination between two group will grow, and people will not work hard to earn money. All citizens have a right to be helped by their government, and helping everyone equally is a healthy approach for our society.', '2025-03-20 16:36:00'),
(5, 51, 'Great job! Your essay has a good structure and you have provided good examples for each advantage. Now let''s take a closer look at the punctuation and revise the content to make it stand out. 1. In the first sentence, you can add a comma after "In these days" to separate the introductory phrase from the main clause. 2. In the second sentence, use "These internet technology devices" instead of "these internet technology devices" to make it more specific. "They" is unclear, so instead of saying "they use these internet technology devices to write down what they learn," say "Students use these internet technology devices to take notes in class." 3. In the third sentence, add a comma after "For example" to separate this introductory phrase from the main clause. 4. In the fourth sentence, use "the post-Covid era" instead of "the post-covid era" and use "Zoom or Google Meet" instead of "Zoom of Google Meets." Also, in this sentence, add a comma after the word "era" to connect the dependent clause better to the independent clause. 5. In the seventh sentence, use <sent>"the most important part of the advantages, which is the usefulness,"</sent> instead of <sent>"the most important part of the advantages, usefulness,"</sent> to make it clear that you are introducing a new idea. 6. Finally, in the last sentence, you can add "as" before "students" so that the sentence reads "As these advantages demonstrate." This will improve the flow of your conclusion. Remember to proofread your work before submitting the final draft. Great job, and keep up the good work!', 'Is it okay with the comma rules? <essay>In these days, most students use their own tablets or laptop computers in class. Students use these internet technology devices to take notes in class, download professor''s lecture notes, and search something that they do not know exactly. There are two big advantages of using a tablet or a laptop computer in class. The first advantage is that students can participate in class well by using the devices. For example, playing Kahoot quiz about what students have learned increases understanding of the concept they have learned, and using QR codes to join some activity in class will rise interest of students. In addition, we are in the post-covid era, students and professor can contact online via Zoom of Google Meets, and it can also increase participation of students in class who are far away. By using tablets and laptops, students can participate in class more actively. The second advantage is the usefulness of using such devices. In class, professor do their class using lecture notes and sometimes they write down some letters on the white board. Students who use tablets or laptops can easily download the lecture note, write what they understand down on it, take some pictures of the white board and share some copy of their online notes. Also, by using some internet platforms such as KLMS or Google Classroom, students can upload their homework or handout more comfortably. The most important part of the advantages, which is the usefulness, is that students can do those things with only one electronic device, they need no paper, no pencil, no erasers. There are two main advantages, the increase of participation of students in class, and the usefulness of using the devices. As these advantages demonstrate, students use their own tablet or laptop computers in class.</essay>', 'In these days, most students use their own tablets or laptop computers in class. Students use these internet technology devices to take notes in class, download professor''s lecture notes, and search something that they do not know exactly. There are two big advantages of using a tablet or a laptop computer in class. The first advantage is that students can participate in class well by using the devices. For example, playing Kahoot quiz about what students have learned increases understanding of the concept they have learned, and using QR codes to join some activity in class will rise interest of students. In addition, we are in the post-covid era, students and professor can contact online via Zoom of Google Meets, and it can also increase participation of students in class who are far away. By using tablets and laptops, students can participate in class more actively. The second advantage is the usefulness of using such devices. In class, professor do their class using lecture notes and sometimes they write down some letters on the white board. Students who use tablets or laptops can easily download the lecture note, write what they understand down on it, take some pictures of the white board and share some copy of their online notes. Also, by using some internet platforms such as KLMS or Google Classroom, students can upload their homework or handout more comfortably. The most important part of the advantages, which is the usefulness, is that students can do those things with only one electronic device, they need no paper, no pencil, no erasers. There are two main advantages, the increase of participation of students in class, and the usefulness of using the devices. As these advantages demonstrate, students use their own tablet or laptop computers in class.', '2025-04-03 18:36:00'),
(1, 52, 'Certainly, I would be happy to help you with any grammar errors in your questions. Just let me know what you need help with.', 'can you tell me if there is any comma splice or run on errors in my essay following? <essay>First year in KAIST, undergraduates does''t have a specific major. Many other university opened major that has no major first year, and some university even have under graduates be free of majors until graduation. Universities should require the first year of college to be major-free. I have three supporting reason that no major on the first year of college is beneficial in different reasons. First, an year without major gives students more freedom to choose, and it enables them to live a more non-passive life. Students can select what their lives and their first year on college would be like. Computer science student from the year would not try to find what they are truly interested in but passively accept the fate that leaning computer science is the fixed future they''ll take. On the other hand freshmen with no major will consider carefully what they can choose and design their future on their own. The process is likely to be painstaking, however actively choosing the path of life will help students build their identity and passion to motivate themselves. Same student will choose challenging scheduals attending lots of classes. Others can attend diverse major class. Secondly, major-free freshmen can create networks with diverse peope. Integration between fields is what makes a breakthrough in not only academic areas but also arts and buissiness. Major-less freshmen will easily make bonds with people with diverse interests and history. Students with major would also make bonds, but not as easily and strong as students without major would. Lastly, it''s hard to get interested in one major until highschool graduation. Lacking life experience, highschool students often choose majors by first look or without knowing what the major is actually about. Universities in South Korea grade highschool students by their ''major compatable rate'' that make highschool student lie on their interests on the school records. First year without major will loosen this tendancy and for the students who weren''t truly interested in the major they applied a second chance.</essay>', 'First year in KAIST, undergraduates does''t have a specific major. Many other university opened major that has no major first year, and some university even have under graduates be free of majors until graduation. Universities should require the first year of college to be major-free. I have three supporting reason that no major on the first year of college is beneficial in different reasons. First, an year without major gives students more freedom to choose, and it enables them to live a more non-passive life. Students can select what their lives and their first year on college would be like. Computer science student from the year would not try to find what they are truly interested in but passively accept the fate that leaning computer science is the fixed future they''ll take. On the other hand freshmen with no major will consider carefully what they can choose and design their future on their own. The process is likely to be painstaking, however actively choosing the path of life will help students build their identity and passion to motivate themselves. Same student will choose challenging scheduals attending lots of classes. Others can attend diverse major class. Secondly, major-free freshmen can create networks with diverse peope. Integration between fields is what makes a breakthrough in not only academic areas but also arts and buissiness. Major-less freshmen will easily make bonds with people with diverse interests and history. Students with major would also make bonds, but not as easily and strong as students without major would. Lastly, it''s hard to get interested in one major until highschool graduation. Lacking life experience, highschool students often choose majors by first look or without knowing what the major is actually about. Universities in South Korea grade highschool students by their ''major compatable rate'' that make highschool student lie on their interests on the school records. First year without major will loosen this tendancy and for the students who weren''t truly interested in the major they applied a second chance.', '2025-02-14 12:40:00'),
(2, 52, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Hello, last week we learned about articles use in sentences. For example, we use the article "the" to indicate something is known/specific.', 'We are also interested in studying the structure of modular forms under various base rings, as different base rings allow us to obtain valuable information about the Fourier coefficients of modular forms. An example of novelty brought by a base ring change comes from modular forms with coefficients in Z. This class of modular forms is interesting, due to the fact that the field Q containing all the Fourier coefficients. As a result, this induces a Galois representation such that the trace of the conjugacy class Frobp in Gal(Q/Q) is an integer, and hence easier to analyze. This is owing to the theorem from Deligne and Serre in [DS]', '2025-02-27 13:40:00'),
(3, 52, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'This paragraph is an overview for the result section. I think there are still many method contents. Can you change it smoothly?', 'We utilized the CRISPR-Cas9 system to generate a HAP1 cell line, in which we confirmed the successful knockout of the CHD3 gene using western blotting with the dTAG system. ChIP-seq experiments revealed that CHD3 was highly enriched in the histone gene cluster region, and its disappearance was observed upon treatment with dTAG-13. During this process, we also observed an increase in transcription factors at the super enhancer region of the histone gene cluster and an increase in E-P interactions in Hi-C experiments. Interestingly, we found that CHD3 in the histone gene cluster region interacted with several transcription inhibitors rather than forming a NuRD complex with CHD4 on a different chromosome.', '2025-03-13 12:10:00'),
(4, 52, 'Certainly, please go ahead and provide me with the sentences you completed with the correct format.', 'Verb Forms (gerund/infinitive) 1. The analysis was limited to _determining_ (determine) the change in the population number. 2. We sought to _improve_ (improve) the yield by adding specific catalysts. 3. Impurities in our samples were barriers to _obatain_ (obtain) chemically pure products using standard isolation techniques. 4. Ongoing volcanic eruptions limited the amount of time that we could dedicate to _collect_ (collect) samples. 5. The reviewers recommend _adding_ (add) more information about the bear habitat. 6. Reaching temperatures as close to absolute zero Kelvin as possible is central to _design_ (design) a quantum computer. Adjectives and Adverbs 1. X behaved (different, differently) than expected. 2. Dark matter, which constitutes most of the mass in the universe, is not _directly_ (direct) _visible_ (visible) but can be inferred due to its gravitational properties. 3. Telomeres, DNA sequences at the ends of chromosomes that keep our chromosomes (intact, intactly), shorten with every cell division and are therefore an indication of aging. 4. Species richness in plants is correlated (biological, biologically) and (geohistorical, geohistorically) and increases ecological opportunities. 5. The resolution of telescopes is restricted by the diffraction of light, which cannot (selective, selectively) focus on anything smaller than a plane wave. 6. Mainstream climate science needs to look more (close, closely) at geoengineering. 7. The impact of vaccinating domestic animals on rabies occurrence was evaluated by comparing (ecological, ecologically) field studies with (empirical, empirically) based models. 8. (Recent, Recently) studies have shown that (new, newly) imported Australian bees have been linked to the virus responsible for infecting and decimating honeybee colonies. Prepositions 1. In connection _to_ 2. Compared _with_ 3. In contrast _of_ 4. Search _on_ 5. Correlated _with_ 6. A comparison _with_ A and_ B 7. Similar _to_ 8. To look forward _that_ 9. Results shown _in_ Fig 3 10. Through the decrease _of_ 11. Analogous _to_ 12. Implicit _to_ 13. Theorize _that_ 14. Different _from_ 15. Attempt (n.) _of_; Attempt (v.) _to_ 16. _in_ respect _of_ Articles 1. Oscillatory behavior was reduced in_the_ presence of a ring electrode. 2. Sea urchin fertilization is _a_ model system in developmental biology. 3. Therefore, _the_ hypothesis we presented previously is further confirmed. 4. Back to _the_ nature. 5. _The_ inorganic chemistry proves to be a very interesting subject. 6. Can you name _the_ inorganic molecule? 7. Conversion of _a_ CK riboside to the base can be regarded as the last step in the pathway. 8. Title: _A_ Role of _the_ Physical Activity on _a_ Severity of Diabetes. 9. _The_ theoretical studies cited earlier depict a variety of different patterns in oscillating media. 10. Here we discuss _a_ physical-chemical mechanisms leading to pattern formation in electrochemical systems 11. Figure 4: _The_ effect of _a_ temperature on _the_ ctx expression. 12. _A_ rainfall in _the_Sahara Desert occurs rarely. 13. _An_ average rainfall in _the_ Sahara Desert is less than 25 mm per year. 14. Under _the_ light microscope, _a_ organelles are visible in _a_ eukaryotes. 15. At the end of its “life,” _an_ mRNA molecule is degraded.', 'Verb Forms (gerund/infinitive) 1. The analysis was limited to _determining_ (determine) the change in the population number. 2. We sought to _improve_ (improve) the yield by adding specific catalysts. 3. Impurities in our samples were barriers to _obatain_ (obtain) chemically pure products using standard isolation techniques. 4. Ongoing volcanic eruptions limited the amount of time that we could dedicate to _collect_ (collect) samples. 5. The reviewers recommend _adding_ (add) more information about the bear habitat. 6. Reaching temperatures as close to absolute zero Kelvin as possible is central to _design_ (design) a quantum computer. Adjectives and Adverbs 1. X behaved (different, differently) than expected. 2. Dark matter, which constitutes most of the mass in the universe, is not _directly_ (direct) _visible_ (visible) but can be inferred due to its gravitational properties. 3. Telomeres, DNA sequences at the ends of chromosomes that keep our chromosomes (intact, intactly), shorten with every cell division and are therefore an indication of aging. 4. Species richness in plants is correlated (biological, biologically) and (geohistorical, geohistorically) and increases ecological opportunities. 5. The resolution of telescopes is restricted by the diffraction of light, which cannot (selective, selectively) focus on anything smaller than a plane wave. 6. Mainstream climate science needs to look more (close, closely) at geoengineering. 7. The impact of vaccinating domestic animals on rabies occurrence was evaluated by comparing (ecological, ecologically) field studies with (empirical, empirically) based models. 8. (Recent, Recently) studies have shown that (new, newly) imported Australian bees have been linked to the virus responsible for infecting and decimating honeybee colonies. Prepositions 1. In connection _to_ 2. Compared _with_ 3. In contrast _of_ 4. Search _on_ 5. Correlated _with_ 6. A comparison _with_ A and_ B 7. Similar _to_ 8. To look forward _that_ 9. Results shown _in_ Fig 3 10. Through the decrease _of_ 11. Analogous _to_ 12. Implicit _to_ 13. Theorize _that_ 14. Different _from_ 15. Attempt (n.) _of_; Attempt (v.) _to_ 16. _in_ respect _of_ Articles 1. Oscillatory behavior was reduced in_the_ presence of a ring electrode. 2. Sea urchin fertilization is _a_ model system in developmental biology. 3. Therefore, _the_ hypothesis we presented previously is further confirmed. 4. Back to _the_ nature. 5. _The_ inorganic chemistry proves to be a very interesting subject. 6. Can you name _the_ inorganic molecule? 7. Conversion of _a_ CK riboside to the base can be regarded as the last step in the pathway. 8. Title: _A_ Role of _the_ Physical Activity on _a_ Severity of Diabetes. 9. _The_ theoretical studies cited earlier depict a variety of different patterns in oscillating media. 10. Here we discuss _a_ physical-chemical mechanisms leading to pattern formation in electrochemical systems 11. Figure 4: _The_ effect of _a_ temperature on _the_ ctx expression. 12. _A_ rainfall in _the_Sahara Desert occurs rarely. 13. _An_ average rainfall in _the_ Sahara Desert is less than 25 mm per year. 14. Under _the_ light microscope, _a_ organelles are visible in _a_ eukaryotes. 15. At the end of its “life,” _an_ mRNA molecule is degraded.', '2025-03-20 16:40:00'),
(5, 52, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today, I learned how to write methodology for scientic writing. The most important thing the writer needs to consider is the reproductability. The purpose of the methodology part is to deliver how I implemented the whole experiment to be confirmed that the process is logically designed for the purpose of the experiment and to provide guidance for the researchers who wants to follow the expriment.', 'First, prepare blocks with ridgids. 1 green flat-surfaced cube block with 4 ridgids, 2 blue blocks with ridges, and 2 green flat-surfaced triangles with 2 ridges each, and one green long gear. In our experiment we decided to build a tree. To do that we followed a specific methodology. First of all, the two triangles should be put together and form a circle in the middle. Inside the newly formed circle, you then put the long green gear inside the formed circle. It should be standing perpendicular with the table surface. Then, we put together two blue cubes in a way that forms a circle in the middle on top of the long green gear in the same way that the triangles were put together in a circle by the end of the gear. The end step is putting the green flat-surfaced cube on the top of the two blue cubes. The green block should be in the middle of the two blue blocks. The green cube will link the two blue cubes by having one part on each cube. The other group’s replica is slightly different because we did not describe the rotation of the two rectangular parts of the tree. We should have checked the angle of our tree structure and described it at the end of the write.', '2025-04-03 18:40:00'),
(1, 53, 'Great! Let''s take a look at your essay together. First, please copy and paste your essay in the chat so that I can review it. Once I review it, I''ll provide feedback on where I think you can use commas to make your writing clear and accurate.', '<essay>Some universities, such as kaist, made the first year of college student as major-free. Still the most college don''t use that method but I think universities should require that the first year of college be major-free for three reasons. First, most student choose college''s name, not a major. In Korea, the most hot standard for college is whether the location of college is Seoul or not. The fame also can be a standard and whether what major they have is not a consideration. So when the the student enter the college, they may regret about their choice of the major. But, when the first year of college is major-free, they can adapt to college system and then can choose the major more carefully. Second, the quality of student can be better. Students in college is still young and most of them don''t have strong image of their future and vision. If they experience other major''s class, which is very attractive for them, they would change their originally thinking major. So we shouldn''t prevent a student from accessing variable subject and the major-free system can be good way for it. As they select the most fit major, the quality of all major group will be improve. Lastly, the community from college to student get activate and it works as positive-feedback. In major-free system, student choose the major. So the people in each major advertise passionally and research hard to make students'' attention. After the students choose the major, they also work hard for next students and for themself to get much budget from the universities. Therefore, for the universities'' future, the major-free system for the first-year is needed. Some says it is irresponsible for students. BUt to acheive a goal in this hard word, students should develop their own''s ability.</essay>', 'Some universities, such as kaist, made the first year of college student as major-free. Still the most college don''t use that method but I think universities should require that the first year of college be major-free for three reasons. First, most student choose college''s name, not a major. In Korea, the most hot standard for college is whether the location of college is Seoul or not. The fame also can be a standard and whether what major they have is not a consideration. So when the the student enter the college, they may regret about their choice of the major. But, when the first year of college is major-free, they can adapt to college system and then can choose the major more carefully. Second, the quality of student can be better. Students in college is still young and most of them don''t have strong image of their future and vision. If they experience other major''s class, which is very attractive for them, they would change their originally thinking major. So we shouldn''t prevent a student from accessing variable subject and the major-free system can be good way for it. As they select the most fit major, the quality of all major group will be improve. Lastly, the community from college to student get activate and it works as positive-feedback. In major-free system, student choose the major. So the people in each major advertise passionally and research hard to make students'' attention. After the students choose the major, they also work hard for next students and for themself to get much budget from the universities. Therefore, for the universities'' future, the major-free system for the first-year is needed. Some says it is irresponsible for students. BUt to acheive a goal in this hard word, students should develop their own''s ability.', '2025-02-14 12:44:00'),
(2, 53, 'I haven''t seen your essay, so I can''t say for sure. Please share your essay with me so I can review it and offer feedback.', 'Many people wondered about how the government uses their taxes. There were many news about the usage of taxes for people that needed help like old people who live alone or orphans. However, news also told that taxes are used at strange that people think they don’t need a help like rich people. Then, the taxes are used only for those most in need? I think it is not a good idea. I want to say three reasons for why government should help all of its citizens. First, everyone need help. Regardless of their background, people need help for many reasons. For example, these who are rich because of their restaurant. But if they have a problem about the pollution that is made by the building right next to restaurant, they can’t do anything regardless of their money. In this situation, government have to help them. Like this, regardless of their background, everyone needs help in their situation. Second, the government and the country is made by the citizens. At Korean law, it says ‘the right of Korea lies with the citizens, and all the power comes from the citizens.’ Citizens contribute to make a government and they should be the most important thing for the government. So, regardless of their background government have to protect all citizens. Finally, taxes are gained by all the citizens. Moreover, rich people pay more taxes. Of course I think it’s fair can common sense that rich people pay more taxes. But the fact is that all citizens pay taxes. It they pat it but there’s not any help, they will confused about why they pay taxes. So, government should help all people that pay taxes. To sum up, all citizen need help and they pay taxes for government. And also they are most important thing for the government. I think it is fair, that most taxes are used for people in need. But their system should be needed that all citizens can get help.', 'Many people wondered about how the government uses their taxes. There were many news about the usage of taxes for people that needed help like old people who live alone or orphans. However, news also told that taxes are used at strange that people think they don’t need a help like rich people. Then, the taxes are used only for those most in need? I think it is not a good idea. I want to say three reasons for why government should help all of its citizens. First, everyone need help. Regardless of their background, people need help for many reasons. For example, these who are rich because of their restaurant. But if they have a problem about the pollution that is made by the building right next to restaurant, they can’t do anything regardless of their money. In this situation, government have to help them. Like this, regardless of their background, everyone needs help in their situation. Second, the government and the country is made by the citizens. At Korean law, it says ‘the right of Korea lies with the citizens, and all the power comes from the citizens.’ Citizens contribute to make a government and they should be the most important thing for the government. So, regardless of their background government have to protect all citizens. Finally, taxes are gained by all the citizens. Moreover, rich people pay more taxes. Of course I think it’s fair can common sense that rich people pay more taxes. But the fact is that all citizens pay taxes. It they pat it but there’s not any help, they will confused about why they pay taxes. So, government should help all people that pay taxes. To sum up, all citizen need help and they pay taxes for government. And also they are most important thing for the government. I think it is fair, that most taxes are used for people in need. But their system should be needed that all citizens can get help.', '2025-02-27 13:44:00'),
(3, 53, 'In general, it is better to start with the general point and narrow down to the specific points. This approach is typically more effective because it gives your readers an overarching idea of what your essay is about before delving into the specific points. This approach is also known as the "inverted pyramid" style, where the most important information is presented first, followed by the specifics.', 'What if the three points are not much related? How should i place three points then?', 'First year in KAIST, undergraduates does not have a specific major. Many other universities opened majors that do not require a specific major in the first year, and some university even have undergraduates be free of majors until graduation. I agree with this Universities should require the first year of college to be major-free. I have three supporting reason that no major on the first year of college is beneficial in different reasons. First, a year without major gives students more freedom to choose, and it enables them to live a less passive life. Students can select what their lives and their first year on college would be like. Computer science student from the year would not try to find what they are truly interested in but passively accept the fate that leaning computer science is the fixed future they''ll take. On the other hand freshmen with no major will consider carefully what they can choose and design their future on their own. The process is likely to be painstaking, however actively choosing the path of life will help students build their identity and passion to motivate themselves. Same student will choose challenging schedules attending lots of classes. Others can attend diverse classes in various majors. Secondly, major-free freshmen can create networks with diverse people. Integration between fields is what makes a breakthrough in not only academic areas but also arts and business. Major-free freshmen will easily make bonds with people with diverse interests and history. Students with major would also make bonds, but not as easily and strong as students without a major would. Lastly, it''s hard to become interested in one major until high school graduation. Lacking life experience, high school students often choose majors by first look or without knowing what the major is actually about. Universities in South Korea grade high school students by their ''major compatible rate'' that cause high school student lie on their interests on the school records. First year without major will reduce this tendency and for the students who were not truly interested in the major they applied for a second chance.', '2025-03-13 12:14:00'),
(4, 53, 'You''re right. Thank you for pointing that out. Here''s another revised introduction that takes this into account: Governments are responsible for providing a wide range of services to their citizens, from healthcare to education to public infrastructure. However, with limited resources and workforce, it is essential that these services be distributed selectively, with a focus on those who require the most support. For example, while public roads, parks, and other common spaces should be accessible to everyone, financial assistance and housing programs should be allocated based on need. This strategic approach to resource allocation not only helps governments to operate within their budget, but also ensures that the most vulnerable populations receive the support they require for their well-being.', 'Can you give me another example that can replace the housing programs?', 'Governments are responsible for providing assistance to their citizens, but with finite resources and a limited workforce, it is important that this assistance be targeted towards those in need. For instance, while public transportation or road infrastructure might be accessible to everyone, certain financial assistance programs or educational programs may be best directed to communities or individuals with low-income or special needs. By using resources efficiently and strategically, governments can ensure that those who require the most support get the assistance they need to lead healthy and fulfilling lives.', '2025-03-20 16:44:00'),
(5, 53, '해당 문장에서는 문법적인 오류가 없으며 문장도 알맞게 구성되어 있습니다. 하지만, 이 문장이 잘 작성된 논문의 첫 문장인 경우, 인트로덕션 내용이 좀 애매한 것 같습니다. 한 문장으로 논문의 성격을 명확하게 하기 보다는, 해당 논문이 주제에 대해 발표할 인사이트를 보여주는 것이 좋습니다. 예를 들어: "School uniforms are a common requirement in many countries around the world. While there is debate about the pros and cons of this policy, it is clear that the practice has benefits that extend beyond the surface level of clothing choice. By examining the reasons why many schools require uniforms, this paper aims to shed light on the impact that this seemingly trivial policy can have on a variety of important educational outcomes." 이렇게 작성하면, 논문의 내용이 더욱 명확해지고, 초록이나 논문의 시작 부분에서 재미를 유발하는 것이 가능해집니다.', '<para>Primary, school uniform is sigh of student, teenager, and weaker in society. If someone wearing uniforms get in troubles, many people will help. There are research and statics that people more help someone when school uniforms in dangerous or emergency situations, so, school uniform protect many students.</para> 의 문법 오류를 알고 싶어', 'School Uniforms are common recommended by many high schools in almost every region of Korea for students to wear. When entering middle school, teenagers in Korea have to wear school uniforms. Some students are uncomfortable with this rule and resist following their school and teacher. To require wearing school uniforms is good for several reasons. Primary, school uniform is sigh of student, teenager, and weaker in society. If someone wearing uniforms get in troubles, many people will help. There are research and statics that people more help someone when school uniforms in dangerous or emergency situations, so, school uniform protect many students. Another reason, school uniform also useful for shopping or boarding public transport. Teenagers get various events that especially sales or gifts freely. If the students wear a school uniform, they will participate and enjoy culture event such as movie, concert, and books not to check extra files that identified student. School uniforms are useable and helpful. We need to one more consider whether removing school uniforms rule from students to society. It will more increase connection all around our region and society.', '2025-04-03 18:44:00'),
(1, 54, 'Sure, please share the part of your essay that you would like feedback on.', 'However, this has been controversial because people were not sure whether it is effective for education or not.', 'Increasingly, schools across the nation are embracing the use of personal technology in the classroom. According to a recent study, over 75% of middle schools now allow students to use their own personal devices, and some teachers even provide them. However, this has been controversial because people were not sure whether it is effective for education or not. The reason why governments still allow them to use such electric devices, even though there are some controversies, is because it has some advantages that can not be taken only with general books or notebooks. First, it is easier to write and erase letters since digital notebooks allow one to remove words that are written as a mistake, and the size of the letters can be changed easily, unlike paper notebooks. Furthermore, digital notebooks have more color options, allowing users to include various color pens. Second, they are useful to search for necessary information. It is hard to find some concepts in books during class; however, it will be much faster to look for them online. Therefore, extra time after a particular class to help students understand what the teachers taught would not be required since they can discover more documents that can help them learn specific concepts. Third, each of the students in a certain class can be connected. As a result, they can share useful information and have debates about what they learned during the day, offering high school students the opportunity to experience teamwork or the cooperation projects usually shown in colleges earlier.', '2025-02-14 12:48:00'),
(2, 54, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about the cause and effect paragraphs. There are signal words to show cause like ''for'', ''beacuase of'', ''due to''. Also there are signal words for effect like ''therefore'', ''so''. Besides, there are sentence connectors, coordinating conjunctions, and subordinationg conjunctions too. By the things I told you and what you know about cause and effect paragraphs, could you organize the content of it?', 'In our university, KAIST, we are major-free in the first year. Unlike other universities, where students select their majors before starting college and continue to study it, we choose a major in the second year. This policy has several benefits for both students and university. First of all, the first year of college being major-free allows students to have extra time to make decisions about their future. High school grades are very important when it comes to selecting majors, which puts a lot of pressure on students. Often, students choose their major solely based on their high school performance, which might not be a reliable indicator of interests or strengths. Choosing a major at the early age of 17 is difficult, and it is important to provide students with enough time to explore their options. The policy allows students to experience different things as adults and have time to think about their dreams. Although this may seem like a waste of time, it is better to spend one extra year exploring than regretting a wrong choice. Secondly, students can benefit from a break after a demanding high school experience that had lasted for three years. Even if students have already decided on their major, taking time to meet people from all over the world and spend time with new friends can be beneficial. The university environment is famous for promoting creativity and new ideas, which can provide students with a chance to improve their thoughts and widen their worldview. Thirdly, over time, many subjects within different majors have started overlapping, especially with the rise of artificial intelligence. Giving students the opportunity to explore various subjects can improve their understanding of the shared topics, which improves their perspective on their major. Since many majors share similar course requirements like mathematics and physics, there would be no concern about wasting time on unrelated courses. Lastly, colleges can worry less about enrolling students for different majors, as not all majors are equally popular. By allowing students to change their major as they wish, colleges do not have to worry about involuntary enrolment in less popular majors or over-enrolling in popular ones. Instead, they can focus solely on ensuring that enrolled students are studying and meeting their academic obligations.', '2025-02-27 13:48:00'),
(3, 54, 'Sure! Here are some suggestions for enriching the body paragraphs of your essay: First Paragraph: <para>One way to enrich this paragraph is to provide an example to support your argument that limiting assistance to only those in need can result in deeper discrimination and hatred between groups. Additionally, you could add data or statistics to bolster the credibility of your argument. You can also consider expanding on the repercussions of deeper discrimination and hatred between groups, discussing how it may lead to societal unrest or even violence if left unchecked.</para> Second Paragraph: <para>To enrich this paragraph, you could discuss some of the pros and cons of providing government assistance to only those in need versus providing assistance to all citizens. Engaging with opposing views can help your reader better understand your stance and why you believe it is the best approach. You may also consider exploring the different types of government assistance that could help motivate people to work while still providing support for those in need, such as job training programs or temporary assistance programs.</para> Third Paragraph: <para>One way to enrich this paragraph is to explore the potential solutions to the problem of determining who qualifies for government aid without resorting to a system that targets only those most in need. For example, you could discuss the merits of programs that benefit everyone, such as universal basic income or free public education, and how they could be implemented efficiently and fairly. Additionally, you could discuss the moral implications of determining who qualifies for government assistance, exploring the potential biases and ethical dilemmas that arise when deciding who gets help and who does not.</para> Remember to integrate any new information you add to your essay seamlessly with your existing content. This will help ensure that your essay flows naturally and communicates your argument effectively.', 'can you give me an example of first paragraph and pros and cons of providing government assistance to only those in need versus providing assistance to all citizens?', 'The government makes laws and protects its citizens from various problems, such as disasters, poverty, and crime. Citizens have their rights to be helped and protected by government. Each citizen has different situations and needs that may require assistance from the government. Therefore, the question arises: should the government help only those most in need rather than help all of its citizens? I want to say ''no'' to this question for several reasons;. While it may seem logical to provide aid only to those most in need, it can be discriminatory and demotivating. A more equitable approach is to provide aid to all citizens in need. First, if we help only people in need then discrimination and hatred between group who gets benefit and who does not will be deeper. Government rules the country with a money from their citizen. Every law and system is possible when there is a money to make and operate it. If people in need only get benefit from them, then people who don''t get benefit will lose their motivation to pay tax. They will discriminate the people who get benefit. One example of how limiting assistance to only those in need can create deeper discrimination and hatred between groups can be seen in the case of healthcare. When healthcare systems focus solely on providing care to those who demonstrate financial need, it can lead to resentment and division. Citizens who are ineligible for assistance may harbor ill will towards those who are receiving aid, seeing them as freeloaders, while those who are receiving aid may feel stigmatized and discriminated against. On the other hand, when assistance is provided to all citizens, it fosters a sense of communal responsibility and shared accountability. By contributing to the healthcare system through taxation, everyone is invested in the well-being of one another, and the government is more accountable to the needs of its citizens. The second reason is that people will lose their motivation to work if the government provides assistance to only those in need. They just have to get money from government and live with it. In such a system, those who do not benefit from government aid may feel disenfranchised and resentful towards those who do. They''re faced with paying for the income of others without receiving any benefits themselves. As a result, their motivation to work decreases. Some people might say that providing assistance only to those in need has potential for greater efficiency, as resources are concentrated where they are most needed. Additionally, the amount of funding needed for assistance programs may be lower, as it is targeted towards those in dire circumstances. However, Those who are ineligible for assistance due to their financial standing may feel that they are being left out of important government programs. They will lose their reason to pay taxes and their motivation to work hard, and consequently, government will lose efficiency gained by helping only those in need. A third problem of implementing a system of aid that targets only those most in need is that the process of determining who qualifies for aid can be highly subjective and prone to abuse. Determining who qualifies for government aid and who does not can be complex and time-consuming. Some people might intentionally misrepresent their situation in order to get assistance, while others might be unjustly excluded from aid due to administrative errors. Then there can be a moral issues. People with greater resources might not need government support, they may still benefit from it in various ways due to the error on determining who qualifies for government assistance. Another reason of why providing assistance to all citizens can be beneficial is in the case of education funding. When governments choose to provide financial aid only to those who demonstrate financial need, they may inadvertently signal to students that their work will not be rewarded except in cases of dire fiscal straits. In such a system, students may feel more effective pursuing an education that does not require them to take out costly student loans, even if it means abandoning their preferred path of study. On the other hand, by promoting assistance to all citizens based on merit and academic achievement, governments can ensure that talented students have an equal opportunity to achieve their goals, and the workforce remains competitive. However, some may argue that providing financial assistance to all students based on merit is a wasteful use of taxpayer dollars. They may argue that only students who demonstrate financial need or who contribute to the public good or a particular industry should be eligible for government funding. However, while this argument may seem logical, it fails to account for the fact that many talented students who do not meet the stringent eligibility criteria may still struggle with the costs of tuition and other expenses that pose a barrier to their educational goals. Additionally, by promoting higher educational achievement and merit, governments can create a better-educated workforce overall, leading to higher economic returns and a more productive and innovative society. The cost to the taxpayer can be balanced against the benefits brought about by a more educated citizenry. For these reasons the government should not help only those most in need. Discrimination between two group will grow, and people will not work hard to earn money. Additionally, in reality it is hard to implement a system of aid that targets only those most in need. In this procedure moral issues can occur. All citizens have a right to be helped by their government, and helping everyone equally is a healthy approach for our society.', '2025-03-13 12:18:00'),
(4, 54, 'Thank you for pointing that out. I apologize for the error. Here is a revised version with that mistake corrected: <essay>"The main objective of this study was to develop a high-quality beatmap generation algorithm using a deep learning language model and evaluate its performance. We not only collected guidelines for evaluating beatmap quality but also generalized the algorithm’s application field from one game to a set of games that share common features. Additionally, we expanded the Fraxtil-ITG dataset with valuable training data for music annotation purposes. Our study contributes to the field of advanced beatmap generation algorithms, which can benefit both beatmap makers and players by speeding up the creation process and enhancing overall user experience. By expediting the generation process, game developers can release updates more frequently, providing players with more diverse and exciting content while allowing beatmappers to focus on the creative aspects of the task."</essay> Thank you for giving me the opportunity to revise my initial feedback. Please let me know if you have any more questions or concerns.', 'I added the limitations and future research directions. can you revise it for me? <essay>Despite the promising results, there are some limitations to consider. Firstly, while the percentage of unique patterns in the generated beatmaps greatly increased, it was still significantly lower than that of human-made beatmaps, especially for higher difficulty levels. Secondly, while the proposed algorithm outperformed the DDC baseline in every aspect, it was slightly worse than the GN baseline for the beginner charts. Future research may investigate ways to improve consistency across all difficulty levels and incorporate the spatial placement of actions for specific game interfaces. It could also examine the variations in beatmaps created by different authors for the same song and develop a metric to quantify them to refine the evaluation guidelines. Obtaining feedback from experienced beatmap creators may be necessary. The algorithm could have practical applications, especially for amateur video game developers who don''t have the resources or expertise to create precise and engaging beatmaps from scratch. It could also be used for motor and cognitive skill recovery rhythm-based games in healthcare and rehabilitation settings.</essay>', 'Despite the promising results, there are some limitations to consider. Firstly, while the percentage of unique patterns in the generated beatmaps greatly increased, it was still significantly lower than that of human-made beatmaps, especially for higher difficulty levels. Secondly, while the proposed algorithm outperformed the DDC baseline in every aspect, it was slightly worse than the GN baseline for the beginner charts. Future research may investigate ways to improve consistency across all difficulty levels and incorporate the spatial placement of actions for specific game interfaces. It could also examine the variations in beatmaps created by different authors for the same song and develop a metric to quantify them to refine the evaluation guidelines. Obtaining feedback from experienced beatmap creators may be necessary. The algorithm could have practical applications, especially for amateur video game developers who don''t have the resources or expertise to create precise and engaging beatmaps from scratch. It could also be used for motor and cognitive skill recovery rhythm-based games in healthcare and rehabilitation settings.', '2025-03-20 16:48:00'),
(5, 54, 'Okay, let''s move on to hyphens. Can you tell me what hyphens are used for?', 'To indicate that two or more words are acting as a single concept to describe the following noun', 'A InGaAs MFS capacitor was fabricated using atomic layer deposition (ALD) machine, e-beam evaporator, and rapid thermal annealing (RTA) machine. Then, ferroelectricity of the capacitor was demonstrated both electrically and chemically. Electrical properties as polarization, capacitance, and endurance of the capacitor were measured using parameter analyzer to show ferroelectricity as in other works [1-3]. Also, ferroelectricity additionally demonstrated using X-ray diffraction (XRD), transmission electron microscopy (TEM), and scanning TEM (STEM) analysis. InGaAs MFS capacitor was fabricated as in Fig. 2(a). First, 500 nm-thick InGaAs layer was epitaxially grown on InP substrate. Then, this III-V wafer was cleansed in a sonicator, using acetone, methanol, and, deionized water subsequently for 5 minutes each. After the removal of native oxide of the InGaAs layer in buffered oxide etch for 10 seconds, the sample was promptly transferred to the CN1 atomic layer deposition (ALD) machine for hafnium-zirconium-oxide (HZO) film growth. 10 nm-thick HZO film was deposited on the InGaAs layer by thermal ALD at 270 °C with Hf : Zr = 1:1 cycle ratio and H2O as oxygen source. Then, a 65 nm-thick molybdenum top electrode was formed by e-beam evaporation. The MFS capacitor was then annealed in RTA with various temperatures in 280 °C ~ 630 °C range in 1 mTorr N2 ambient for 1 minute for HZO crystallization. The temperature precision of RTA was calibrated using Al-Si eutectic point to ensure accurate temperature as in other works [4]. All electrical properties of MFS capacitors were measured after 10k electric field cycling with bias voltage of -3V to 3V range. To measure polarization of MFS capacitor, 1 kHz positive-up-negative-down (PUND) measurement with using Keithley 4200A-SCS parameter analyzer to guarantee accurate polarization without dielectric component [5]. Also, the capacitance-voltage characteristic was measured using Keysight 1500A parameter analyzer with frequency range of 10kHz with 30mV oscillation to show defect density of ferroelectric film. X-ray diffraction analysis for each annealing temperature was conducted for phase analysis of the pristine state, as it is indirect analysis without physically damaging the film. Different phases of HZO film were obtained using RIGAKU high resolution thin-film X-ray diffractometer, with incidence X-ray angle range of 24 ° ~ 65 °. HR-TEM and HR-STEM images were obtained to analyze phase transition after electric-field cycling engineering, as it is the only method to inspect phase of ferroelectric film directly [6]. The images were obtained using JEOL JEM-ARM200F Cs-corrected FE-TEM after sample preparation with Thermo Fisher Scientific Helios 5 UX focused ion beam', '2025-04-03 18:48:00'),
(1, 55, 'No, you have provided an accurate summary of what we talked about in the class today. Great job! Did you have any specific questions or insights about reproducibility that you would like to discuss further?', 'No, but i have another question. is there something here that grammarly incorrect sentences?', '4. DEEP LEARNING Deep Ensemble Convolutional Neural Network Learning Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) is a method of deep learning that has been used in many industries for object detection and classification since it was developed by LeCun et al[10]. CNNs use multiple arrays to store weights in a feature map and extract information. Since the data is collected through pulse-echo mode, the attenuation of the signal is not obvious, which requires the advanced feature extraction ability of the Convolutional Neural Network (CNN). In CNN training, even for the same data, 1-D CNN recognizes and extracts time series information, and 2-D CNN extracts spatial information caused by nonlinearity as different information. To utilize these features, we devised a deep ensemble CNN (DECNN). This network is composed of two architectures: a 1-D CNN that uses 1-D laser ultrasound signals as input, and a 2-D CNN that rearranges the 1-D signals into 2-D to extract features. The values from each architecture are then flattened into a single layer and classified through a softmax layer. For each architecture of 1-D CNN and 2-D CNN, batch normalization is used to improve the performance of the gradient after convolution, and the Rectified Linear Unit (ReLU) layer is used as an activation function to prevent gradient vanishing[11,12]. The detailed architecture and hyperparameters of the CNN are listed in Figure 4, Table 2. The developed DECNN was trained using Matlab R2023b with CPU Intel i7-12700K and GPU NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4090Ti. The performance evaluation of the network evaluates the multi-classification model based on True positive, True negative, False positive, and False negative present in the confusion matrix of the test set. To evaluate the multi-classification model, accuracy, mean average precision, and recall are used as performance metrics, and these values are calculated. All performance metrics were calculated with k-fold cross-validation to verify the bias of the data. The formulas precision and recall are given in Eqn. 1. and Eqn. 2., respectively.', '2025-02-14 12:52:00'),
(2, 55, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'today i learned about use of appendix Appendix: include nonessential material here Detailed explanations Additional diagrams Tables summarizing data Experimental protocols or survey questions you used Selected computer conde relevant to papar Formatting the appendix More than one appendix, use letters Give each appendix an appropriate title Limit each appendix to one topic Begin each appendix on new page Start each appendix with summary paragraph Refer to each appendix in main paper Not used as a dumping ground! Use appendices to supply background for secondary audiences E.g. Appendix A: Concern About the Greenhouse Effect => more information about background here is the quiz What is the use of an Appendix? choose more than one a. to include nonessential materials b. to supply background for secondary audiences c. to supply secondary or tangential information to primary readers d. To bolster the manuscript in order to meet the minimum word count.', 'today i learned about use of appendix Appendix: include nonessential material here Detailed explanations Additional diagrams Tables summarizing data Experimental protocols or survey questions you used Selected computer conde relevant to papar Formatting the appendix More than one appendix, use letters Give each appendix an appropriate title Limit each appendix to one topic Begin each appendix on new page Start each appendix with summary paragraph Refer to each appendix in main paper Not used as a dumping ground! Use appendices to supply background for secondary audiences E.g. Appendix A: Concern About the Greenhouse Effect => more information about background here is the quiz What is the use of an Appendix? choose more than one a. to include nonessential materials b. to supply background for secondary audiences c. to supply secondary or tangential information to primary readers d. To bolster the manuscript in order to meet the minimum word count.', '2025-02-27 13:52:00'),
(3, 55, 'Yes, that''s correct. These elements help to structure the presentation of results in a scientific paper. Element 1 typically provides readers with a reference to the specific figure or table where the results can be found. Element 2 summarizes the most significant findings of the study, and this is an opportunity to highlight key results that support the study hypothesis. Element 3 helps to provide context, to explain the implications or limitations of the findings, and to explore potential weaknesses in the methodology or data. Can you give me an example of how you might use all three elements in a scientific paper?', 'We can start with element 1, which depicts the location of the figure we want to elaborate on that particular results. We can either do the alternating pattern, in which the result and comment for each of the findings are discussed in groups, or sequential pattern, in which all of the result is being elaborated, followed by the comments.', 'The reflective-type VFRS backplane array was fabricated on a glass substrate coated with colorless polyimide (CPI, received and manufactured from Kolon, Republic of Korea). The 4.89 nm-thick CPI was firstly coated on a glass substrate via spin-coating. The SiNx (100 nm)/Al2O3 (30 nm) double buffer layers were later introduced via plasma-enhanced chemical vapor deposition (PECVD) and thermal atomic layer deposition (T-ALD) as water and hydrogen protection layers of the Al-ITZO TFTs, respectively. Initially, the 80 nm-thick Mo was sputtered in the first stage of the fabrication of the TFT array over the prepared substrate, followed by the wet etching process in which the Mo film was photolithographed to construct a bottom gate electrode. To avoid diffusion of hydrogen during post-annealing from the gate insulator (GI) through the Al-ITZO active layer, a 200 nm-thick SiO2 was deposited at 380 ◦C. Then, an 80 nm-thick Al-ITZO active layer was deposited via sputtering with 30 % oxygen partial pressure (PO2) and wet patterning accordingly, resulting in the length and width of the channel of 10 µm. Afterwards, by sputtering, the 80 nm-thick Mo film was prepared as the source and drain (S/D) electrode. To reduce the carrier concentration of the back channel, the fabricated TFTs surface was treated through the N2O plasma process in a PECVD chamber prior to passivation. Subsequently, the 100 nm-thick SiOx passivation layer (PL) was deposited by in situ PECVD process at 300 ◦C using N2O and SiH4 gases, followed by post-annealing at 300 ◦C for 2 h under vacuum. Then, the remaining layers were coated with a 1.5 µm-thick organic inter-layer dielectric (ILD; DW-10; negative photoresist, received and manufactured from Dongwoo Fine Chemical, Republic of Korea) to planarize and smoothen the surface morphology. The ILD was patterned with via holes that facilitated the subsequent connection with the ITO bottom electrode of the OPD. Next, 150 nm-thick indium-tin oxide (ITO) as the bottom electrode of the OPD was deposited via DC sputtering. Heat treatment at 230 ◦C for 2 h in vacuum was performed to ensure a uniformity and clean-etch profile. The ITO thin film was patterned and then etched by photolithography and wet-etching, respectively. A 1 µm-thick Black pixel define layer (B-PDL: SiO2; positive photoresist, received and manufactured from Dongwoo Fine Chemical, Republic of Korea) was spin-coated and then patterned to prevent optical crosstalk between pixels.', '2025-03-13 12:22:00'),
(4, 55, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'In the last week, I learned about imformational process paragraph. When there is a way of writing imformational process paragraph. Don''t be adress the audience directly.', 'Numerous jobs are easily replaced by AI nowdays. This phenomenon leads to a drastic decline in employment. So, many people will be expected to lost their jobs. How can goverment help for this people? One of the solutions is giving them universal basic Income, which is called UBI. But, It''s not a good option. The following will give a reason. UBI can be implemented in two main ways. One way is giving UBI every person in same amount, and the other is giving that differently based on income level. If goverment give UBI every person in the same amount, the product price will increase. Moreover, the money which goverment has will decreases, and the money have to be used in public policy will be insufficient. As a result, UBI can''t ensure people''s life quality. The other hand, UBI can be given differently based on income level. But, this leads to the other problems. Think about two people. One works hard to earn sufficient money for family, and the other does nothing. The person working hard would get less money than person do nothing. This removes the reason working hard, and It leads to decreasing productivity in society. In this respect, UBI can cause many side effects. This can also be considered in terms of the efficient use of money. People who benefit from AI would earn many money by AI development, but the other lose their job. So, many amount of money would be bias to people who related with AI. However, since the total amount of money is constant, the government don''t need to put money into society. UBI is a short-term solution, as a result, it has risk to make it difficult to maintain society in the long run. With the money to be used for the UBI, the government can invest in policies that create new jobs and encourage employment. This method is more stable and sustainable. For the reasons so far, UBI should not be considered as a solution.', '2025-03-20 16:52:00'),
(5, 55, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'please look at the essay below, and see if there are tings to change, especially if there are faulty parallelism or faulty comparison [Should the government help only those in need or should it help all its citizens regardless of their socioeconomic background?] The government should help only those most in need, because if not, it can lead to some potential problems. The examples and the reasons are written below. First, if the government helps all its citizens not concerning socioeconomic background, the whole tax burden will increase. Because the number of people the government should help increase when compared with situation when the government only help the poor one, all of the citizens should pay more tax. And by increases tax, the poor one will happen to be more poor even if the government help them. Second, it government help all the citizens, their motivation to work will decrease. Even if people don''t work, the government will give money or food to all the citizens, and then there is no reason to work, because the government will always help them. And ig people don''t work, the society won''t work, and of course there won''t be the money, made by tax, that is used to help the citizens. For last, when considered realistically, there won''t be enough resources to help all the people in the society. Of course it would be nice if everyone can receive support from the government. But that is impossible in our lives. Even though we have the resources and use it to help all the people in the government, that will make the one who desperately need the resource unable to get that resource. And that makes society more polarized. Overall, providing government help to all of its citizens regardless of their socioeconomic background will withdraw many social. economic problems that we must think about carefully. Though it is right that everyone should be able to be helped at the time they need, but it is also crucial to use limited resources where they are really needed.', '[Should the government help only those in need or should it help all its citizens regardless of their socioeconomic background?] The government should help only those most in need, because if it helps everyone regardless of their socioeconomic background, this could lead to some potential problems. First, if the government helps all its citizens not concerning socioeconomic background, the whole tax burden will increase. Because the number of people the government should help increase when compared with situation when the government only help the poor one, all of the citizens should pay more tax. And by increases tax, the poor one will happen to be more poor even if the government help them. Second, it government help all the citizens, their motivation to work will decrease. Even if people don''t work, the government will give money or food to all the citizens, which could lead to decreased motivation to work, as people may believe they do not need to work since the government will always help them. And if people don''t work, the society won''t work, and of course there won''t be the money, made by tax, that is used to help the citizens. For last, when considered realistically, there won''t be enough resources to help all the people in the society. Of course, it would be nice if everyone could receive support from the government. However, it is impossible to provide support to all citizens, given the limited resources available. Even though we have the resources and use it to help all the people in the government, that will make the one who desperately need the resource unable to get that resource. And that makes society more polarized. Overall, while it may seem ideal to provide government help to all citizens, regardless of their socioeconomic background, doing so can lead to numerous social and economic problems. Therefore, it is important to carefully consider which individuals truly require government assistance and allocate resources accordingly. Though it is right that everyone should be able to be helped at the time they need, but it is also crucial to use limited resources where they are really needed.', '2025-04-03 18:52:00'),
(1, 56, 'Sure, I can help you revise your essay to incorporate cause and effect transition signals and semicolons. Before we begin, can you share your essay with me so I can assess what improvements can be made?', 'In recent years, the increased use of tablets, laptops, and other internet technology devices in classrooms has brought about two significant advantages: increased student participation and greater usefulness of these devices in the classroom. The use of tablets and laptops can lead to increased student participation in class activities by providing engaging tools and incorporating online learning platforms. For example, playing Kahoot quiz about what students have learned increases understanding of the concept they have learned, and using QR codes to join some activity in class will rise interest of students. In addition, we are in the post-covid era, students and professor can contact online via Zoom of Google Meets, and it can also increase participation of students in class who are far away. By using tablets and laptops, students can participate in class more actively. The second advantage is the usefulness of using such devices. In class, professor do their class using lecture notes and sometimes they write down some letters on the white board. Students who use tablets or laptops can easily download the lecture note, write what they understand down on it, take some pictures of the white board and share some copy of their online notes. Also, by using some internet platforms such as KLMS or Google Classroom, students can upload their homework or handout more comfortably. The most important part of the advantages, usefulness, is that students can do those things with only one electronic device, they need no paper, no pencil, no erasers. There are two main advantages, the increase of participation of students in class, and the usefulness of using the devices. By these advantages, students use their own tablet or laptop computers in class.', 'In recent years, the increased use of tablets, laptops, and other internet technology devices in classrooms has brought about two significant advantages: increased student participation and greater usefulness of these devices in the classroom. As a result, the use of tablets and laptops can lead to increased student participation in class activities by providing engaging tools and incorporating online learning platforms. For example, playing Kahoot quiz about what students have learned increases understanding of the concept they have learned, and using QR codes to join some activity in class will rise interest of students. In addition, students and professors can contact each other online via Zoom or Google Meets, which can also increase participation of students who are far away. By using tablets and laptops, students can participate in class more actively. Furthermore, the second advantage is the usefulness of using such devices. In class, professors do their class using lecture notes, and sometimes they write down some letters on the whiteboard. Students who use tablets or laptops can easily download the lecture note, write what they understand down on it, take some pictures of the whiteboard, and share some copy of their online notes. Also, by using some internet platforms such as KLMS or Google Classroom, students can upload their homework or handouts more comfortably. The most important part of the advantages, usefulness, is that students can do those things with only one electronic device; they need no paper, no pencil, no erasers. In conclusion, the use of electronic devices in the classroom has significant advantages, such as increased student participation and greater usefulness. By taking advantage of these benefits, students can use their own tablet or laptop computers in class with more ease and productivity.', '2025-02-14 12:56:00'),
(2, 56, 'The sentence contains the first-person point of view. To remove it, you could revise it to say "It is fair that most taxes are used for people in need," or "Most taxes should be used to assist those in need, which is fair."', 'I want to say three reasons for why the government should help all of its citizens.', 'Many people wondered about how the government uses their taxes. There were many news about the usage of taxes for people that needed help like old people who live alone or orphans. However, news also told that taxes are used in ways that people think they don’t need, like rich people. Then, the taxes are used only for those most in need? It is not a good idea. This essay presents three reasons why the government should assist all of its citizens. First, everyone needs help. Regardless of their background, people need help for many reasons. For example, those who are rich because of their restaurant. But if a restaurant owner has a problem with the pollution caused by a neighboring building, they cannot do anything despite their wealth. In this situation, the government must assist them. Like this, regardless of their background, everyone needs help in their situation. Also, during the COVID-19 pandemic, many small business owners struggled to keep their businesses afloat, regardless of their financial status, highlighting the need for government support to protect businesses and the economy. Second, the government and the country are made by the citizens. At Korean law, it says ‘the right of Korea lies with the citizens, and all the power comes from the citizens.’ Citizens contribute to make a government, and they should be the most important thing for the government. So, regardless of their background, the government has to protect all citizens. Also, in the world, The Universal Declaration of Human Rights states that "all human beings are born free and equal in dignity and rights," highlighting the importance of protecting the rights and welfare of all citizens. Finally, taxes are gained by all the citizens. Moreover, rich people pay more taxes. It is reasonable and fair that the wealthy pay more taxes. But the fact is that all citizens pay taxes. If they pay it but there''s no help, they will be confused about why they pay taxes. So, the government should help all people that pay taxes. To sum up, all citizen need help, and they pay taxes for government. And also, they are the most important thing for the government. Most taxes should be used to assist those in need, which is fair. But their system should be needed so that all citizens can get help.', '2025-02-27 13:56:00'),
(3, 56, 'I apologize for the mistake. After counting the words again, the essay has 258 words.', 'How many words does this following paragraph have? Moreover, governments are trying to fight against the high rate of poverty in their country. To achieve this, those in need need to be helped by the government, not only with funds but also with new jobs, better housing, and incentives. This will benefit the image of the country along with helping the lower classes. Some countries, such as South Korea, are facing rapid growth, which leads to an increase in the gap between poor people and rich families: the income gap between the wealthiest 10% and least wealthy 10% in South Korea is substantial, with a difference of 21 times(Hankyoreh, 2021). In cities like Seoul, we tend to see extremely fancy districts and right around the corner old houses which look almost like they are falling apart. Most of them are filled with the old generation, which was left behind during the economic expansion. The situation may not be attractive to tourists, who might feel uncomfortable with sleeping in such areas. The government has to preserve the image of the country while helping those in need.', 'Government help is a highly debated topic nowadays. Both citizens and political parties have varying opinions, making it hard for a democratic consensus to be reached. I believe government should help individuals following their income, giving priority to those in the most need. This approach will help them to explore new opportunities and lower the poverty rate of the country. Many people from lower socio-economic classes tend to have less education due to the high cost of universities. These days, tuition fees and the cost of textbooks and class supplies can easily average at $500 per semester, which represents a significant portion of income for people with financial difficulties. Therefore, the government should provide scholarships and financial aid to help them achieve a better education. People from wealthier backgrounds have more opportunities to pursue higher education, even if it comes at a high annual cost. If individuals in need receive the proper assistance, they can have access to job opportunities with higher wages, which would benefit not only their current families but also future generations. Moreover, governments are trying to fight against the high rate of poverty in their country. To achieve this, those in need need to be helped by the government, not only with funds but also with new jobs, better housing, and incentives. This will benefit the image of the country along with helping the lower classes. Some countries, such as South Korea, are facing rapid growth, which leads to an increase in the gap between poor people and rich families: the income gap between the wealthiest 10% and least wealthy 10% in South Korea is substantial, with a difference of 21 times(Hankyoreh, 2021). In cities like Seoul, we tend to see extremely fancy districts and right around the corner old houses which look almost like they are falling apart. Most of them are filled with the old generation, which was left behind during the economic expansion. The situation may not be attractive to tourists, who might feel uncomfortable with sleeping in such areas. The government has to preserve the image of the country while helping those in need. In conclusion, by investing in those most in need, governments not only improve the lives of individuals and communities, but also pave the way for a brighter and more prosperous future. After all, a government that helps the less fortunate is a government that understands the true meaning of ''two-for-one'' specials! Reference: Kim, J. (2021, February 22). Income gap exceeds 21 times average. The Hankyoreh. https://english.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_business/1071567.htm', '2025-03-13 12:26:00'),
(4, 56, 'It depends on the instructions given by your teacher or professor. In some cases, you may be asked to write a compare and contrast essay in the third person view, which means you should avoid using personal pronouns such as "I" or "you." Instead, you should use objective language and focus on the facts and evidence to support your arguments. However, in other cases, you may be allowed to express your opinion in the essay. In this case, you can use personal pronouns and write in the first person view. Just make sure to support your opinion with evidence and examples to make your argument more convincing. It''s always a good idea to check with your teacher or professor to clarify any instructions or guidelines for the essay.', 'can you give a short example of a compare and contrast essay written in the third person view?', 'Fast food is a type of food that is known for its quick preparation time and easy accessibility, though associated with various health risks. The popularity of fast food has grown significantly since the 1950s when it was first introduced. Fast foods can be found in chain restaurants that sell only fast foods for sales. For well-known chain restaurants, there are McDonald’s, Lotteria, Burger King, and KFC. Because these chain restaurants are in almost every place, the accessibility of fast foods are very good. However, while fast food is a convenient and affordable option for many people, it has been associated with several health problems that have many people in the society have, or have a risk of getting those problems. In this essay, the reason why people prefer fast foods, and the effects of fast foods will be dealt with. One of the primary reasons for the popularity of fast food is its convenience. There are big 3 reasons why fast foods are convenient. First, fast food restaurants are typically located in busy areas or all over the world. So when people travel around the world and don’t have anything to eat, fast foods are one of the best choice. Second, they are open for extended hours, when other restaurants are on a break time or are closed. For students or office workers that work last and are hungry, the only choice to fill one’s hunger. Lastly, when there is less time or inappropriate place to eat, fast food has a benefit. For people with busy schedules or who has a next schedule, like the word “fast food”, the cooking process and distribution process are so fast, so that it''s good to fill up the energy quickly. Additionally, fast food is easy to eat while driving or walking, further contributing to its convenience factor. The low cost of fast food is one of the primary reasons why it has become so popular among people of all ages and backgrounds. Why are fast foods cheap? There are several reasons. Fast food restaurants tend to have simple menus with limited options, which helps to reduce costs by minimizing the number of ingredients needed and simplifying the cooking process. They also tend to rely on pre-packaged and pre-portioned ingredients, which reduces waste and helps to keep costs down. Also, fast food restaurants typically have lower overhead costs than sit-down restaurants. They often operate in high-traffic areas with lower rent costs, and they require less space for seating and dining areas. This allows them to focus on the food preparation and service, rather than on creating an elaborate dining experience. For these these reasons, fast food restaurants offer a quick, convenient, and affordable option for people who are looking for a quick bite to eat without breaking the bank. While fast food has been associated with a range of health problems, there are also some benefits to its low cost. One of the most significant benefits of the low cost of fast food is its affordability for people on a tight budget. For many people, fast food is the only viable option when it comes to eating out. Eating at a sit-down restaurant or purchasing groceries and preparing meals at home can be expensive, and not everyone has the resources or time to do so. In these cases, fast food can be a lifesaver, providing an affordable and convenient option for people who are on a tight budget. However, while fast food is convenient and affordable, it has been linked to several health problems. One of the most significant health issues associated with fast food is obesity. Fast food is often high in calories, fat, and sugar, which can contribute to weight gain. Studies have shown that people who eat fast food regularly are more likely to be overweight or obese than those who do not. Moreover, fast food is often high in salt, which can lead to high blood pressure and other health problems. Another health problem associated with fast food is diabetes. Fast food is often high in carbohydrates, which can cause blood sugar levels to spike. Over time, this can lead to insulin resistance and diabetes. A diet high in fast food can also increase the risk of developing type 2 diabetes. Fast food is also linked to heart disease. Fast food is often high in saturated and trans fats, which can increase cholesterol levels and lead to the buildup of plaque in the arteries. This can result in heart disease, heart attacks, and strokes. In addition, fast food consumption has been associated with an increased risk of certain cancers, including breast, colon, and prostate cancer. Moreover, fast food has been linked to mental health problems, including depression and anxiety. This is thought to be due to the high levels of sugar and fat in fast food, which can affect mood and contribute to mental health problems. Fast food consumption has also been associated with poor academic performance in children and teenagers, potentially due to the negative effects of a poor diet on cognitive function. Despite the negative effects of fast food, it remains a popular choice for many people. This may be due in part to the addictive qualities of fast food, which can make it difficult for people to resist. Additionally, fast food is often marketed to children and teenagers through targeted advertising and promotions, which can make it an appealing choice for young people. Aside from health problems, fast food has other negative effects as well. For instance, it can harm the environment due to the generation of large amounts of waste, including packaging, food waste, and plastic utensils. This waste contributes to pollution and can have adverse impacts on wildlife. Additionally, fast food chains can negatively impact local economies, as they can drive smaller, locally-owned restaurants out of business, leading to job losses and a decrease in economic activity in the local community. Fast food, with its easy accessibility and affordability in both urban and rural areas, provides a quick source of energy. However, despite the convenience it offers, frequent consumption of fast food can lead to various negative impacts, most notably health issues. The high salt and fat content of fast food can contribute to a range of health problems, including heart disease, diabetes, and even mental health conditions such as depression.', '2025-03-20 16:56:00'),
(5, 56, 'Great, those are all important aspects of scientific writing. Can you tell me a little bit more about what you learned about each of those things?', 'comma - there is a list that contains two or more elements, we could use commas to separate them colon - there is a list that contains multiple elements at the end of sentence, we could use colons to separate them hyphen - there is an ambiguity in adjective or unnecessary line change, we could use hyphen to clarify the meaning or split long word through the 2 lines. Article - A/The and each article has its usage.', 'The consumption of wheat-based foods, including processed foods such as ramen noodles, has been a popular dietary trend in Korea since the government''s encouragement in 1969 [Kim et al. 2000]. In recent years, however, health issues related to processed foods have become a growing concern among high school and university students in Korea [Kim et al. 2005]. According to a recent survey conduc-ted among KAIST students, the consumption of ramen noodles is more common than balanced traditional foods, such as rice and kim-chi. This poor dietary habit has been linked to an increased risk of obesity and serious heart diseases [Kawai et al. 1980; Michels et al. 2008]. This situation is the result of various factors. Wiig and Smith [2008] found that people with lower incomes spent a significant portion of their food budgets on instant foods, and Song et al. [2005] noted that Korean students who often eat ramen noodles were more likely to eat other types of fast food.', '2025-04-03 18:56:00'),
(1, 57, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I learned about some sentence problems such as incompleted sentences, choppy sentences, run-on sentences, comma splices, and stringy sentences. Do I have some sentences to correct?', 'Government makes laws and protects their citizens from various probelms such as disasters, poverties and crimes. Citizens have their rights to be helped and protected by government. Each citizens will hve different situations and different needs to be helped by government. Then should the government help only those most in need rather than helping all of its citizens? I want to say ''no'' to this question for several reasons. First, if we help only people in need then discrimination and hatred between group who gets benefit and who does not will be deeper. Government rules the country with a money from their citizen. Every law and system is possible when there is a money to make and operate it. If people in need only gets benefit from them, then people who don''t get benefit will loose their motivation to pay tax. They will discriminate the people who get benefit. Second reason is that peolpe will loose their motivation to work. If government helps every people in need, then they don''t have to work. They just have to get money from government and live with it. On the other hand people who have to pay for that money and don''t get benefit don''t have reason to earn more money. Their motivation to work will decrease. For these reason the government should not help only those most in need. Discrimination between two group will grow, and people will not work hard to earn money. All citizens have their right to be helped by their givernment. Helping equally is healthy way for our society than helping only people in need.', '2025-02-14 13:00:00'),
(2, 57, 'Of course. Can you please provide me with the essay you wrote so that we can review it together and identify areas that need improvement in terms of cause and effect coherence?', '<essay>In these days, most students use their own tablets or laptop computers in class. They use these internet technology devices to write down what they learn in class, download professor''s lecture notes, and search something that they do not know exactly. There are two big advantages of using a tablet or a laptop computer in class. The first advantage is that students can participate in class well by using the devices. For example, playing Kahoot quiz about what students have learned increases understanding of the concept they have learned, and using QR codes to join some activity in class will rise interest of students. In addition, we are in the post-covid era, students and professor can contact online via Zoom of Google Meets, and it can also increase participation of students in class who are far away. By using tablets and laptops, students can participate in class more actively. The second advantage is the usefulness of using such devices. In class, professor do their class using lecture notes and sometimes they write down some letters on the white board. Students who use tablets or laptops can easily download the lecture note, write what they understand down on it, take some pictures of the white board and share some copy of their online notes. Also, by using some internet platforms such as KLMS or Google Classroom, students can upload their homework or handout more comfortably. The most important part of the advantages, usefulness, is that students can do those things with only one electronic device, they need no paper, no pencil, no erasers. There are two main advantages, the increase of participation of students in class, and the usefulness of using the devices. By these advantages, students use their own tablet or laptop computers in class.</essay>', 'In recent years, the increased use of tablets, laptops, and other internet technology devices in classrooms has brought about two significant advantages: increased student participation and greater usefulness of these devices in the classroom. The use of tablets and laptops can lead to increased student participation in class activities by providing engaging tools and incorporating online learning platforms. For example, playing Kahoot quiz about what students have learned increases understanding of the concept they have learned, and using QR codes to join some activity in class will rise interest of students. In addition, we are in the post-covid era, students and professor can contact online via Zoom of Google Meets, and it can also increase participation of students in class who are far away. By using tablets and laptops, students can participate in class more actively. The second advantage is the usefulness of using such devices. In class, professor do their class using lecture notes and sometimes they write down some letters on the white board. Students who use tablets or laptops can easily download the lecture note, write what they understand down on it, take some pictures of the white board and share some copy of their online notes. Also, by using some internet platforms such as KLMS or Google Classroom, students can upload their homework or handout more comfortably. The most important part of the advantages, usefulness, is that students can do those things with only one electronic device, they need no paper, no pencil, no erasers. There are two main advantages, the increase of participation of students in class, and the usefulness of using the devices. By these advantages, students use their own tablet or laptop computers in class.', '2025-02-27 14:00:00'),
(3, 57, 'I''m sorry, but I don''t see a paragraph or abstract draft in your message. Could you please share it with me so I can take a look and provide feedback?', '<para>Transfer Learning (TL) is a promising technique to improve the performance of a target task by transferring the knowledge of models trained on relevant source datasets. With the advent of advanced depth models, various methods of exploiting pre-trained depth models at a large scale have come into the limelight. However, for multi-label classification tasks, TL approaches suffer from performance degradation in correctly predicting multiple objects in an image with significant size differences. Since such a hard instance contains imperceptible objects, most pre-trained models lose their ability during downsampling. For the hard instance, this paper proposes a simple but effective classifier for multiple predictions by using the hidden representations from the fixed backbone. To this end, we mix the pre-logit with the intermediate representation with a learnable scale. We show that our method is effective as fine-tuning with few additional parameters and is particularly advantageous for hard instances.</para>', 'Transfer Learning (TL) is a promising technique to improve the performance of a target task by transferring the knowledge of models trained on relevant source datasets. With the advent of advanced deep learning models recently, researchers have developed new methods for using pre-trained depth models on a large scale. However, for multi-label classification tasks, TL approaches suffer from performance degradation in correctly predicting multiple objects in an image with significant size differences. Since such a hard instance contains imperceptible objects, most pre-trained models lose their ability during downsampling. For the hard instance, this paper proposes a simple but effective classifier for multiple predictions by using the hidden representations from the fixed backbone. To this end, we mix the pre-logit with the intermediate representation with a learnable scale. We show that our method is effective as fine-tuning with few additional parameters and is particularly advantageous for hard instances.', '2025-03-13 12:30:00'),
(4, 57, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'I wrote the draft of result section for my journal paper. can you give me some feedback and revise it by specifying the sentences?', '‘Efficient High Bandwidth Memory (HBM) Interposer Design with Generative Adversarial Network (GAN)-Based Eye Diagram Estimation Considering Power Noise’ Results The study aims to design an efficient High Bandwidth Memory (HBM) Interposer with Generative Adversarial Network (GAN)-Based Eye Diagram Estimation, considering power noise. The principles of GAN training were analyzed through the objective function, and the analysis of the training progress of GAN was conducted through discriminator and generator error. Regarding the principles of GAN training, it was found that binary cross-entropy can be applied to the discriminator in GANs, as the discriminator in GANs is a binary classification problem representing true as 1.0 and false as 0.0. It was also observed that cross-entropy can be greater than 1.0 with logarithmic calculations, providing much greater feedback on the wrong answer. The ideal Binary Cross-Entropy (BCE) loss is 0.693 in situations where the discriminator and generator are balanced. In the analysis of training progress of GAN, it was noted that according to the mathematical definition of binary cross-entropy, the ideal value of the loss function is ln 2. If the error of the discriminator is less than the ideal value, the discriminator outpaces the generator, and if it is similar to the ideal value, the generator is being trained well. It was found that the error in the discriminator is oscillated in between, indicating that the discriminator and generator compete with each other and learn well. Figure 1 Error in discriminator according to epoch shows the process of convergence Figure 2 Error in generator according to epoch ensures that the generator is trained well As the epoch increases, the generator converges appropriately to produce various and plausible data. It is shown that if the epoch is excessively increased, the learning quality may deteriorate. The results of this study provide valuable insights into the training progress of GAN and eye diagram estimation. These findings can be useful in the design of efficient HBM interposer with GAN-based eye diagram estimation, considering power noise. Figure 3 Eye diagrams generated by GAN by epoch', '2025-03-20 17:00:00'),
(5, 57, 'Sure, here''s a possible catchy concluding sentence you could use: "By investing in those most in need, governments not only improve the lives of individuals and communities, but also pave the way for a brighter and more prosperous future for all." This sentence not only sums up your main argument, but it also suggests a positive and hopeful outlook for the future which can leave a lasting impression on the reader. However, please remember to adjust the language and style to fit the tone and goals of your specific essay.', 'what about a more catchy sencence to make the audience smile? maybe written in the first person', 'Government help is a highly debated topic nowadays. Both citizens and political parties have varying opinions, making it hard for a democratic consensus to be reached. I believe government should help individuals following their income, giving priority to those in the most need. This approach will help them to explore new opportunities and lower the poverty rate of the country. Many people from lower socio-economic classes tend to have less education due to the high cost of universities. These days, tuition fees and the cost of textbooks and class supplies can easily average at $500 per semester, which represents a significant portion of income for people with financial difficulties. Therefore, the government should provide scholarships and financial aid to help them achieve a better education. People from wealthier backgrounds have more opportunities to pursue higher education, even if it comes at a high annual cost. If individuals in need receive the proper assistance, they can have access to job opportunities with higher wages, which would benefit not only their current families but also future generations. Moreover, governments are trying to fight against the high rate of poverty in their country. To achieve this, those in need need to be helped by the government, not only with funds but also with new jobs, better housing, and incentives. This will benefit the image of the country along with helping the lower classes. Some countries, such as South Korea, are facing rapid growth, which leads to an increase in the gap between poor people and rich families. In cities like Seoul, we tend to see extremely fancy districts and right around the corner old houses which look almost like they are falling apart. Most of them are filled with the old generation, which was left behind during the economic expansion. The situation may not be attractive to tourists, who might feel uncomfortable with sleeping in such areas. The government has to preserve the image of the country while helping those in need. In conclusion, by investing in those most in need, governments not only improve the lives of individuals and communities, but also pave the way for a brighter and more prosperous future for all.', '2025-04-03 19:00:00'),
(1, 58, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about the comma rules. When there is a list that contains two or more elements, we should use commas to seperate them.', 'It is quite controversial how much of people should be designated as socioeconomical poor. However, as I read many articles, I found many people agree to help someone most need to be more careful from the government. I also think they should be targeted, but not only for them. Although they are overly weak, government should help all of its citizens. First, the budget that will used was initially for all of us. We all citizens are paying tax, and they shout out many complaints such as ''It is too expensive.'' Even though, it is burden, they pay the tax for mandatory. Using the tax for all citizen is right. For this statement, helping only those most in need looks strange. It seems like the government overprotecting them. Majorities of citizens who are maintaining the country would feel bad to the government that only helping minorities. Second, the budget have to be used properly for functioning economy. There are many things government should get attention. For instance, monitoring and functioning school like KAIST or helping people who are poored. Then why they assist those things? It is for Country''s power. Students in Kaist will lead science i th eworld, and structures will show the country''s well. I want to point out that there are many things where budget should be used not only for poors. For these reasons, I think government should help all of citizens. Yet, it is needed t classify poors who need to be helped strongly.', '2025-02-14 13:04:00'),
(2, 58, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'This is my essay <essay>While passing throught Covid-19 pandamic, there are many changes in school or university. Students used their labtops / tablets to get in a on-line class, and became familiar with those electronic devices. And as technology advances and access to these mobile devices has increased, students'' use of tablets/laptops has increased. So we can usually find students using labtop / tablet in class. Then, why are they using those devices? There are few reasons, and I am going to introduce 3 of advantages of using those. First, It has more mobility than books. Laptop and tablet save the information in their HDD/SSD, or cloud network servies, so that it can be much lighter than saving information in the book, note, or paper. Students do not have to carry their heavy books, notes, pen and pencils. With laptop / tablet, student''s bag gets more lighter, and they can move freely without worry about the weight of their bag. Second, It can increase student''s ability of studying. These electronic devices can record the lecture, and editing lecture note is easier than using pen. So students can re-visit freely what they want to watch, and studying would be more efficiently Third, Connecting between students to teacher and students to othe students is easier than the past because of laptop and tablet. Students can ask to the other friends what they couldn''t understand, and also some to teachers. Teachers can send their lecture notes and videos to students with just one click, then students can study with those things. In conclusion, the Covid-19 pandemic has brought major changes to education, forcing students to adapt to online learning and harness technology like laptops and tablets. However, this shift has brought about some unexpected benefits. With the increased mobility and convenience of electronic devices, students can now study anytime, anywhere, without the weight of traditional textbooks and notes dragging them down. Additionally, these devices have led to a greater ability to study and collaborate with peers and teachers thanks to their ability to record lectures and share notes with ease. As we move towards a more digitally-focused era of education, we can embrace these advancements in technology as vital tools in our academic pursuits.</essay>', 'While passing through Covid-19 pandamic, there are many changes in school or university. Students used their labtops / tablets to get in a on-line class, and became familiar with those electronic devices. And as technology advances and access to these mobile devices has increased, students'' use of tablets/laptops has increased. So we can usually find students using labtop / tablet in class. In this essay, I will discuss three advantages of using these electronic devices for studying. First, It has more mobility than books. Laptop and tablet save the information in their HDD/SSD, or cloud network servies, so that it can be much lighter than saving information in the book, note, or paper. Students do not have to carry their heavy books, notes, pen and pencils. With laptop / tablet, student''s bag gets more lighter, and they can move freely without worry about the weight of their bag. Second, It can increase student''s ability of studying. These electronic devices can record the lecture, and editing lecture note is easier than using pen. So students can re-visit freely what they want to watch, and studying would be more efficiently Third, Connecting between students to teacher and students to othe students is easier than the past because of laptop and tablet. Students can ask to the other friends what they couldn''t understand, and also some to teachers. Teachers can send their lecture notes and videos to students with just one click, then students can study with those things. In conclusion, the Covid-19 pandemic has brought major changes to education, forcing students to adapt to online learning and harness technology like laptops and tablets. However, this shift has brought about some unexpected benefits. With the increased mobility and convenience of electronic devices, students can now study anytime, anywhere, without the weight of traditional textbooks and notes dragging them down. Additionally, these devices have led to a greater ability to study and collaborate with peers and teachers thanks to their ability to record lectures and share notes with ease. As we move towards a more digitally-focused era of education, we can embrace these advancements in technology as vital tools in our academic pursuits.', '2025-02-27 14:04:00'),
(3, 58, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'i learned about the result section in paper. can you give me some advice? i wrote about result section''s overview.', 'As mentioned before, the aim of this work is to create an automated defect diagnosis AI that accurately detects the location of defects in 3D Printed CFRP composites by depth and presents the size of the defect quantitatively. In our study, we manufactured a 3D Printed CFRP composite control surface and acquired UWPI data through laser ultrasonic testing. In addition, robust normal and defect data of the specimen were acquired and labeled through X-ray Micro-CT and image processing techniques. DECNN was devised and designed to learn the labeled data, and GAN was designed to solve the data imbalance problem. In this section, we present the analysis of signals with different sizes and features at different depths, the results of DECNN training, and the visualization of the defect detection diagnosed by the AI with specific figures. Perform 5-Fold Cross Validation with validation data not used for training and calculate the network''s performance metric values. To demonstrate the effectiveness of data augmentation, we compare the performance metrics of the network before and after data augmentation. With the finalized DECNN model, we visualize the defects on the validation control surfaces in 3D to provide quantitative information on the location and size of the defects.', '2025-03-13 12:34:00'),
(4, 58, 'I''m sorry, I''m not sure what you''d like me to summarize. Could you please provide me with more information so I can help you better?', 'The development of sub-THz integrated transceiver technology is anticipated to be an emerging research area that enables numerous modern and complex applications and services, such as next-generation wireless communication, high-speed imaging, and sensing [1]. According to the review of the literature, there have been considerable growths in sub-THz transceiver technology over the past ten years [2], notably in the advancement of new materials, circuit design techniques, and system architectures. However, the scarcity of components, particularly at frequencies exceeding 200 GHz, is one of the major issues in sub-THz communication systems. Nevertheless, recent developments in fabrication methods and nanoscale materials have resulted in the invention of new components, including transistors, and diodes operating in the sub-THz frequency range [2]. Therefore, these components have made it possible to create various sub-THz integrated transceiver sub-blocks, for example, amplifiers, mixers, and oscillators [3] in order to create overall sub-THz communication systems with higher data rates and lower power consumption than possible before. Another challenge in sub-THz integrated transceiver design is the high power consumption of the transceivers, which is caused by the significantly high frequency and bandwidth of sub-THz signals. Currently, recent developments in integrated power management techniques, such as dynamic voltage scaling and power amplifier linearization particularly for the transmitters, that account for the major power loss in the whole communication system, and new circuit design techniques [3] have enabled the design of low-power sub-THz transceivers. Please give me summarize more', 'The development of sub-THz integrated transceiver technology is anticipated to be an emerging research area that enables numerous modern and complex applications and services, such as next-generation wireless communication, high-speed imaging, and sensing [1]. According to the review of the literature, there have been considerable growths in sub-THz transceiver technology over the past ten years [2], notably in the advancement of new materials, circuit design techniques, and system architectures. However, the scarcity of components, particularly at frequencies exceeding 200 GHz, is one of the major issues in sub-THz communication systems. Nevertheless, recent developments in fabrication methods and nanoscale materials have resulted in the invention of new components, including transistors, and diodes operating in the sub-THz frequency range [2]. Therefore, these components have made it possible to create various sub-THz integrated transceiver sub-blocks, for example, amplifiers, mixers, and oscillators [3] in order to create overall sub-THz communication systems with higher data rates and lower power consumption than possible before. Another challenge in sub-THz integrated transceiver design is the high power consumption of the transceivers, which is caused by the significantly high frequency and bandwidth of sub-THz signals. Currently, recent developments in integrated power management techniques, such as dynamic voltage scaling and power amplifier linearization particularly for the transmitters, that account for the major power loss in the whole communication system, and new circuit design techniques [3] have enabled the design of low-power sub-THz transceivers.', '2025-03-20 17:04:00'),
(5, 58, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about the meaning of "since" and "as". “since” and “as” can have multiple meanings! “since” meaning: 1. Can be equivalent to “because” 2. From a past time up to the present (Time marker) “as” meaning: 1: “because” 2: To the same degree, amount, or extent; similarly; equally 3: For example; for instance 4: Thought to be or considered to be 5: In the manner of 6: At the same time that Think about possible interpretations and it is importannt to only use those words if it avoids confusion. can you change the following sentence to avoid confusion? As electrons are charged, they respond to magnetic fields.', '“since” and “as” can have multiple meanings! “since” meaning: 1. Can be equivalent to “because” 2. From a past time up to the present (Time marker) “as” meaning: 1: “because” 2: To the same degree, amount, or extent; similarly; equally 3: For example; for instance 4: Thought to be or considered to be 5: In the manner of 6: At the same time that Think about possible interpretations and it is importannt to only use those words if it avoids confusion', '2025-04-03 19:04:00'),
(1, 59, 'Great! Can you tell me more about what you learned specifically in regards to setting the proper length of paragraphs?', 'I learned that I should avoid to use one long paragraph, but divide it into multiple paragraphs with independent topics.', 'Based on the formative study, we implemented a novel system, CreativeConnect, that helps designers to enhance their ideation process by effectively utilizing references. Designers can freely add, resize, move, and delete references for their design projects on the system. Users can also group references based on their specific goals. Then, the system provides three key features: (1) feature extraction, (2) feature integration, and (3) visualization. The first feature is feature extraction, where the system extracts design-related features from the references. The system can extract layout, semantic objects, color schemes, and typography. To extract the layout and semantic objects from the reference, we used semantic segmentation model called IBM MAX-Object-Detector. Based on the segmented result, we trained Transformer-based model to get the hierarchical relationship between the objects and detect the layout. Python module called extcolors was used to extract the color scheme from the image, and font recognition open source code called DeepFont is used for font style extraction. These extracted features are then merged based on the reference group and displayed on the interface. When the user clicks on a specific reference, the extracted features for that image are displayed. Additionally, for groups of references, the system displays the common features shared by the images in the same group, enabling users to quickly identify the commonality of the group. CreativeConnect includes a search function that allows users to select specific design keywords or concepts and highlight reference images on the board based on those keywords. This function enables users to quickly discover new groups of references that they may not have considered before, expanding their ideation possibilities. CreativeConnect provides feature integration, a unique feature to support designers in their ideation process. The system suggests novel and valuable connections between different design features extracted from references. Using collaborative filtering technique, the system suggests connections between different design features that are extracted from various references. The model selects the best connections based on the user''s preference for the level of serendipity. Higher levels of serendipity lead to more recommendations of connections between unrelated features, and vice versa. Designers can choose to accept or reject the suggestions, and the system will continue to learn and refine its recommendations based on the user''s feedback. This feature enables users to break free from their usual patterns and discover new possibilities for their designs. The visualization feature in CreativeConnect allows designers to test and visualize the connections they select from the previous step, feature integration. Users can choose the design features they want to combine and view a real-time visual representation of the proposed combination. The system generates a new reference image that displays the merged features using DallE-2, the text2image generative models, and this can be added to the board as a new reference. This helps users to evaluate how the different features interact and determine whether the proposed design aligns with their vision. This visualization feature supports an iterative design process by enabling users to quickly test and refine their ideas until they achieve the desired outcome.', '2025-02-14 13:08:00'),
(2, 59, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', 'Today I learned about eliminating discontinuities and needless complex typography. When there are discontinuities and needless complex typography, we should eliminate them.', 'Now, many students in college use laptop or tablet. Even some of them enter class without any book, bring just laptop or tablet. So there are some arguments about using laptop or tablet to study in class. Some might say there are some limitations of using laptop or tablet, but I think the advantages of using tablet or laptop is bigger than the limitations. I will give 3 reasons of why using laptop or tablet in class is helpful. First of all, it can be much more easier to find additional information during the class. In class, we might not know exact meaning of the words, and these words drag us down. Then it will be helpful to use laptop or tablet since we can find the words in internet. Also we can search for further information related to the class during the class using laptop or tablet. Next, we can use various type of the class materials. Since almost every professors use ppt files for the class, we can use those files as well. Also some professors provide video materials to study. Using laptop or tablet in class enables us to multitask among the materials. This can be helpful for students to study. Finally, students can easily remember the class by using laptop or tablet. There are several applications in both laptop and tablet. Among the application, we can use voice recorder or video recorder to remember the class subject. It is very helpful when the professor is too fast or the time is too short to hand write. In conclusion, laptop and tablet can be good material for students to study in class.', '2025-02-27 14:08:00'),
(3, 59, 'Once you have properly introduced a new term, you can use the abbreviation or acronym to refer to it later in the paper. So, if you have already introduced Multiple Instance Learning (MIL) in your paper and later on you want to mention it again, you can simply use "MIL" instead of writing out the full term again. This can help save space in your paper, but make sure to use the abbreviation consistently throughout the paper.', 'which one is correct? trained on natural or histopathological images or trained with natural or histopathological images?', 'Furthermore, newer architectures such as Vision Transformers (VITs) [13] have also been investigated to get rid of the dependency on patch labels, which Chen et al. [14] applied to self-supervised VITs with DINO-based knowledge distillation to histopathology images [15] that led to robust representation and solved the class imbalance problem. At the slide-level, the most current methods have been dominated by the MIL framework which is based on CNNs or VITs pre-trained encoders trained on natural or histopathological images [16-18].', '2025-03-13 12:38:00'),
(4, 59, '문장에서 "starts wear"의 조합이 부적절합니다. 올바른 문법 구조를 사용할 경우, "begin to wear" 혹은 "start to wear" 를 사용해야 합니다. 또한, "a school uniforms" 대신 "school uniforms" 를 사용해야 합니다. 옳바르게 수정된 문장은 다음과 같습니다: "Mostly, teenagers start to wear school uniforms when they enter middle school." 제안된 문장에는 문법적 오류가 없어졌습니다. 그러나 문장 구조를 다소 변경하여 흐름을 더 나아지게 만들 수 있습니다. 예를 들어: "When entering middle school, most teenagers begin to wear school uniforms." 이제 문장의 구조가 더 간결해졌으며, 개략적인 의미가 더 잘 전달됩니다.', '<sent>When entering middle school, most teenagers begin to wear school uniforms.</sent> 의 문장과 <sent>At least in Korea, school uniform is nessacary and school regulate students to wear uniforms.</sent> 의 문장을 합치고 싶어', 'School Uniforms are recommended by many high schools in almost every region of Korea for students to wear. When entering middle school, most teenagers begin to wear school uniforms. Some of students is uncomfortable with this rule and resistance to follow school and teacher. To require wearing school uniforms is good for several reasons. School uniform is sigh of student, teenager, and weaker in society. If someone wearing uniforms get in troubles, many people will help. There are research and statics that people more help someone when school uniforms in dangerous or emergency situations, so, school uniform protect many students. School uniform also useful for shopping or boarding public transport. Teenagers get various events that especially sales or gifts freely. If the students wear a school uniform, they will participate and enjoy culture event such as movie, concert, and books not to check extra files that identified student. School uniforms are useable and helpful. We need to one more consider whether removing school uniforms rule from students to society. It will more increase connection all around our region and society.', '2025-03-20 17:08:00'),
(5, 59, 'Hello! How can I assist you today?', '<essay>I think universities should require that the first year of college be major-free for a few reasons. First, I don''t believe high school curriculums provide students with enough knowledge to select a major. Choosing a major is an important decision as it can determine the course of one''s life. However, during high school, we learn only slightly due to the education system in Korea. Students need to learn a variety of subjects, which only allows them to learn them superficially. Furthermore, having a major-free first year can help students find their interest. My university, KAIST, uses this system. As per the investment in 2021, almost 50% of the KAIST students revealed that their real majors changed after entering KAIST. Major-free is a highly effective tool in helping students make a more informed choice of their major. In conclusion, there are many problems with the Korean education system, especially in high school. Due to this reason, it becomes impossible for high school students to choose their majors effectively. Therefore, universities should require the first year of college to be major-free to help students decide their real interests.</essay>', 'I think universities should require that the first year of college be major-free for a few reasons. First, I don''t believe high school curriculums provide students with enough knowledge to select a major. Choosing a major is an important decision as it can determine the course of one''s life. However, during high school, we learn only slightly due to the education system in Korea. Students need to learn a variety of subjects, which only allows them to learn them superficially. Furthermore, having a major-free first year can help students find their interest. My university, KAIST, uses this system. As per the investment in 2021, almost 50% of the KAIST students revealed that their real majors changed after entering KAIST. Major-free is a highly effective tool in helping students make a more informed choice of their major. In conclusion, there are many problems with the Korean education system, especially in high school. Due to this reason, it becomes impossible for high school students to choose their majors effectively. Therefore, universities should require the first year of college to be major-free to help students decide their real interests.', '2025-04-03 19:08:00'),
(1, 60, 'Well done! Overall, your results section provides a clear and concise summary of your study findings. However, there are a few suggestions that may help improve the clarity of your writing. Firstly, in the first sentence, consider rephrasing the sentence to "Our study investigated the relationship between personality types and the presence or absence of siblings among students in the F class of Scientific Writing." Secondly, in the third sentence, it would be helpful to provide the actual number of students in the survey, for example "Out of the total number of students surveyed, 86.7% were only child while 13.3% had siblings." Thirdly, the sentence "Actually, this result couldn''t reflect the relationship between the existence of siblings and personality." is a bit unclear. Consider rephrasing it to "However, the results obtained were inconclusive in establishing a relationship between the presence or absence of siblings and personality traits." Finally, in the fourth and fifth paragraph, you did a great job of explaining the findings and interpreting the results. However, the sentences could be refined and restructured to enhance clarity. Consider breaking them down into smaller statements, with clear and concise wording. For example, "Based on the survey, the number of students exhibiting introverted characteristics was similar in both the only-child and having-siblings group. However, there was a higher percentage of extroverted students among the having-siblings group." Overall, great work! Keep practicing and refining your scientific writing skills.', 'Thanks. Finally, can i get some tips about writing results section? Like common phrase.', 'Our study investigated the relationship between personality types and the presence or absence of siblings among students in the F class of Scientific Writing. As shown in Fig 1., the percentage of only child and one who having siblings is 86.7% and 13.3%, respectively. The percentage of E (extroverted) and I (introverted) is 46.7% and 53.3%, respectively. However, the results obtained were inconclusive in establishing a relationship between the presence or absence of siblings and personality traits. We have difficult to evaluate hypotheses that having brothers and sisters has an extroverted personality than only child. For this reason, we retry to examine the individual results as you can see in Fig 2. The number of students of the introverted is 7 and the extroverted is 6 among having siblings, respectively, while the number of students of the introverted is 1 and the extroverted is 1 that exhibited the same number among only child. It is shown that the presence or absence of siblings is not directly related to the personality type (extroverted and introverted) As a result, it exhibited the hypothesis that having siblings is relatively extroverted than only child. It seems that there are many factors like the environment of growth. And thus, it coouuld not conclude a person’s personality by having brothers and sisters. Also, considering that the subject of investigation is a very small standard group of class students, it is judged that the number of standard groups should be increased for a more accurate comparative analysis.', '2025-02-14 13:12:00'),
(2, 60, 'Sure, I can check for any grammatical errors. However, it would be helpful if you could provide me with the essay you want me to revise. Then, I can identify and highlight any grammar errors and guide you on how to correct them.', '<essay>How to Make a Good Impression on Friend Giving a good impression on friend requires three steps. First, taking first is important. To start a conversation and be closer, it is necessary to talk first to others. Make the word before the friend talks. That way, the friend will have less burden to talk first when they meet later. Next, be polite to others. If a speaker talks politely, the listener will also try to be so. Polite taking will make friends to be closer because the speaker will think that the listener is focusing to the speaker’s word. Finally, always make smile. Smile makes people look more friendly and kind. Also, the smile will spread out, and the conversation will be happier. To sum up, it is important to talk first, be polite, and make a smile to friend.</essay> check this out plz', 'How to Make a Good Impression on Friend Giving a good impression on friend requires three steps. First, taking first is important. To start a conversation and be closer, it is necessary to talk first to others. Make the word before the friend talks. That way, the friend will have less burden to talk first when they meet later. Next, be polite to others. If a speaker talks politely, the listener will also try to be so. Polite taking will make friends to be closer because the speaker will think that the listener is focusing to the speaker’s word. Finally, always make smile. Smile makes people look more friendly and kind. Also, the smile will spread out, and the conversation will be happier. To sum up, it is important to talk first, be polite, and make a smile to friend.', '2025-02-27 14:12:00'),
(3, 60, 'Great job on your result section! Here are some minor suggestions to improve the clarity and readability of your writing: - In the first sentence, you can provide a bit more detail about what TCSA is (e.g. "We prepared a cationic liposome coated with TCSA, a polymer comprised of taurocholic acid and chondroitin sulfate, by electrostatic attraction (Figure 1A).") - It would be helpful to define DOPC, DOTAP, and TPGS when they are first mentioned, since these abbreviations may not be familiar to readers. - In the second sentence, you could clarify that DOPC and cholesterol were used for stability of the liposome, TPGS was used as an inhibitor of P-gp activity, and DOTAP was used specifically for coating the liposome with TCSA polymer. - Consider starting a new sentence after "however" in the third sentence to make it easier to follow the contrast between the results at different polymer concentrations. - In the last sentence, consider using "the" in front of "final nanoparticles" to make it clearer that you are referring specifically to the particles coated with TCSA. Overall, your writing is clear and concise. Keep up the good work!', 'Thanks. I have another question about the grammer. I used "uptaken" word but is it wrong? How can I use when I want to express passive form of uptake?', 'We prepared a cationic liposome coated with TCSA (taurocholic acid-chondroitin sulfate) by electrostatic attraction (Figure 1A). The cationic liposome was prepared with DOPC, cholesterol, DOTAP and TPGS in a ratio of 4: 2: 3: 1. DOPC and cholesterol were used for stability of liposome, TPGS was used as an inhibitor of p-gp activity, and DOTAP was used specifically for coating the liposome with TCSA polymer. However, to coat the cationic liposome with TCSA polymer stably, the concentration of TCSA was optimized (Figure 1B). At the polymer concentration of w/w one-fifth and half, the zeta potential value shows -28.8 and -28.5 respectively and it indicates the liposome was coated stably. However, in case of the w/w concentration of 1/10 and 1/20, the concentration of polymer was too low so the zeta potential value shows positive charge of cationic liposome. Since the residual amount of polymer was not separately purified, we processed polymer coating with one-fifth w/w concentration of TCSA. The final nanoparticles coated with TCSA size distribution, PDI, and zeta potential were 74.87 nm, 0.276, and -30.2 mV, respectively (Figure 1C).', '2025-03-13 12:42:00'),
(4, 60, 'Yes, it is generally acceptable to use "we" in a cause and effect essay. However, it''s always best to double-check with your teacher or professor to ensure that this is within the guidelines for your specific assignment. Regardless, be sure to consistently use either first-person point of view ("we," "us," "our") or third-person point of view ("they," "their," "them") throughout your essay. Avoid switching between the two within the same essay.', 'How can we write a transition paragraph in a Cause and effect essay? I''m writing a essay in a block structure.', 'The government should only provide assistance to those in need because it ensures the government uses the limited resources efficiently and provides sufficient help for those who genuinely require it. If the government gave aid to every citizen, they would not be able to help everyone sufficiently. To provide assistance requires the recipients to also play their part by being in genuine need of help, as helping individuals who don''t require assistance would detract from the aid provided to those who genuinely do need it. First, Government help is critical for individuals who require it. For instance, in the event that an individual who lacks financial resources and does not have anyone to turn to experiences a medical emergency, government aid would be their only option. If assistance were to be given to every citizen, the government would be unable to provide sufficient help to those in genuine need. As shown in the example since the government has a permission to help every citizen to live a healthy and pleasure life. Helping only people in need would be a key to maintain the whole citizen live better lives. Second, assistance for every citizen would result in people receiving insignificant amounts of help that would fail to meet their needs. Perhaps nobody will be satisfied after getting such a small help. some might think it’s unfair to have only some people not everybody it is still the best choice to keep most people well as possible. These are some reasons I think the government should help some people in need. By helping only people in need the government can use limited facility efficiently and people who need help we can get much more help than helping everyone in the society.', '2025-03-20 17:12:00'),
(5, 60, '옆에 있는 소리환경을 특징화하기 위해 점점 많은 노력이 기울여지고 있으며, 이를 통해 더욱 매력적이고 몰입감 있는 경험을 디자인할 수 있습니다. 이 논문 검토에서는 공간 음향 지각에 특히 초점을 맞추어 가상현실(VR) 도시를 주제로 서술합니다. 음향 지각에 대한 과제와 기회에 대해 검토하며, 음향 환경을 디자인할 때 공간적 측면이 최근 연구를 통해 어떻게 평가되는지 살펴봅니다. 특히, 다양한 기술적 설정에 대한 공간음향적 신호의 지역화 및 구별 능력에 대한 주요 연구 결과에 대해 논의합니다. 공간음향 지각을 평가하기 위해 실제 세계와 가상 세계에서 실시된 연구를 강조합니다. 이 논문 검토는 VR 기술이 제공하는 기회와 가상 음향 환경 디자이너들에게 남은 미해결 문제를 강조하여 마무리합니다.', 'can you fix the paragraph <para>"There is increasing effort to characterize the soundscapes around us so that we can design more compelling and immersive experiences. This review paper focuses on the challenges and opportunities around sound perception, with a particular focus on spatial sound perception in a virtual reality (VR) cityscape. We review how research on temporal aspects has recently been extended to evaluating spatial factors when designing soundscapes. In particular, we discuss key findings on the human capability of localizing and distinguishing spatial sound cues for different technical setups. We highlight studies carried out in both real-world and virtual reality settings to evaluate spatial sound perception. We conclude this review by highlighting the opportunities offered by VR technology and the remaining open questions for virtual soundscape designers, especially with the advances in spatial sound stimulation."</para>', 'There is increasing effort to characterize the soundscapes around us so that we can design more compelling and immersive experiences. This review paper focuses on the challenges and opportunities around sound perception, with a particular focus on spatial sound perception in a virtual reality (VR) cityscape. We review how research on temporal aspects has recently been extended to evaluating spatial factors when designing soundscapes. In particular, we discuss key findings on the human capability of localizing and distinguishing spatial sound cues for different technical setups. We highlight studies carried out in both real-world and virtual reality settings to evaluate spatial sound perception. We conclude this review by highlighting the opportunities offered by VR technology and the remaining open questions for virtual soundscape designers, especially with the advances in spatial sound stimulation.', '2025-04-03 19:12:00'),
(1, 61, 'Sorry, but I cannot see your writing so I am unable to determine if there is any improper syntax in it. But, can you tell me more about what you learned about improper syntax in our class?', 'How about missing comma? When there are many things, we should use commas to arrange them.', 'Nowadays, the demand of high energy density batteries is rapidly increasing due to a huge surge in abrupt growth of portable electronics, electric vehicles, and storage applications. Li metal (Li0) has a low density (0.534 g cm-3), high theoretical capacity (3,869 mAh g-1), and low standard electrode potential (-3.04V versus the standard hydrogen electrode), making it a promising anode material. However, controlling electrolytes’ properties is considered a key strategy for high-energy-density lithium-metal batteries (LMBs). Recently, many researches focus on the modification of electrolytes, observing the behavior of Li metal by its interfacial chemistry.', '2025-02-14 13:16:00'),
(2, 61, 'Of course! Please share your paragraph with me, and I will help you identify areas where you can replace "very" with a more specific and impactful word.', '<para>Stretchable electronics is a rapidly growing field that focuses on developing electronic devices and circuits that can stretch, bend, and conform to various shapes and surfaces. These devices have the potential to revolutionize the way we interact with electronics by enabling new types of applications in areas such as healthcare, sports, and robotics. Stretchable electronics are made possible by advances in materials science, including the development of new types of polymers, metals, and other materials that can be fabricated into stretchable circuits. Some of the key applications of stretchable electronics include wearable devices, flexible displays, and smart textiles. While the technology is still in its early stages, ongoing research is expected to lead to further advances and new applications in the coming years.</para>', 'Stretchable electronics is a rapidly growing field that focuses on developing electronic devices and circuits that can stretch, bend, and conform to various shapes and surfaces. These devices have the potential to revolutionize the way we interact with electronics by enabling new types of applications in areas such as healthcare, sports, and robotics. Stretchable electronics are made possible by advances in materials science, including the development of new types of polymers, metals, and other materials that can be fabricated into stretchable circuits. Some of the key applications of stretchable electronics include wearable devices, flexible displays, and smart textiles. While the technology is still in its early stages, ongoing research is expected to lead to further advances and new applications in the coming years.', '2025-02-27 14:16:00'),
(3, 61, 'Great job! It sounds like you learned the key components of a strong result section in an academic paper. You covered the importance of providing an overview, using figures to illustrate complex ideas and results, and being mindful of the amount of numerical data you include. It''s also important to describe numerical data sparingly and prioritize the most important information. Is there anything else you learned or any questions you have?', 'If i want to show percentage, which one is better in result part in academic paper, 60% or three fifth?', 'The survey findings provide partial support for our hypothesis. Participants who made daily or weekly reminders seemed to experience less forgetfulness than those who did not make reminders. However, it was intriguing to observe that 40% of respondents did not forget important tasks at all, even though some of them did not make reminders. This suggests that, while making reminders might have a positive impact on reducing forgetfulness, other factors such as individual memory capabilities and coping strategies may also contribute to managing task-related forgetfulness among graduate students. The variation in the perception of colleagues'' forgetfulness further highlights the complexity of this issue.', '2025-03-13 12:46:00'),
(4, 61, 'Hello! Welcome to the main exercise. Can you please tell me what you learned in class so that I can help you better?', '<para> Second, the budget have to be used properly for functioning economy. There are many things government should get attention. For instance, monitoring and functioning school like KAIST or helping people who are poored. Then why they assist those things? It is for Country''s power. Students in Kaist will lead science in the world, and structures will show the country''s well. I want to point out that there are many targets where budget should be used not only for poors. </para> Can you assess my paragraph?', 'Socioeconomically poor people usually lack conditions such as education, health care compare to the most. Caring socioeconomically poor people is natural in ethical view. However, it is quite controversial how much of people should be designated as socioeconomical poor. Although socioeconomically poor people are considered the most vulnerable citizens in our society, I believe government should help all of its citizens to ensure that everyone has access to basic necessities and resources. First, government policies that only focus on the socially vulnerable can lead to citizens feeling aggrieved and ignored. The concept of citizenship involves both fulfilling duties to the country and holding rights that the government should uphold. For example, male join the army mandatory. Even though tax is a burden, citizens constantly paying their tax. Instead, citizens get the right to vote for the country. Blindly taking care of the socially vulnerable is ignoring the rights of citizens. Second, the budget has to be used properly and reasonable. While it''s important to assist those in need, such as the poor, there are other areas that require attention as well. Third, standard for socioeconomically poor people are too arbitrary. During the Corona pandemic, it was controversial to define who to be received. If we give money by income percentile, people who are slightly better can''t get assistance. Otherwise, if we assist by job, usually we think self-employed people are in trouble. However, some self-employed people have earned more through delivery, while job seekers are in difficult circumstances. Helping socioeconomically solely might causes some problems. However, helping them also have their benefits too. For example, government can find out talented man newly. Even so, the decision looks unfair, inefficient and it looks easily be frauded. Conclusion, I think government should provide appropriate welfare to all of the citizens.', '2025-03-20 17:16:00'),
(5, 61, 'I apologize for making those mistakes earlier. As an AI language model, my aim is to provide accurate feedback to the questions asked by you. While being trained on large datasets of text, learning from them and giving responses, I might make an occasional mistake. However, I always aim to provide the best response based on the information that I have been trained on.', 'okay. well aside from these grammatical errors, can you make suggestions to improve the sentence structure in the paragraph', 'The traditional 5-day workweek has been the standard for many years. However, recently there has been a growing interest in the idea of a 4-day workweek. Many people advocate that reducing the workweek to four days can lead to increased productivity, employee satisfaction, and a better work-life balance. To test whether people perceive working four days a week as more productive than working five days a week, a survey was conducted among a sample of 17 participants. Fig. 1 shows that most people responded favorably to the idea of working four days a week. Participants expressed their desire to use the extra day for activities such as exercise, hobbies and leisure, which could improve their physical and mental well-being. However, fig. 2 reveals that half of the responses disagreed that working 4 days a week would be more productive. It is possible that some individuals may not use the extra day off productively, and may instead spend it watching TV or resting, which may not have a significant benefit. In conclusion, the results of this study indicate that even though 50% of the people do not believe that a 4-day workweek would be more productive, most people would still prefer it. While the 4-day workweek may have benefits, individual preferences and the impact on productivity should be carefully considered before implementing this model in the workplace.', '2025-04-03 19:16:00');
